const alumniData = [{"id":1,"n":"Eric Adams","u":"Ric","g":"H2","p":"I3","ph":"(570) 320-1835","em":"ericadamsvs@outlook.com","tw":"Bedford","st":"NH"},{"id":2,"n":"Rhys Adsit","u":"Rhys","g":"E2","p":"C3","ph":"(801) 822-2357","em":"radsit.knrt@gmail.com","tw":"Provo","st":"UT"},{"id":3,"n":"Robert Albino","u":"Bob","g":"I2","p":"E4","ph":"909-552-5267","em":"raawhite@aol.com","tw":"Rancho Cucamonga","st":"CA"},{"id":4,"n":"David Alexander","u":"Butch","g":"D3","p":"B4","tw":"Beckley","st":"WV"},{"id":5,"n":"Jeffrey Allen","u":"Jeff","g":"E1","p":"E3","ph":"253-229-1713","em":"jeff.c.allen@outlook.com","tw":"University Place","st":"WA"},{"id":6,"n":"Curtis Andersen","u":"Curt","g":"C4","p":"B3","ph":"(912) 665-6937","em":"wmflyer007@gmail.com","tw":"Stuttgart","st":"Germany","ac":"Travel, hiking, skiing, sailing","w":"Curt Anderson Curt Andersen lives in Stuttgart, Germany with his wife. They have 6 children and 6 grandchildren. He was an exchange cadet to USAFA and particularly enjoyed beating Air Force that year. His plebe year company was B3. Curt served as S4 with the 82nd Airborne. His last deployment was humanitarian support after Hurricane Andrew. After the Army, he spent 30 years with Walmart logistics, including 18 years as a facility manager working across Regional, Grocery, and Import formats. His assignments took him through multiple facility types and distribution systems. He enjoys travel, hiking, skiing, and sailing. His time in Germany and work with international logistics keeps him connected to Europe. He can be reached at wmflyer007@gmail.com | (912) 665-6937."},{"id":7,"n":"David Anderson","u":"Dave","g":"F4","p":"G1","ph":"(703) 347-7832","em":"davekara@ymail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":8,"n":"Frank Anderson","u":"Frank","g":"B4","p":"I1","ph":"757-582-8797","em":"frank.h.anderson3@gmail.com","tw":"Chesapeake","st":"VA"},{"id":9,"n":"Michael Anderson","u":"Mike","g":"F2","p":"F4","ph":"(405) 889-6453","em":"mandersonhome@aol.com","tw":"Oklahoma City","st":"OK"},{"id":10,"n":"Tom Anderson","u":"Tom","g":"B1","p":"","em":"andert17@gmail.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":11,"n":"Douglas Andrews","u":"Doug","g":"H1","p":"E4","ph":"253-381-9320","em":"dougandrews86@gmail.com","tw":"Lake Tapps","st":"WA","ac":"Golf, travel, skiing, fishing, hiking. He enjoys travel, golf, social trips, and mini-reunions. His H1 cohort still gathers regularly for football weekends and destination meet-ups. He and Shannon travel widely—Hawaii, London, Italy, Ireland, Australia—and he is open to trips with classmates. He values reconnecting as part of “smelling the roses.”"},{"id":12,"n":"Ronald Anglin","u":"Ron","g":"H4","p":"G2","ph":"770-584-0571","em":"qcatch@yahoo.com","tw":"Thomaston","st":"GA","ac":"Disc golf and travel","w":"Ron Anglin Ron lives in Thomaston, Georgia. His daughter Miriam is the senior graphic designer for TrindGroup based in Auburn, Alabama and has a four-year-old daughter, Ron's only granddaughter. Ron was a plebe in G2 and graduated from H4. He remembers leading the H-4 prank team along with Ranger Jim Yentz to cadet borrow the I-4 Beam and place it in numerous locations like the bottom of the Cadet Pool or the waterworks of Lusk Reservoir. He served in the Assault Helicopter Platoon of 1-17th Cavalry, 82nd Airborne, and deployed to Honduras for Operation Golden Pheasant. He sat on Green Ramp in reserve for Operation Just Cause and had to figure out how to wire speakers to blast rock music at the Vatican Embassy in Panama.  After the Army, he worked as a high school teacher and coach, then became a professional entertainer in 1999. He is currently the team leader for Laughter League Atlanta, a nonprofit hospital clown organization. He also does grief therapy group work for kids with another nonprofit called Kate's Club. Ron enjoys disc golf and travel. He can be reached at qcatch@yahoo.com | 770-584-0571."},{"id":13,"n":"Steven Antoch","u":"Steven","g":"F4","p":"G1","ph":"425-246-7369","em":"steve.antoch@yahoo.com","tw":"Riverview","st":"FL","w":"Steve Antoch Steve lives in Riverview, Florida. He has three grown daughters in Seattle and Los Angeles. No grandchildren yet. He served at Fort Carson with 124th Sig BN, spending the first half as a platoon leader and then in the DAMO creating a home-grown prototype battlefield computer system using off-the-shelf Zenith laptops and desktops to help automate the \"Beans, Bullets and Bodies\" (TACSOP) reports. He and two other LTs with CS degrees designed it, wrote the code, taught classes, maintained it, fielded it, and administered it, even soldering together RS232-to-TTL-CMOS adapters to talk over tactical commo systems. He got out in 1990 and joined a software company in Boston doing database design, then joined a couple co-workers as their first employee in their startup, which was eventually acquired by Visio, then by Microsoft. He bounced around another startup and a couple other companies (Barnes and Noble Education, ATI Consulting). He now works for Salesforce on their Tableau product. He's married with three daughters. His sister-in-law gave him a Mr. Beer homebrewing kit for Christmas in 2002. He's now a GrandMaster III Beer and Mead judge and Assistant Regional Rep for the Southern Region of the Beer Judge Certification Program. He can be reached at steve.antoch@yahoo.com | 425-246-7369."},{"id":14,"n":"Patrick Antonietti","u":"Pat","g":"D4","p":"D1","ph":"301-793-6443","em":"antoniepm1@aol.com","tw":"Rockville","st":"MD","ac":"He enjoys sports, travel, and outdoor life. Golf has been a consistent interest since cadet days and throughout his Army career. He values time with friends at sporting events, reunions, and informal gatherings. He also takes annual trips back to Montana and anticipates returning there more permanently.","w":"Patrick Antonietti Pat lives in Rockville, Maryland. He has two daughters, now ages nineteen and twenty-one. One is in college in Rhode Island; the other is taking time off from school and working while managing some health issues. He remains closely involved in their lives and has structured his career and retirement timing around supporting them. He grew up in Montana in a large family with deep roots in the state and maintains strong ties there, taking annual trips back and anticipating returning more permanently. His plebe company was D1, graduating from D4. His early years in Germany were formative: serving as a Vulcan platoon leader in 1st ID Forward, live-firing over the Baltic, and participating in the Normandy historical staff ride with WWII veterans. He served as an Olmsted Scholar in Slovakia, studying political transition in the immediate post-Cold War era at a former communist institution. Later highlights include deploying to Kosovo as a brigade FSO and battalion XO, speaking Slovak to local populations, and helping build stability after conflict. As a battalion commander in Iraq during OIF III, he led soldiers through intense combat while supporting elections and constitutional development. His most memorable cadet experiences include Reorgy Week when, assigned as head mail carrier in D-1, he struggled to deliver mail across Old South and Persian Barracks, ultimately landing in a company board when the regimental XO's mail piled up. He also remembers failing his first plebe English paper, then receiving an unexpected A on the next essay when Major Lynn Moore read it aloud as an example. After twenty-one years of service, he briefly explored private-sector roles but ultimately returned to government. For the past seventeen years he has served as a civilian on the Secretary of Defense staff, working Middle East policy, UN peacekeeping issues, and now Central and Eastern Europe. His work involves interagency coordination, crisis response, and implementing U.S. national-security policy. He enjoys golf, which has been consistent since cadet days and throughout his Army career. He values time with friends at sporting events, reunions, and informal gatherings. He can be reached at antoniepm1@aol.com | 301-793-6443."},{"id":15,"n":"Patrick Appleman","u":"Pat","g":"G4","p":"F3","ph":"(815) 885-2268"},{"id":16,"n":"Kevin Arbanas","u":"Kevin","g":"A1","p":"D3","ph":"509-435-6904","em":"arbanask@msn.com","tw":"Spokane","st":"WA","w":"Kevin Arbanas lives in Spokane, Washington. He can be reached at arbanask@msn.com | 509-435-6904."},{"id":17,"n":"Thomas Archinal","u":"Thomas","g":"A4","p":"A1","ph":"(313) 640-4717","em":"Thomas.o.archinal.civ@mail.mil","tw":"Grosse Pointe Park","st":"MI"},{"id":18,"n":"Donna (Lee) Ariyoshi","u":"Donna","g":"D2","p":"H3","ph":"808-203-0187","em":"dariyoshi@hotmail.com","tw":"Honolulu","st":"HI","ac":"Baseball","w":"Donna Lee Ariyoshi Donna  lives in Honolulu, Hawaii. She has one daughter, age 23. Her plebe company was H3, graduating from D2. Her most memorable cadet experience was sprinklers interrupting the Saturday parade. She served at Fort Lewis, Camp Humphreys, and Fort Devens. After the Army, she worked in the telecom industry and then in psychiatric nursing. She can be reached at ariyoshi@hotmail.com | 808-203-0187."},{"id":19,"n":"Rocco Armonda","u":"Rocco","g":"E3","p":"C2","ph":"240 350-5317","em":"rocco.armonda@gmail.com","tw":"Silver Spring","st":"MD","ac":"hiking, cycling","w":"Rocco Armonda Rocco lives in Silver Spring, Maryland. He has six adult children. As a cadet, he remembers being on the field for the Cherry Bowl victory and the Army-Navy victory in 1984. Rocco served 31 years in the Army, including a deployment with the 207th Neurosurgery Team during Operation Iraqi Freedom in 2003-04.  Since leaving active duty, he has practiced as a neurosurgeon at MedStar Georgetown and Washington Hospital Center. He teaches at Georgetown Hospital and has served as a medical volunteer in Ukraine since 2022, including teaching at Mechnikov Hospital in Dnipro. Rocco enjoys hiking and cycling. He can be reached at rocco.armonda@gmail.com | 240-350-5317."},{"id":20,"n":"Alan Arnholt","u":"Alan","g":"E1","p":"A4","ph":"828-262-5406","em":"alanarnholt@gmail.com","tw":"Boone","st":"NC"},{"id":21,"n":"Michael Arthur","u":"Michael","g":"A3","p":"F4","ph":"281-923-8460","em":"marthur19@yahoo.com","tw":"Brookshire","st":"TX"},{"id":22,"n":"Yolanda Arts-Brick","u":"Yolanda","g":"B4","p":"I1","ph":"414-491-5569","em":"CNQ86@yahoo.com","tw":"Cornell","st":"MI","ac":"Traveling.","w":"Yolanda Arts-Brick Yoland lives in Cornell, Michigan. No children. She served at Fort Bragg, North Carolina, and Fort Clayton, Panama. In Panama, she got her NAUI scuba certification, panned for gold, and did 120 hours of pool training to become Brigade Life Guard. The Brigade Commander tasked her to put together the first annual Brigade Organization Day. After the Army, she went back to school for secondary education certification, did substitute teaching, coached girls' JV basketball at her old high school, tended bar and DJ'd at a nightclub, worked as a reporter for the Daily Press Newspaper, became an estimator for a log home company, and finally worked for Ameritech (later AT&T). Within AT&T, she worked as a field foreman with a crew of 18 men, became an analyst scheduling construction technicians, and finished her career as a Project Manager for the whole state of Michigan for high-speed internet. She travels. She can be reached at CNQ86@yahoo.com | 906-384-6914."},{"id":23,"n":"Ricanthony Ashley","u":"Ricanthony","g":"F4","p":"A2","ph":"(845) 938-6669","em":"ashley6md@aol.com","tw":"Spring Lake","st":"NC"},{"id":24,"n":"John Atkins","u":"John","g":"F3","p":"I4","tw":"Darlington","st":"SC"},{"id":25,"n":"Mark Aubrey","u":"Mark","g":"H4","p":"","ph":"863-978-9258","em":"markaubrey_7@msn.com","tw":"Winter Haven","st":"FL"},{"id":26,"n":"John Bachleda","u":"John","g":"F1","p":"H2","em":"cptjbach@gmail.com","tw":"Morganville","st":"NJ"},{"id":27,"n":"Colyn Bacon","u":"Colyn","g":"H2","p":"A1","ph":"(919) 846-2230","em":"colynb@hotmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":28,"n":"John Bacot","u":"John","g":"B4","p":"I1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":29,"n":"Victor Badami","u":"Vic","g":"F1","p":"D4","ph":"703-606-2786","em":"vic.badami@gmail.com","tw":"Woodbridge","st":"VA","ac":"Travel, attend sporting events, just hanging out","w":"Vic Badami Vic and his wife, Laura, live in Woodbridge, Virginia. Their daughter Christina is an elementary school principal in Stafford County Public Schools and lives in Montclair with her husband Joseph and three children, ages 9, 7, and 5. Their son Victor lives in New York City and works as an interior and furniture designer for David Scott Interiors, LTD. Vic served in Baumholder and Mannheim, Germany, then Desert Shield and Desert Storm. He was a battery commander at Fort Campbell, served at White Sands Missile Range, then worked on the Army Staff and the Joint Staff. He never walked the area at West Point as he claims he was never caught doing the crazy things he did. When he retired in 2006, he worked for Booz Allen Hamilton for four years, then moved to Akima for 15 years as a Senior Operations Director for three companies. After 10 months of what he thought was a second retirement, an opportunity came up and he now works at Miami Federal as General Manager of two companies: Miami Technology Solutions and Miami Technical Services. He travels, attends sporting events, and likes just hanging out. He coaches and mentors service members transitioning from active duty to civilian life. He can be reached at vic.badami@gmail.com | 703-606-2786."},{"id":30,"n":"John Badovinac","u":"John","g":"D4","p":"C3","ph":"224-723-9943","em":"badovinac.jmb@gmail.com","tw":"Chicago","st":"IL","ac":"#1 Ask - need some folks to do some adventure mountain bike races with! I’ve got 3 big races in the 40-100 mile range and would love company to share the adventure! Happy to ski or travel as well!","w":"John Badovinac John lives in Chicago. He has been remarried for seven years to Nicole. His daughter Hailey, 31, lives in Mexico City and works remotely as a UI designer for mobile apps and eCommerce sites. She has a fabulous friend group constantly traveling and adventuring together. John got to cheer her on at a Spartan Race with all her friends at Valle de Bravo. His son Casper, 25, is finishing undergrad at a local liberal arts school on a full academic scholarship, majoring in history with a focus on labor relations. He has already been offered a research staff role by the department chair and has turned into an absolute bad-ass mixologist. He has many memories including allegedly removing all the table numbers in the mess hall the night before table change, creating pandemonium. He remembers John Poncy giving Jim McAllister the world's worst haircut and getting absolutely flamed for it at dinner formation. He did monkey rolls in the gig pit at jump school for no reason. He had great trips to Puerto Rico with repeat visitors including FJ, Fin-Dog, Karl Snyder, Chad and Peggy, Mark Schemine, Fred Rudolph, Billy Manning, Jen Shaw, Carrie Stoudt, and Nancy Morales. He served with 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment on the East-West German border and was the last Border Officer on a 200K sector when the wall came down, serving with classmates Steve Cannon, Kurt Gutierrez, Scott Pierce, and Chuck McLaughlin. After the Army, he ended up in payment tech beginning at Discover and advancing through other niche industry leaders. His most interesting role is now: leading partnerships for a payment platform where he meets with brilliant nerds and helps them monetize and scale their business. John's #1 ask is he needs some folks to do adventure mountain bike races with—he has three big races in the 40-100 mile range and would love company to share the adventure. He is happy to ski or travel as well. He and Nicole enjoy travel, tiny house adventures, and running/volunteering at STEM events in the Chicagoland area. He can be reached at badovinac.jmb@gmail.com | 224-723-9943."},{"id":31,"n":"Joel Bagnal","u":"Joel","g":"H3","p":"C4","ph":"(512) 695-1981","em":"joel.bagnal@gmail.com"},{"id":32,"n":"William Baier","u":"William","g":"D2","p":"I3","tw":"Boise","st":"ID"},{"id":33,"n":"Eugene Baker","u":"Gene","g":"D1","p":"I3","em":"genebaker@yahoo.com","tw":"Berkeley","st":"CA"},{"id":34,"n":"Steve Balentine","u":"Steve","g":"H1","p":"A4","ph":"(650) 325-3349","em":"msbalentine@mac.com","tw":"Palo Alto","st":"CA"},{"id":35,"n":"William Balkovetz","u":"Bill","g":"A2","p":"G1","ph":"770-301-5734","em":"billb427@gmail.com","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":36,"n":"Douglas Balsbough","u":"Douglas","g":"I4","p":"B1","ph":"860-690-3514","em":"Balsbough@yahoo.com","tw":"Cornelius","st":"NC"},{"id":37,"n":"Aniceto Bantug","u":"Chito","g":"D2","p":"C1","ph":"(518) 373-7070","em":"aniceto.bantug.2023@gmail.com","tw":"Port St. Lucie","st":"FL","w":"Chito Bantung Chito lives in Port St. Lucie, Florida. He has four children and one grandchild. He can be reached at aniceto.bantug.2023@gmail.com | 518-373-7070."},{"id":38,"n":"Michael Barbee","u":"Mike","g":"H2","p":"","ph":"913-547-3236","em":"Michael.barbee43@gmail.com","tw":"Gurley","st":"AL"},{"id":39,"n":"Brett Barraclough","u":"Brett","g":"A3","p":"","ph":"(703) 866-1484","em":"brett.barraclough@gmail.com","tw":"Lexington","st":"VA"},{"id":40,"n":"John Barrington","u":"Scott","g":"B1","p":"I2","ph":"703-307-9168","em":"scott.barrington@mac.com","tw":"Broadlands","st":"VA","ac":"Golf (although I'm a poor golfer), attending sporting events, finding good BBQ joints, cycling","w":"Scott Barrington Scott lives in Broadlands, Virginia with his wife Malia. They have three daughters—two work as assistant English teachers in Japan, and the third is a process improvement analyst in South Carolina in her first post-college job. Barrington's favorite assignment was at Caserma Ederle in Vicenza, Italy, which he calls his \"hardship tour.\" After company command, his favorite job was serving as a small group instructor at the Infantry Officers Advanced Course at Fort Benning. He served as Y2K Project Officer for USAREUR from 1998-99, a role he credits with saving \"millions of US and European lives from the scourge of Y2K.\" He retired from the Army in 2008 and moved into IT sales, where his first sales manager had no sales experience, provided no training, and led a team of deeply unhelpful peers—an experience he attributes either to his grit or stupidity. He earned a Master's Degree in e-Commerce as a full-time student, which he believes makes him unique among Army officers. He golfs poorly, attends sporting events, searches for good BBQ joints, and cycles. He remains friends with Karl Snyder, who on St. Patrick's Day during plebe year convinced him to run past the Cadet Jewish Chapel to drink from a St. Pauli Girl bottle Snyder had stashed in a hollowed tree the previous October, followed by Scope mouthwash to cover their breath—a story his daughters dismissed as \"what a couple of losers.\" He can be reached at scott.barrington@mac.com | 703-307-9168."},{"id":41,"n":"William Basnett","u":"Bill","g":"F4","p":"D1","ph":"404-822-1723","em":"basnett.billjr@hotmail.com","tw":"Kennesaw","st":"GA"},{"id":42,"n":"Samuel Bass","u":"Jud","g":"I3","p":"B2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":43,"n":"Tommie Bates","u":"Tommie","g":"E1","p":"F4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":44,"n":"Erin (O'Brien) Batt","u":"Erin","g":"I1","p":"B2","ph":"(260) 625-3908","em":"dcbatt05@yahoo.com","tw":"Fort Wayne","st":"IN"},{"id":45,"n":"David Baum","u":"Dave","g":"I3","p":"G2","ph":"703-895-8852","em":"davidbaum@mac.com","tw":"Midland","st":"GA","ac":"Life near Fort Moore suits him well. He values friendship, conversation, and shared experiences more than specific hobbies. He appreciates gatherings built around meaningful connection and would welcome classmates visiting the Columbus area, which he describes as a surprisingly rich place to live.","w":"Dave lives in Midland, Georgia near Fort Benning. He is married to Marie, daughter of former C4 TAC Captain Bingham, whom he met while serving at Fort Irwin. They have two daughters, ages 26 and 23. The eldest is engaged to be married, lives at home temporarily, and is studying to become a nurse practitioner. The younger recently graduated from Covenant College with a music degree and now teaches in challenging public schools in Columbus, working with students from difficult backgrounds. Both daughters are thriving and each is in a serious relationship with men he respects. His plebe company was G2, graduating from I3. He arrived at West Point with little preparation and felt lost for much of plebe year, but admired the professionalism of the upperclassmen and found their example compelling. He remembers forming deep friendships in G2 and later in I3, where humor and camaraderie sustained him. West Point also sparked his early spiritual awakening, including long evenings in the Cadet Chapel reading his sister's recommended books and beginning to ask serious questions about life, faith, and purpose. His formative years were as an infantry lieutenant and later as a scout platoon leader with the OPFOR at the National Training Center, where the tempo, responsibility, and mentorship from gifted NCOs shaped him as a leader. A signature accomplishment was co-authoring \"The Way,\" the Ranger School devotional, a collaborative project still in circulation and one of the achievements he values most. After 22 years of service, concluding with a staff tour at the Pentagon, he retired and pursued ministry full-time. He attempted to plant a church in a hard part of Columbus, which proved meaningful but exhausting. Today he serves as a chaplain at MercyMed, providing counseling, mental-health support, and social-services assistance. He and his wife also lead a weekly Officer Christian Fellowship group for young lieutenants at Fort Moore. He continues to write and is developing a book on how people grow spiritually through the different relationships in their lives. He values friendship, conversation, and shared experiences more than specific hobbies and appreciates gatherings built around meaningful connection. He would welcome classmates visiting the Columbus area, which he describes as a surprisingly rich place to live. He can be reached at davidbaum@mac.com | 703-895-8852."},{"id":46,"n":"James Baum","u":"Jim","g":"H1","p":"E4","ph":"972-978-0404","em":"JimBaum2@verizon.net","tw":"Rowlett","st":"TX","ac":"He enjoys road biking, swimming, touring wine country, and vacationing on the beautiful island of Maui.","w":"Jim Baum Jim lives in Rowlett, Texas, where he has built a long career in advanced composite materials for the aerospace industry. As a cadet, his most vivid memory was flying up and down the Hudson Valley during flight labs with then-Major Bill McArthur, whom he later encountered as a colonel after McArthur had completed two of his four space missions. He served one tour as an infantry officer with the 2nd Armored Division at Fort Hood, Texas, before transitioning to the private sector. Over the past 30 years, he has led manufacturing and engineering groups worldwide, building and improving facilities across Europe, Asia, the Middle East, and the United States. Jim and Ann have three sons: Jimmy Jr., 30, and Matthew, 27, both Eagle Scouts and aerospace engineering graduates of the University of Texas, and Robbie, 17, who has accepted a bowling scholarship at Newman University in Wichita, Kansas. Ann recently retired after a 43-year career in IT at State Farm Insurance. Jim's interests include road biking, swimming, touring wine country, and vacationing in Maui. Jim can be reached at 972-978-0404 and JimBaum2@verizon.net."},{"id":47,"n":"Jeffrey Baum","u":"Jeffrey","g":"I1","p":"D2","em":"jc3hb@msn.com","tw":"Rochester","st":"MN"},{"id":48,"n":"James Baumgardner","u":"Jim","g":"H4","p":"G3","ph":"619-997-1213","em":"jbbaumgardner61@gmail.com","tw":"Chula Vista","st":"CA","ac":"He enjoys hands-on, detail-oriented hobbies rather than organized sports, including building scale aircraft models and advanced Lego kits. He values family-centered activities, especially time with grandchildren, and is open to travel to see family and attend reunions. He maintains interest in aviation-related pursuits and informal social connection rather than competitive recreation."},{"id":49,"n":"Cleveland Bazemore","u":"Cleveland","g":"B4","p":"D2","ph":"336-906-9142","em":"cbaze57354@aol.com","tw":"Oak Island","st":"NC"},{"id":50,"n":"William Beane","u":"Bill","g":"A4","p":"D3","ph":"831-212-0981","tw":"Stow","st":"OH"},{"id":51,"n":"Arthur Beasley","u":"Arthur","g":"A1","p":"A2","em":"artbeasley@aol.com","tw":"Mims","st":"FL"},{"id":52,"n":"Peter Bechtel","u":"Pete","g":"A2","p":"A1","ph":"(202) 257-6114","em":"petebechtel@yahoo.com","tw":"Gaithersburg","st":"MD"},{"id":53,"n":"Bruce Beck","u":"Bruce","g":"E3","p":"H1","ph":"(831) 264-3826","em":"bbeck64@aol.com","tw":"Marina","st":"CA"},{"id":54,"n":"Douglas Bedell","u":"Douglas","g":"H3","p":"C1","em":"metroma781@hotmail.com","tw":"Miami Beach","st":"FL"},{"id":55,"n":"James Belanger","u":"Jimmy","g":"B1","p":"B4","ph":"248-661-2515","em":"jbelanger@ncswash.com","tw":"Superior Township","st":"MI"},{"id":56,"n":"Edward Belcher","u":"G2","g":"F3","p":"G2","ph":"(253) 238-9122","em":"edbelcher@hotmail.com","tw":"Tomball","st":"TX"},{"id":57,"n":"Anne (Stouffer) Bell","u":"Anne","g":"F4","p":"H3","ph":"(910) 487-1689","em":"annebell386@gmail.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"NC"},{"id":58,"n":"James Bell","u":"Jim","g":"D2","p":"F4","ph":"(253) 238-9122","em":"jimcbell@gmail.com","tw":"University Place","st":"WA"},{"id":59,"n":"Therese (Boylan) Bell","u":"Terri","g":"F4","p":"G2","ph":"(703) 704-6533","em":"belltm@earthlink.net","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":60,"n":"Nicholas Bellucci","u":"Nick","g":"B1","p":"D3","ph":"210 872-2224","em":"nickbellucci@hotmail.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX","ac":"Travel, Wine","w":"Nick Bellucci lives in San Antonio, Texas with his wife Tracie. Both of his sons attended SMU studying finance. Alex graduated in 2026 and Luke in 2028. He has been in Medical Sales for 35 years, 28 of them working with Implantable Pacemakers and Defibrillators.  He only work a few hours a week now and will make retirement official in 2026. He enjoys travel and wine. He and Tracie enjoy travelling whenever they can.  When they were first together they would take a trip every month.  He has been an avid wine and cigar collector in the past, although now he feels it more appropriate to consume those products rather then leaving them on the shelf. He can be reached at nickbellucci@hotmail.com | 210-872-2224."},{"id":61,"n":"Kevin Belmont","u":"Kevin","g":"F2","p":"C4","ph":"908-295-9071","em":"cptkevin1986@gmail.com","tw":"White Plains","st":"NY","ac":"Sharing a bottle of fine wine and a good meal while swapping stories from our past (much like the interviews PLaf does on his podcast).","w":"Kevin lives in White Plains, New York. He has three grandsons: Austin, Gideon, and Elijah. After OBC and before starting his first assignment in Italy, he lived in downtown Carmel, California, along with Maura O'Brien '86, Steve Merkel '86, and Brian McGowen '86, sharing a house with a deck overlooking the Pacific while studying at the Defense Language Institute in Monterey. He majored in computer science and got his master's degree. After nine years on active duty, he spent the last 30 years in IT. He has a level 3 certification from WSET (Wine and Spirits Education Trust) and has a part-time job at a local wine superstore helping on the sales floor. He plans to stay active in the wine trade after retirement. He enjoys sharing a bottle of fine wine and a good meal while swapping stories. He can be reached at kevin.belmont@west-point.org | 908-295-9071."},{"id":62,"n":"John Bencivenga","u":"John","g":"G1","p":"C3","ph":"813-505-5398","em":"jbencivenga@verizon.net","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL","ac":"traveling, sports, would be happy to connect with classmates who are Catholic and take their faith seriously.","w":"John Bencivenga resides in Tampa, Florida, where he works as General Counsel. Contact information includes 813-505-5398 and jbencivenga@verizon.net. He described his cadet experience candidly, noting that he disliked West Point and does not dwell on it, while recognizing the paradox that many of his closest and deepest friendships are with classmates, whom he considers reliable and worth supporting without hesitation. His cadet years are remembered less for specific highlights and more for the enduring bonds formed. His most significant Army experience consisted of a series of strong assignments, including service at Fort Ord and Fort Lewis, which he recalled as enjoyable and formative. After leaving the Army, he attended law school with a fellow G-1 classmate Rich Bradford, practiced law together for a period, then moved into an in-house legal role in 2003. He has served as General Counsel since 2007 and participated in the sale of a company to a UnitedHealth Group entity alongside a close H-1 classmate. His current interests include traveling, sports, and connecting with classmates who take their Catholic faith seriously, and he remains actively connected with members of G-1 through frequent communication. He and his wife Chrissy have four sons."},{"id":63,"n":"Albert Beninati","u":"Al","g":"B2","p":"E4","ph":"630-386-6589","em":"abeninatijr@yahoo.com","tw":"Malvern","st":"PA"},{"id":64,"n":"Kemal Benouis","u":"Ian","g":"F2","p":"E1","ph":"512-538-8213","em":"ian@benouis.com","tw":"Bastrop","st":"TX","ac":"hanging out together","w":"Ian Benouis Ian lives in Bastrop, Texas. He served as a Blackhawk pilot and reports he was the top Blackhawk pilot in the Army. He was in Panama for the invasion run-up and Operation Just Cause, becoming a pilot-in-command with only 74 total hours, in less than a year from the Blackhawk transition. His unit became the 4th Battalion of SOAR (Task Force 160) when Fort Ord was shut down shortly after he left. After leaving the Army, he became an intellectual property attorney. He co-founded the Church of the Sacred Synthesis at www.psilomethoxin.com and was patient number one at the Mission Within for 5-MeO-DMT and ibogaine treatment, where over 1,000 special operators have since followed. Ian enjoys hanging out with classmates. He can be reached at ian@benouis.com | 512-538-8213."},{"id":65,"n":"Kirk Benson","u":"Kirk","g":"E4","p":"C3","em":"kirk@bensco.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":66,"n":"Michael Bertha","u":"Mike","g":"I4","p":"I3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":67,"n":"Anne Berton","u":"Anne","g":"H2","p":"A3","ph":"(915) 833-4522","em":"berton16@aol.com","tw":"El Paso","st":"TX"},{"id":68,"n":"Andrew Bessmer","u":"Andrew","g":"F4","p":"H3","ph":"509-230-1295","em":"adbessmer@comcast.net","tw":"Spokane","st":"WA"},{"id":69,"n":"Burt Biebuyck","u":"Burt","g":"I1","p":"H4","ph":"(719) 238-6413","em":"bbolsm82@aol.com"},{"id":70,"n":"Philip Biggs","u":"Philip","g":"C4","p":"B1","ph":"614-256-9203","em":"pbiggs88@gmail.com","tw":"Greer","st":"SC"},{"id":71,"n":"John Billie","u":"Scott","g":"B3","p":"E4","ph":"757-634-7558","em":"jscott.billie@gmail.com","tw":"Chesterfield","st":"VA","ac":"Attend sporting events, dinner, wine tasting.","w":"J Scott Billie Scott lives in Chesterfield, Virginia. He has three children. His fondest cadet memory, among many from a great B3 cohort, is belly-whopping on the third floor of Eisenhower Barracks until water flowed into the Central Guard Room. His first Army assignment was with 1-8 CAV, 1st Cavalry Division, where he deployed to Desert Storm alongside Bill Vredenburgh, Aubrey Garner, Bruce Wilson, and Dave McCarley. After leaving active duty, he stayed on as a DA Civilian teaching Operations Research Systems Analysis students at Fort Lee, Virginia. Current interests include attending sporting events, dinners, and wine tastings, and he loves to cook. He stays active with the West Point Society of Richmond and extends an open invitation: stop by RVA and look him up. Scott can be reached at jscott.billie@gmail.com | 757-634-7558."},{"id":72,"n":"William Birchfield","u":"Randy","g":"D3","p":"G1","ph":"678-630-9514","em":"randybirchfield@gmail.com","tw":"Largo","st":"FL","ac":"Attending sporting events, dining at new restaurants, live music and shows, travel","w":"Randy Birchfield Randy lives in Largo, Florida. He and his wife have five children - four girls and one boy. All of their children are out of college and gainfully employed. Their son is Class of 2019 and serves as a Psychological Warfare officer in Special Operations. He was formerly an Apache pilot. His plebe company was G1, graduating from D3. The summer after cow year he went to Los Alamos National Lab as a research associate in the laser fusion project, which he describes as an unbelievably enlightening experience. He served as a combat engineer sapper in the 65th Engineer Battalion, 25th Infantry Division, and was deployed across the Pacific basin in joint exercises with host nation armed forces. After the Army, he went back to business school and began a business career doing troubled company work. He was recruited to the insurance industry where he spent the bulk of his career working in large national insurance carriers. He currently works for a large private-equity backed insurance distributor. He enjoys attending sporting events, dining at new restaurants, live music and shows, and traveling for pleasure. He can be reached at randybirchfield@gmail.com | 678-630-9514."},{"id":73,"n":"Dale Bisek","u":"Dale","g":"F2","p":"C3"},{"id":74,"n":"Russell Bittle","u":"Rusty","g":"A3","p":"I2","ph":"571-436-5278","em":"rustybittle0327@gmail.com","tw":"Dumfries","st":"VA"},{"id":75,"n":"Douglas Black","u":"Doug","g":"A1","p":"A3","ph":"678-495-8293","em":"dougblack3221@gmail.com","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA","ac":"Football games, hanging out and catching up, Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund events","w":"Doug Black Doug lives in Atlanta with his wife Joanne, married 40 years. They have sons JD, 38, and Luke, 13. Their son Justin passed away at 19. Grandchildren are Avery, 8, and Andrew, 4. His favorite assignment was the 92nd Engineer Battalion at Fort Stewart, with projects in Ecuador and Honduras. After the Army, he attended business school, worked at McKinsey & Company and Oldcastle, and now serves as Chairman and CEO of SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc. He attends football games and Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund events. He can be reached at dougblack3221@gmail.com | 678-495-8293."},{"id":76,"n":"Kenneth Blakely","u":"Ken","g":"G2","p":"B1","em":"ken@blakelys.us","tw":"Williamsburg","st":"VA"},{"id":77,"n":"Gregory Bleszinski","u":"Greg","g":"G4","p":"B3","ph":"(860) 659-2890","em":"gblesz@gmail.com","tw":"Manchester","st":"NH"},{"id":78,"n":"Howard Blevins","u":"Howard","g":"E2","p":"H1","ph":"256-415-7013","em":"howard.blevins@gmail.com","tw":"Harvest","st":"AL"},{"id":79,"n":"Jonathan Blevins","u":"J David","g":"B1","p":"F4","ph":"(757) 471-1938","em":"jdblevdog@yahoo.com","tw":"Virginia Beach","st":"VA"},{"id":80,"n":"Lorie (FLeming) Blount","u":"Lorie","g":"A1","p":"B2","ph":"425-449-1434","em":"loblount86@gmail.com","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA","ac":"Travel, sporting events, and of course attending concerts or music festivals.","w":"Lorie Blount Lorie lives in Atlanta with two daughters. Cameron, her oldest, is a third-year psychiatry resident at Duke and married. Alex lives in Atlanta and works as a CPA for Dolby. No grandkids yet. She served five years, including time at Fort Ord with the 7th Infantry Division (Light) with trips to NTC, one admission cycle at USMA as an Outreach Officer recruiting in the Southeast, and a year teaching logistics at the Finance School at Fort Benjamin Harrison. After the Army, she attended Stanford Law School and worked at a large firm before moving in-house across telecom, software, and healthcare industries. Her most meaningful work was with hospital systems. She now works remotely on a flexible schedule. She experienced adult-onset epilepsy in her 40s that led to brain surgery and shifted her focus toward family and friends over career. She travels, attends sporting events, and goes to concerts and music festivals. She can be reached at loblount86@gmail.com | 425-449-1434."},{"id":81,"n":"Sharri (Davis) Board","u":"Sharri","g":"E4","p":"H1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":82,"n":"George Bond","u":"George","g":"G1","p":"A2","ph":"907-978-1310","em":"glbond@msn.com","tw":"Owens Cross Roads","st":"AL","ac":"Skiing, Football games (Huntsville is within easy travel of several of the American League schools we play in football), potentially travel. As the class starts retiring all of this should get easier.","w":"George Bond resides in Huntsville, Alabama, where he is retired and actively engaged in community and volunteer work. He described his cadet experience as a lot of work but with too many fond memories to count. As a member of the G1 “Activity Staff” he was known for organizing company parties and events, including a memorable one held aboard the Superintendent’s Yacht. His most significant Army assignment was commanding the Arctic Test Center in Alaska, a role he cited as one of the few in which he genuinely looked forward to going to work on Mondays. This was followed by service with the Missile Defense Agency in both Alaska and Germany, including technically demanding and diplomatically sensitive liaison work. After military service, he remained in Germany fielding missile defense systems in Poland and Romania. He retired completely at age 54 to prioritize time over income. His current interests include skiing, extensive travel, G1 get togethers, camping, fitness, and volunteer work. He is married to Lori Bond, a retired Army Nurse. Their two daughters currently live in Denver and their first grandchild is due in Feb 2026."},{"id":83,"n":"Vincent Bons","u":"Vincent","g":"A2","p":"","ph":"(937) 310-6033","em":"bonsvc@att.net","tw":"Bellbrook","st":"OH"},{"id":84,"n":"David Bonsavage","u":"David","g":"I2","p":"E4","em":"dbonsa@hotmail.com","tw":"Bradenton","st":"FL"},{"id":85,"n":"Darren Booth","u":"Darren","g":"I1","p":"A4","ph":"813-310-0196","em":"darren.tampa@gmail.com","tw":"Bradenton","st":"FL"},{"id":86,"n":"Christopher Borgerding","u":"Christopher","g":"G3","p":"F1","tw":"Suwanee","st":"GA"},{"id":87,"n":"John Born","u":"John","g":"A3","p":"H1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":88,"n":"Jeffery Bost","u":"Jeffery","g":"A4","p":"","tw":"Bisbee","st":"AZ"},{"id":89,"n":"John Boule","u":"John","g":"I4","p":"C3","ph":"(703) 937-7508","em":"jboule@dewberry.com","tw":"Red Bank","st":"NJ"},{"id":90,"n":"Oswald Boykin","u":"Steve","g":"D1","p":"B4","ph":"410-274-2778","em":"steve.boykin@verizon.net","tw":"Silver Spring","st":"MD"},{"id":91,"n":"Richard Bradford","u":"Rich","g":"G1","p":"G2","ph":"813-847-1793","em":"fsusma86@gmail.com","tw":"Valrico","st":"FL","ac":"golfsport eventssoccerfootballtravel","w":"Richard Bradford resides in Valrico, Florida, where he works in the legal field. Contact information includes 813-847-1793 and fsusma86@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience through specific moments rather than general characterization, recalling as a highlight the ceremony after completing hours as a firstie private when his TAC presented him his sabre at accountability formation, followed weeks later by travel to the Air Force Academy for the Army–Air Force game, where he declined a beer offered by an Air Force cadet in the dorms. His most significant Army assignment involved work connected to the School of the Americas while stationed at Fort Benning, where he participated in taking Salvadoran war veterans to Disney World and Epcot. After military service, he transitioned into the legal profession, including serving as second chair in a trial approximately one to two weeks after September 11. Rich left the Army in 1992 during the post–Cold War drawdown period. His current interests include golf, sports events, soccer, football, and travel, and his family includes a son serving as an Airman First Class at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base and a daughter expected to finish high school in 2026."},{"id":92,"n":"Mark Bradley","u":"Mark","g":"G1","p":"G2","ph":"732-859-1184","em":"bradleymk5@verizon.net","tw":"Shrewsbury","st":"NJ","ac":"Golf, attending sports events, and would consider travel","w":"Mark Bradley resides in Shrewsbury, New Jersey, where he works in software, professional services, sales, and management while approaching retirement. Contact information includes 732-859-1184 and bradleymk5@verizon.net. He described his cadet experience with humor, noting that he spent his high school years trying to get into West Point and his cadet years trying to get out, remaining on academic probation for much of his time before graduating in the middle of the class and branching Aviation. His Army service included assignments with 4/7 Cavalry (later reflagged 5/17 Cavalry) in 2nd Infantry Division in Korea, followed by 3-101 Aviation in the 101st Airborne Division. After Desert Storm he served at Fort Rucker as an Instructor Pilot, primarily teaching helicopter gunnery, and later commanded an Air Traffic Control company before leaving the Army to start a family. After military service he worked for Booz Allen Hamilton supporting Army digitization initiatives in New Jersey, then transitioned to software firms in progressively broader roles. His current interests include golf, attending sports events, and travel. Mark and his wife Marianne have four children currently living across New Jersey, Mississippi, Delaware, and Mississippi."},{"id":93,"n":"Stephen Bradley","u":"Steve","g":"E1","p":"C2","ph":"904-571-6158","em":"sbra63@yahoo.com","tw":"Jacksonville Beach","st":"FL","af":"150-Pound Football","ac":"Golf and travel are my extracurricular activities","w":"Steve lives in Jacksonville Beach, Florida. His children are in Denver and Albany, and he's working hard in his job with a couple of years until retirement. His plebe company was C2, graduating from E1. His most memorable cadet experiences were sitting in Grant Hall with Chris Townley and John Cannon, and playing 150-pound football with an amazing team. He served in the 7th Infantry Division in Monterey and commanded in the 3rd Infantry Division in Schweinfurt, with visits to Panama and the First Gulf War. After the Army, he spent 31 years in MedTech, going from Group VP at Stryker (a Fortune 200 company) to small company CEO and now partner at Deloitte. He enjoys golf and has traveled the world extensively - he will spend Christmas in India, his 72nd country visited. He can be reached at sbra63@yahoo.com | 904-571-6158."},{"id":94,"n":"Mary Brady","u":"Meg","g":"I3","p":"A1","tw":"Minneapolis","st":"MN"},{"id":95,"n":"Matthew Brady","u":"Matt","g":"B1","p":"A4","em":"mattbradyaz@gmail.com","tw":"Phoenix","st":"AZ"},{"id":96,"n":"John Brau","u":"John","g":"B3","p":"D2","em":"jwbrau@aol.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":97,"n":"Ann (MacIntyre) Brechbuhl","u":"Anne","g":"G3","p":"E2","ph":"603-715-7189","em":"abrechbuhl@gmail.com","tw":"Earlysville","st":"VA"},{"id":98,"n":"Thomas Brechbuhl","u":"Uhlrich","g":"D3","p":"D2","ph":"(404) 869-1189","em":"ubrechbuhl@outlook.com","tw":"Brookhaven","st":"GA"},{"id":99,"n":"James Breen","u":"Jim","g":"F4","p":"H2","ph":"(817) 846-6887","em":"jim.breen@wellsfargoadvisors.com","tw":"Fort Worth","st":"TX"},{"id":100,"n":"Therese (Schiffer) Brehm","u":"Therese","g":"G3","p":"E4","ph":"703-795-5100","em":"tbrehm86@gmail.com","tw":"Carlisle","st":"PA","ac":"sporting events, social events","w":"Therese Brehm Therese Brehm lives in Carlisle, Pennsylvania with her husband Les. She has four children, stepdaughters 39 and 37, son 29, and daughter 27, and two grandchildren, ages 12 and 10. Her youngest daughter is currently a Captain and Apache pilot stationed at Fort Drum, surprising Therese and Les by following in their footsteps. Her first assignment after flight school was with 3rd MI Battalion at Camp Humphreys, South Korea, where she was schooled by crusty old Vietnam-era aviation warrant officers who presented her with an honorary warrant officer card when her tour ended. She stayed in the Army six years, leaving when she and Les started a family. After taking five years off, she worked as a manufacturing engineer before moving to IT Program Management for a government contractor during overseas assignments in Germany, Korea, and Kenya. When Les retired and they moved to Pennsylvania, she transitioned to IT Program Management as a civil servant, ending her career with DLA. She moved 14 times across four continents raising her children. She remembers fondly providing advice from a woman's perspective to her G3 gopher friends during evening counseling sessions, and they still maintain a big group text. She enjoys cooking, skiing, golf and travel as well as attending sporting and social events. She can be reached at tbrehm86@gmail.com | 703-795-5100."},{"id":101,"n":"Nicholas Brent","u":"Nick","g":"I1","p":"D4","tw":"Lantana","st":"TX"},{"id":102,"n":"Mark Brick","u":"Mark","g":"C1","p":"F2","ph":"425-422-0035","em":"armylax1986@gmail.com","tw":"Cornell","st":"MI","ac":"Traveled to Ireland in 2025 with a group of '86 grads.  Planning on traveling to Scotland in 2026 with a similar group.","w":"Mark Brick Mark lives in Cornell, Michigan with his wife Yolanda Arts, also Class of '86, whom he married in 2012. They both retired in 2023 and settled in Michigan's Upper Peninsula. He raised a nephew who now works as a contractor for Microsoft in Seattle. Mark I spent plebe year in F-2 (Go Zoo!), graduating from C-1. He served as a tank platoon leader and support platoon leader in 1st Squadron/4th Cavalry, 1st Infantry Division (Big Red One), then transferred to Signal to work in computer roles his final years. After the Army, he worked in IT for 30 years, mostly with the University of Washington Medical Centers in Seattle, focusing on Windows Server administration and serving as Citrix team lead. He earned his MBA from UW for free during this time. His most memorable cadet experience was reporting to the man in the red sash during R-Day, being told to get in line for haircuts, then pinging at 100 mph in the wrong direction until stopped and told \"Get over here you stupid bean head!\" He still plays lacrosse actively with old guy squads in tournaments in Hawaii, Ireland, Canada, Vail, Lake Placid, and Fort Lauderdale, having competed three times in the World Lacrosse Championships. He traveled to Ireland in 2025 with a group of '86 grads and is planning a Scotland trip in 2026 with a similar group. He can be reached at  armylax1986@gmail.com | 425-422-0035."},{"id":103,"n":"Winston Bridge","u":"Jay","g":"G3","p":"E4","ph":"(303) 928-4233","em":"wjbridge@aol.com","tw":"Carefree","st":"AZ"},{"id":104,"n":"Rhonda (Barush) Bright","u":"Rhonda","g":"F3","p":"E4","ph":"(706) 545-9838","em":"royaloak@mchsi.com","tw":"Midland","st":"GA"},{"id":105,"n":"Thomas Brittain","u":"Thomas","g":"E1","p":"D3","em":"thomashbrittain@gmail.com","tw":"Sykesville","st":"MD"},{"id":106,"n":"David Britten","u":"David","g":"H4","p":"I2","ph":"(540) 972-3296"},{"id":107,"n":"Stephen Brooks","u":"Stephen","g":"I2","p":"B1","ph":"603-722-1639","em":"stephen.e.brooks@gmail.com","tw":"West Chesterfield","st":"NH","ac":"He regularly attends Johnny Mac golf events and enjoys reconnecting with classmates there. His interests center on outdoor activity, travel, and social gatherings linked to the Northeast, including mountaineering, hiking, and winter environments he has preferred since cadet days.","w":"Stephen Brooks Brooksie lives in West Chesterfield, New Hampshire. He and his wife have two sons. The eldest graduated from the University of Edinburgh and now works in AI outside London. The younger remains in New Hampshire, interested in technology while working through early-career choices. He comes from a deep New England lineage dating to 1630, with family roots at Lexington-Concord and Navy service through WWII. He met his wife through a Capitol Hill connection. His plebe company was B1, graduating from I2. His memories span a prior-service head start on military skills, the intensity of B-1 hazing, and the infamous \"white socks incident\" that drew the attention of multiple upperclassmen. He played intramural lacrosse until blowing out his ACL a month before graduation, then crossed the stage in a brace. He also recalls the camaraderie of the 5th-floor \"frat,\" working as a track manager, climbing with friends, and mechanical-engineering mentorship from Colonel Barber that tied together mechanical and electrical concepts. His early service included earth-moving and road-building platoons at Fort Belvoir, then a consequential tour at the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers headquarters during Hurricane Katrina and the Loma Prieta earthquake. He consolidated disaster reports for the Chief of Engineers and witnessed the Corps' unique ability to mobilize nationwide assets during crises. He left the Army in 1990 just before stop-loss. He moved into construction management, earned his PE, and then transitioned through multiple engineering and manufacturing leadership roles with Ford and Osram Sylvania. Later he became COO of Littleton Coin Company, an employee-owned retail coin business, using continuous-improvement skills, cross-training, and technical systems expertise to strengthen operations. He regularly attends Johnny Mac golf events and enjoys reconnecting with classmates there. His interests center on outdoor activity, travel, and social gatherings linked to the Northeast, including mountaineering, hiking, and winter environments. He is an introvert who manages energy carefully, credits the Highlands Ability Battery with reshaping his career choices, and believes firmly that \"nice guys don't have to finish last.\" He can be reached at stephen.e.brooks@gmail.com | 603-722-1639."},{"id":108,"n":"Jeffery Brown","u":"Jeff","g":"I2","p":"H3","ph":"864-580-0942","em":"brown953@gmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":109,"n":"John Brown","u":"Jake","g":"C1","p":"C4","ph":"917-748-1755","em":"jabro100@hotmail.com","tw":"Montclair","st":"NJ"},{"id":110,"n":"Todd Brown","u":"Todd","g":"A2","p":"H1","ph":"(401) 783-8954"},{"id":111,"n":"Scott Bruner","u":"Scott","g":"A2","p":"A1","ph":"(703) 764-2160","em":"Bruners@aol.com","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA"},{"id":112,"n":"Jeffrey Bruno","u":"Jeffrey","g":"H1","p":"A3","ph":"949-636-6021","em":"fivebrunos@earthlink.net","tw":"Foothill Ranch","st":"CA"},{"id":113,"n":"Edward Brunot","u":"Ed","g":"C2","p":"C1","ph":"(757) 663-1779","em":"ebrunot@mac.com","tw":"Norfolk","st":"VA"},{"id":114,"n":"Mark Bryant","u":"Mark","g":"A2","p":"F4","tw":"Albany","st":"OR"},{"id":115,"n":"James Buck","u":"Jim","g":"G4","p":"F1","ph":"(919) 535-8919","em":"Jim.Buck64@gmail.com","tw":"Chapel Hill","st":"NC"},{"id":116,"n":"Aaron Buckley","u":"Aaron","g":"E3","p":"I1","ph":"(619) 855-8613","em":"abuckley@paulplevin.com","tw":"San Diego","st":"CA"},{"id":117,"n":"Matthew Buckner","u":"Matt","g":"A4","p":"H1","em":"mdbuckner22@gmail.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"AR"},{"id":118,"n":"Brian Bulatao","u":"Brian","g":"D3","p":"A1","ph":"316-393-6832","em":"brian.bulatao@outlook.com","tw":"Colleyville","st":"TX"},{"id":119,"n":"Robert Bullard","u":"Bobby","g":"I3","p":"F4","ph":"703-593-1728","em":"robert.bullard@yahoo.com","tw":"Heathvulle","st":"VA","ac":"A lifelong waterman, Bobby loves fishing and boating, especially from his home in Heathsville, Virginia, where the Potomac River meets the Chesapeake Bay. He’s passionate about waterfront living and spending time outdoors. His coastal setup and boat access make him ideally suited for fishing trips or water-based gatherings with classmates.","w":"Robert Bullard Bobby lives in Heathsville, Virginia, where the Potomac River meets the Chesapeake Bay. He has three daughters: Brittany, born 1990 in Fort Sill, Oklahoma, is an Air Force Veteran and lives overseas passionately practicing yoga, pottery, and tea ceremonies; Lauren, born 1992 in Fort Polk, Louisiana, is a nurse and lives in Fairfax, Virginia with her husband (Dennis) and newborn daughter, Carley; and Sophia, born 1998 in Fairfax, Virginia, is an associate scientist for EnviroLogix in Portland, Maine. He is very proud of their independence and enjoys their reunions, though the distance makes those moments even more special. He grew up in St. Petersburg, Florida with a Panamanian mother and a veteran father. His love for the Army started young, influenced by family military service and his older brother's West Point interest. He credits his mother's discipline and early ROTC experience for preparing him well. His plebe company was F4, graduating from I3. His most vivid cadet memory is from Plebe Year when he disastrously cut a Martha Washington sheet cake during lunch. As punishment, he had to salute George Washington's statue and apologize loudly for \"massacring his wife's cake,\" which became a source of great amusement for his company. He also fondly recalls being part of a resistance calisthenics pilot and how his upbringing by a strict Panamanian mother had already prepared him for the fourth-class system. One of his most memorable Army moments was during a chemical training exercise when a CS gas grenade exploded in his hand, giving him a full-face dose and sparking chaos as soldiers thought he'd turned into a gasping zombie. He earned the \"Pink Elephant\" award for that event. He also served as a Battalion FSO in the Third Armored Division during Desert Storm, where he successfully stepped up after another officer couldn't deploy, earning praise from his leadership. After leaving active duty in 1998, he continued to serve in the Army Reserve until 2013, including work as an individual mobilized augmentee at USARPAC in Hawaii, traveling annually from DC. As a defense contractor, he helped design the Worldwide Individual Augmentation System, which became pivotal post-9/11. He also served in various roles as a policy analyst and operations researcher, earned a master's from George Mason, and now works as an Enterprise Architect supporting defense efforts at Fort Belvoir. A lifelong waterman, he loves fishing and boating from his home where his coastal setup and boat access make him ideally suited for fishing trips or water-based gatherings with classmates. He still makes his bed with military precision every morning and maintains a strong sense of self-reflection, encouraging younger leaders to stay grounded, treat people well, and never forget to enjoy life. He can be reached at robert.bullard@yahoo.com | 703-593-1728."},{"id":120,"n":"Christopher Bump","u":"Chris","g":"B4","p":"E1","ph":"972-768-4149","em":"cncbump@verizon.net","tw":"Flower Mound","st":"TX","ac":"Chris is not a golfer but enjoys travel, especially international travel, having recently visited Italy, Spain, and Greece. He values informal gatherings tied to reunions, Army–Navy events, shared meals, and company-centered meetups. He also enjoys cooking and hosting or contributing to large family-style meals, which would translate well to classmate gatherings built around food, conversation, and shared stories rather than formal activities.","w":"Chris Bump Chris lives in Flower Mound, Texas, with his wife and twin daughters who are seniors in college. One attended the University of Virginia on a soccer scholarship, and the other studies at Texas A&M. Both are pursuing healthcare paths, particularly microbiology-related fields. A major highlight was serving in an 8-inch artillery battalion as a corps-level asset during Desert Storm, ultimately serving as battery XO. He left active duty in 1991 and transitioned into healthcare and medical sales through Cameron-Brooks. He has spent more than three decades in healthcare-related commercial roles, including leadership positions, and currently serves as a regional business director responsible for a large portion of the country. He was a prep school graduate and majored in military history with a focus on 18th-century Europe and the Napoleonic Wars. He later developed professional-level miniature painting skills, primarily for UK clients. He travels, especially internationally, having recently visited Italy, Spain, and Greece. He enjoys cooking and hosting large family-style meals. He can be reached at cncbump@verizon.net | 972-768-4149."},{"id":121,"n":"Andy Bunn","u":"Andy","g":"G3","p":"","ph":"469-600-4541","em":"abunnhbunn@aol.com","tw":"Savannah","st":"TX","af":"Glee Club","ac":"Golf, sporting events","w":"Andy Bunn Andy lives in Savannah, Texas with two children and two grandchildren. He is a Desert Storm veteran who served in Kuwait. Many of his cadet memories involve the Glee Club.He is an ordained minister serving with a ministry that shares the Gospel of Jesus with children. He golfs and attends sporting events. He can be reached at abunnhbunn@aol.com | 469-600-4541."},{"id":122,"n":"Keith Burnham","u":"Keith","g":"I1","p":"C2","ph":"301-906-4845","em":"kburnham@comcast.net","tw":"Washington","st":"DC"},{"id":123,"n":"Gregory Butts","u":"Gregory","g":"I1","p":"G4","em":"buttsgk@aol.com","tw":"Lansing","st":"KS"},{"id":124,"n":"Richard Cabrey","u":"Mike","g":"C1","p":"A4","em":"mikecabrey@me.com","tw":"Colonial Beach","st":"VA"},{"id":125,"n":"John Callahan","u":"Jack","g":"A1","p":"C3","em":"tracyjohnb6@yahoo.com","tw":"Minoa","st":"NY","ac":"Jack did not explicitly list preferred activities, but his stories point to interest in conversation, reconnecting, and shared history. He remains active, social, and engaged with Army–Navy games, Academy visits, and West Point family traditions.","w":"Jack Callahan Jack lives in Minoa, New York, with five children, four currently serving in the military. His eldest daughter is USMA '20, a cyber officer with a master's in data analytics. His second is USNA '22, now at the Naval Postgraduate School studying computer science. His third is a firstie at West Point branching infantry, and his fourth is a youngster at the Naval Academy preparing for nuclear surface warfare. His youngest daughter Kate is in high school. No grandchildren yet. He served in Germany with the 74th Detachment in the Pershing 1A community under a German air base, handling theater nuclear responsibilities and translating German medical documentation for personnel reliability program reviews. He left the Army during the drawdown and completed medical school with help from West Point connections. After training in internal medicine and working in Watertown, he settled in Syracuse. He now works as an internal-medicine physician for the VA, running home-based primary care for elderly and critically ill veterans, including hospice patients. He grew up in Syracuse as one of seven children; his mother was a German national who survived wartime hardships. During his cadet years, he nearly failed out due to rock math after staying up all night folding socks, completed a Bolivia exchange trip, and was later flagged by two departments as a potential future faculty member. He remains active and engaged with Army-Navy games, Academy visits, and West Point family traditions. He can be reached at tracyjohnb6@yahoo.com."},{"id":126,"n":"Terence Callahan","u":"Terry","g":"E1","p":"D3","ph":"508-613-5163","em":"terrycallahan1@verizon.net","tw":"Miami","st":"FL","ac":"I enjoy golf and spending time with family.  Looking forward to the first grandchild on the way.","w":"Terry Callahan Terry and his wife Kelly live in Miami with grown children spread across the northeast. His eldest son Chris graduated from West Point in 2018 and works in medtech in the Boston area. Daughter Cara works for TJX and lives in Newport, Rhode Island. Son Michael plays professional hockey, splitting time between Boston and Providence. Daughter Mary just graduated from Ohio State. The first grandchild is on the way. Terry served in Bamberg, Germany, where he traveled around Europe and skied in the Alps whenever possible. He left the Army in 1990 and started a career in medtech, working various commercial roles primarily in the Boston area before a recent move brought him to Miami. He plays golf, follows his son's hockey career, and likes simple gatherings with family and friends over a few beers on weekends. He can be reached at terrycallahan1@verizon.net | (508) 613-5163."},{"id":127,"n":"Dennis Calloway","u":"Dennis","g":"D1","p":"G3","ph":"(832) 563-0280","em":"dennis121@comcast.net"},{"id":128,"n":"Tedson Campagna","u":"Tedson","g":"G3","p":"A2","em":"jacki87@juno.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"NC"},{"id":129,"n":"John Cannon","u":"John","g":"H3","p":"G4","em":"jlcannon4@verizon.net","tw":"Lucas","st":"TX","af":"150-Pound Football","ac":"He remains active and enjoys sports, particularly football and rugby from his younger days. His present life is oriented around family, work, and dogs, but he would welcome reconnecting at reunions and gatherings. He appreciates time with classmates and is open to travel, events, and shared experiences that fit his schedule.","w":"John Cannon John lives in Lucas, Texas. He and his wife have two adult daughters. One is a Texas A&M petroleum engineer working in oil and gas, and the younger is a University of Arkansas graduate working as a nurse at Baylor Hospital. He has four grandchildren: three little boys and a girl. All live in the Dallas area and he sees them most weekends. His plebe company was G4, graduating from H3. His earliest and strongest memory is upperclassmen demanding he \"just talk\" so they could laugh at his Alabama accent. Another foundational memory is learning that effort no longer mattered—only results. He recalls G-4 plebe year, meeting future lifelong friends, and realizing that people from all backgrounds are worth knowing. He remembers rugby injuries, 150-pound football, and the camaraderie of H-3. He never visited West Point before reporting. His Army highlights were flying brand-new Black Hawks from the Sikorsky factory to El Paso, then deploying them immediately for Desert Shield/Storm, supporting 3rd ACR with logistics flights, moving fuel and engines forward, and occasionally backhauling grateful Iraqi POWs. Later he commanded the only Black Hawk company in Hawaii, learning to fly night-goggles over water and running demanding inter-island missions. He left during the post-Desert Storm drawdown. Using a JMO hiring firm, he entered semiconductor sales in Dallas, rising quickly to general manager. He transitioned to healthcare IT, spending thirteen years in rehabilitation-software sales and becoming a subject-matter expert. He is semi-retired from a role in hospital communications technology. He sees himself as introverted and still surprised to have built a successful sales career. His approach is consultative: listen, answer honestly, follow through. Core Army lessons—do what you say you will do, and never expect others to do what you won't—remain the backbone of his professional style. He remains active and enjoys sports, particularly football and rugby from his younger days. His present life is oriented around family, work, and dogs. He can be reached at jlcannon4@verizon.net."},{"id":130,"n":"Stephen Cannon","u":"Steve","g":"C4","p":"E1","ph":"404-360-9108","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":131,"n":"Steven Cannon","u":"Steven","g":"F2","p":"","em":"steveatdblookup@gmail.com","tw":"Sterling","st":"VA"},{"id":132,"n":"Gregory Canter","u":"Gregory","g":"H4","p":"","em":"gcanter@atnex.net","tw":"Kennesaw","st":"GA"},{"id":133,"n":"Duane Cantey","u":"Duane","g":"G4","p":"D2","ph":"(501) 556-5595","em":"duanecantey86@yahoo.com","tw":"Mount Vernon","st":"AR"},{"id":134,"n":"Louis Capezzuto","u":"Lou","g":"A1","p":"G3","ph":"(732) 524-2218","tw":"Monroe","st":"NJ"},{"id":135,"n":"Steven Cardin","u":"Steven","g":"F2","p":"D3","ph":"(616) 682-4825","em":"Sgjcardin@gmail.com","tw":"Boston","st":"MA"},{"id":136,"n":"Bruce Carniglia","u":"Bruce","g":"B2","p":"E3","ph":"770-241-7213","em":"bfcarniglia@gmail.com","tw":"Braselton","st":"GA"},{"id":137,"n":"Forrest Carpenter","u":"Forrest","g":"I3","p":"E2","ph":"580-350-7323","em":"carpenterfl@gmail.com","tw":"Ardmore","st":"TN"},{"id":138,"n":"Scott Carr","u":"Scott","g":"F1","p":"G2"},{"id":139,"n":"Kenneth Carrick","u":"Ken","g":"B3","p":"D2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":140,"n":"Roger Carstens","u":"Roger","g":"B2","p":"C4","ph":"202-297-6742","em":"Roger.Carstens@gmail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":141,"n":"Richard Carter","u":"Richard","g":"A3","p":"F2","em":"jenisecarter@gmail.com","tw":"Hendersonville","st":"NC"},{"id":142,"n":"Thomas Cartledge","u":"Thomas","g":"D3","p":"I1","ph":"(571) 285-2797","em":"tcartledge@att.net","tw":"Woodbridge","st":"VA","w":"Tom Cartledge Tom lives in Woodbridge, Virginia. His plebe company was I1. After the Army, he worked in research and development. He has finally succeeded in retiring. He can be reached at tcartledge@att.net | 571-285-2797."},{"id":143,"n":"Robert Carty","u":"Robert","g":"I2","p":"","ph":"414-406-6356","em":"ccarty@wi.rr.com","tw":"Germantown","st":"WI","w":"Robert Carty Bob lives in Germantown, Wisconsin. He is married to his wife Cherie since 1993 and has two children. Both graduated from Marquette University, and one is now in the master's program at Marquette. His plebe company was not specified, graduating from I2. He attended flight school and served in the 2/227th in Hanau, Germany. He left the service in 1990 and joined the Wisconsin National Guard in 1991, serving until retiring in 2013 with two stateside deployments. He served in various staff and line positions, with the most interesting being as commander of the 832nd Med Co (AA) during its deployment to Fort Lewis in 2003-2005. After leaving active duty, he moved to the Milwaukee area in 1991 and worked in the quality field for various companies in the area, culminating as the Director of Quality for a family of companies. He retired in 2025. He can be reached at ccarty@wi.rr.com | 414-406-6356."},{"id":144,"n":"James Casey","u":"Jim","g":"A2","p":"H1","ph":"512-674-5508","em":"jyicasey@msn.com","tw":"Buda","st":"TX"},{"id":145,"n":"Matthew Cashin","u":"Matt","g":"A3","p":"G1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":146,"n":"Charles Cavin","u":"Chuck","g":"F1","p":"H2","em":"charles.cavin@icloud.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":147,"n":"Scott Chaisson","u":"Scott","g":"E1","p":"H2","em":"chaisson1@comcast.net","tw":"Duxbury","st":"MA"},{"id":148,"n":"Benjamin Chambers","u":"Ben","g":"D4","p":"C3","ph":"(281) 900-7409","em":"bnchambers@yahoo.com","tw":"Kingwood","st":"TX"},{"id":149,"n":"Wendell Champion","u":"Wendell","g":"C1","p":"E2","em":"wendell.champion@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":150,"n":"James Chapel","u":"Scott","g":"A4","p":"","ph":"(325) 260-0300","em":"scott@thechapels.com"},{"id":151,"n":"David Chaplin","u":"David","g":"F4","p":"A2","ph":"(703) 955-1076","em":"chaplind@yahoo.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":152,"n":"Daniel Charron","u":"Dan","g":"G1","p":"D4","ph":"678-520-5791","em":"Charrond2022@gmail.com","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA","ac":"Outdoor activities","w":"Daniel Charron resides in Atlanta, Georgia, where he works in financial technology. Contact information includes charrond2022@gmail.com. His cadet experience was marked by milestone moments, with R Day and Graduation standing out as defining highlights that framed his time at the Academy. His most significant Army service included deployment to Iraq, which provided operational experience in a deployed environment. After military service, he transitioned into the financial technology sector, where he continues his professional career. His current interests include outdoor activities, and he notes that his children and grandchildren are all doing well."},{"id":153,"n":"Christopher Chiarello","u":"Chris","g":"H2","p":"C3","em":"cpchiarello@protonmail.com","tw":"Dulles","st":"VA"},{"id":154,"n":"Willie Childs","u":"Willie","g":"F1","p":"F4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":155,"n":"Michael Chinn","u":"Michael","g":"G2","p":"H3","em":"mkchinn@yahoo.com","tw":"University Place","st":"WA"},{"id":156,"n":"Fredrick Choi","u":"Fredrick","g":"D2","p":"","em":"Fredrick.choi@gmail.com","tw":"Acworth","st":"GA"},{"id":157,"n":"Michael Chopp","u":"Mike","g":"I3","p":"A2","ph":"629 252-4126","em":"m.chopp@yahoo.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO","w":"Mike Chopp Mike lives in Colorado Springs, Colorado. He has two children: a daughter born in 1994 at Fort Bliss while he was deployed to Saudi Arabia on a PATRIOT ADA rotation, who works as an aircraft mechanic for a regional delivery company in Montana; and a son born in 1996, who works as a cybersecurity contractor for the government in Colorado Springs after serving in the Army in Germany as a Signal officer. His son is married but no kids yet. The kids' locations prompted Mike and his wife's move from Tennessee to Colorado. Mike was a plebe in A2 and graduated from I3. One of his best memories was when a yearling asked if he wanted to \"hang out\" and listen to the Asia album—he and another plebe had to get up on wardrobe doors between their arms and hang out while the music played. The other plebe asked to leave after the first song, but Mike stayed for several until the yearlings lost interest. He was enlisted Infantry for about three years before West Point and served as a PATRIOT Air Defense Officer after graduation. He joined a newly formed battalion at Fort Bliss that trained there for certification and deployment to Ansbach, Germany, volunteering for Advance Party to help prepare the battalion and B Battery for a smooth transition. He met his wife in Germany and they married in Denmark in 1990. He had two commands: rear detachment commander and later A Battery. His daughter's birth halfway through his six-month deployment to Saudi Arabia prompted his resignation, which surprised his wife, he loved serving but decided being a present father meant more to him. In 1995 he resigned his commission and hired on with a Swedish telecom company as a site manager. Within 10 months he was offered a regional operations manager position and was asked to do both operations and project management. He spent 28 years in the telecom industry as Project Manager and later Program Director for introducing new products into customer labs and live networks, with his last two years as a Proposal Manager. He retired at the end of 2022. He can be reached at m.chopp@yahoo.com | 629-252-4126."},{"id":158,"n":"Matthew Christ","u":"Matt","g":"I4","p":"F2","em":"mdchrist@yahoo.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":159,"n":"James Clancy","u":"James","g":"H4","p":"H2","em":"jclancytx@outlook.com","tw":"Corpus Christi","st":"TX"},{"id":160,"n":"Christopher Clark","u":"Christopher","g":"E3","p":"C1","ph":"(830) 625-5847","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":161,"n":"Curt Clark","u":"Curt","g":"E2","p":"E4","ph":"(978) 377-0824","em":"curtjclark@gmail.com","tw":"Haverhill","st":"MA"},{"id":162,"n":"Harley Clark","u":"Wally","g":"A2","p":"D1","ph":"301-38-5299","em":"harley.clark2@gmail.com","tw":"Perdido Key","st":"FL","ac":"Golf and travel","w":"Wally Clark Wally lives in Perdido Key, Florida. He has one granddaughter, Harleigh, who was named after him. Walley remembers spring break in Fort Lauderdale with classmates. Tthe Winnebago trip was crazy. He served at Fort Polk, Fort Campbell, West Point, Schofield Barracks, and the Pentagon, where he was assigned on 9/11. After retirement, he worked at NSA for 10 years. His most interesting role was after NSA, babysitting his granddaughter Harleigh for 4½ years starting at three months old, four days a week, nine hours a day. He loved it but it wore him out. Wally enjoys golf and travel. He can be reached at harley.clark2@gmail.com | 301-388-5299."},{"id":163,"n":"Linda Clark","u":"Linda","g":"I4","p":"I2","em":"call_linda_911@hotmail.com","tw":"South Lake Tahoe","st":"CA"},{"id":164,"n":"Harris Clarke","u":"Harris","g":"I1","p":"E2","ph":"206-512-5591","em":"harrisgclarke@gmail.com","tw":"Winthrop","st":"WA","ac":"Skiing, Concerts, Sports Events"},{"id":165,"n":"Cary Clayborn","u":"Cary","g":"E4","p":"I2","ph":"214-202-8939","em":"cary.clayborn.abt@gmail.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX","ac":"Golf - starting playing at age 30 and have since played 774 different courses worldwide…in 45 states (been to all 50) and 17 countries (traveled to 55 mostly before golf), member Big Creek CC in Mountain Home, Arkansas which allowed me to join EPIC Golf Club and have access to almost every single private course in the top 250 including Augusta, so always interested golf some place and/or a golf tripTravel - despite the 55 countries, I’ve only once been below the equator to South Africa, so I’m looking to travel to South America, Australia/New Zealand, and continue adding to the total to get to 100Scuba - resort recreational diving, golf and travel go together as well as scuba and travel, so interested in travel to unvisited Caribbean islands and/or the Asian Pacific Skiing - R knee was replaced 18 years ago and L knee replaced in 2024, so I can ski again with no issue, therefore interested in the occasional ski trip to offset golf and scuba","w":"Cary Clayborn Cary lives in Frisco, Texas. He has one child, his 19-year-old daughter Carly, currently attending Honors College of Charleston studying pre-law. His plebe company was I2, graduating from E4. His closest cadet friends were Chuck Luigs, Tom O'Brien, Dennis Kibby, Chris Cole, and Roger Knowles, and during firstie year he dated Kathy O'Brien. Firstie year he slammed into the ground during a stupid maneuver in a skydiving competition in Connecticut, but still jumped twice, producing air bubbles under his skin throughout his neck, chest, and stomach. He stayed in the ICU on oxygen for a week. Dennis Kibby told him just a few years ago that Keller didn't know if he would live and the red blotches all over his face were crazy. He's disappointed he doesn't have video of the accident or pictures of his face as both would be great social media material today. He also cherishes friendships with Tom McCann and Matt Pawlikowski (plebe roommates), Marc Harris and Rock Marcone (plebe/Beast roommates), Dan Schafer (initial medical sales days close friend), current DFW classmates Joe DePinto, Jesus Delgado-Jenkins, and Larry Hughes (also E4 brother), and dozens of other classmates he admires immensely. He served all five years in Mainz, Germany with 1/59th ADA supporting 8th Infantry Division, initially defending The Fulda Gap with an air defense umbrella, then became General's aide-de-camp to Tim Grogan (Class of '63) and John Landry (Class of '62). He had an amazing time in Europe before and after The Wall came down, but decided not to stay in and got his MSM from Troy University. He was pre-med at USMA and his MSM in business led to 30 years of medical sales overlapping with 20 years of financial industry interests (advisory, investments, analytics). His favorite job of all time was training minimally invasive heart surgery for five years with Heartport, putting the heart and lungs on bypass and conducting full heart surgeries without cracking the chest. Today he's involved in six different businesses, his current favorite two being Profit Inc (supporting the SMB community with advanced analytics) and Warrior Centric Health (teaching the commercial sector that they are taking care of veterans). He started playing golf at age 30 and has since played 774 different courses worldwide in 45 states and 17 countries. He's a member of Big Creek CC in Mountain Home, Arkansas which allowed him to join EPIC Golf Club and have access to almost every single private course in the top 250 including Augusta. He's traveled to 55 countries, though only once below the equator to South Africa, and is looking to travel to South America, Australia/New Zealand, and continue adding to the total to get to 100. He enjoys resort recreational diving, combining scuba with travel to unvisited Caribbean islands and the Asian Pacific. His right knee was replaced 18 years ago and left knee replaced in 2024, so he can ski again with no issue and is interested in occasional ski trips to offset golf and scuba. He can be reached at cary.clayborn.abt@gmail.com | 214-202-8939."},{"id":166,"n":"Dale Cleland","u":"Dale","g":"F1","p":"H3","ph":"913-683-3274","em":"cleland@engineer.com","tw":"Leavenworth","st":"KS"},{"id":167,"n":"Ross Clemons","u":"Ross","g":"G3","p":"B1","ph":"850-257-1978","em":"rossclemons@gmail.com","tw":"Panama City","st":"FL","af":"Sailing","ac":"Skiing, shooting, anything with classmates","w":"Ross Clemons Ross Clemons lives in Panama City, Florida. His daughter, 25, practices law in NYC, and his son, 21, is class of 2026 at West Point. He served 25 years and loved every tour, blessed with great teammates and fascinating jobs. The latter half he spent as an African Foreign Area Officer, raising his kids in Africa—an experience that gave them a lifelong interest in the wider world. He recalls the incredible camaraderie in G3 and great times on the USMA sailing team. He works at the Panama City Rescue Mission helping people overcome substance abuse. He skis, shoots, and enjoys anything with classmates. He can be reached at rossclemons@gmail.com | 850-257-1978."},{"id":168,"n":"Charles Climer","u":"Tom","g":"G3","p":"I4","ph":"334-464-4357","em":"tomclimer@hotmail.com","tw":"Holliston","st":"MA"},{"id":169,"n":"Joanie (Fontaine) Close","u":"Joanie","g":"C1","p":"G2","ph":"864-386-0292","em":"mclose@charter.net","tw":"Simpsonville","st":"SC"},{"id":170,"n":"Mark Coats","u":"Mark","g":"E3","p":"G2","ph":"719-510-4354","em":"coatsmarkb@gmail.com","tw":"Monument","st":"CO","ac":"fishing, skiing, travel, attending sport events","w":"Mark Coats Mark lives in Monument, Colorado. He has identical twin boys, now 31 and both married, with no grandchildren yet. He is still married to his bride from 1987. Mark was a plebe in G2 and graduated from E3. He remembers meeting President Nixon outside the library during one of his random visits. He served at Fort Knox, Germany (two tours), DC (two tours), Fort Riley, DTRA, USACE HQ, and attended normal schools. After the Army, he worked as COO at a construction firm for 12 years, followed by running CBRE's global operations for construction, facility maintenance, and base operating support services. Mark enjoys fishing, skiing, travel, and attending sport events. He can be reached at coatsmarkb@gmail.com | 719-510-4354."},{"id":171,"n":"Wendy (Peart) Coddington","u":"Wendy","g":"G4","p":"F1","ph":"360-481-8288","em":"nickandwendycoddington@hotmail.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA"},{"id":172,"n":"Christopher Cole","u":"Chris","g":"E4","p":"D3","ph":"405-626-3532","em":"chris.cole@thecoleshop.com","tw":"Chicago","st":"IL"},{"id":173,"n":"Leanne (Garner) Collazzo","u":"Leanne","g":"H3","p":"D2","ph":"978-549-8253","em":"leannecollazzo@comcast.net","tw":"Westford","st":"MA","ac":"We have a lake house in New Hampshire and whenever we have a fellow grad visiting us we always hoist the Army flag from the flagpole at the end of our dock. We would love to share our favorite place with any classmates who love boating, fishing, swimming, good food, good drink and a few laughs. Come on by.","w":"Leanne (Garner) Collazzo Leanne lives in Westford, MA with her husband Ed ('83). They have three grown sons and two daughters, all happy, healthy, and productive, plus five grandchildren ranging in ages 1-8. They have a lake house in New Hampshire where they hoist the Army flag from the flagpole at the end of their dock whenever a fellow grad visits. She and roommate Jaimy Rand kept Sparky the Hamster hidden above the closet as the company mascot. Sparky would roll around the hall in his hamster ball during study barracks, named after their Tac who would suddenly roll up on his toes during formation. One evening she discovered Sparky had made his first jump out of the 6th floor window attached to a flare parachute, complete with jump wings on his nameplate. Sparky made four more jumps before his chute failed to open on the last one and he was given a military burial on the plain at midnight under full dress with a 21-gun salute. She asked for \"anywhere except the South\" on her assignment sheet and got Ft Polk, LA, then didn't ask for anything the next time and got Ft. Wainwright, AK with two kids. She left active duty from there and served 15 years in the New Mexico National Guard, retiring as an LTC flying the mountains and canyons. After a few years at J&J in Medical Device Manufacturing, she went to Honeywell Aerospace and Defense where she worked as an engineer and salesperson on army helicopter avionics before going into commercial aviation. She retired in 2019 and has been enjoying being a professional grandma. She can be reached at leannecollazzo@comcast.net | 978-549-8253."},{"id":174,"n":"Craig Collier","u":"Craig","g":"D1","p":"I2","ph":"703-396-6672","em":"rakkasan_66@yahoo.com","tw":"Nokesville","st":"VA"},{"id":175,"n":"John Collison","u":"John","g":"B2","p":"","ph":"480-209-0191","em":"Azcollison@gmail.com","tw":"Phoenix","st":"AZ"},{"id":176,"n":"Edward Columbus","u":"Ed","g":"B2","p":"G4","ph":"415-233-1045","em":"dwrdcolumbus@gmail.com","tw":"Calistoga","st":"CA","ac":"Golf, golf, golf","w":"Ed Columbus Ed lives in Calistoga, California with his wonderful gal, Leslie. They’ve been together for a decade. He has two kids, both Auburn grads, his son in Orlando and daughter near Washington, DC, both married and thriving. Ed was a plebe in G4 and graduated from B2. He served in Germany with the 9th Engineer Battalion, VII Corps, in the 3rd Infantry Division community in Aschaffenburg, Bavaria, as platoon leader and XO. And he finished his Army career at Ft. Carson as the BMO, 4th Engineers, 4th ID, and left the service after the first Gulf War. After the Army, he had a great career in pharmaceutical sales with Pfizer, Johnson & Johnson, and others, developing sales representatives to be future leaders. He has worked in Kentucky, Georgia, Tennessee, Iowa, Florida, Alabama, and California, with headquarters mostly in New York/New Jersey. He enjoys golf and will play anyone willing! He can be reached at dwrdcolumbus@gmail.com | 415-233-1045."},{"id":177,"n":"Patrick Connelly","u":"Patrick","g":"C4","p":"F2","ph":"513-378-7136","em":"patconnelly86@gmail.com","tw":"Saint Louis","st":"MO"},{"id":178,"n":"Glenn Connor","u":"Glenn","g":"D3","p":"A4","ph":"(727) 953-3886","em":"GlennMichaelConnor@gmail.com"},{"id":179,"n":"Mark Connor","u":"Mark","g":"H1","p":"H4","ph":"(571) 357-2340","em":"mark1855@gmail.com","tw":"Kingstowne","st":"VA"},{"id":180,"n":"Eric Conrad","u":"Eric","g":"I1","p":"","ph":"931-431-0069","tw":"Braselton","st":"GA"},{"id":181,"n":"William Cook","u":"Wade","g":"C4","p":"F3","ph":"(585) 442-1658","em":"wcook2@rochester.rr.com","tw":"Rochester","st":"NY"},{"id":182,"n":"Berkley Cooke","u":"Berkley","g":"B4","p":"E3","ph":"470-217-47886","em":"brenberk1@hotmail.com","tw":"Marietta","st":"GA"},{"id":183,"n":"Byron Cooper","u":"Byron","g":"A2","p":"H1","em":"bwcooper@sbcglobal.net"},{"id":184,"n":"Richard Cornman","u":"Rick","g":"F4","p":"F1","em":"rickcornman@hotmail.com","tw":"Lisle","st":"IL"},{"id":185,"n":"John Corsi","u":"John","g":"C1","p":"A4","ph":"704-953-6958","em":"johncorsi12@gmail.com","tw":"Charlotte","st":"NC","w":"John Corsi John lives in Charlotte, North Carolina. He and his wife Carolyn have a blended family with six children: Halee, Christian, Katie, Jack, Lizzy, and Anne. Christian and his wife Becky have four children, making John a grandfather. His plebe company was A4, graduating from C1. He served in Korea and Fort Leonard Wood with Engineers. After the Army, he moved into manufacturing and general business leadership roles.He can be reached at johncorsi12@gmail.com | 704-953-6958."},{"id":186,"n":"Neil Costello","u":"Neil","g":"I3","p":"I2","ph":"404-406-0916","em":"Nfcostello@gmail.com","tw":"Peachtree City","st":"GA"},{"id":187,"n":"Wanda Costen","u":"Wanda","g":"C1","p":"A3","em":"wandausma86@gmail.com","tw":"Kingston","st":"ON"},{"id":188,"n":"Craig Cotter","u":"Craig","g":"A4","p":"G1","ph":"(832) 509-7516","em":"craignoracotter@yahoo.com","tw":"Friendswood","st":"TX"},{"id":189,"n":"Roger Cotton","u":"Roger","g":"E1","p":"E4","em":"rogercotton139@comcast.net","tw":"Arnold","st":"MD"},{"id":190,"n":"David Courtoglous","u":"David","g":"F4","p":"F1","ph":"(858) 679-8306","em":"dcourtoglous@rocketmail.com","tw":"San Diego","st":"CA"},{"id":191,"n":"Loretta (Garrigan) Craig","u":"Loretta","g":"E1","p":"A2","ph":"(913) 728-2005","em":"lcraig86@gmail.com","tw":"Basehor","st":"KS"},{"id":192,"n":"James Crawford","u":"Jim","g":"I3","p":"B1","ph":"757-876-3011","em":"jojatekie@msn.com","tw":"Poquoson","st":"VA","ac":"Crawford enjoys travel and now that Tracy is retired, she often accompanies him on trips related to his NASA work. Given his long history with music and the cadet band, as well as his enthusiasm for shared experiences, he would most naturally connect with classmates through travel, reunions, and extended visits built around conversation, local exploring, and cultural events rather than organized sports.","w":"Crawdad lives in Poquoson, Virginia, just minutes from NASA Langley. He and his wife Tracy have three adult sons. Denver lives in New York City working in and around the entertainment industry with his partner Trey. Davis is a computer engineer for Capital One, working fully remotely from Salt Lake City, where he climbs in summer and skis in winter. Dell, the youngest, recently graduated from Texas State in San Marcos as a theater student and is beginning his own path into the entertainment world. They are empty nesters. Tracy is deeply civic-minded and has served as a local city councilwoman. His plebe company was B1, graduating from I3. As a plebe in B-1, he became known for telling a daily joke at the lunch table after an upperclassman demanded one on the spot. What began as a small survival tactic turned into a year-long ritual, with tables informally \"bidding\" to have him assigned so they could hear the joke of the day, and neighboring tables leaning back to listen. Classmates quietly fed him material, and the routine gave him a positive identity in a tough company. Later in I-3, he remembers the dayroom pool table and an epic three-day weekend drive to St. Pete to see a classmate's girlfriend and play in a Navy soccer game. His Army highlight was his tour as a field artillery officer with the 25th Infantry Division in Hawaii. One defining episode was an unauthorized solo climb from the training area up Mauna Kea to the summit and back, which prompted a near search-and-rescue launch and a furious battalion commander, but also cemented his reputation for endurance and drive. After five years of active duty, he left the Army, used accumulated leave to travel with Tracy, and then entered graduate school at Georgia Tech, where he moved into the young field of atmospheric chemistry, working under a demanding airborne-science PI and flying research missions. That work led directly to NASA, and since 1997 he has been at NASA Langley in Virginia. He is now the senior scientist for airborne atmospheric chemistry for the agency, leading and participating in global aircraft campaigns to understand atmospheric composition and pollution. He enjoys travel and now that Tracy is retired, she often accompanies him on trips related to his NASA work. His West Point foundation—band, math-heavy curriculum, and leadership in hard units—translated directly into leading teams of strong-willed scientists; he notes that getting forty scientists aligned can be as challenging as leading soldiers. Though much of his scientific reputation is strongest overseas in places like Korea and Thailand, he credits the academy's broad education and leadership training for making his NASA career possible. He can be reached at jojatekie@msn.com | 757-876-3011."},{"id":193,"n":"William Creeden","u":"William","g":"D1","p":"H4","ph":"(770) 591-7313","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":194,"n":"Joseph Creekmore","u":"Jody","g":"F1","p":"H4","ph":"(256) 464-7098","em":"jpcreek1963@gmail.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL","ac":"golf; travel; attending sports events","w":"Jody Creekmore Jody lives in Madison, Alabama. His eldest son JP lives in North Carolina and is a software engineer working for Google. His middle child Maddy lives in Texas and is a chemical engineer working in the petrochemical industry. His youngest son Michael is West Point class of 2014, medically retired as a Captain, and works as a civil engineer and process engineer for an aluminum ingot manufacturer in South Carolina. He has six grandchildren—three in North Carolina and three in Texas. He flew 1,000+ hours in the UH-1H, served as Exchange Officer in the Hungarian Air Force, was MiTT Chief in Iraq (2006-2007) with the 3rd Iraqi Brigade/5th Iraqi Division in the Dyala River Valley, and held Brigade Command in the Army Reserve. In civil service while simultaneously serving in the Army Reserve, he designed the Army's UH-60 flight simulator/trainer—the Black Hawk Aircrew Trainer (BAT). As Government Senior Engineer and Project Director, he led production and fielding of 37 devices, six of which were sold to allied countries (Australia, Lithuania, Latvia, Sweden, and Austria). He's retiring from Civil Service at the end of October 2026. He golfs, travels, and attends sports events. He can be reached at jpcreek1963@gmail.com | 256-464-7098."},{"id":195,"n":"Cynthia Crenshaw","u":"Cynthia","g":"B2","p":"H3","em":"crenshawcd@msn.com","tw":"Newnan","st":"GA"},{"id":196,"n":"Chad Creveling","u":"Chad","g":"D4","p":"I2","em":"chad_creveling@yahoo.com"},{"id":197,"n":"Edward Cummings","u":"Ted","g":"F4","p":"I2","ph":"703-286-9398","em":"usma86@cox.net","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA","ac":"He enjoys sports, especially baseball, and remains active in church and community life. He is comfortable with travel, outdoor activities, and social gatherings. He appreciates time with friends, faith communities, and other veterans. He is game for shared activities tied to service, music, or athletics. Travel, golf, skiing, hikes, sports and musical events. Pretty much any social setting (restaurants, distilleries, breweries).","w":"Ted Cummings Ted lives in Fairfax, Virginia. He and his wife Sonia have three adult children. Their eldest, Teddy, is a captain in the Army Reserve and works in finance for a Navy-related program at the Washington Navy Yard. Their daughter Shannon is a marketing manager at Carahsoft. Their youngest son Daniel recently graduated from Virginia Tech and works in sports performance analytics for U.S. Soccer, with periodic assignments in Atlanta.His aviation career was central: flying Cobras and later Kiowa Warriors, commanding a headquarters troop, and serving as a systems automation officer at the Hohenfels Combat Training Center. He deployed to Iraq, where he ran information-operations assessments and produced the metrics used in senior-level briefings during the surge. He retired as a colonel after 30 total years of combined active and reserve service. He transitioned into technology early, working for Fujitsu for more than a decade, then Dell, Unisys, and Salesforce/MuleSoft. He recently accepted a position as the Army account executive for Armis, a cybersecurity company. He met his wife in church in Fulda. He grew up as an Army brat with formative years in Panama. He enjoys sports, especially baseball, and remains active in church and community life. He can be reached at usma86@cox.net | 703-286-9398."},{"id":198,"n":"Steven Cummings","u":"Steven","g":"G2","p":"F3","em":"steven.f.cummings@gmail.com","tw":"Rockaway","st":"NJ"},{"id":199,"n":"Gerard Curran","u":"Jerry","g":"B1","p":"E2","ph":"203-694-9997","em":"gcurranlara@cshore.com","tw":"Madison","st":"CT","ac":"Hanging out and eating/getting a drink.","w":"Gerard Curran Gerry lives in Madison, Connecticut, with his wife of 28 years. They have three children: Brendan, 26, part owner of the Madison Watch Company and a Quinnipiac graduate; Luke, 24, who works for Vanguard in Devon, Pennsylvania; and Larissa, 20, a junior at FIT in New York City. He served as an ER doctor, deploying to Afghanistan with Task Force Bagram attached to 5th Special Forces Group from November 2001 to April 2002. He has practiced at MidState Medical Center in Meriden, St. Francis Hospital in Hartford, and the VA in West Haven, Connecticut. He can be reached at gcurranlara@cshore.com | 203-694-9997."},{"id":200,"n":"Michael Curran","u":"Mike","g":"H4","p":"G1","ph":"(713) 254-6691","em":"mike.curran@sulzer.com","tw":"Spring","st":"TX","w":"Mike Curran, splits time 70/30 living between The Woodlands, Texas and Chattanooga, TN with his beautiful and ageless wife Sheri.  4 kids (boy & 3 girls, all grown and out). 1 new grandson Declan. Plebe company G-1.  Strongest memories of Woops were my constant and never-ending struggle to survive both the Dean and the Tac, loving the hockey rink the most,  and laughing thru life in the lost 50’s with this unique cast of characters we called Hog 4. Army Life: After graduating, thru only the good grace of Curtis Scaparrotti,  I branched ADA, got married to Sheri and went to 3ID in Kitzingen, Germany for three years. Platoon Leader, Mech-Infantry Brigade Liaison (with Col Eric Shinseki Commanding, a very rewarding experience, great leader), company XO. Berlin Wall came down. Mission accomplished. Went home. Returned to El Paso  for the Advanced Course, decided on a whim one afternoon ½ way thru that course that my heart wasn’t in it, left the service of Uncle Sam early (no more Commies to kill) played a lot of golf at the Fort Bliss GC in the Spring of ’90 with Mark Aubrey and Billy Schiffer (waiting to punch out too), and didn’t have much of a plan beyond (hard to believe I know). Post Army: In 1990, making good use of my finely-tuned sociology skills and never-quit hockey mentality, we moved to Houston and I found work at a little Turbomachinery company called Hickham Industries.  There I reached into my limited thermodynamics memory to become proficient at and fixed and made parts for a lot of GE gas turbines over the years. We grew, got acquired by Sulzer (Swiss Company), are now called Sulzer Turbo Services Houston. Somehow, they still allow me to be here in year 36 as VP of Sales for The Americas.  In the middle of this run, Sheri and I spent a 3-year tour (’19-’22) with our Sulzer Pumps facility in Chattanooga supplying parts for, repairing and growing our Nuclear Pumps platform in the US Nuclear Industry. We loved that time, still own our home there and find time to WFH in TN to decompress and plan for retirement which is coming soon. Family: Wife Sheri.  Married 38 years. Love of my life and best Mom on Earth. Son Matt (UT Austin grad, married to Michaela, no kids yet, lives in Stamford, CT) Daughters Angela (A&M grad, engaged to Dylan, new Mom, mother of our only grandson Declan, lives near The Woodlands, TX), Caitlin (A&M grad,  married to Killian, no kids yet, lives in Coppel, TX) and Amanda (UT Knoxville grad, married to Ryan, no kids yet, lives in Knoxville, TN). More grandkids on the way.  Everyone should own some.  So much joy."},{"id":201,"n":"Michael Curry","u":"Mike","g":"C2","p":"F4","ph":"541-408-1693","em":"michael@webmentors.com","tw":"Sisters","st":"OR","ac":"Something that doesn't involve alcohol LoL, I've been sober for decades.","w":"Mike Curry Mike lives in Sisters, Oregon. His kids are doing well; he has no grandchildren yet. He's been sober for decades and looks for activities that don't involve alcohol. His plebe company was F4, graduating from C2. He loved the pranks cadets used to play, like putting a boat in the messhall for Army-Navy. He served in Germany, which he found wonderful, then attended grad school in Oregon, which really shaped his after-Army life. He's now a professor at Oregon State working virtually. He's single and pretty active, doing a lot of acrobatics and rock climbing. He can be reached at michael@webmentors.com | 541-408-1693."},{"id":202,"n":"Howard Curtis","u":"Howie","g":"C4","p":"E1","ph":"603-591-1343","em":"hcurtis_148@comcast.net","st":"NY","ac":"Howie enjoys skiing, hockey, and spirited travel adventures. He also has a love for storytelling and reconnecting with classmates, often through humor and memorable tales. His life on the water and in the mountains suggests he’d enjoy outdoor activities like hiking, fishing, and skiing trips with CNQ members. He thrives on camaraderie and spontaneous fun—ideal for future class gatherings.","w":"Howard “Howie” Curtis Howie  lives in Saratoga Springs, New York, in the very building he and his wife lived in a decade ago. His three sons have settled in Montana near Whitefish: Michael works construction in the mountains near Jefferson, Colorado; Scott served in the Navy as a P-3 crew member and now works as a defense contractor flying drones; and Joshua supports Scott's work while caring for the dogs and traveling with him. Howie was a legendary \"double-century man\" at West Point, accumulating 200 hours of punishment tours through exploits like putting a beer bottle on the Supe's windowsill, sneaking over the wall, and placing a sailboat on top of the barracks. He served in Air Defense Artillery at the Fulda Gap in Germany, then deployed to Dhahran and King Khalid Military City during Desert Storm, working in the Combined Reporting Center coordinating multinational air defense. After the Army, Howie built a successful pharmaceutical career with Bristol Myers Squibb, working in kidney transplant immunosuppressants, cardiovascular sales, and government accounts. He especially enjoyed serving as national account manager for New York and Pennsylvania, later moving to Maine and Colorado covering large territories. He enjoys skiing, hockey, and spirited travel adventures, thriving on camaraderie and spontaneous fun. He can be reached at hcurtis_148@comcast.net | 603-591-1343."},{"id":203,"n":"Kenneth Curtis","u":"Kenneth","g":"F2","p":"D1","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX"},{"id":204,"n":"Charles Cushman","u":"Chuck","g":"G3","p":"F4","ph":"202-904-3887","em":"ccdc20009@gmail.com","tw":"Washington","st":"DC","af":"Debate","ac":"Open. He enjoys conversation, storytelling, and reconnection. Academic life and public service are central to his identity, and he would welcome gatherings built around discussion, shared meals, or visits. He is also planning a future that includes time at the beach in Rehoboth and summers in France, and classmates visiting in those settings would be welcome.","w":"Chuck Cushman Chuck lives in Washington, DC. He has had three great cats: Garbo, Danaerys, and Drake.His CTLT rotation with 3rd ACR at Fort Bliss hooked him on armor. He served with 2-66 Armor, 2AD (FWD) in Germany from 87-89, then at Fort Knox with E Troop, 6/12 Cav, and later in the Sosh Department at USMA. In Germany he worked extensively with NATO allies, transitioned from M1 to M1A1, and drove an M1A1 through downtown Hamelin—a signature memory. After nine years he took the early-out offered to his year group. He completed his doctorate at UNC in 1996, then worked in practical politics—campaigns, lobbying, defense consulting—to gain real-world grounding. His civilian career spanned teaching government at Georgetown, training federal officials on congressional relations, and senior academic administration. He served as program director, department chair, and associate dean at GWU from 2001-11, Georgetown from 11-14, Dean of the College of International Security Affairs at NDU from 14-19, associate provost from 19-20, and founding Dean of Academics at the US Naval Community College from 21-present, opening educational doors for USN, USMC, and USCG enlisted personnel. He grew up moving frequently across Massachusetts, Illinois, Florida, Connecticut, and South Carolina because his father designed golf clubs. He adopted the name \"Chuck\" on R-Day as an intentional break from childhood. He joined the speech and debate team where Major Jack Midgley taught him how to think, argue, and lead, skills that shaped his teaching career and made him the \"voice of the TOC\" in Germany. He enjoys conversation, storytelling, and reconnection, and is planning a future that includes time at the beach in Rehoboth and summers in France. He just started a foodie blog, \"What will you have?\" at chucksworldkitchen.com. He still marches everywhere and wears his tar bucket the Monday after every Army-Navy game to irritate Navy colleagues. He can be reached at ccdc20009@gmail.com | 202-904-3887."},{"id":205,"n":"Patrick Cusick","u":"Pat","g":"A3","p":"H1","ph":"414-336-6378","em":"cusickp86@gmail.com","tw":"Louisville","st":"KY","ac":"Hiking, camping, shooting at the range, mid-western US sport events, NSACAR, Lionel trains, classic trains,  board gaming (in person and on line), general class get togethers in mid-western US","w":"Patrick Cusick Pat lives in Louisville, Kentucky with his wife. They moved there to be near their oldest daughter and two grandchildren, whom they see four to five times a week. Their second daughter is in her third year of medical school, and their son gained social media recognition during the October 2024 Asheville floods when his Rivian electric truck kept running after being swept away, allowing him to continue humanitarian work in the aftermath. Cusick's first assignment was as a tank platoon leader with 3-64 Armor in Schweinfurt, Germany, then moved to 4.2\" mortar platoon leader. He PCS'd to Fort Polk where he worked in G3 and 5th Infantry Division DTAC for two years before leaving active duty in 1992. He entered manufacturing, starting in telecommunications with fiber optics and networking cable, then moved into aerospace. Over fifteen years he rose from shop floor supervision to Global Director of Operations managing factories in the US, Europe, China, and Mexico, producing commercial aircraft wiring and components for missiles, guidance systems, satellites, and the Mars Rover. As Plant Manager in St. Augustine, Florida, he grew the facility from $80M to become the world's largest manufacturer of wire for commercial aircraft, winning supplier of the year awards from Airbus and excellence awards from Boeing. He moved sixteen times across eight states after leaving the Army—more than during his military service. He shoots at the range, hikes, camps, follows NASCAR and Midwestern sports, collects Lionel trains and plays board games both in person and online. He stays connected to Ken Curtis and Tom Davis from Beast Barracks, where he was assigned the number \"42 and a half\" when his name wasn't on the alphabetical roster between Curtis (42) and Davis (43). He can be reached at cusickp86@gmail.com | 414-336-6378."},{"id":206,"n":"Patrick Daly","u":"Pat","g":"H3","p":"A1","ph":"412-266-5631","em":"pdaly@dcbiolife.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC","ac":"Golf, skiing, travel and family","w":"Patrick Daly Pat lives in Raleigh, North Carolina. He has three kids: two boys in college and one girl in high school. His plebe company was A1, graduating from H3. His most memorable cadet experience was the food fight plebe year that involved the goat chili. He served at Fort Lewis with the 9th Infantry Division. His most interesting assignment was as XO of the MLRS Battery for I Corps. After the Army, he has been in the medical device and life sciences field. He was with Johnson & Johnson and held positions throughout the globe including Sydney, Australia and Asia Pacific. He then started a medical device company and grew it over 12 years culminating in a sale to Private Equity. He has held positions at IQVIA and Terumo and is currently the CEO of GMLx, a global logistics business in healthcare. He has run two marathons and has coached lacrosse for over 30 years at all levels from college to middle school. He enjoys golf, skiing, travel, and family. He can be reached at pdaly@dcbiolife.com | 412-266-5631."},{"id":207,"n":"Daniel D'Amico","u":"Daniel","g":"I4","p":"A2","ph":"(214) 695-6273","em":"dandamico@hotmail.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX"},{"id":208,"n":"Patricia (Melcher) Davies","u":"Patricia","g":"G4","p":"D2","ph":"(419) 768-2972","em":"pdavies337@gmail.com","tw":"Fredericktown","st":"OH"},{"id":209,"n":"Bruce Davis","u":"Bruce","g":"D2","p":"G3","ph":"(706) 596-0495","em":"bjd1964@aol.com","tw":"Fortson","st":"GA"},{"id":210,"n":"Charles Davis","u":"Charles","g":"D1","p":"F3","ph":"(719) 226-0292","em":"rakman86@hotmail.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":211,"n":"Michell (Collins) Davis","u":"Michell","g":"I3","p":"A1","ph":"404-545-6635","em":"michell.davis@gmail.com","tw":"Grovetown","st":"GA"},{"id":212,"n":"Steven Davis","u":"Steven","g":"D1","p":"C3","ph":"(303) 517-9214","em":"steve@scooby.co","tw":"Longmont","st":"CO"},{"id":213,"n":"Thomas Davis","u":"Thomas","g":"G4","p":"","ph":"(715) 424-5989","em":"tomdavis.wi@gmail.com","tw":"Wisconsin Rapids","st":"WI"},{"id":214,"n":"Tanya Davis-Lukowiak","u":"Tanya","g":"B2","p":"I4","em":"tanyaluke00@yahoo.com","tw":"Bradenton","st":"FL"},{"id":215,"n":"John Day","u":"John","g":"H3","p":"I4","ph":"404-372-7181","em":"jday86@comcast.net","tw":"Auburn","st":"AL"},{"id":216,"n":"Richard Day","u":"Richard","g":"D2","p":"D3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":217,"n":"Thomas Defilippo","u":"Thomas","g":"D3","p":"H4","ph":"(757) 806-6324","em":"tom.defilippo@gmail.com","tw":"Manassas","st":"VA"},{"id":218,"n":"Julie Del Giorno","u":"Julie","g":"C2","p":"I3","ph":"610-554-4061","em":"jdelgiorno32@gmail.com","ac":"Kayaking, hiking, traveling","w":"Julie Del Giorno Julie is retired and living in Rehoboth Beach, Delaware with no children or grandchildren. She volunteers at her local volunteer fire company, where she serves as Corporate Secretary—interestingly, Station 86. Her plebe company was I3, graduating from C2. She served as a transportation officer supporting the 2/75th Ranger Regiment at Fort Lewis as Platoon Leader and XO, served as Battalion Adjutant during Operation Desert Storm, and commanded a company during Operation Restore Hope in Somalia. After the Army, she worked in various positions in intercollegiate athletics and senior administration at colleges and universities, serving as Chief of Staff for two college presidents. She was hired as the first ever Athletics Integrity Officer at Penn State University in the wake of the Jerry Sandusky scandal. Her strongest cadet memory is the way classmates pulled together to help one another—connections that could be years long or only for a class or two, but when they see each other now, it's as if they were just hanging out in the day room or struggling through Rock Math together. She initiated the Chicks of '86 after learning her sister's Class of '82 women held annual mini-reunions and pushed to replicate it in '86. A 2009 ovarian cancer diagnosis was a key motivator to reconnect with classmates while she still could. She is a primary driver of the Chicks' annual mini-reunion model and values travel-based gatherings built around long unstructured time for talking, relaxing, and shared meals. The group maintains a hard rule of no spouses, partners, or kids to preserve candor and cohesion. She loves being retired, enjoys kayaking, hiking, and travel. She can be reached at jdelgiorno32@gmail.com | 610-554-4061."},{"id":219,"n":"Ramon DeLeon","u":"Ramon","g":"E3","p":"F1","em":"ramon_deleon@comcast.net","tw":"Fort Collins","st":"CO"},{"id":220,"n":"Jesus Delgado-Jenkins","u":"Jesus","g":"D1","p":"I3","ph":"(972) 828-0711","em":"jdelgadoj@icloud.com","tw":"Encino","st":"CA"},{"id":221,"n":"Terrence DeLong","u":"Terry","g":"C3","p":"D1"},{"id":222,"n":"Andrew Dempsey","u":"Andy","g":"D4","p":"H3","ph":"720-626-0634","em":"andydempsey@comcast.net","tw":"Breckenridge","st":"CO","ac":"Golf, skiing, hiking, attending sports events.","w":"Andrew Dempsey Andy lives in Breckenridge, Colorado. He has two children: Sean, an electrical engineer, and Kelsey, a civil engineer. His plebe company was H3, graduating from D4. His most memorable cadet experience was teaching Don Smith how to do a cartwheel in Plebe Gymnastics. He served with the 4th Engineer Battalion at Fort Carson, Colorado, where he served as acting company commander for over three months. After the Army, he worked as a civil engineer consultant, then as city engineer and public works director, then as city manager, before returning to the federal government as a civil engineer to end his career. He enjoys golf, skiing, hiking, and attending sports events. He once ran a marathon, two half marathons, two 10Ks, and two 5Ks all in less than 24 hours at an American Cancer Society Relay for Life Event to raise money for charity. He can be reached at andydempsey@comcast.net | 720-626-0634."},{"id":223,"n":"Joseph DePinto","u":"Joe","g":"G3","p":"G3","ph":"214-215-4967","em":"josephdepinto@yahoo.com","tw":"Westlake","st":"TX"},{"id":224,"n":"David Des Roches","u":"Dave","g":"E1","p":"I4","ph":"(301) 951-7273","em":"lucky714dog@yahoo.com","tw":"Bethesda","st":"MD"},{"id":225,"n":"Lisa Diane DiCiro","u":"Angie","g":"C4","p":"H2","em":"angie.diciro@gmail.com","tw":"New Kent"},{"id":226,"n":"David DiMeo","u":"David","g":"H2","p":"F3","ph":"(845) 938-4143","tw":"Bowling Green","st":"KY"},{"id":227,"n":"James Diorio","u":"Jim","g":"C4","p":"D1","ph":"732-609-6473","em":"jdiorio006@gmail.com","tw":"Rumson","st":"NJ","ac":"We golf with a large group of 86ers every year and see in each often at Johnny Mac events.","w":"Jim DiOrio lives at the Jersey Shore and is most grounded when he is close to family.Family is everything to Jim. He is the proud father of two and the grateful grandfather of two boys who keep him anchored to what matters. His daughter Jen and son-in-law Matt are raising Sal, three, and Vin, one, two little men who already define his sense of legacy. His son Jim married Anastasia on November 1, 2024, a moment Jim considers one of the great blessings of his life. He is also deeply grateful for his relationship with Kristen, whose steady presence, love, and support have brought peace, joy, and balance into his life in ways he does not take for granted. Jim stays close to his West Point Class of 1986. He golfs regularly with a wide circle of ’86ers and reconnects often at Johnny Mac events, reunions, and the informal gatherings that matter most. Right out of West Point, Jim took what he calls a surprising path that few classmates knew much about at the time. He worked in intelligence and then spent decades in the FBI as a street agent, handling difficult, complex cases and building assets where trust was earned the hard way. After retiring, he founded his own company with his lifelong best friend Anthony Boffa and trusted colleagues from the intelligence community. In 2022, during the celebration of life for Laurie Whipple, the wife of his classmate Eric, Jim began his walk with Christ. That moment changed everything. His classmate Stan Olson played a pivotal role in leading him back to God, a gift Jim carries with deep gratitude. Jim remains closely connected to his classmates and friends and is always glad to hear from them. He can be reached at jdiorio006@gmail.com  732-609-6473"},{"id":228,"n":"Barry DiRuzza","u":"Barry","g":"I4","p":"G1","em":"barry.diruzza@gmail.com","tw":"Charlotte","st":"NC"},{"id":229,"n":"Michael Dishman","u":"Michael","g":"C4","p":"I1","em":"dishmanm@hotmail.com","ac":"Travel","w":"Mike Dishman Mike’s his wife lives in Texas while he's based in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. They have a 24-year-old daughter at the University of Texas. His plebe company was I1, graduating from C4. His most memorable cadet experience was serving as Sergeant of the Guard following completion of his 206th area tour.His military service took him through assignments in the US, Korea, Greece, Turkey, Lebanon, and Qatar. He found Lebanon his most interesting posting, CENTCOM his most rewarding, and Turkey the most fun and educational. After the Army, he became a defense contractor, starting with small consultancies before moving to larger defense sector companies. His most interesting role was serving as an advisor to the UAE Land Forces and the Presidential Guard—work that kept him engaged in the Middle East and connected to senior military leadership across the region. He enjoys travel, with extensive experience across the Middle East, Mediterranean, and Asia. He can be reached at dishmanm@hotmail.com."},{"id":230,"n":"Mark Ditrolio","u":"Mark","g":"H4","p":"I1","ph":"(210) 632-0408","em":"MDITROLIO@MSN.COM","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":231,"n":"Craig Doescher","u":"Craig","g":"F1","p":"C4","ph":"703-209-0475","em":"Cdoescher64@gmail.com","tw":"Newport News","st":"VA","ac":"Living near Virginia Beach in Newport News, Craig enjoys beach days, historic sites like Jamestown and Williamsburg, and welcomes visits from classmates. He also enjoys reconnecting through storytelling and humor. Activities he’d likely enjoy include beach gatherings, travel to historic sites, and casual outdoor social events.","w":"Craig Doescher Doesch lives in Newport News, Virginia. He has two sons: one is a police officer in Northern Virginia, and the other is an Army logistician who went through ROTC at James Madison University and is currently stationed at Fort Campbell with deployments to Poland and the Middle East. He was stationed in Bamberg, Germany, during the fall of the Berlin Wall. His unit was nuclear-capable artillery, and he took visiting family into East Berlin through Checkpoint Charlie. He later served at Fort Lewis and Fort Polk and helped run warfighter training at JRTC. After serving in Germany, he earned a master's degree at the University of Central Florida and returned to West Point as a systems engineering instructor. Today, he works for a Federally Funded Research and Development Center (FFRDC) conducting war games and simulations to improve military decision-making. He remains closely connected to West Point, mentoring cadets through summer internships focused on topics like UAV swarm optimization and modern battlefield technology. His older brother Kurt is class of '83. He grew up 28 minutes from West Point. He enjoys beach days, historic sites like Jamestown and Williamsburg, and welcomes visits from classmates. He can be reached at Cdoescher64@gmail.com | 703-209-0475."},{"id":232,"n":"Joseph Dole","u":"Joe","g":"F1","p":"I4","em":"jdole00@yahoo.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":233,"n":"Gary Domke","u":"Gary","g":"F1","p":"B3","tw":"Leavenworth","st":"KS"},{"id":234,"n":"Randall Donaldson","u":"Rand","g":"I4","p":"F2","ph":"202-803-1018","em":"Donaldson.Loft436@gmail.com","tw":"Falls Church","st":"VA"},{"id":235,"n":"Scott Donaldson","u":"Scott","g":"G2","p":"B4","em":"sdonaldson@delreyoaks.org","tw":"Monterey","st":"CA"},{"id":236,"n":"Hope Donnelly","u":"Hope","g":"H4","p":"NA","ph":"813-466-9091","em":"dcdonnelly@aol.com","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL","ac":"She enjoys sports, especially swimming, yoga, walking the Tampa Riverwalk, and attending local professional games such as Tampa Bay Lightning hockey and Buccaneers football. She likes cultural events, outdoor festivals, and travel. She frequently takes weekend trips and enjoys social gatherings with friends, including annual get-togethers with female classmates."},{"id":237,"n":"George Donovan","u":"Tom","g":"H2","p":"I1","ph":"(207) 310-4210","em":"donovangt86@gmail.com","tw":"Scarborough","st":"ME"},{"id":238,"n":"Sean Donovan","u":"Sean","g":"A4","p":"E2","ph":"(616) 243-3563"},{"id":239,"n":"Dean Dorman","u":"Deano","g":"D1","p":"A3","ph":"857-222-0602","em":"dean.dorman@yahoo.com","tw":"Carmel","st":"NY","af":"Rugby","ac":"Travel (for example Scotland with CNQ in 2026)","w":"Dean Dorman Deano lives in Carmel, New York. He has been married to MaryBeth for 37 years. They have four grown children, two currently in the military including one USMA graduate, plus two grandchildren. His plebe company was A3, graduating from D1. His most memorable cadet experiences were D1 Ducks and Army Rugby. He served mostly at Fort Lewis with a great group of lieutenants, plus a cool stint in Honduras. After the Army, he attended Harvard Business School, worked at McKinsey and GE as CEO, then spent 23 years (and currently still) in private equity operations. He ran an Army-Navy tailgate at the game location for 30 consecutive years, retiring in 2023 where attendance peaked at over 3,000 attendees. It's also a Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund event, and he serves on the Board of Johnny Mac. He is also co-founder in 2017 of all men's Army Rugby Alumni efforts. He enjoys travel, including a Scotland trip with CNQ planned for 2026. He can be reached at dean.dorman@yahoo.com | 857-222-0602."},{"id":240,"n":"Edward Dougherty","u":"Bill","g":"A3","p":"D1","ph":"(703) 861-1896","em":"doughe35@aol.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":241,"n":"Robert Douthit","u":"RD","g":"C1","p":"A4","ph":"512-983-1509","em":"rd862006@gmail.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX","af":"Squash","ac":"RD is active, social, and outdoors-oriented. He skis often—helped by the fact that two of his sons work in the ski and outdoor industry—and mountain bikes with them despite the hazards. He enjoys visiting Colorado regularly, reconnecting with classmates, and spending time in Austin with long-standing friends. He would fit easily into classmate activities involving skiing, outdoor recreation, informal gatherings, and travel.","w":"RD (easily the most popular graduate among his ’86 classmates) lives in Austin, Texas. He has four adult children: his eldest, a University of Texas graduate, lives in Houston with her husband and two young children; his second son, also a Texas graduate, is the global ops manager and designs skis for Icelantic Skis in Golden, Colorado; his third child works for Strafe, a winter/ski outer-wear company based in Aspen/Snowmass; and his youngest daughter is an ER physician assistant in Chicago. RD's military career included deployments to Desert Shield with the 24th Infantry Division, first as the LNO to 2nd Bde, (he appears in the grainy background of a picture first published in Parade Magazine and subsequently in GEN Schwarzkopf’s Book “It Doesn’t take a Hero”). RD subsequently moved to the 24th AVN Brigade to be the TAC OIC just prior to Operation Desert Storm— He later served alongside classmate John Magness with the 160th SOAR in Somalia, RD also deployed as the S3 for 6-6 Cav to Bosnia in ’97, and then later to Kosovo in ’98. RD commanded 4/3 Cavalry Squadron (’03-’04) the first US element to occupy and operate from Al Asad Airbase in the Anbar Province. He played squash and later 150s football, as a cadet in A-4 then C-1 with roommates who have remained friends now for decades. After retiring, he spent 14 years at Dell in Austin. RD currently consults/invests in military/dual-use start up companies. He skis often—helped by two sons working in the ski and outdoor industry—Fashion conscious as he is, RD notes he looks much better kitted in world class gear/clothing (from where his son’s work) than he appears actually skiing down the slopes, or mountain biking the trails with them. He grew up in Huntsville, Alabama, where his father was a high school coach and athletic director whose name adorns the UAH Softball Pressbox. He remains deeply connected to classmates and still attends myriad classmate focused gatherings. He can be reached at robert_douthit@yahoo.com | 512-983-1509."},{"id":242,"n":"Shane Downey","u":"Shane","g":"D4","p":"A3","ph":"(814) 525-1180","em":"dowshane@aol.com","tw":"Johnstown","st":"PA"},{"id":243,"n":"Robert Dowse","u":"Rob","g":"I3","p":"D4","ph":"720-470-2141","em":"robdowse@me.com","tw":"Marina Del Ray","af":"Sailing, Track","ac":"Travel, Skeet/Sporting Clays, Cocktails","w":"Rob lives in Marina del Rey, California. He has been married to Kim for 29 years, and they've lived in 28 places during that time. He has no children, joking \"Ha! Me, kids??? I'm not responsible enough for that.\" His plebe company was D4, graduating from I3. His most memorable cadet experiences include an evening spent stuffing BG Boylan's office with newspaper, men's track and field, sailing team, serving as snow sport instructor, and tactics club (infantry). He loved being 2-60 Infantry AT Platoon leader as they helped develop the HMMWV in the Army at Fort Lewis, Washington. After the Army, he tried the cop thing for a couple of years, but it wasn't the job for him, so he started climbing mountains. He worked in the outdoor industry for quite a while—in shops, in climbing gyms, as an independent rep, as a tech rep, and as an alpine climber. He also repped a few bike companies. Now he drives boats, having started with dive boats in Hawaii and now tourist boats in Marina del Rey (up to 500 passengers). He stands in awe at what the class has accomplished, joking that he hasn't had a real job in 30-plus years and is gobsmacked at how well everyone has done. Despite being out of the Army, he still seems to move all the time. He enjoys travel, skeet and sporting clays, and cocktails. He can be reached at robdowse@me.com | 720-470-2141."},{"id":244,"n":"Wayne Doyle","u":"Wayne","g":"A1","p":"G3","em":"wdoyle1@emich.edu","tw":"Saline","st":"MI"},{"id":245,"n":"Kevin Drevik","u":"Kevin","g":"I3","p":"H2","ph":"856-630-2485","em":"kdrevik@yahoo.com","tw":"Moorestown","st":"NJ","ac":"Backpacking, woodworking","w":"Kevin Drevik Kevin lives in Moorestown, New Jersey. He was married in July 1986 at Fort Knox and is still married, getting ready to celebrate his 40th anniversary with family and friends in July. His plebe company was H2, graduating from I3. His most memorable cadet experience was at Buckner. He served with the 8th Infantry Division in Mainz, Germany and 3rd Armored Division in Desert Storm, where he was BMO. After the Army, he worked in logistics and supply chain. His most interesting role was Director of Engineering for a 3PL firm, traveling throughout North America setting up warehousing (racking, automation, etc.), which he describes as a great job that was always interesting. He enjoys backpacking and woodworking. He can be reached at kdrevik@yahoo.com | 856-630-2485."},{"id":246,"n":"Brian Drinkwine","u":"Brian","g":"D3","p":"E1","ph":"703-431-0454","em":"brian.drinkwine82@gmail.com","tw":"Conroe","st":"TX"},{"id":247,"n":"Leighton Drisdale","u":"Leighton","g":"F2","p":"D1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":248,"n":"Llewellyn Dryfoos","u":"Lew","g":"B1","p":"A2","ph":"(570) 436-5737","em":"lew.dryfoos@gmail.com","tw":"Sugarloaf","st":"PA"},{"id":249,"n":"William Duke","u":"Will","g":"C1","p":"F3","ph":"770-315-0120","em":"Rangerduke86@gmail.com","tw":"Georgetown","st":"SC","ac":"Cycling, Fishing, swimming and any kind of sports events.","w":"Will Duke Will lives in Georgetown, South Carolina after 20+ years in Atlanta. His daughter Emily (30) graduated TCU in 2018, worked at Textron, Korn Ferry, Heidrick & Struggles, and McKinsey before earning her MBA from SMU in 2025. She now works at Texas Capital in Dallas. His son Dallas (28) graduated University of Oklahoma in 2020 and lives in Atlanta working as a salesman for Pinnacle Freight, a logistics brokerage company. His plebe company was F3, graduating from C1. His most memorable assignment was the first Gulf War. As S-3 Air, the night before the ceasefire he navigated an un-armored HMMWV across two brigades of M1 Tanks and M2 Bradleys on a moonless night without GPS to reach the Division Jump TOC. After two hours of dead reckoning and getting stuck on a berm for 90 minutes, he learned they came extremely close to being fired upon. He was carrying a portrait of Saddam Hussein from Jalibah Airfield that the battalion commander wanted to give to General Barry McCaffrey, that portrait reportedly still sits in the 24th ID museum at Fort Stewart. Following the Gulf War, he attended Duke business school and since 1993 has worked in the financing sector with private equity firms investing in healthcare. His strongest cadet memories are C-1 trips to NYC with Tony Hylton and others—including a Billy Idol concert at Nassau Coliseum where Hylton's \"brilliant idea\" to take the 59th Street bridge back to avoid tolls left them stuck for 90 minutes, and a trip to see The Romantics at a venue in Manhattan's East Village. He stopped drinking cold turkey on Labor Day 2008 with a goal for taking September off, and by grace hasn't had alcohol since. He enjoys cycling, fishing, swimming, and attending sports events. He can be reached at Rangerduke86@gmail.com | 770-315-0120."},{"id":250,"n":"Jeffrey Duncan","u":"Jeff","g":"C3","p":"C1","ph":"(540) 207-7358","em":"duncanja80@gmail.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA"},{"id":251,"n":"Todd Dunlap","u":"Todd","g":"A3","p":"","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":252,"n":"Chester Dymek","u":"Jay","g":"E3","p":"D2","em":"jaydymek@earthlink.net","tw":"Charlottesville","st":"VA"},{"id":253,"n":"Patrick Echols","u":"Tom","g":"G3","p":"D4","ph":"(360) 705-0551","em":"tomechols@aol.com","tw":"Olympia","st":"WA"},{"id":254,"n":"Robert Eckelbarger","u":"Bob","g":"D3","p":"C1","em":"reckelbarger@gmail.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":255,"n":"Michael Eddy","u":"Mike","g":"C4","p":"D3","ph":"425-869-2453","em":"CNQ@MEINNOVATIONS.COM","tw":"Lacey","st":"WA","af":"Cross Country","ac":"CYCLING, HIKING","w":"Mike Eddy Mike lives in Lacey, Washington. He has two kids and ran All Army Cross Country at the Presidio during his time at West Point. His most vivid cadet memory is \"wipe Navy.\" Mike's post-Army career took him into defense engineering, where he worked on the 737 MAX test rig at Boeing—a project that he notes could have prevented two crashes if middle management had respected the test results. He shared a bathroom with Bill Gates during this work. His engineering background and athletic discipline carried into competitive cycling, where he became a world champion cyclist. He enjoys cycling and hiking, maintaining the competitive drive that defined both his military and civilian careers. He can be reached at CNQ@MEINNOVATIONS.COM | 425-869-2453."},{"id":256,"n":"Brian Egeling","u":"Brian","g":"C3","p":"G1","ph":"(616) 292-5914","em":"cutoncemi@yahoo.com","tw":"Grand Rapids","st":"MI"},{"id":257,"n":"Keeven Edwards","u":"Keeven","g":"A1","p":"","ph":"404-226-5330","em":"keevinedwards@yahoo.com"},{"id":258,"n":"Andrew Eger","u":"Andy","g":"H3","p":"B2","ph":"804-895-2077","em":"andyandzaida@gmail.com","tw":"Chester","st":"VA","af":"SCUBA Club","ac":"Hunting, SCUBA Diving","w":"Andy Eger Andy lives in Chester, Virginia. He and his wife, Zaida, have been married for 37 years and have two sons: Charles, 36, who works as an aerospace engineer for the Air Force at Edwards Air Force Base, and Nick, 33, who is a cybersecurity program manager with Reynolds and Reynolds. He served twenty years without deploying. His first assignment at Fort Ord was also his most expensive—he arrived with a truck and a dog, left five and a half years later with a van, car, wife, two boys, and two dogs. He worked for the Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Army for Procurement and retired as Director of the Acquisition (Contracting) Force Management Office at Fort Lee, Virginia. During firstie year spring break, he helped organize the SCUBA club trip to Key Largo, Florida. On a night dive, he and Mike Switzer got \"lost\" with their students and swam through a swarm of barracudas to the wrong boat.He still hunts and SCUBA dives. He can be reached at andyandzaida@gmail.com | 804-895-2077."},{"id":259,"n":"Andrew Eiseman","u":"Andy","g":"E3","p":"F2","ph":"301-792-9044","em":"jaaame1@aol.com","tw":"Mount Pleasant","st":"SC"},{"id":260,"n":"Johanna (McDonald) Elgin","u":"Johanna","g":"E4","p":"H2","ph":"(201) 651-1188","em":"jelgin@optonline.net","tw":"Franklin Lakes","st":"NJ"},{"id":261,"n":"Carolyn Elliot-Lewis","u":"Carolyn","g":"H4","p":"E2","ph":"936-235-1500","em":"carolynelliotlewis@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX","ac":"Army Football and Any travel trips","w":"Carolyn Elliott-Lewis Carolyn divides her time between Oklahoma and Texas. She has two stepchildren and four grandchildren. Her plebe company was E2, graduating from H4. She served at Fort Riley, Kansas, where she participated in NTC rotations. Her most memorable cadet experience was the Army game at the Rose Bowl in Pasadena. After the Army, she transitioned from manufacturing to technology and cyber security. She still works and maintains her career in the cyber security field. She joined the Chicks of '86 early, beginning with the first Bradenton gathering, and quickly became part of the core group that sustains the annual tradition. She emphasized how welcoming the group is to first-time attendees, noting that initial nervousness reliably gives way to comfort and repeat attendance. She follows Army football closely and enjoys travel trips. She can be reached at carolynelliotlewis@gmail.com | 936-235-1500."},{"id":262,"n":"Joseph Elliott","u":"Joseph","g":"F3","p":"G2","ph":"(303) 403-8223","em":"elliottsx5@aol.com","tw":"Arvada","st":"CO"},{"id":263,"n":"Joshua Elliott","u":"Joshua","g":"H1","p":"","ph":"703-408-3205","em":"elliottjoshua@hotmail.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":264,"n":"Robert Elliott","u":"Robert","g":"I1","p":"C2","ph":"(505) 892-3991","tw":"Rio Rancho","st":"NM"},{"id":265,"n":"Steven Elliott","u":"Steven","g":"E1","p":"H3","tw":"Carmel","st":"IN"},{"id":266,"n":"Michael Ellis","u":"Mike","g":"I3","p":"A1","ph":"913-240-9155","em":"mdellis33@gmail.com","tw":"Kansas City","st":"KS","af":"Basketball","w":"Mike lives in Kansas City, Kansas. His plebe company was A1, graduating from I3. His most memorable cadet experience was playing on the men's basketball team. After the Army, he became a Business Excellence Innovation Leader and Certified Lean Six Sigma Master Black Belt at Black & Veatch. He can be reached at mdellis33@gmail.com | 913-240-9155."},{"id":267,"n":"Douglas Elmore","u":"Doug","g":"C3","p":"","ph":"(713) 864-7554","em":"douge86@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":268,"n":"Michael Endres","u":"Mike","g":"I1","p":"B2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":269,"n":"Gregory Enochs","u":"Greg","g":"I4","p":"D2","ph":"901-305-1142","em":"gregenochs@gmail.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":270,"n":"Phyllis Erkins","u":"Phyllis","g":"C2","p":"F4","ph":"804-386-9932","em":"dstltclady@aol.com","tw":"Opelika","st":"AL","ac":"I love to travel, attend concerts, and sporting events (mostly football).","w":"Phyllis Erkins Phyllis lives in Opelika, Alabama. She moved south to be near her parents in Eufaula, Alabama and her daughter Ashley and son-in-law Keith in Florida. No human grandbabies yet but two beautiful dogs that she spoils when she goes to Florida. Her best memories from cadet days stem from the friendships she made as we bonded together to get through the years. She has very special memories of her roommates Julie, Patti, and Ranelle, and her bestie Valerie (Washington) Pendergrass. She could not have made it through without them. She was privileged to serve 20 years and retire. Her favorite assignments were in Germany, with her most favorite being her time as a company commander in Baumholder, the Rock. Being in Germany allowed her to travel to many different countries in a few short hours, and she would go back today. After the Army, she transitioned to civil service with the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA) as an Operations Research Analyst. She had many logistics jobs with DLA before moving to FEMA for her last year. She enjoyed her time with both agencies but had no regrets hanging up her boots to retire and move close to family. Phyllis enjoys the Chicks of 86 mini reunions and hopes to make more of them in the coming years. She loves to travel, attend concerts, and sporting events, mostly football. She can be reached at dstltclady@aol.com | 804-386-9932."},{"id":271,"n":"Mark Esper","u":"Mark","g":"H1","p":"E4","em":"mtesper@gmail.com","tw":"Northern","st":"VA"},{"id":272,"n":"Stephen Ethen","u":"Stephen","g":"F1","p":"F2","em":"scethen@icloud.com","tw":"St Thomas","st":"VI"},{"id":273,"n":"Tod Etheredge","u":"Todd","g":"H3","p":"H1","ph":"(601) 278-3056","em":"tetheredge@trustmark.com","tw":"Pike Road","st":"AL"},{"id":274,"n":"Orel Everett","u":"Mike","g":"B2","p":"E4","tw":"Corpus Christi","st":"TX"},{"id":275,"n":"Dale Fakkema","u":"Dale","g":"D4","p":"H2","ph":"360-393-7524","em":"dsfakkema@comcast.net","tw":"Lynnwood","st":"WA"},{"id":276,"n":"John Farley","u":"John","g":"D1","p":"A3","ph":"240-672-2056","em":"farleyjh@me.com","tw":"Scottsdale","st":"AZ"},{"id":277,"n":"Kevin Farrell","u":"Kevin","g":"I3","p":"H4","ph":"845-248-7268","em":"kevin.farrell@battlefieldleadership.com","tw":"Greenville","st":"SC","w":"Kevin Farrell Kevin lives in Greenville, South Carolina. He has been married for 35 years to the former Sheila Newman of Lugoff, South Carolina. They have three adult children: Elizabeth F. Thompson, 31, a former elementary school teacher married to Zach Thompson (USMA 2015, former Armor officer), now a business executive, expecting their first child in June; Will Farrell, 28, a Cybersecurity Analyst with State Farm living in Chicago; and Caroline Farrell, 23, a public relations and marketing specialist for a company in Columbia, South Carolina. Kevin was a plebe in H4 and graduated from I3. His best cadet memory was having a STRAC company. He served a full career as an armor officer, retiring as a colonel. He served in four different tank battalions: platoon leader and HHC XO in 3-32 AR, 1st Cavalry Division at Fort Hood; company commander in 3-68 AR, 4th Infantry Division at Fort Carson; battalion S-3 and battalion XO in 1-77 AR, 1st Infantry Division in Schweinfurt, Germany and Kosovo; and battalion commander of 1-64 AR, 3rd Infantry Division at Fort Stewart, Georgia and Tissa Nissan, Iraq. His most interesting and meaningful assignment was battalion commander of a 1,000-man combined arms battalion in extended combat operations in Iraq for thirteen months. His most enjoyable assignments were being stationed in Germany twice. He also served as a History Professor from 1995-1998 at West Point's Department of History, in staff assignments, as Aide de Camp to the V Corps Commanding General, at Fort Leavenworth, and as an advisor to the Afghan National Army. He finished his career as an Academy Professor, leading the International History Division and then the Military History Division in the Department of History. Since retiring in 2013, he has worked at Battlefield Leadership, LLC, becoming CEO in 2016. He works with corporate groups and senior executives at historic sites to help leaders improve, combining practical leadership experience with academic interest in history. He served as senior military advisor on the 2014 WWII Hollywood film Fury starring Brad Pitt, which was an interesting experience especially for his wife. He can be reached at kevin.farrell@battlefieldleadership.com | 845-859-4453."},{"id":278,"n":"James Fasone","u":"Jim","g":"A4","p":"C2","ph":"(301) 262-5158","em":"vze2vt3u@verizon.net","tw":"Bowie","st":"MD"},{"id":279,"n":"Timothy Faulkner","u":"Tim","g":"F2","p":"F3","ph":"757-478-5000","em":"timf@thebreedencompany.com","tw":"Norfolk","st":"VA","ac":"Attending sports events","w":"Tim lives in Norfolk, Virginia. He has four children: Andrew, Lydia, Leighton, and Luke. He has one grandchild, Fallon, age one. He served in 3/4 ADA in the 82nd Airborne Division. Deploying to Jungle School with an infantry brigade and being the opposing force was very exciting. After the Army, he worked for Proctor and Gamble, then smaller manufacturing companies. For 15 years, he has been COO and CEO of a regional real estate development company that develops, has a construction company, and property management company. He has been involved in several local boards and nonprofits, including serving as chairman of the Virginia Symphony Orchestra. He had dinner with Yo-Yo Ma. He attends sporting events. He can be reached at timf@thebreedencompany.com | 757-478-5000."},{"id":280,"n":"Bruce Fauth","u":"Bruce","g":"H4","p":"A2","ph":"615-796-0012","em":"fauth63@gmail.com","tw":"Smyrna","st":"TN"},{"id":281,"n":"Peter Feeney","u":"Peter","g":"B4","p":"E2","ph":"973-902-1327","em":"pfeeney82@gmail.com","tw":"Summit","st":"NJ","ac":"Golf.  Skiing","w":"Peter Feeney Pete lives in Summit, New Jersey. His son Brian, class of '18, left the Army last year and is getting his MBA in London. His son Malcolm lives and works in New York City and is getting married to his high school sweetheart in May 2026. He served nine years in the Army. He golfs and skis.He can be reached at pfeeney82@gmail.com | 973-902-1327."},{"id":282,"n":"Benjamin Felts","u":"Ben","g":"E1","p":"I2","ph":"(813) 655-7574","em":"bfelts86@gmail.com","tw":"Brandon","st":"FL"},{"id":283,"n":"Gregory Fenton","u":"Greg","g":"C4","p":"E1","em":"greg.fenton86@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":284,"n":"Beth (Schleeter) Ferrier","u":"Beth","g":"D1","p":"B3","ph":"(571) 594-2505","em":"bethferrier@aol.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA"},{"id":285,"n":"Michael Ferrier","u":"Mike","g":"A2","p":"F4","ph":"(571) 594-2551","em":"ferrierms@aol.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA"},{"id":286,"n":"Linda Fetko","u":"Linda","g":"I4","p":"G2","em":"linda.fetko@gmail.com","tw":"Durham","st":"NC"},{"id":287,"n":"Robert Field","u":"Bobbie","g":"I4","p":"B2","ph":"(703) 868-3255","em":"robfield714@yahoo.com","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL"},{"id":288,"n":"Terrence Finley","u":"Terry","g":"C4","p":"H2","ph":"609-636-7204","em":"terry@westpointtb.com","tw":"Bowling Green","st":"KY","w":"Terry Finley Terry splits his time between Bowling Green, Kentucky; Hollywood, Florida; and Saratoga Springs, New York, with his wife Debbie. They have a son and a daughter and five grandchildren. After graduating from West Point in 1986, Terry served as an Army officer before transitioning into business. In 1991, he founded West Point Thoroughbreds with one partner and one claiming horse, driven by the idea that more people should have access to the excitement and camaraderie of Thoroughbred racing. Over the past three decades, he has grown the company into the largest Thoroughbred partnership organization in the world, with more than 700 partners and about 150 horses currently in training. West Point runners have earned more than 1,250 career victories and nearly $100 million in purses. The stable has campaigned top-level performers including Kentucky Derby winner Always Dreaming, Horse of the Year and Breeders’ Cup Classic champion Flightline, and 2025 Champion Two-Year-Old Filly Super Corredora. Terry earned an MBA from Boston University and later completed the Owner/President Management program at Harvard Business School. He serves as a steward of The Jockey Club, is a board member of the Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation, chairs the New York Racetrack Chaplaincy, and is a longtime board member of the Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund. He enjoys time with family, classmates, and partners at the racetrack. He can be reached at terry@westpointtb.com | 609-636-7204"},{"id":289,"n":"Gregory Fitzharris","u":"Gregory","g":"B3","p":"C1","em":"gfitzharris@hotmail.com","tw":"Newport News","st":"VA"},{"id":290,"n":"Michael Flanagan","u":"Mike","g":"B1","p":"A2","ph":"804-349-6235","em":"mike.flanagan.usma86@gmail.com","tw":"Manakin Sabot","st":"VA","ac":"Great question - we'd be interested in travel, especially after two tours in Germany with several classmates.","w":"Mike Flanagan Mike lives in Manakin Sabot, Virginia, with his high school sweetheart Melia. They have three children—Thomas (TJ), Mary, and Catherine (Kate)—and six granddaughters ranging from 1 to 17 years old, all living in Virginia. After 27 years in the Army, Mike retired from the Army in Orlando, FL (2013) and moved back to Virginia in 2015 to be closer to the granddaughters. As a Cadet, Mike’s CTLT with the 11th ACR led him to Armor for the first nine years in the Army. Mike later transitioned to the Army Acquisition Corps following grad school and served in program management and R&D assignments. His favorite assignment took him to arms shows across Europe, the Middle East, and Africa. The most rewarding job was leading the Abrams Tank System program office (2004-6) during OIF. Following retirement from the Army, Mike worked in the defense industry for CACI, LMI, and The Spectrum Group. During Mark Esper’s tenure as Secretary of the Army, Mike was one of eight to ten classmates that Mark appointed as Civilian Aides (aka CASA) for their respective states. As CASA Virginia (South) for six years, Mike reconnected with the Army and worked with several classmates that he hadn’t known at West Point. Mike has also enjoyed serving on the board of his local West Point Society, especially returning for the annual class and society leader conferences. He and Melia are interested in travel, particularly after two tours in Germany with classmates. He welcomes visitors passing through Richmond and is glad to help classmates needing connections in Virginia. He can be reached at mike.flanagan.usma86@gmail.com | 804-349-6235."},{"id":291,"n":"Timothy Flanagan","u":"Tim","g":"F4","p":"E3","ph":"703-657-9369","em":"flanagan.tim@gmail.com","tw":"Herndon","st":"VA"},{"id":292,"n":"David Flint","u":"David","g":"H2","p":"I4","tw":"Rockville","st":"MD"},{"id":293,"n":"Franklin Flowers","u":"Frank","g":"H1","p":"H4","ph":"678-576-1062","em":"fsflowers@hotmail.com","tw":"Snellville","st":"GA"},{"id":294,"n":"Charles Fluekiger","u":"Nick","g":"F3","p":"H2","ph":"No Publish","em":"nickf5555522@gmail.com","tw":"No Publish","st":"No Publish","w":"Nick Fluekiger Nick is fully retired from the US Army and FBI. He can be reached at nickf5555522@gmail.com"},{"id":295,"n":"Robert Fogtman","u":"Kent","g":"C3","p":"I4","em":"rkfogtman@gmail.com","tw":"Winter Springs","st":"FL","ac":"Tennis and golf","w":"Kent Fogtman Kent lives in Winter Springs, Florida. He has three children and three grandchildren. His favorite cadet memory was flying to Pasadena, California and watching the Army-Navy game at the Rose Bowl during yearling year in December 1983. He served in Germany from 1987-1990. After the Army, he became a pilot at Southwest Airlines and has flown for 28 years. His wife has been a flight attendant at Southwest Airlines for 40 years. Kent enjoys tennis and golf. He can be reached at rkfogtman@gmail.com."},{"id":296,"n":"Brett Folse","u":"Brett","g":"I3","p":"G2","em":"bfolse44@aol.com","tw":"Lakeland","st":"FL"},{"id":297,"n":"Robin Fontes","u":"Robin","g":"E2","p":"C3","ph":"202-361-0899","em":"fontesrl@gmail.com","tw":"Boise","st":"ID","ac":"Fishing, travel, golf","w":"Robin Fontes Robin lives in the central mountains of Idaho, 1.5-2 hours away from a city. Her plebe company was C3. Her most memorable assignment was serving as Defense Attache in Tajikistan from 1998 to 2000. After retiring from the Army, she works a bit as a consultant but mainly fly fishes. She enjoys fishing, travel, and golf and can be reached at fontesrl@gmail.com | 202-361-0899."},{"id":298,"n":"Timothy Ford","u":"Timothy","g":"A2","p":"A3","em":"timford21@yahoo.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":299,"n":"Matthew Fortunato","u":"Matt","g":"G4","p":"B2","ph":"(786) 239-7702","em":"mjfortunato@yahoo.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":300,"n":"Kevin Foster","u":"Kevin","g":"D2","p":"E4","em":"kevin.lee.foster@gmail.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL"},{"id":301,"n":"Thomas Fowler","u":"Thomas","g":"G4","p":"C2","ph":"(703) 845-1416","em":"tmfowler@outlook.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":302,"n":"David Fralen","u":"Dave","g":"B2","p":"H1","ph":"(540) 840-3309","em":"davefralen@mac.com","tw":"Smith Mountain Lake","st":"VA","ac":"Fishing, skiing","w":"Dave Fralen Dave lives at Smith Mountain Lake, Virginia. His best assignment was Kitzingen, Germany, as battalion FDO with the best battalion and group of lieutenants. After the Army, he worked as a Project Manager at IBM with JIEDDO and Program Manager at CACI with DTRA. He fishes and skis. He can be reached at davefralen@mac.com | 540-840-3309."},{"id":303,"n":"Neal Freeman","u":"Neal","g":"A2","p":"","ph":"765-620-8029","em":"nfreeman61@hotmail.com","tw":"Anderson","st":"IN","ac":"Traveling","w":"Neal Freeman Neal lives in Anderson, Indiana. He’s been in love with and married to Laura since shortly after graduation and he still thanks Wally Clark for the introduction! He has two sons: Adam, superintendent of a K-12 Christian school, and Joshua, who works for the Golden State Warriors. His two grandchildren are Witten and Landry. He completed a three-week deployment 200 miles north of the Arctic Circle in Norway. He became an FBI Special Agent in 1997, retired in 2017, and now teaches criminal justice classes at Anderson University. He has been doing Christian mentoring at a juvenile prison for more than 20 years. He travels. He can be reached at nfreeman61@hotmail.com | 765-620-8029."},{"id":304,"n":"Kristin (Knapp) French","u":"Kristin","g":"D1","p":"","em":"kkfrench86@gmail.com","tw":"Clifton","st":"VA"},{"id":305,"n":"Richard French","u":"Rick","g":"H1","p":"G4","ph":"703-785-0413","em":"frenchrl86@gmail.com","tw":"Clifton","st":"VA","ac":"Kristin and I love the Yankees and the Washington Capitals. Love photographing all types of activities and trvels."},{"id":306,"n":"Edward Froelich","u":"Edward","g":"G1","p":"C2","ph":"803-206-1104","em":"efroelich@yahoo.com","tw":"Elgin","st":"SC","ac":"Fishing, traveling","w":"Ed Froelich resides in Columbia, South Carolina where he practices medicine as an Anesthesiologist. His contact information includes (803) 206-1104 and efroelich@yahoo.com.  Ed was one of if not the hardest working cadets at the academy with a laser focus on going to medical school. While he can’t say he enjoyed his time at USMA, his work ethic paid off when he was one of ten from the class chosen to attend the Uniform Services Health academy and went on to serve at Fort Jackson, Fort Gordon, and in Bosnia. After 20 years in the Army he settled in South Carolina where he fishes at every chance he gets. Ed married his wife Suzann shortly after graduation and has 4 children and 3 grandchildren."},{"id":307,"n":"Ronald Frost","u":"Ronald","g":"B2","p":"D1","ph":"(256) 782-2056","tw":"Jacksonville","st":"AL"},{"id":308,"n":"Peter Fuenfhausen","u":"Peter","g":"B4","p":"H2","ph":"972-400-0397","em":"pete.fuenfhausen@outlook.com","tw":"Flower Mound","st":"TX"},{"id":309,"n":"Brian Fues","u":"Brian","g":"B3","p":"B2","ph":"949-279-4544","em":"Brian.Fues@gmail.com","tw":"Bolivia","st":"NC","ac":"Boating, hiking and traveling.","w":"Brian and his wife Lynn live in Bolivia, NC. They have one daughter who is an occupational therapist at Franciscan Children's Hospital in Boston and is engaged to be married next August. Brian served mostly in Germany and Fort Carson.  While in Germany he served as a platoon leader and XO, but he also had the opportunity to do multinational air defense HAWK battery evaluations, working with German and other NATO team leaders.  Following his first assignment, Brian branch-transferred to the Transportation Corps and was lucky enough to meet his wife Lynn who was also attending in the TC Advanced Course at Ft. Eustis.  Luckily they had a great assignment officer who agreed to send them both to Ft. Carson.  Following his 7 years of active duty and 3 years of dating,  Brian and Lynn married and he attended the University of Tennessee to earn his MBA in Logistics & Transportation. Brian's civilian career included 2 years at CSX Transportation and then 27 years with Penske Logistics. His most interesting Penske role was as the operational leader for the Starbucks account for 8 years. Last February Brian retired and they moved from PA to NC.  He enjoys boating, hiking, travel and volunteering.  His most recent volunteer gigs are helping to teach elementary school science class and as a Team Rubicon Greyshirt (food pantry support, Habitat for Humanity builds, etc.).  He can be reached at Brian.Fues@gmail.com | 949-279-4544."},{"id":310,"n":"David Fulton","u":"David","g":"D4","p":"I1","ph":"49-162-2965403","em":"david_fulton86@yahoo.com","tw":"Heidelberg"},{"id":311,"n":"David Funk","u":"David","g":"D4","p":"F3","ph":"(717) 440-2007","em":"david.funk2@aol.com","tw":"Chino","st":"CA"},{"id":312,"n":"Richard Gabaldon","u":"Rich","g":"I4","p":"C2","ph":"770-608-7886","em":"Richgabaldon@gmail.com","tw":"Maitland","st":"FL","af":"Football","ac":"Love to travel and be with family and friends.","w":"Richard Gabaldon Rich lives in Maitland, Florida. He has a blended family with five grown children and a new grandchild with another on the way in March 2026. His plebe company was C2, graduating from I4. His most memorable cadet experiences were walking the Corps prior to Sosh/Econ due dates campaigning for Class VP, being Captain of the GOAT football team, and powerlifting in the \"Animal House.\" Most of his time was with the 7th and 15th Infantry regiments at Fort Stewart, Georgia and in Germany. Serving in Desert Storm after IOAC was a unique experience at the \"Tip of the Spear.\" After the Army, he spent 20 years at Ericsson introducing digital cellular communications primarily in the Southeast and is currently looking for that next exciting role. He loves to travel and be with family and friends. He can be reached at Richgabaldon@gmail.com | 770-608-7886."},{"id":313,"n":"Bruce Gagne","u":"Bruce","g":"E2","p":"C4","ph":"304-261-2163","em":"bjgagne@gmail.com","tw":"Charles Town","st":"WV","ac":"Attending sporting and social events with ample opportunity to catch up with each other."},{"id":314,"n":"Eric Gaines","u":"Eric","g":"C3","p":"F2","ph":"727-237-4624","em":"eagfllvn@gmail.com","tw":"Phoenix","st":"AZ","ac":"He is deeply committed to outdoor activities, especially hiking, backpacking, mountaineering, and extended travel. He lives a “digital nomad” lifestyle centered on van life, road travel, and national parks, and would enjoy reconnecting with classmates through travel, informal meetups, shared outdoor experiences, and stop-in visits while on the road rather than structured or competitive activities.","w":"Eric Gaines Eric lives a digital nomad lifestyle, primarily identifying with both Florida and Arizona but traveling extensively across North America in his van. He has four adult children in their late 20s to mid-30s. One daughter lives in Florida with five children and a sixth on the way—he's currently spending extended time with that family. One son survived a severe traumatic brain and spinal injury from a work accident, underwent years of rehabilitation, returned to school, and now works in Indiana with people with physical and cognitive disabilities. He grew up near West Point in Peekskill, New York and entered the Academy late in his senior year. He flew Blackhawks in an Apache brigade at Fort Hood during a major transition period for Army aviation, serving as motor officer, platoon leader, S4, and property book officer during rapid unit activation and equipment fielding, transferring hundreds of millions of dollars of equipment to deploying units during Desert Storm preparations. He graduated as an electrical and computer engineering major, serving on battalion and regimental staff. After leaving active duty during the early 1990s drawdown, he began as an engineer with Quaker Oats in Illinois, then spent 17 years with General Electric, including time as a Six Sigma Black Belt. He later transitioned to flexible contract work, allowing partial retirement and location independence. He lost his wife to cancer after a long illness and later reinvented his life around adventure, faith, and service to family. He's deeply committed to hiking, backpacking, mountaineering, and extended travel, including solo backcountry trips in Alaska. He works only when he chooses, supported by remote connectivity, while prioritizing travel and family. Grandchildren are a major focus of his life and travel decisions. He can be reached at eagfllvn@gmail.com | 727-237-4624."},{"id":315,"n":"David Galloway","u":"David","g":"D4","p":"I1","ph":"(571) 278-2738","em":"david.s.galloway@gmail.com","tw":"Brambleton","st":"VA"},{"id":316,"n":"Stephen Galloway","u":"Stephen","g":"D3","p":"C4","ph":"901-497-2359","em":"achvet@yahoo.com","tw":"Williston","st":"TN","ac":"I still love the outdoors, hunt a little, fish a lot, and backpack off-grid at least once a year!  Fly fishing & fly tying are my current obsessions (according to Melanie)!  Our family also travels abroad as much as possible.","w":"Stephen Galloway Stephen lives in Williston, Tennessee with his wife Melanie. They have triplets who have graduated from college: both daughters are in Physicians Assistant graduate programs with one daughter married, and their son is an Aerospace Engineer in Huntsville, Alabama. Stephen was a plebe in C4 and graduated from D3. He attended West Point with his twin brother David, who was in D4. He had a family-like relationship with Col Albert Rushton's home and remembers the Whiner Fests as memorable unofficial D3 events. After Fort Benning, he served his entire Army commitment in the 3/504th PIR, 82nd Airborne Division, during an active period that included deployments to Panama for Operation Just Cause and to Saudi Arabia and Iraq for Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm. After leaving the Army, he attended NC State for veterinary school, where he met Melanie. They practiced in the Texas Panhandle for a few years before returning to Tennessee to start their current practice 25 years ago. Stephen became a specialist in dentistry and orofacial surgery, was a founder of the equine dentistry specialty, and has treated patients of numerous species including guinea pigs, rabbits, dogs, cats, horses, camels, lions, and tigers. He is still working but has retirement in sight. Stephen loves the outdoors, hunts a little, fishes a lot, and backpacks off-grid at least once a year. Fly fishing and fly tying are current obsessions. The family travels abroad as much as possible. He can be reached at achvet@yahoo.com | 901-497-2359."},{"id":317,"n":"Michael Garcia","u":"Mike","g":"E2","p":"D4","ph":"803-322-9651","em":"mdg64@mac.com","tw":"Toronto","st":"Canada","ac":"Golf, Skiing, attending sporting events","w":"Michael Garcia Michael lives in Tucson, Arizona. His plebe company was D4, graduating from E2. He served with the 2nd Squadron, 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment after Basic Armor Course. After leaving the Army, he started his civilian career as a production team leader at Kimberly-Clark making diapers in Paris, Texas. He earned his MBA from Harvard in 1999 and spent the next 25 years in heavy industry - aluminum, steel, and pulp and paper - with assignments in China, South Africa, and Canada. He served on the Board of the Federal Reserve Bank of Richmond and now serves on the Board of Alliant Energy. He officially retired at the end of 2025 after serving as President and CEO of Algoma Steel, which he describes as the most interesting role of his career - part industrial transformation, part trade-policy roller coaster, part international diplomacy, and part \"herding cats at -30°C.\" He enjoys golf, skiing, and attending sporting events. He can be reached at mdg64@mac.com | 803-322-9651."},{"id":318,"n":"Paul Garland","u":"Paul","g":"E2","p":"I3","ph":"513-262-9144","em":"tlims1111@gmail.com","tw":"Denver","st":"CO"},{"id":319,"n":"Aubrey Garner","u":"Aubrey","g":"H3","p":"F2","em":"aubreygarner@gmail.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"GA","ac":"He did not list specific hobby “activity menu” items like golf or fishing, but he emphasized how much he values reconnecting with classmates and the ease of picking up relationships instantly despite decades passing. He spoke positively about reunions and the role of the internet and social media in maintaining bonds across distance, suggesting his preferred “activities” are primarily social reconnection and shared time with classmates rather than structured events."},{"id":320,"n":"Pat Gavin","u":"Pat","g":"G2","p":"D1","ph":"816-210-2712","em":"PMGavin86@gmail.com","tw":"Lees Summit","st":"MO","ac":"Golf, attending sports/cultural events, axe throwing, wine tasting","w":"Pat Gavin Pat lives in Lee's Summit, Missouri. He has two sons: Nick, 28, and Jack, 25. Nick and his wife Maddy have a two-month-old son named Noah. He served as battalion S-3 Air in 1st Infantry Division during Desert Storm, helping coordinate operations during the 100-hour ground campaign. His unit breached Iraqi trench lines as part of the \"Hail Mary\" maneuver and ultimately secured the Safwan airfield where surrender negotiations occurred. After returning from the Gulf War, he left active duty, married, and attended law school in Kansas City. He became an employment lawyer, first in private practice and then moving in-house. He now serves in the legal department at T-Mobile and has spent nearly three decades in the field. He grew up in Dunkirk, New York, majored in political science, and developed a deep interest in presidential studies, completing research at the Eisenhower and Roosevelt libraries. He met his wife while stationed at Fort Riley and has lived in Lee's Summit for more than 30 years. He golfs, attends sports and cultural events, throws axes, and goes wine tasting. He can be reached at PMGavin86@gmail.com | 816-210-2712."},{"id":321,"n":"James George","u":"Jay","g":"C2","p":"B3","em":"jayinhisgrip@gmail.com"},{"id":322,"n":"Scott Gerig","u":"Scott","g":"B4","p":"A1","ph":"219-213-0976","em":"scott.gerig@gmail.com","tw":"Valparaiso","st":"IN"},{"id":323,"n":"Mark Gibbons","u":"Mark","g":"E3","p":"H1","em":"markdgibbons1963@gmail.com","tw":"Powderly","st":"TX"},{"id":324,"n":"Louis Gibson","u":"Louis","g":"H3","p":"C1","ph":"(918) 680-0068","em":"3sonsshining@gmail.com","tw":"Muskogee","st":"OK"},{"id":325,"n":"James Gigrich","u":"Jim","g":"G4","p":"","ph":"703-244-0428","em":"gigrichj@yahoo.com","tw":"Lorton","st":"VA","ac":"Astrophotography, Traveling, Golf, Fly-Fishing, Cars","w":"Jim Gigrich Jim Gigrich lives in Lorton, Virginia and has four sons ages 20, 20, 23, and 26. He served at stations including England, Hawaii, Germany, DC, Atlanta, and West Point before attending graduate school and moving into the high-tech sector. He pursues astrophotography, travels, golfs, and fly-fishes. He can be reached at gigrichj@yahoo.com | 703-244-0428."},{"id":326,"n":"Thomas Gilchrist","u":"Tom","g":"F1","p":"A4","ph":"(321) 576-2418","em":"tcmoor@gmail.com","tw":"Winter Springs","st":"FL"},{"id":327,"n":"Todd Gile","u":"TA","g":"G2","p":"I4","ph":"906-360-3335","em":"tagile82@gmail.com","tw":"Hoosick Falls","st":"NY","ac":"He described living on a farmhouse in northern New York near the Vermont border, hosting classmates who visit and participate in farm chores such as feeding chickens and sheep. He emphasized an outdoors, rural setting and also referenced skiing in the Garmisch area when he was stationed there, suggesting comfort with travel and outdoor recreation tied to classmate visits.","w":"Todd Gile TA lives in Hoosick Falls, New York. He has five children. His oldest is an Army captain serving as a recruiting company commander in Manhattan with a daughter. His second child lives in Minneapolis with two children. His third child, born at West Point, lives in Louisville with one child. He and his wife adopted a boy from Ukraine while stationed in Germany who lives with them. His youngest enlisted in the Guard and recently started basic training at Fort Leonard Wood. He highlighted operational assignments including jumping into Honduras shortly after arriving at Fort Bragg, serving during Desert Storm as part of a replacement engineer element, and later commanding in Alaska. He repeatedly emphasized satisfaction with engineer demolitions work, including large cache-destruction missions. After the Army, he worked for about 12 years with a leadership consulting firm affiliated with West Point's Thayer Hotel, supporting programs and coordinating work partly from home and partly on-site. He grew up in Appleton, Wisconsin, earned a master's in exercise science at Indiana University, returned to West Point, and ran and streamlined the boxing program after Herb Kraton's long tenure. He lives on a farmhouse in northern New York near the Vermont border, hosting classmates who visit and participate in farm chores. He can be reached at tagile82@gmail.com | 906-360-3335."},{"id":328,"n":"Kirk Gill","u":"Kirk","g":"D3","p":"A1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":329,"n":"Maura (O'Brien) Gillen","u":"Mo","g":"F2","p":"H4","ph":"757-602-9651","em":"mo_gillen@yahoo.com","tw":"Haverford","st":"PA","ac":"Love seeing new places with the Chicks!! Open to anything. I don't golf or bowl very well, but will happily round out a team with low expectations. Also happy to watch any and all sports competitions - football, lacrosse, equestrian, Army Women's Ice Hockey - all of it.","w":"Mo lives in Haverford, Pennsylvania. She and her '78 grad husband have three adult kids. The older two are both married and living in Virginia; the younger lives with them in Philadelphia. She has one granddaughter. She spent time in the Netherlands and Baghdad. One of her most interesting assignments was as Marketing Officer in the Admissions office at West Point, working on catalogs, posters, and videotapes. She served as a nuclear-certified Lance missile officer in Holland. Her 2008–2009 deployment to Baghdad as day MOC chief in the U.S. Embassy involved monitoring Arabic and international media, coordinating messaging among State, DoD, and senior leaders, and helping stand up operations in the new embassy compound. After 27 years of active duty, she retired as a field artillery officer with public affairs as her functional area and went to a veteran-serving nonprofit. She throttled back from full-time employment to part-time roles to take care of family, worked for the Census Bureau during COVID, then in local customer-facing jobs including AAA travel services. She currently works part-time for a small insurance firm while attending part-time evening law school at Rutgers Law in Camden, New Jersey. She helps lead the class TAPS project. She loves seeing new places and watches any and all sports competitions—football, lacrosse, equestrian, Army Women's Ice Hockey. She can be reached at mo_gillen@yahoo.com | 757-602-9651."},{"id":330,"n":"Alfred Glaeser","u":"Al","g":"E1","p":"C2","em":"alglaeser1986@gmail.com","tw":"Wilmington","st":"NC"},{"id":331,"n":"Randy Glaeser","u":"Randy","g":"B4","p":"","ph":"509-730-3304","em":"rvglaeser@msn.com","tw":"Sun Prairie","st":"WI"},{"id":332,"n":"Vivian Glaeser","u":"Vivian","g":"I2","p":"","ph":"(509) 240-5289","em":"vglaeser63@gmail.com","tw":"Sun Prairie","st":"WI"},{"id":333,"n":"Joseph Gleeson","u":"Joe","g":"C2","p":"G4","ph":"(615) 791-5752","em":"jmg1011@hotmail.com"},{"id":334,"n":"Alyson Goermar","u":"Alyson","g":"I4","p":"E3","ph":"(561j 767-0284","em":"AlysonGoermar@gmail.com","tw":"Boca Raton","st":"FL","ac":"Travel…Normandy would be a winner","w":"Alyson Goermar Alyson lives in Boca Raton, Florida. Her plebe company was E3, graduating from I4. Her most memorable cadet experiences were traveling away from West Point for volleyball matches with wonderful teammates and going to her sponsor's house to chill on occasional weekends. She attended Fort Lee, Virginia (home of the Quartermaster) for OBC and QM schools, then was stationed in Germany where the Berlin Wall came down in the middle of her tour in 1989. As the 501st Support Battalion fuel platoon leader, she created and implemented the first Refuel On The Move for the 1st Armored Division, which was groundbreaking at the time. After the Army, she worked in process improvement and quality control. She was a Lead Examiner for the Florida Sterling Council where her team examined public and private organizations based on National Malcolm Baldrige business excellence practices, working as an efficiency expert and management consultant. Her current hobby is wildlife and landscape photography. She loves to travel, with Normandy as a winner destination. She can be reached at AlysonGoermar@gmail.com | 561-767-0284."},{"id":335,"n":"Darcy (Dierks) Good","u":"Darcy","g":"D2","p":"B1","ph":"(410) 551-4838","em":"darcygood@comcast.net","tw":"Severn","st":"MD"},{"id":336,"n":"Jerome Goodrich","u":"Chip","g":"A1","p":"F2","ph":"(480) 330-1386","em":"chipgoodrich63@gmail.com","tw":"Scottsdale","st":"AZ"},{"id":337,"n":"Michael Goodridge","u":"Mike","g":"E3","p":"F4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":338,"n":"David Gordon","u":"David","g":"G4","p":"C1","ph":"(713) 630-1080","em":"david.m.gordon@me.com","tw":"Bellaire","st":"TX","ac":"Can’t do much, what with the 4-yr-old","w":"David Gordon David and his wife Ashley live in Bellaire, Texas, with their four-and-a-half-year-old child. David served with the 10th Mountain Division at Fort Drum—extreme heat, extreme cold. He's been in investment management for 32 years and counting, currently working for Goldman Sachs. He comments that he can't do much socializing with a four-year-old! And he can be reached at david.m.gordon@me.com | 713-630-1080."},{"id":339,"n":"Dana Goulette","u":"Dana","g":"B3","p":"I2","ph":"540-273-7354","em":"danagoulette@comcast.net","tw":"Stafford","st":"VA"},{"id":340,"n":"Walter Grandberry","u":"Walter","g":"C2","p":"G4","ph":"(847) 224-0867","em":"walter.grandberry@gmail.com","tw":"Chicago","st":"IL","w":"Walter Grandberry Walt lives in Chicago, Illinois. He has five children (three girls and two boys) and seven grandchildren. His plebe company was G4, graduating from C2. He served at the Infantry Center at Fort Benning. After the Army, he spent nearly 20 years in pharmaceutical sales and sales leadership before transitioning into his current role as a nonprofit executive. He can be reached at walter.grandberry@gmail.com | 847-224-0867."},{"id":341,"n":"Thomas Graves","u":"Thomas","g":"C4","p":"E3","ph":"(757) 502-4419","em":"tgravesk@yahoo.com","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":342,"n":"Jonathan Green","u":"Jon","g":"H4","p":"D3","ph":"256-653-5036","em":"jgreenesq@gmail.com","tw":"Cullman","st":"AL","ac":"Tractor, woodworking, learning to weld"},{"id":343,"n":"Mark Green","u":"Mark","g":"C2","p":"E1","em":"mgreennsdq@gmail.com","tw":"Ashland City","st":"TN"},{"id":344,"n":"Terrance Greene","u":"\"T\"","g":"I2","p":"E1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":345,"n":"Dennis Greenwood","u":"Dennis","g":"E3","p":"G4","ph":"571-237-9151","em":"dengrnwood@verizon.net","tw":"McCordsville","st":"IN","ac":"Travel","w":"Dennis Greenwood Dennis lives in McCordsville, Indiana with his wife Carol Genseal. They have two daughters—Sarah in Lincoln, Nebraska and Shannon in San Francisco. He retired as a Lieutenant Colonel in June 2006 from the Pentagon where he served on the OSD SOLIC staff. His career as a Military Police Officer and in special operations emphasized Civil Affairs and antiterrorism, taking him through Fort McClellan twice, Fort Riley, Grafenwoehr and Vilseck in Germany, Fort Benjamin-Harrison, Fort Leavenworth, Fort Bragg twice, Bosnia, and Saudi Arabia. His most notable assignments came as the ARCENT liaison to the Saudi military immediately after the Khobar bombing and as an antiterrorism action officer in the Pentagon after 9/11. After active duty he worked for Northrop Grumman as an analyst supporting the J-8 Joint Staff, then became a DoD civilian in the same role with the Warfighting Analysis Division until retiring in December 2025. During Beast he remembers Tim Knight volunteering without hesitation to help deliver the heavy Sunday New York Times papers—when Knight became First Captain, Greenwood thought it well deserved. Now retired, he travels and looks forward to more once Carol retires in a couple of years. He can be reached at dengrnwood@verizon.net | 571-237-9151."},{"id":346,"n":"Christopher Greer","u":"Chris","g":"B4","p":"A3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":347,"n":"Dixon Greffey","u":"Grant","g":"I3","p":"G2","ph":"703-455-5664","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":348,"n":"James Griffen","u":"James","g":"I1","p":"I3","em":"jgriff2@hallmark.com","tw":"Kansas City","st":"KS"},{"id":349,"n":"Paul Groce","u":"PJ","g":"H2","p":"I3","ph":"201-988-9646","em":"pjgroce@yahoo.com","tw":"Pawleys Island","st":"SC"},{"id":350,"n":"John Groeschner","u":"Groesch","g":"C2","p":"C4","ph":"563-528-9944","em":"blindjustice1@bellsouth.net","tw":"New Smyrna","st":"FL"},{"id":351,"n":"Richard Gronemeyer","u":"Rick","g":"E3","p":"H1","ph":"563-528-9944","tw":"Gilbert","st":"AZ"},{"id":352,"n":"Donald Groom","u":"Don","g":"A2","p":"E1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":353,"n":"Don Guggemos","u":"Chip","g":"F3","p":"A1","ph":"612-229-4157","em":"chip.g@live.com","tw":"Winsted","st":"MN"},{"id":354,"n":"Ronald Guiao","u":"Ronald","g":"H3","p":"B1","ph":"(608) 833-0198","em":"rpguiao@gmail.com","tw":"Middleton","st":"WI"},{"id":355,"n":"Thomas Guleff","u":"Tom","g":"I3","p":"E1","em":"tomguleff@gmail.com","tw":"Memphis","st":"TN"},{"id":356,"n":"Douglas Gurian","u":"Doug","g":"E1","p":"B4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":357,"n":"Kurt P. Gutierrez","u":"Kurt","g":"H2","p":"D1","ph":"(828) 638-5851","em":"k_gutz@yahoo.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":358,"n":"Jonathan Guy","u":"Jon","g":"C2","p":"G3","em":"jon.guy@verizon.net","tw":"Newtown","st":"PA","ac":"He enjoys international travel, especially to the UK and Europe, and values shared experiences tied to history and culture. Current leisure interests include travel with family, attending sporting events such as cricket matches, and informal social time with classmates at reunions and society events rather than organized competitive sports.","w":"Jonathan Guy Jon lives in Newtown, Pennsylvania. He has one daughter, Elizabeth, born in London while he and his wife were living in the UK. Health complications around her birth meant they did not have additional children. Elizabeth is now an adult, works as a nurse, and travels with him. His plebe company was G3, graduating from C2. His cadet memories emphasize company life: starting in G3, then moving to C2 (\"Flying Circus\"), mastering the academic and physical invisibility needed to survive. A defining moment was a German professor advising him to major in languages, a decision he credits as pivotal to his later success. He served as an armor officer in Germany with 2-8 Infantry, leveraging language skills (German, French, Danish) in liaison roles with German, Dutch, and British units, including close ties with the Scots Dragoon Guards. After leaving active duty early, he built an international civilian career with the East Asiatic Company and Heidelberg, working in the US, Germany, and the UK in senior operational and commercial roles. He later acquired and now leads Waltron as owner and CEO, a 122-year-old company manufacturing ultra-pure water analysis instruments. He rejoined the Army Reserve after nearly 20 years due to a sense of unfinished service, serving as a Reserve Foreign Area Officer and reaching lieutenant colonel, with assignments in FEMA coordination, DIA, EUCOM/J5, and senior Pentagon advisory roles. He balances reserve service, business leadership, and caregiving for a disabled spouse. He enjoys international travel, especially to the UK and Europe, attending sporting events such as cricket matches, and informal social time with classmates at reunions rather than organized competitive sports. He plans to mentor veteran entrepreneurs while preparing to transition Waltron to its next owner. He can be reached at jon.guy@verizon.net."},{"id":359,"n":"Daniel Guzman","u":"Dan","g":"F1","p":"D3","tw":"Glendale","st":"AZ"},{"id":360,"n":"Anthony Guzzi","u":"Tony","g":"F2","p":"A3","ph":"203-843-8811","em":"tguzzi4@gmail.com","tw":"Fairfield","st":"CT","ac":"Still love Army football, the Steelers, trying to keep some level of fitness, and golf.  I have been blessed to enjoy some great golf trips with classmates over the last 10 years.","w":"Tony lives in Fairfield, Connecticut with his wife Michelle, whom he met on a beach in Hawaii nearly 36 years ago. They have three children: John, who married Nadeen in March 2022 and lives in Connecticut with their son Zachary, born in May 2025; Ann Marie, who married Will in May 2023 and lives in Washington, DC; and Louis, who graduated from West Point in 2023 and serves as a Medevac pilot with the 101st Airborne Division. Tony served as an Infantry officer, spending significant time in Hawaii with frequent deployments throughout the Pacific. One of his most memorable experiences came during a deployment to Korea, when his team set up an LZ for a large air assault at the site of the Battle of Chipyong-ni from the Korean War, where an elderly Korean woman tearfully recounted the bravery of the Americans who fought there. After leaving the Army, Tony built and ran EMCOR Group for over 20 years, which he considers the highlight of his professional career. Tony follows Army football and the Steelers, tries to maintain fitness, and golfs regularly. He has enjoyed golf trips with classmates over the last decade and would welcome traveling with classmates. He can be reached at tguzzi4@gmail.com | 203-843-8811."},{"id":361,"n":"Daniel Gwynn","u":"Dan","g":"I2","p":"D3","ph":"(972) 345-4444","em":"danieljgwynn@gmail.com","tw":"Carrollton","st":"TX"},{"id":362,"n":"Michael Gwynn","u":"Michael","g":"D1","p":"I3","ph":"510-502-5059","em":"repointer@gmail.com","tw":"San Ramon","st":"CA"},{"id":363,"n":"Michele (Mahady) Haberlach","u":"Michele","g":"A4","p":"H3","em":"michele.haberlach@wsu.edu","tw":"Portland","st":"OR"},{"id":364,"n":"Darwin Haines","u":"Darwin","g":"D4","p":"B1","em":"darwinhaines@hotmail.com","tw":"Jersey City","st":"NJ"},{"id":365,"n":"Thomas Haislop","u":"Tater","g":"D2","p":"F3","ph":"864-324-4455","em":"thaislop@aol.com","tw":"Seneca","st":"SC","af":"150-Pound Football","ac":"Sporting events. He enjoys hiking, mountains, waterfalls, and general outdoor life. He and his fiancée Nancy love exploring the Carolinas and hosting visitors. He would welcome classmates coming to visit, reconnecting socially, and sharing trips or outdoor activities. He also enjoys travel, reunions, tailgates, and any gathering with strong class spirit.","w":"Tater Haislop Tater lives in Seneca, South Carolina. He has one daughter, Carmen, age twenty-one, who lives locally. She is high-functioning autistic, very outgoing, and central to his daily life. He speaks of her with pride and humor, describing their close relationship and frequent shared adventures. His wife Nancy. His plebe company was F3. His nickname \"Tater\" came when Steve Cummings declared he looked like Mr. Potato Head after seeing his shaved head and acne. He remembers the 150-pound football lifestyle of extreme weight cuts, and wild team trips where he and Ted Johnston once emptied a fire extinguisher in a hotel. Ranger School was a major shared hardship with classmates. His biggest highlight was completing the Venezuelan Ranger Course, earning the nickname \"Oso Polar,\" enduring live-fire training, swamp survival, and a divided class of Marxist and pro-U.S. officers that reflected regional tensions. He later served in Panama, Honduras, and Tiger Island, calling the real-world missions some of his best experiences. He left during the drawdown seeking a new direction. A move to California and a placement by classmate Scott Poirier launched him into chemical sales in Silicon Valley. He shifted into financial services with Dean Witter during the Netscape IPO era, building a career in a notoriously high-attrition field. After many roles, he now works independently within a mutual company, focusing on tax abatement and insurance, running his own practice, and traveling frequently to clients. He sees this decade as the window for Class of '86 to deepen its connections and is committed to helping make that happen. He can be reached at thaislop@aol.com | 864-324-4455."},{"id":366,"n":"Elaina (King) Hajduk","u":"Elaina","g":"F3","p":"E2","ph":"315-559-5012","em":"ehajduk5@gmail.com","tw":"Manlius","st":"NY","ac":"I would like to  travel and/or attend sports events with classmates.","w":"Elaina Hajduk Elaina lives in Manlius, New York. She and her husband Jeff have four adult children and one grandchild with a second on the way. Some of the best years of her life were at Giebelstadt Army Airfield outside of Wurzburg, Germany, where she started as a second lieutenant Huey platoon leader and became the Battalion S4. After the Army, she got a master's degree from Syracuse University and became a secondary mathematics teacher, teaching at the high school her kids attended for 22 years. She retired in June 2026. She married her classmate Jeff Hajduk and they have been married for 40 years as of June 21. She stays in regular contact with her West Point roommate Rhonda (Barush) Bright and teammate Jill (Spangler) Reilly. She met Jill on R-Day when she slipped down the stairs in Eisenhower Barracks and they both started laughing hysterically. She and Jeff are now retired and living near Charlotte, North Carolina. She travels and attends sports events. She can be reached at ehajduk5@gmail.com | 315-559-5012."},{"id":367,"n":"Jeffrey Hajduk","u":"Jeff","g":"F3","p":"B4","ph":"315-466-9523","em":"hajduk332@gmail.com","tw":"Manlius","st":"NY","ac":"I like to fish, hike and be on the water doing activities related to that","w":"Jeff Hajduk Jeff lives in Manlius, New York. He has one grandchild (girl) and one child in the Air Force Flight Surgeon based in the Charlotte area. He served in Europe (Würzburg), Fort Sill, and Fort Rucker. After the Army, he worked for several companies including Clarke American (Harland Clarke), Cooper Crouse Hinds (Eaton) twice, Amazon, and Pall Corp. He's been retired since June 2024 and currently substitute teaches at his wife's school. He and his wife are moving to Charlotte, North Carolina, in June 2026. He fishes, hikes, and does water-related activities. He can be reached at hajduk332@gmail.com | 315-466-9523."},{"id":368,"n":"Kathryn (O'Brien) Hall","u":"Kat","g":"I2","p":"E3","ph":"865-323-2309","em":"khall4books@gmail.com","tw":"Knoxville","st":"TN"},{"id":369,"n":"Kathryn Hall","u":"Kay","g":"C1","p":"C4","em":"kayrhall@icloud.com"},{"id":370,"n":"Rex Hall","u":"Rex","g":"E2","p":"F1","tw":"Peachtree City","st":"GA"},{"id":371,"n":"Charlotte (Callari) Hallengren","u":"Charlotte","g":"D2","p":"B1","tw":"Dulles","st":"VA"},{"id":372,"n":"John Halstead","u":"John","g":"C2","p":"G3","ph":"805-206-4950","em":"usma.uva@gmail.com","tw":"Simi Valley","st":"CA","ac":"Golfing, fly fishing, upland bird and duck hunting.","w":"John Halstead John retired to Simi Valley, California, where he and his wife, Melanie, welcomed their first grandchild in March 2025. Notably, their youngest of four children was the first to become a parent. Their eldest daughter, Autumn, serves as an Army reserve officer residing in Lee’s Summit, Missouri. The eldest son, Brandon, lives in San Diego, California. JJ, the youngest son, is a Navy reserve officer based on Bainbridge Island, Washington. Bridgette, the youngest daughter, also resides in Simi Valley. During his cadet years, John appreciated the winter season, particularly enjoying the snow and skiing as a cadet. He began in G-3 and graduated from C-2. Although initially intending to serve for only five years, John concluded his service as a Colonel after 25 years serving in Armor and Operations Research assignments. Following completion of a Doctorate in Systems and Information Engineering at the University of Virginia—supported by the U.S. Army—he returned to West Point as a Professor in Systems Engineering. After Army retirement, John’s first landing was with Rand Corporation as a Senior Research Fellow. He eventually ended his civilian career in Silicon Valley where he led many data science, ML/AI teams in marketing and compliance AI initiatives. He interests are golf and hanging out with granddaughter, Scarlette. For contact, please reach out via email: usma.uva@gmail.com | 805.206.4950."},{"id":373,"n":"James Hamby","u":"Jim","g":"F3","p":"A1","tw":"Hilton Head Island","st":"SC"},{"id":374,"n":"Michael Hanifan","u":"Mike","g":"E4","p":"F3","ph":"(775) 267-9348","em":"hanifanm@charter.net","tw":"Carson City","st":"NV"},{"id":375,"n":"Jeffrey Hanko","u":"Jeff","g":"A2","p":"I4","ph":"303-888-7174","em":"JeffaHanko@gmail.com","tw":"Shrewsbury","st":"VT","ac":"Since 1992, a group of classmates and I have gone to a NASCAR race every year. This year, we are headed to Daytona. Later in the year, we are trying a F1 race in Austin.","w":"Jeff Hanko Jeff lives in Shrewsbury, Vermont with his wife Gina. They have three cats and two dogs. No kids. Jeff was a plebe in I4 and graduated from A2. He remembers setting a water bomb trap on their door for their company CQ, but the duty officer, a captain, came instead. The captain got soaked, and Jeff, Hudock, and Rotella got in trouble. He served in Gulf War One. After the Army, he worked in manufacturing for 16 years before buying a business in 2007. He retired from the business in 2024 after selling it. He lived in Denver for 31 years until retiring in Vermont. Since 1992, a group of classmates and Jeff have gone to a NASCAR race every year. This year they are headed to Daytona. Later in the year, they are trying an F1 race in Austin. He can be reached at JeffaHanko@gmail.com | 303-888-7174."},{"id":376,"n":"Theodore Hanley","u":"Teddy","g":"I3","p":"D4","ph":"703-350-6456","em":"tedhanley@hotmail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":377,"n":"Christine Hansen","u":"Christine","g":"C3","p":"B2","em":"chansen508@yahoo.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":378,"n":"Craig Harlow","u":"Craig","g":"G4","p":"G1","em":"Craig_Harlow@andersonsinc.com","tw":"Bluffton","st":"OH"},{"id":379,"n":"David Harmon","u":"David","g":"H2","p":"E3","ph":"309-645-0849‬","em":"DAVIDHARMONFARM@aol.com","tw":"Brimfield","st":"IL"},{"id":380,"n":"John Harnois","u":"Johnny","g":"F3","p":"A4","ph":"508-333-1728","tw":"Warren","st":"RI"},{"id":381,"n":"Marc Harris","u":"Marc","g":"E4","p":"D1","ph":"407-670-5794","em":"marc_d_harris@post.harvard.edu","tw":"Moseley","st":"VA","ac":"Sporting events and tailgating","w":"Marc D. Harris Marc lives in Moseley, Virginia and has five children: his 29-year-old son teaches in Connecticut, his 18-year-old daughter attends Hampton University, his 16-year-old daughter is in high school, his 11-year-old son is in middle school, and his 8-year-old daughter is in elementary school.  Marc's plebe company was D1, graduating from E4. Marc commissioned into the Signal Corps.  A highlight of his career was serving as a Presidential Communications Officer at the White House during the September 11, 2001 attacks. Following his military service, he transitioned to corporate America, working at Amazon before starting his own company. His favorite role, however, was as a stay-at-home dad. These days Marc makes an annual pilgrimage to Disney and never gets bored. His favorite West Point memory involves the time Roger Knowles predicted 8 out of 10 TEE questions, and Chris Cole (along with all the other HPA cadets in the company) used his copy of Roger's crib notes to pass his exam after his calculator ran out, receiving max partial credit by copying the crib notes onto the TEE (wrong numbers and all). Marc reflects that the amount of talent and intelligence at the Academy was and remains truly remarkable. He can be reached at marc_d_harris@post.harvard.edu | 407-670-5794"},{"id":382,"n":"Patricia (Medina) Harris","u":"Patti","g":"C2","p":"D3","ph":"941-735-9042","em":"pattijcw@yahoo.com","tw":"Bradenton","st":"FL","ac":"She expressed enjoyment of travel, especially meaningful travel tied to history and place, shaped by years living overseas in Australia, Thailand, and the Philippines. She values relaxed social connection, reunions, and shared experiences rather than competitive activities, and spoke positively about cruises, road trips, and low-stress gatherings with classmates.","w":"Patti (Medina) Harris Patti lives in Florida's panhandle on a large rural property with her husband, focused on land stewardship and self-directed projects. She and her husband chose to leave the Army before starting a family, driven by a firm decision not to raise children while subject to deployments. She has two grown, independent sons, one born in Sydney, Australia during an expatriate assignment. Her plebe company was D3, graduating from C2. Her standout cadet memory is a Beast Barracks incident when her roommate Lisa Studa Baker accidentally drank from a cup containing contact lenses, temporarily leaving her unable to see. She served as a Signal Corps officer in Korea in a highly sensitive artillery detachment with a nuclear mission, managing top-secret communications materials and vaults as a junior lieutenant. She deployed with the 101st Airborne Division during Desert Storm as executive officer and logistics lead, including running a Thanksgiving mess operation in theater. After leaving active duty, she completed a master's degree in engineering technology and spent years overseas as an expatriate spouse in Australia, Thailand, and the Philippines before reentering the workforce as a science and engineering teacher. She later joined the University of Florida as part of an inaugural engineering extension and innovation office, coordinating workforce development, industry outreach, and K-12 engineering recruitment before retiring early. She and her husband now manage multiple real-estate holdings. She enjoys travel, especially meaningful travel tied to history and place shaped by years living overseas, cruises, road trips, and low-stress gatherings with classmates. She can be reached at pattijcw@yahoo.com | 941-735-9042."},{"id":383,"n":"David Hartley","u":"David","g":"H1","p":"B3","em":"david.hartley208@gmail.com","tw":"Owasso","st":"OK"},{"id":384,"n":"Robert Hartley","u":"Robert","g":"H3","p":"C4","ph":"(925) 606-7901","em":"robh52361@gmail.com","tw":"Livermore","st":"CA"},{"id":385,"n":"John Harwig","u":"John","g":"B2","p":"A4","ph":"512-944-5786","em":"harwigj@earthlink.net","tw":"Round Rock","st":"TX"},{"id":386,"n":"Warren Hauert","u":"Warren","g":"I1","p":"E2","ph":"(518) 884-9916","em":"whauert@outlook.com","tw":"Ballston Spa","st":"NY"},{"id":387,"n":"Keith Hauk","u":"Keith","g":"I1","p":"D2","ph":"(410) 988-5747","em":"keithhauk04@gmail.com","tw":"Ellicott City","st":"MD"},{"id":388,"n":"Michael Haydak","u":"Mick","g":"H2","p":"A4","em":"Mickhaydak@aol.com","ac":"He enjoys golf and regularly participates in golf outings connected to West Point, including the Army Football Club event. He is an active sports fan, holding season tickets for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and supporting local teams. He values reunions, small group gatherings, and staying connected through informal, technology-enabled meetups rather than large formal events."},{"id":389,"n":"William Hays","u":"Bill","g":"C4","p":"I1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":390,"n":"Robert Hazen","u":"Rob","g":"C3","p":"E2","tw":"Naperville","st":"IL"},{"id":391,"n":"Robert Healy","u":"Rob","g":"B3","p":"","em":"rhealy@lsquaredcap.com","tw":"Laguna Beach","st":"CA","ac":"Skiing, fishing","w":"Rob Healy Rob lives in Laguna Beach, California. He has three children, one married and one who graduated from West Point in 2024. As a cadet and remembers sliding in central area. He served at Fort Ord, Korea, and Panama. After leaving the Army, he went into private equity. Rob enjoys skiing and fishing. He can be reached at rhealy@lsquaredcap.com."},{"id":392,"n":"Lawrence Heckel","u":"Larry","g":"E2","p":"H1","ph":"(904) 262-5515","em":"lrheckel@gmail.com","tw":"Jacksonville","st":"FL"},{"id":393,"n":"Timothy Hein","u":"Tim","g":"A1","p":"B3","ph":"360-991-6300","em":"cthein89@comcast.net","tw":"Camas","st":"WA","ac":"Skiing, travel, cycling, hiking","w":"Timothy Hein Tim lives in Camas, Washington, with two sons. Zach, 29, lives in Seattle and works as an R&D development engineer with Meta; he's marrying Meg Price on September 12, 2026. Riley, 29, lives in Vancouver, Washington, and works as a Clinical Specialist with Medtronic's TAVR cardiovascular division after serving four years as an active-duty armor officer with 1st Cav. He served at Fort Lewis (now Joint Base Lewis-McChord) for five years, with his last assignment as Company Commander of HHC USAG. After the Army, he worked in medical device sales for 30 years and currently serves as VP of Sales and Marketing with Synergy Spine Solutions. He skis, travels, cycles, and hikes. He can be reached at cthein89@comcast.net | 360-991-6300."},{"id":394,"n":"Joseph Helmick","u":"Joe","g":"B4","p":"D3","ph":"720-215-7748","em":"joe.helmick@proton.me","tw":"Florence","st":"AL","w":"Joe Helmick Joe  lives in Florence, Alabama. No children. He served in West Germany as platoon leader, community adjutant, and aide de camp. After resigning, he's been doing software development. He started three companies, worked in Corporate America, and now does contract software development. He can be reached at joe.helmick@proton.me | 720-215-7748."},{"id":395,"n":"Michael Henderson","u":"Michael","g":"C4","p":"D2","em":"mahendo64@yahoo.com","tw":"Dresher","st":"PA"},{"id":396,"n":"Alan Hendricks","u":"Alan","g":"D3","p":"B4","ph":"571-447-3938","em":"hendricksemail@yahoo.com","tw":"Osada","st":"MI","ac":"Alan enjoys backcountry backpacking (taking only a hammock, no tent), cruising on the lake in his pontoon boat, traveling/sightseeing (including a 5-month, border-to-border and coast-to-coast trip this year across the US), and just hanging out on the deck with a bourbon and cigar.","w":"Alan Hendricks Alan lives in Oscoda, Michigan, with his wife Gina, whom he married in 2000. They adopted Talia, who recently graduated from college and now works as an adoption caseworker. He has two children from a previous marriage: Robert, a high school teacher and administrator with two sons, and Erin, a speech pathologist expecting to deliver another grandson in May. His favorite cadet memory involves white-over-white, knitting needles, kazoos, and the theme from 2001: A Space Odyssey, enough said. A close second involves wheelchair races in Newark Airport; if curious, ask him at the reunion. His Army career began with the 82nd Airborne Division, where he deployed on Golden Pheasant, Just Cause, and Desert Shield/Desert Storm, and commanded the Advanced Airborne School at Fort Bragg. He then branch-transferred to Military Intelligence, spent two years in Korea managing intel information systems, and five years at the National Reconnaissance Office extending national-level intel to the warfighter. Following the post-Cold War RIF, he transitioned to the Army Reserve, where he commanded the last remaining ground-based HF jamming unit in the Army, served as a Defense Foreign Liaison Officer and CGSC instructor, established a special intel unit supporting the National Media Exploitation Center, and deployed with a 10-man Military Transition Team embedded with an Iraqi Army brigade during Operation Iraqi Freedom, experiencing more combat than his previous three deployments combined. He retired in 2009 as a Senior Intelligence Officer at the Defense Intelligence Agency. Simultaneously, Alan built a cybersecurity executive career, holding leadership roles at Netigy, Northrop Grumman, SRA International, and McAfee, culminating as Senior Director of Cybersecurity at DMI, while teaching cybersecurity as an adjunct professor at George Washington University for four to five years. In 2024, he returned all his badges, bought a lake house, and retired from civilian life as well. Current pursuits include backcountry backpacking with only a hammock, cruising his pontoon boat, traveling, including a five-month border-to-border, coast-to-coast trip this year, and hanging out on the deck with a bourbon and cigar. He makes much of his own backpacking gear, excels at pinochle, is a Maker's Mark Ambassador, and may be the only person to have gained tangible financial benefit from plebe poop, winning concert tickets by correctly identifying on a radio call-in show that the U.S. Silver Depository is located at West Point. Alan can be reached at hendricksemail@yahoo.com | 571-447-3938."},{"id":397,"n":"Edwin Hendricks","u":"Ed","g":"B3","p":"C4","ph":"408-667-6316","em":"ed.hendricks@gmail.com","tw":"Tacoma","st":"WA"},{"id":398,"n":"William Hensley","u":"William","g":"G3","p":"D4","em":"bill.hensley.ccg@gmail.com","tw":"Aurora","st":"CO"},{"id":399,"n":"James Herron","u":"James","g":"C1","p":"A3"},{"id":400,"n":"Amanda (Wade) Hiatt","u":"Amanda","g":"F4","p":"G1","ph":"(703) 498-8466","em":"dahiatt@earthlink.net","tw":"Springfield","st":"KY"},{"id":401,"n":"Graydon Hicks","u":"Graydon","g":"A1","p":"D3","ph":"432-249-0154","em":"gwhicks3@gmail.com","tw":"Fort Davis","st":"TX","ac":"Fishing, traveling, attending sporting events, visiting","w":"Graydon Hicks Graydon lives in Fort Davis, Texas. His oldest son works for Texas Parks and Wildlife in San Antonio, his youngest son has a motorcycle repair shop in Waco, his oldest daughter lives in Hutto and is engaged, and his youngest daughter works as a pharmacist at the hospital in Alpine. He has a grandson in seventh grade.His favorite assignment was Fort Carson with the 2-7 Cav as A Troop FSO. After the Army, he worked in an iron foundry making valve bodies and automotive parts, followed by the residential furniture industry, then moved into public education as a teacher, principal, and superintendent. He owned a gun shop for two years, sold it to another shop in an adjacent town, and now helps run that business. He currently helps a private Christian school with operations and grant writing.He fishes, travels, attends sporting events, and visits family. He can be reached at gwhicks3@gmail.com | 432-249-0154."},{"id":402,"n":"Michael Higginbottom","u":"Mike","g":"F3","p":"B2","ph":"913-702-6947","em":"mike.higginbottom@hotmail.com","tw":"Leavenworth","st":"KS","w":"Mike Higginbottom Mike and his wife Cathy live in Leavenworth, Kansas, approaching their 40th anniversary. They have two sons. Patrick was born in 1987 at Fort Carson, graduated from West Point in 2010, and served six years as a field artillery officer including a deployment to Kandahar Province with 1/25 IN (Stryker). He's now an ICU nurse in Leavenworth. Brendan was born in 1992 at Fort Bliss, graduated from the University of Kansas and UC Davis, and lives in Minneapolis. Mike served 28 years in armor and cavalry positions with the 4th and 24th Infantry Divisions, 1st and 2nd Armored Divisions, and 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment, plus staff and advisory assignments with TRADOC, Multi-National Security Transition Command-Iraq, and US Army Europe. He deployed to the Middle East with 3rd ACR during Desert Shield/Storm and Operation Intrinsic Action, to Macedonia/Kosovo with 1st AD during KFOR, and to Baghdad with MNSTC-I. He and Cathy were stationed at 18 different posts across the US and Germany. When the Army reassigned him to Fort Leavenworth in 2011 following a tour as Chief of Staff, 7th Army Training Command in Grafenwoehr, they bought a home in the city and Cathy declared she wasn't moving again. His final position was TRADOC Capability Manager-Mission Command, retiring as a colonel on July 1, 2014. After retirement he worked as a military analyst with Booz Allen before being hired by the Department of the Army in 2016 as a supervisory training analyst with the Combined Arms Center-Training. He retired from federal service October 1, 2025. Mike rides and cleans his motorcycles, reads, and tries to stay calm watching the national news. Cathy reads, gardens, and rides as a passenger with Mike. Both do strength training, biking, walking, and yoga. To celebrate their 40th anniversary, they're traveling to Vienna in July for several days before linking up with a motorcycle tour group in Bratislava for a 10-day ride across multiple countries. He can be reached at mike.higginbottom@hotmail.com | 913-702-6947."},{"id":403,"n":"Richard Higley","u":"Richard","g":"D3","p":"D4","ph":"(281) 361-4567","em":"rick.higley@lubrizol.com","tw":"Pointblank","st":"TX"},{"id":404,"n":"Lloyd Hill","u":"Jeff","g":"G3","p":"A1","em":"l_jhill@yahoo.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":405,"n":"Matthew Hinkle","u":"Matt","g":"A1","p":"E2","ph":"616-291-2521","em":"mshinkle@me.com","tw":"Harrisonburg","st":"VA"},{"id":406,"n":"Stephen Hitz","u":"Stephen","g":"G2","p":"G4","ph":"703-498-0698","em":"sjhitz@gmail.com","tw":"Boulder","st":"CO"},{"id":407,"n":"John Hluck","u":"John","g":"C4","p":"A2","em":"jhluck@mac.com","tw":"Charlotte","st":"NC"},{"id":408,"n":"Ronald Hocker","u":"Ronald","g":"H3","p":"H2","tw":"Davenport","st":"IA"},{"id":409,"n":"Joel Hodge","u":"Joe","g":"A4","p":"F2","ph":"541-922-7580","em":"joehodge4@charter.net","tw":"Hermiston","st":"OR","af":"Cross Country","ac":"Attending sporting event.","w":"Joel Hodge Joe lives in Hermiston, Oregon. He has two sons: Peter, 35, and Michael, 31, both living in Spokane. No grandchildren. His best assignment was Aschaffenburg, Germany from November 1986 through December 1989. Desert Storm was his most challenging and interesting assignment. After the Army, he worked nine months at Kaiser Aluminum in Spokane, then 20 years with Walmart Transportation in Hermiston as an operations manager in a transportation office. He's now retired. He runs three to four miles each morning and in summer runs weekdays with the high school cross country team of 20 to 25 kids and two coaches. He became a master gardener eight years ago and grows vegetables and herbs. And he I reads storybooks to preschool kids a few times each month during the school year.He attends sporting events. He can be reached at joehodge4@charter.net | 541-922-7580."},{"id":410,"n":"Thomas Hoenstine","u":"Tom","g":"I3","p":"I3","ph":"770-846-6274","tw":"Kennesaw","st":"GA"},{"id":411,"n":"Jud Hoff","u":"Jud","g":"C2","p":"B3","ph":"269-207-1268","em":"judhoff123@yahoo.com","tw":"Portage","st":"MI","ac":"Sporting events, Rock Concerts, Dinner","w":"Jud Hoff Jud lives in Hilton Head Island, South Carolina. He has four children: a married daughter with two kids in Michigan; a son (USMA 2014) who is married with two kids in Chicago; an engaged son in North Carolina; and a daughter in grad school in South Carolina. His plebe company was B3, graduating from C2. He completed Flight School (UH60) and served at Fort Lewis with 2-9 Aviation, Honduras, and fighting forest fires in Yellowstone. After the Army, he spent 26 years with Stryker Corporation in various division and corporate leadership roles, retiring in 2016. Since retirement he started two nonprofits, serves as angel investor for seven entities (leading two), and holds multiple board positions for nonprofits and for-profits. He's an avid pickleball player and weightlifter, a consummate researcher about health, fitness, and cancer treatment who has developed protocols for cancer treatment, and is developing expertise in blockchain quantum security. He enjoys sporting events and rock concerts. He can be reached at judhoff123@yahoo.com | 269-207-1268."},{"id":412,"n":"Daniel Hokanson","u":"Dan","g":"C1","p":"","ph":"503-602-6000","em":"dannyandkelly1990@gmail.com","tw":"Fort McNair","st":"DC"},{"id":413,"n":"John Holley","u":"Dow","g":"D3","p":"F2","ph":"646-420-5792","em":"dowholley1@gmail.com","tw":"New York City","st":"NY","ac":"Junking","w":"Dow Holley Dow lives in New York City, New York. Dow remembers going to ask Ulrich a question, and Randy, Brian, Pompeo and some others might be discussing sports. Go in another day and the topic was poly-sci, another time national security. During COVID he realized he was a witness to guys planning the world 35 years before taking over. He served with 3rd Armored Division in Friedberg (Ray Barracks, Elvis's post), Bad Nauheim, and Frankfurt. After the Army, he worked in media planning/buying, including work with 7-Eleven (Joe & Larry Hughs), and in between. Dow enjoys junking. He can be reached at dowholley1@gmail.com | 646-420-5792."},{"id":414,"n":"Guy Holliday","u":"Doc","g":"E3","p":"D4","ph":"(732) 558-4090","em":"docguyh@gmail.com","tw":"Columbus","st":"NJ"},{"id":415,"n":"Thomas Hood","u":"Tom","g":"A1","p":"D2","ph":"901-265-0933","em":"thood86@gmail.com","tw":"Memphis","st":"TN","ac":"Golf, skiing, travel, hiking","w":"Tom Hood Tom lives in Memphis, Tennessee, where he stays active in the outdoors and on the golf course. His interests include golf, skiing, travel, and hiking. Tom can be reached at 901-265-0933 and thood86@gmail.com."},{"id":416,"n":"Michael Hoskinson","u":"Mike","g":"G2","p":"B3","ph":"(703) 860-8696","em":"BlackKnight86@gmail.com","tw":"Reston","st":"VA","w":"Mike Hoskison Mike lives in Reston, VA. He is married with one child. He works as a defense contractor. He can be reached at BlackKnight86@gmail.com | (703) 860-8696."},{"id":417,"n":"Paul Houge","u":"Paul","g":"A2","p":"H1","ph":"(719) 200-3161","em":"paulhouge@yahoo.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":418,"n":"Christopher Houseman","u":"Christopher","g":"I4","p":"A3","ph":"(269) 857-4273","tw":"Holland","st":"MI"},{"id":419,"n":"David Houston","u":"Dave","g":"D3","p":"H2","ph":"770-855-4783","em":"houstondave86@gmail.com","tw":"Peachtree City","st":"GA","af":"Parachute Team","ac":"Golf, travel, Army Football","w":"David Houston Dave lives in Peachtree City with Anne, his wife since 1988. They have three married children—Katie, Emily, and Garrett—and four granddaughters. His son Garrett graduated from West Point in 2020 and went Engineers. His brother Mark '95 has a son who was drafted by the Minnesota Twins in the first round of the 2025 MLB Draft. David served at Fort Benning and Fort Campbell, with his most notable assignment in Operation Desert Storm with the 101st Airborne Division. After the Army, he moved into manufacturing and then consulting, working with various clients and running into a few classmates along the way. He plays golf, travels, and follows Army football. His most memorable West Point experience was jumping with the Parachute Team and Spring Break 1986. He can be reached at houstondave86@gmail.com | 770-855-4783."},{"id":420,"n":"Frederica (Smith) Houston","u":"Frederica","g":"H1","p":"F4","ph":"(615) 361-0144","em":"khous78539@aol.com","tw":"Antioch","st":"TN"},{"id":421,"n":"James Howard","u":"Jim","g":"C3","p":"E1","ph":"254-319-0211","em":"borkenkat@yahoo.com","tw":"Harker Heights","st":"TX"},{"id":422,"n":"Joe Howard","u":"Joe","g":"C1","p":"","tw":"West Jefferson","st":"NC"},{"id":423,"n":"Patrick Hoyes","u":"Pat","g":"I2","p":"H3","em":"pat_moondog@hotmail.com","tw":"Basehor","st":"KS"},{"id":424,"n":"James Hoyt","u":"Ted","g":"A4","p":"C1","em":"jhoyt@hoytlegalllc.com","tw":"Hopkinton","st":"MA","ac":"None.  I hate all my living classmates.","w":"Ted Hoyt Ted lives in Hopkinton, Massachusetts. He is married with three children and no grandchildren yet. His daughter Ellora graduated in 2025 from UMass Amherst Honors College with a dual major in Microbiology and Organic Chemistry and currently works as a tech marketing consultant. His son Jack is a junior at Norwich University in Vermont studying geology and is in the Corps of Cadets but has not contracted with the military yet. His son Ryan is a freshman at Roger Williams University studying criminal justice. Ted remembers Wayne Locklin saving him from beatings and swirlies at the hands of the cows. During his Army service, he was sent twice for a month at a time to Russia as OIC when the Soviet Union was collapsing, he doesn't remember or won't tell much about those trips, but he did receive a letter of reprimand to help him remember. After the Army, he spent a year riding a Harley until drawdown money was gone, then went to law school courtesy of the VA and now practices law. He can be reached at jhoyt@hoytlegalllc.com."},{"id":425,"n":"James Hradecky","u":"Jim","g":"F2","p":"F4","ph":"603-540-6564","em":"jhradecky86@gmail.com","tw":"Peterborough","st":"NH","ac":"Golf, Travel, Attending Sporting Events, Getting together for dinners","w":"Jim and his wife Joan live in Peterborough, New Hampshire. Their son Joey is hoping to join the West Point Class of '27, and their daughter Ellie is at Hofstra, Class of '28. Jim served twice with the 82nd Airborne Field Artillery, jumping out of planes and enjoying the crazy pace. He also served in Germany. He got out in '93 and started in medical sales, rising through management ranks before starting several medical home service and billing companies. He sold three of the four companies. The most interesting was a post-op ortho service company where he navigated billing denials effectively, took care of his employees well, and got bought out when he wanted to retire by the company he started. Neil Costello was his President and COO, now CEO. Darryl MacDonald worked in sales with them for six years. Tony Guzzi's son, now Dr. John Guzzi, worked as a service rep during his undergrad. Jim remembers Ring Weekend get-togethers, all the home football games, and trying to study for finals, usually with Darryl MacDonald. He plays golf, travels, attends sporting events, and gets together for dinners. He can be reached at jhradecky86@gmail.com | 603-540-6564."},{"id":426,"n":"David Hudock","u":"David","g":"A2","p":"B1","em":"dhudock@verizon.net","tw":"Bridgeville","st":"PA"},{"id":427,"n":"Kevin Huggins","u":"Kevin","g":"I1","p":"B3","tw":"Mechanicsburg","st":"PA"},{"id":428,"n":"Lawrence Hughes","u":"Lawrence","g":"E4","p":"C2","ph":"214-478-3485","em":"tyhughes@gmail.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX"},{"id":429,"n":"Wendell Hull","u":"Wendell","g":"D1","p":"A4","ph":"(513) 769-7133","em":"wendell@fuse.net","tw":"Cincinnati","st":"OH"},{"id":430,"n":"Paul Humphreys","u":"Paul","g":"B4","p":"","ph":"706-575-4339","em":"paul.humphreys@hotmail.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":431,"n":"Kristopher Hurst","u":"Kris","g":"H1","p":"G3","ph":"916-557-7445","tw":"Napa","st":"CA"},{"id":432,"n":"Andrew Hutchinson","u":"Andrew","g":"E4","p":"C2","em":"andrewfhutchinson@me.com","tw":"Hershey","st":"PA"},{"id":433,"n":"Anthony Hylton","u":"Tony","g":"C1","p":"I3","ph":"(513) 469-0317","em":"hylton86@aol.com","tw":"Bentonville","st":"AR"},{"id":434,"n":"Matthew Igel","u":"Matt","g":"F4","p":"I2","ph":"408-368-4193","em":"mwigel@yahoo.com","tw":"Morgan Hill","st":"CA"},{"id":435,"n":"Damon Igou","u":"Damon","g":"C4","p":"E2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":436,"n":"Peter Inokoji-Kim","u":"Peter","g":"I4","p":"F3","ph":"916-628-1713","em":"inokoji@hotmail.com","tw":"Orcas Island","st":"WA","w":"Peter Inokoji-Kim Peter lives on Orcas Island, Washington. After the Army, he became a high school math and chemistry teacher. He can be reached at inokoji@hotmail.com | 916-628-1713."},{"id":437,"n":"Lewis Irwin","u":"Lew","g":"F4","p":"C2","ph":"724-263-9412","em":"lew.irwin@verizon.net","tw":"Pittsburgh","st":"PA","ac":"Army football games, etc.","w":"Lew Irwin Lew lives in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. He has three kids, including Mary (USMA '12), Eva, and Andrew (USMA '16). Lew has too many cadet memories to recount. He completed 34½ years of service, finishing dual-hatted as the Commandant of the Joint Forces Staff College in Norfolk, Virginia and in the J-7 on the Joint Staff at the Pentagon. He had many commands over the years and combat tours in Desert Storm and Afghanistan. Lew enjoys Army football games and similar events. He can be reached at lew.irwin@verizon.net | 724-263-9412."},{"id":438,"n":"Mark Iverson","u":"Mark","g":"G3","p":"E1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":439,"n":"Darin Jackson","u":"Darin","g":"E1","p":"D4","tw":"Forest","st":"VA"},{"id":440,"n":"Thurman Jackson","u":"Thurman","g":"I2","p":"A1","em":"samfaithincolor@aol.com","tw":"Monaca","st":"PA"},{"id":441,"n":"David Jacoppo","u":"David","g":"G3","p":"C1","ph":"(770) 973-9175","em":"goarmy1@bellsouth.net","tw":"Marietta","st":"GA"},{"id":442,"n":"Terry James","u":"Terry","g":"G1","p":"A3","ph":"919-609-9759","em":"tmjames86@gmail.com","tw":"Holly Springs","st":"NC","af":"Baseball","ac":"golf, sporting events, especially baseball and college football","w":"Terry James resides in Holly Springs, North Carolina, where he works in sales. Contact information includes 919-609-9759 and tmjames86@gmail.com. He described himself as a cadet as “a regular guy that loves God, family, and country,” and his cadet highlight was walking on and earning a place on the Army baseball team, reflecting persistence and commitment. His most significant Army assignments included serving as an AOC at Fort Knox and with 3/37 Armor Battalion at Fort Riley from 1986 to 1991, roles notable for line-unit responsibility and operational tempo during his early officer years. After military service, he transitioned into a civilian sales career, where he has continued professionally to the present. His current interests include golf and attending sporting events, with particular enthusiasm for baseball and college football. Terry and his wife Susan are currently living in Myrtle Beach, SC and have two sons."},{"id":443,"n":"Jose Jarque","u":"Rene","g":"C2","p":"A1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":444,"n":"Dawn (Thomas) Jeffries","u":"Dawn","g":"F1","p":"C4","tw":"Harrisonburg","st":"VA"},{"id":445,"n":"Howard Jeffries","u":"Howard","g":"H3","p":"D2","tw":"Harrisonburg","st":"VA"},{"id":446,"n":"James Jenkins","u":"Jimmy","g":"H1","p":"B2","ph":"915-525-5473","em":"Jenkinsjimmy9@gmail.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL","ac":"I'd love to do anything!  Like many of you, we, H-1 Hawgs, get together often.  I enjoy golfing, hunting, fishing, water and snow skiing, drinking games, etc."},{"id":447,"n":"Donald Johantges","u":"Donald","g":"B2","p":"B4","ph":"(540) 931-6294","em":"ps361@hotmail.com","tw":"Liberty Township","st":"OH"},{"id":448,"n":"Beverly Johnson","u":"Beverly","g":"F1","p":"B2","em":"bjohnson@teachthem2fish.net","tw":"Plano","st":"TX"},{"id":449,"n":"David Johnson","u":"David","g":"B4","p":"I2","ph":"720-435-2831","em":"djohnson9496@gmail.com","tw":"Effort","st":"PA"},{"id":450,"n":"James Johnson","u":"James","g":"H3","p":"F1","ph":"(941) 799-9180","em":"jhjohnson3@gmail.com","tw":"University Park","st":"FL"},{"id":451,"n":"Lynn (McNames) Johnson","u":"Lynn","g":"B4","p":"F2","ph":"210-492-1935","em":"LMJohnson57@gmail.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":452,"n":"Mark Johnson","u":"Mark","g":"G2","p":"F3","ph":"307-315-1130","em":"acbrof@gmail.com","tw":"Casper","st":"WY","ac":"Enjoy traveling the world, backpacking in the Rockies during the summer, and snowshoeing in the winter.","w":"Mark Johnson Mark lives in Casper, WY. He met his wife Elyse while an ROTC instructor at the University of Wyoming. Their daughter Brittany is a grad student in Texas and a Signal Corps warrant officer in the Wyoming Army National Guard. Their son Spencer is an Airborne-Infantry sergeant on active duty in the 11th Airborne Division. He started out in Germany with the 3d ID, then the 101st Airborne, and finished his RA career at the University of Wyoming as an ROTC instructor before transitioning to the USAR. He worked for Andersen Consulting in Atlanta for a couple of years while commanding a military history detachment, then came back on active duty through the AGR program in 1999: brigade ops officer in USAREC, APMS at Siena College, brigade XO in First Army, and finished as PMS at the University of Wisconsin-La Crosse. He retired in 2012 as an O-5, then served as branch historian of the U.S. Army Chaplain Corps at Fort Jackson for three years. He moved back to Wyoming in 2015 as adjunct professor of history at UW in Laramie, Civilian Aide to the Secretary of the Army for Wyoming, and state coordinator of the West Point Field Force. He got into secondary education as a high school administrative manager, then in 2022 took over the school's Army JROTC program—likely among the last of the class still wearing a uniform to work every day. He knocked out a masters and doctorate in history while on active duty and has a contract with Wyoming to write a two-volume history of the Wyoming National Guard. The first volume, \"Cowboy Soldiers,\" releases in March 2026. His first book was \"That Body of Brave Men: The U.S. Regular Infantry and the Civil War in the West.\" He enjoys traveling the world, backpacking in the Rockies during the summer, and snowshoeing in the winter. He can be reached at acbrof@gmail.com | 307-315-1130."},{"id":453,"n":"Marybel (Huston) Johnson","u":"Mary","g":"B3","p":"G4","ph":"(302) 535-6872","tw":"Dover","st":"DE"},{"id":454,"n":"Royce Johnson","u":"Royce","g":"H4","p":"H2","ph":"920-227-8501","em":"Royce.johnson5@gmail.com","tw":"Clermont","st":"FL","ac":"Pickleball, skiing, college football, Pokemon Go (don't knock it or judge I've met many wonderful friends playing)."},{"id":455,"n":"Howard Johnston","u":"Howard","g":"I2","p":"G4","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":456,"n":"Ted Johnston","u":"Ted","g":"D1","p":"G3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":457,"n":"Douglas Jones","u":"Douglas","g":"B1","p":"G4","ph":"(920) 430-2874","em":"dsj_wi@yahoo.com","tw":"Green Bay","st":"WI"},{"id":458,"n":"Jack Jones","u":"Jack","g":"G4","p":"E2","em":"otpcommish@gmail.com","tw":"Tulsa","st":"OK"},{"id":459,"n":"Jeffrey Jones","u":"Jeffrey","g":"G2","p":"B4","ph":"913-300-1834","em":"dadpad3@embarqmail.com","tw":"Vass","st":"NC"},{"id":460,"n":"Wade Jost","u":"Wade","g":"B4","p":"I1","ph":"253-509-2013","em":"wade@640-acres.com","tw":"Gig Harbor","st":"WA"},{"id":461,"n":"Eric Judkins","u":"Eric","g":"E2","p":"I1","em":"ejudkins@aol.com","tw":"Albuquerque","st":"NM"},{"id":462,"n":"Stephen Kaczmarek","u":"Steve","g":"D3","p":"E1","em":"skaczmarek64@outlook.com","tw":"Winter Garden","st":"FL"},{"id":463,"n":"Paul Kapsner","u":"Paul","g":"B3","p":"A1","ph":"952-470-2363","em":"kapsnerpaul@gmail.com","tw":"Excelsior","st":"MN"},{"id":464,"n":"William Kearney","u":"Bill","g":"H2","p":"A4","tw":"Southern Pines","st":"NC"},{"id":465,"n":"Barry Kellar","u":"Barry","g":"A4","p":"B3","ph":"270-348-2916","em":"barrykellar1@gmail.com","tw":"Clarksville","st":"TN","ac":"travel, scuba, sporting events.  Golf, if I drive the cart.","w":"Barry Kellar Barry lives in Clarksville, Tennessee. He is still married to his high school sweetheart Allison. They have no children but have dogs, cats, nephews, and nieces—they like the dogs more. Barry was a plebe in B3 and graduated from A4. He remembers Fred Manzo holding a hat outside the barracks 6th floor window, threatening Wayne Locklin he would drop the hat if Wayne took one more step toward him. Wayne did, the hat was dropped. Wayne informed Fred it was Pete Kuring's hat. He served at Fort Stewart with the 24th Mechanized Infantry Division and briefed General Schwarzkopf. After the Army, he worked at GE for 10 years, with his last position running a global team for GE Plastics as global director. He then moved to filtration with Freudenberg (German HQ entity) as CEO North America and global VP, retiring in 2022. He came out of retirement as CEO for HOMAG Americas, which he considers his best role—great industry and customers in the wood industry with a great company. Barry enjoys travel, scuba, sporting events, and golf if he drives the cart. He can be reached at barrykellar1@gmail.com | 270-348-2916."},{"id":466,"n":"Richard Kellar","u":"Rick","g":"C1","p":"I4","ph":"330-283-1086","em":"rkellar@pegsfoundation.org","tw":"Tallmadge","st":"OH","ac":"sport and socializing - activities are just the medium to connect, so anything that maximizes that opportunity","w":"Rick (“Gus”) lives in Tallmadge, Ohio. He's married to Sherry and has two married daughters, Sophia and Emma, each with one child—grandchildren Reagan Jane Lowery (26 months) and Oliver Douglas Skrapics (3 weeks). His plebe company was I4, graduating from C1. He served in the Infantry and Special Forces including two years on an SF A-Team (ODA-SCUBA). He retired in 2014 having served his final 14 years in a JSOC Special Mission Unit. His most vivid cadet memory is being on the Apron for the longest July 4th celebration, thinking \"OMG, does every state have a flower, bird, and motto?\" After the Army, he became CEO of a philanthropic grantmaker based in Ohio. He's more \"user friendly\" now and still rides a Harley. His activities focus on sport and socializing, viewing activities as the medium to connect with the many friends he wonders if he deserves. He can be reached at rkellar@pegsfoundation.org | 330-283-1086."},{"id":467,"n":"Philip Keller","u":"Philip","g":"H2","p":"D1","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"GA"},{"id":468,"n":"John Kelley","u":"John","g":"F1","p":"B4","ph":"(757) 227-5880","tw":"Pflugerville","st":"TX"},{"id":469,"n":"Paul Kelley","u":"Paul","g":"G2","p":"C4","ph":"425-577-2257","em":"pknwb3@hotmail.com","tw":"Mercer Island","st":"WA","ac":"Paul would enjoy connecting with classmates through rugby reminiscing, sports events, and travel. He lives on Mercer Island in Washington and has a strong appreciation for the outdoors and camaraderie. With a background in competitive rugby and a career that involved global assignments, he’s well-suited for adventurous or social activities involving classmates.","w":"Paul Kelley PK lives on Mercer Island, Washington. He has two adult children living near him in the Seattle area. His 25-year-old son works in human resources as a benefits specialist, and his 23-year-old daughter is a communications manager for a nonprofit. His military highlight was jumping into Panama as a rifle platoon leader with the 2nd Ranger Battalion. Later, in civil affairs with the 96th CA Battalion, he supported missions in the Pacific, including one on Wake Island managing the return of Chinese migrants. He retired from the Army in 2006 as a lieutenant colonel—the first in the class to do so by date—and immediately joined Boeing as a strategy analyst on the defense side. His work focused on Army programs like the Future Combat Systems. He hails from Quincy, Massachusetts, and was inspired to attend West Point after a neighborhood connection to future Army Chief of Staff Jim McConville. He studied Math, Science & Engineering. He enjoys rugby reminiscing, sports events, and travel. He can be reached at pknwb3@hotmail.com | 425-577-2257."},{"id":470,"n":"Thomas Kelley","u":"Thomas","g":"E1","p":"A4","tw":"Winchester","st":"VA"},{"id":471,"n":"Timothy Kelley","u":"Timothy","g":"E3","p":"C1","tw":"Liverpool","st":"NY"},{"id":472,"n":"Kevin Kelly","u":"Kevin","g":"E1","p":"I4","ph":"301-659-3325","em":"kelly6pack@comcast.net","tw":"Spotsylvania","st":"VA"},{"id":473,"n":"David Kemp","u":"David","g":"C4","p":"H3"},{"id":474,"n":"Sean Kenna","u":"Sean","g":"H3","p":"A2","ph":"904-903-8757","em":"sean_kenna@yahoo.com","tw":"Fernandina Beach","st":"FL"},{"id":475,"n":"Frank Kennedy","u":"Frank","g":"A2","p":"B4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":476,"n":"Dennis Kibby","u":"Dennis","g":"E4","p":"C3"},{"id":477,"n":"Richard Kidd","u":"Rich","g":"F4","p":"D2","ph":"703-772-2890","em":"kiddri4@gmail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA","ac":"food and wine, hiking,","w":"Richard Kidd Rich lives in Alexandria with his wife of nearly 30 years. Their son is a junior at West Point in the Class of 2027.After a short uniformed career that included time at Fort Lewis, Richard left the Army for graduate school and spent seven years with the UN. He returned to public service and served as an SES across four federal agencies and the White House. His final assignment oversaw all energy and environmental policy issues for DoD. He's interested in food and wine, hiking, and stays connected to his F4 friends and their shared antics from cadet days. He can be reached at kiddri4@gmail.com | 703-772-2890."},{"id":478,"n":"Verner Kiernan","u":"Verner","g":"I4","p":"","em":"kiernan@mindspring.com","tw":"Orlando","st":"FL"},{"id":479,"n":"Richard Killian","u":"Richard","g":"G4","p":"I1","em":"rickillian86@gmail.com","tw":"Fort Leavenworth","st":"KS"},{"id":480,"n":"David Kilpatrick","u":"David","g":"F3","p":"E4","ph":"410-519-6484","em":"beatnavy86@hotmail.com","tw":"Severn","st":"MD"},{"id":481,"n":"Patrick Kilroy","u":"Pat","g":"B4","p":"G2","ph":"503-536-5297","em":"pkilroy86@gmail.com","tw":"Boise","st":"ID"},{"id":482,"n":"James Kim","u":"James","g":"E2","p":"","em":"jkim2106@comcast.net","tw":"Aledo","st":"TX"},{"id":483,"n":"Kevin Kimzey","u":"Kevin","g":"D1","p":"E2","ph":"(610) 662-6629","em":"kkimzey@aol.com","tw":"Ardmore","st":"PA"},{"id":484,"n":"Mary Kinder","u":"Mary","g":"C1","p":"F2","em":"brandtkinder@gmail.com","tw":"Huntsville","st":"AL"},{"id":485,"n":"William King","u":"William","g":"B1","p":"","ph":"(781) 237-3047","em":"pk.shakamar@gmail.com","tw":"Wellesley","st":"MA"},{"id":486,"n":"Walter Kleinfelder","u":"Flip","g":"H1","p":"A3","ph":"571-239-2349","em":"flip.kleinfelder@gmail.com","tw":"Bristow","st":"VA","ac":"Skiing, traveling, attending football and hockey games. I enjoy golf, also, but if anyone asks what my handicap is, it's that I play golf!"},{"id":487,"n":"Robert Kleinhample","u":"Bob","g":"D3","p":"E4","ph":"757-325-0014","em":"bob.kleinhample@gmail.com","tw":"Williamsburg","st":"VA","ac":"Golf","w":"Robert Kleinhample Bob lives in Williamsburg, Virginia. He has two children: Sarah, who lives in Chicago, and Julia, who lives in San Diego. His plebe company was E4, graduating from D3. His most interesting assignment was his first, the 7th Infantry Division in Monterey, California. They deployed to remove Noriega during Operation Just Cause. They trained hard and lived in a beautiful place to enjoy time off. His wife Rebecca also worked at Pebble Beach, so he was able to golf often there. He retired from the Army in 2006, and his last job was managing Army modeling and simulation for experimentation. He then joined SAIC and continued the modeling and simulation career. He continues in this career today as a consultant helping companies grow in the modeling and simulation market. He enjoys golf and follows the resurgence of Army football. He can be reached at bob.kleinhample@gmail.com | 757-325-0014."},{"id":488,"n":"John Knier","u":"John","g":"F1","p":"I2","tw":"Green Bay","st":"WI"},{"id":489,"n":"Timothy Knight","u":"Tim","g":"B3","p":"H4","ph":"216-272-8911","em":"taknight64@icloud.com","tw":"Fairlawn","st":"OH","ac":"He values reunions and informal reconnections over time, noting that even long gaps are easily bridged with classmates. He did not emphasize specific hobbies like golf or fishing, but expressed strong interest in attending reunions, reconnecting one-on-one, and spending unstructured time talking and catching up. He plans to attend the 40th reunion if circumstances allow.","w":"Tim Knight Tim lives in Fairlawn, Ohio, with his wife Pam in the same home for nearly 30 years. He has two adult children, both married, and is now a grandfather. His family is centered in Northeast Ohio. A major highlight was being selected as First Captain, a formative leadership experience requiring him to lead classmates while maintaining trust and credibility. He earned a Marshall Scholarship and studied at Oxford, followed by operational service in Korea with 2nd Infantry Division engineers and deployment to Desert Shield and Desert Storm with the 20th Engineer Brigade supporting XVIII Airborne Corps. After leaving active duty during the post-Desert Storm drawdown, he entered Procter & Gamble's management training program, then moved into product management at Rubbermaid. He spent 22 years at Sherwin-Williams, rising to senior leadership roles including global business president and leading mergers and acquisitions, culminating in the $11.3B Valspar acquisition. For the past nine years, he has worked as an independent consultant focused on private equity, M&A, and board service with lower- and middle-market firms. He's from Massillon, Ohio, and majored in electrical engineering at West Point. He values reunions and informal reconnections with classmates. He can be reached at taknight64@icloud.com | 216-272-8911."},{"id":490,"n":"Roger Knowles","u":"Roger","g":"E4","p":"E2","ph":"973-294-9049","em":"rknowles@drew.edu","tw":"Madison","st":"NJ","w":"Roger Knowles Roger lives in Madison, New Jersey. He has two children: his daughter Abby is an MD in her second year of Neurology residency at UPenn, and his son John is in his final year at Gettysburg College as a philosophy major. Roger was in E4 as a cadet and remembers helping Chris Cole study for exams while eating oatmeal raisin cookies made by Chris's grandmother. Meeting her the week before graduation, when Alzheimer's had robbed her memory, was Roger's first encounter with the disease and became one of his inspirations for later research. He served in Air Defense Artillery in West Germany, working as a platoon leader, XO, and on battalion staff. He was given a project to help transition a battalion from Colorado to West Germany, probably the easiest job he ever had at maybe 30-40 minutes a day, yet it was cited as the reason for his service award when he left the unit. After the Army, he went to Harvard for his PhD in Neuroscience, then did a research fellowship at Massachusetts General Hospital in their Alzheimer's Disease Research Unit. Since 1998, he has been a professor at Drew University teaching Neuroscience to undergraduates. He can be reached at rknowles@drew.edu | 973-294-9049."},{"id":491,"n":"Reinhard Koenig","u":"Rhino","g":"B1","p":"F4","ph":"(703) 901-3639","em":"rwkoenig1@yahoo.com","tw":"Fairfax Station","st":"VA","ac":"He values informal connection with classmates more than specific hobbies. He enjoys travel with his wife, particularly international travel, and spoke positively about reunions, class gatherings, and time spent reconnecting with classmates. His current leisure time is largely centered on family life, youth sports, travel planning, and maintaining friendships rather than organized recreational activities like golf or fishing.","w":"Reinhard Koenig Rhino lives in Fairfax Station, Virginia, with his wife Melissa and their two children—a teenage daughter around 15 and a son around 11. He stepped back from professional advancement to be present for his children's activities, particularly his son's baseball games. He served more than 30 years as an Army engineer officer, with early assignments in Germany with VII Corps and deployments related to Desert Storm. He held company and battalion command at Fort Leonard Wood, senior engineer leadership roles in Iraq reconstruction, and brigade-level command in Alaska, along with multiple Pentagon assignments. He retired as a colonel in 2016. After active duty, he transitioned to federal civilian service with the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, rising to the Senior Executive Service with major assignments including New York City. He retired from civilian service about seven months ago. He grew up in rural Northern California near Happy Camp with classmate Dan Hokenson, attending Oregon State for a year before West Point. He met his wife in an immigration line in Beijing; she later became a JAG officer. During Beast Barracks, he and Hokenson developed a private \"bull drawing\" code they used to communicate. He values informal connection with classmates and enjoys international travel with his wife. His current time centers on family life, youth sports, travel planning, and maintaining friendships with classmates. He can be reached at rwkoenig1@yahoo.com | 703-901-3639."},{"id":492,"n":"Richard Kolpasky","u":"Richard","g":"D2","p":"I1","ph":"586-489-1340","em":"richiesk@comcast.net","tw":"Shelby Township","st":"MI"},{"id":493,"n":"Michael Kommer","u":"Michael","g":"E4","p":"D2","ph":"(563) 249-7298","em":"mfkommer@msn.com","tw":"Mokena","st":"IL"},{"id":494,"n":"Michael Kosalko","u":"Michael","g":"C1","p":"C2","em":"mike.koko1986@gmail.com","tw":"Burnet","st":"TX"},{"id":495,"n":"Theodore Kostich","u":"Ted","g":"B3","p":"F4","ph":"704-773-0349","em":"tkostich@gmail.com","tw":"West Long Branch","st":"NJ","ac":"golf, hunting, hiking, cruising, and anything to do with football, cigars, or bourbon.","w":"Ted Kostich Ted lives in West Long Branch, New Jersey, with four children (38, 36, 34, 31) and four grandchildren (15, 11, 8, 6). He became a pastor and has pastored churches in Georgia, Pennsylvania, and North Carolina. He currently serves as pastor of the First Baptist Church in Lakewood, New Jersey. He officiates high school and college football and high school basketball. He golfs, hunts, hikes, cruises, and enjoys anything to do with football, cigars, or bourbon. He can be reached at tkostich@gmail.com | 704-773-0349."},{"id":496,"n":"David Kozuch","u":"Dave","g":"F3","p":"C2","ph":"(281) 685-0130","em":"david.j.kozuch@pfizer.com","tw":"Danbury","st":"TX"},{"id":497,"n":"Robert Krall","u":"Rob","g":"B2","p":"G1","em":"robckrall@gmail.com","tw":"Stuart","st":"FL"},{"id":498,"n":"David Kramer","u":"David","g":"G4","p":"E2","ph":"(757) 369-4874","em":"kramers4@cox.net","tw":"Seaford","st":"VA"},{"id":499,"n":"Wayne Kropp","u":"Wayne","g":"E4","p":"B4","ph":"(757) 369-5219","em":"kroppfamily4@gmail.com","tw":"Yorktown","st":"VA"},{"id":500,"n":"Peter Kuring","u":"Peter","g":"A4","p":"A2","ph":"(860) 350-1567","em":"pkuring64@yahoo.com","tw":"Sherman","st":"CT"},{"id":501,"n":"Christopher Kurkowski","u":"Chris","g":"D3","p":"B1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":502,"n":"Landon Lack","u":"Landon","g":"G3","p":"G4","ph":"415-310-5697","em":"landon.lack@gmail.com","tw":"Truckee","st":"CA"},{"id":503,"n":"Mark LaDu","u":"Marko","g":"B1","p":"A2","ph":"(330) 334-0765","em":"meladu@neo.rr.com","tw":"Cuyahoga Falls","st":"OH"},{"id":504,"n":"Peter LaFleur","u":"Pete","g":"F1","p":"D3","ph":"402-659-2527","em":"pjlafleur@cox.net","tw":"Papillion","st":"NE"},{"id":505,"n":"Paul LaFontaine","u":"Paul","g":"I3","p":"C4","ph":"720-537-6400","em":"paulklafontaine@proton.me","tw":"Myrtle Beach","st":"SC","ac":"Battlefield tours, He places highest value on reconnecting socially with classmates rather than on specific recreational activities. He enjoys travel, shared meals, reunions, informal gatherings, skiing trips, and simply spending time talking and laughing with classmates. Experiences and relationships consistently take priority over structured hobbies or competitive sports.","w":"PLAF lives in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina with his wife of 26 years, Colleen. He has one son, Luke (33) who is a mechanical engineer working in the defense industry. His cadet memories are adopting the \"Moo Baba\" persona through exaggerated exploration of martial arts, Zen, and meditation. He loved both is plebe company (C4) and the Polar Bears. Mostly he used humor as a way to offset the Academy grind. He branched Military Intelligence, and his Army highlight was deploying to Desert Storm where he was a Battalion S4 then ran night operations in the 24th Infantry Division G2. After leaving the Army, he had a varied civilian career, including early internet startups, executive roles at larger companies like Ticketmaster and Disney. He had a ten year stint living in London and Helsinki acquiring and running company units. He also took roles at companies in the US specializing in renewable energy, fitness and internet gaming. When he retired he went to India for an extended meditation retreat, visited the Muktananda Ashram, and from its grounds texted Darren Moore. The cycle was complete. He hasn’t touched the stuff since. In retirement, he focuses on maintaining class relationships, designing wargames, producing military history content online, and prioritizing people over collecting things. He enjoys battlefield tours, travel, shared meals, reunions, informal gatherings, skiing trips, and simply spending time talking and laughing with classmates. Experiences and relationships consistently take priority over structured hobbies or competitive sports. He can be reached at paul@paulklafontaine.com | 720-537-6400."},{"id":506,"n":"Tye Lageman","u":"Tye","g":"F4","p":"B1","em":"tmlag@yahoo.com","tw":"Williamsburg","st":"VA"},{"id":507,"n":"Benjamin Lambert","u":"Shane","g":"D3","p":"E4","em":"bennyshane@icloud.com","tw":"Alameda","st":"CA"},{"id":508,"n":"John Landgraf","u":"John","g":"H1","p":"E4","ph":"812-272-1032","em":"john.landgraf@icloud.com","tw":"Bloomington","st":"IN"},{"id":509,"n":"Sherman Lane","u":"Sherman","g":"G4","p":"H2","em":"sherman.lane@sbcglobal.net"},{"id":510,"n":"Richard Lange","u":"Rick","g":"D3","p":"A2","em":"rick86@pacbell.net","tw":"Sherman Oaks","st":"CA"},{"id":511,"n":"Kevin Lanham","u":"Kevin","g":"H1","p":"H4","em":"kevin_lanham2@yahoo.com","tw":"Boyce","st":"VA"},{"id":512,"n":"Kelly LaPorte","u":"Kelly","g":"I1","p":"H4","ph":"808-544-3848","em":"klaporte@cades.com","tw":"Honalulu","st":"HI"},{"id":513,"n":"Larry Larimer","u":"Larry","g":"C3","p":"F1","tw":"Leavenworth","st":"KS"},{"id":514,"n":"James Larsen","u":"Jay","g":"H1","p":"","ph":"210-289-0138","em":"jay_larsen@hotmail.com","tw":"Granbury","st":"TX","ac":"Reunions, travel, sporting events.","w":"James Larsen lives in Granbury, Texas. His son Jake works as an attorney in Fort Worth with his wife Hillary and daughter McKay, with a grandson on the way. His daughter Grace works in marketing and communications for a commercial real estate company in Austin with her husband Foster. Jay served as a career aviator with assignments in Korea, Germany, Hawaii, Okinawa, and CONUS. His most interesting assignment was in Okinawa, Japan, as an amphibious planner for US 7th Fleet, where as the only Army member of the organization he developed a \"Soldier of the Quarter\" program and won easily every quarter. His terminal Colonel assignment was with US Army North at Fort Sam Houston as Chief of Training & Exercises. After retirement, he transitioned to contractor work supporting Homeland Defense training and exercises for Army North, later becoming a DA Civilian in the same organization. His most interesting post-retirement role was Chief of the Urban Search & Rescue training team. Jay skis with his H-1 brothers, attends reunions, and travels to sporting events. He's been married since 1991. He can be reached at jay_larsen@hotmail.com | 210-289-0138."},{"id":515,"n":"Wilma Larsen","u":"Wilma","g":"I2","p":"D3","ph":"254-760-0561","tw":"Temple","st":"TX"},{"id":516,"n":"Mark Lassiter","u":"Mark","g":"D2","p":"I3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":517,"n":"Kevin Lauterjung","u":"Kevin","g":"C1","p":"E2","ph":"330-607-2829","em":"sklauterjung@gmail.com","tw":"Akron","st":"OH","ac":"Army football.  Tailgating.","w":"Kevin Lauterjung Kevin  lives in Akron, Ohio. He and his wife Sally have three kids in their 20s, all living in New York: Ellen practices law in Albany and is married to her Ohio State sweetheart Chris; Luke lives in Brooklyn working in marketing for pet insurance company Pumpkin; and John is finishing college at RPI in Troy. His plebe company was E2, graduating from C1. He served, worked, and played with an amazing group of lieutenants in the 9th Combat Engineer Battalion in Aschaffenburg, Germany, including Rhino Koenig and Don Johantges. They took ski trips to the Alps every Thanksgiving, played a memorable tackle football game against the armor battalion officers, and trained with our sister Panzer Battalion in Fulda.  His most memorable cadet experience was a trip to NYC with about eight Chargin' Charlie classmates, doing a Billy Idol concert, and staying with Tony Hylton's parents in Queens. After the Army, he worked in health care consulting, then spent 15 years at a health insurance company culminating as EVP of Managed Care. He started an energy brokerage in 2013 and an energy services company in 2021, remaining active with both while dabbling in real estate and commercial property development. Sally and their two oldest kids are all Ohio State graduates. The family holds season tickets and follows Buckeyes football closely. He's an Army football fan who particularly enjoys tailgating. He can be reached at sklauterjung@gmail.com | 330-607-2829."},{"id":518,"n":"John Lazar","u":"John","g":"B3","p":"A4","ph":"717-609-3313","em":"jml06@mac.com","tw":"Holland","st":"MI","w":"John Lazar lives in Holland, Michigan. John can be reached at 517-609-3313; jml06@mac.com."},{"id":519,"n":"Jeffrey Leach","u":"Jeff","g":"I4","p":"H1","ph":"(845) 266-4915","em":"jeffleach1986@hotmail.com","tw":"Clinton Corners","st":"NY"},{"id":520,"n":"Martin Leal","u":"Martin","g":"D2","p":"B3","ph":"972-400-1305","em":"porkchop933@gmail.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX"},{"id":521,"n":"Kevin Lech","u":"Kevin","g":"G2","p":"D4","ph":"(919) 562-1513","em":"klech7@aol.com","tw":"Wake Forest","st":"NC"},{"id":522,"n":"Karen Lee","u":"Kat","g":"G1","p":"G3","ph":"206-510-0504","em":"ktl1986@msn.com","tw":"Des Moines","st":"WA","ac":"Anything!  We hosted the chicks in Seattle this past year.","w":"Karen “Kat” Lee (Turner)  lives in Des Moines, Washington. She and her husband Alan Ellison have five children combined and eight grandchildren. Her son Marshall is completing his degree in molecular biology and wants to teach and research. Her daughter Mariah is a professional soccer player who will retire either this year or next year to attend NYU Law School. Her stepdaughter is a lawyer with six kids. Her stepgrandson Tyce is graduating from SDSU this year and will work for an engineering firm. She was stationed in Germany in the 1980s and was able to take a team to participate in the annual Nijmegan International March. She practiced law for a few years, then spent her middle management years at Puget Sound Energy, an electric and gas utility based in Bellevue, Washington. She served on the Governor's Cabinet and as an Agency Director in the Gregoire Administration, then was CEO of Pioneer Human Services, a social enterprise aerospace manufacturing company that hires people coming out of prison. She's now CEO of Plymouth Housing, the region's largest provider of Permanent Supportive Housing, serving close to 4,000 formerly homeless people annually. Her father was the first African American General Officer in the Army Medical Corps. Her plebe company was G1, graduating from G3. She and her husband powerboat and keep a 59-foot yacht in downtown Seattle. She's working on her golf game and plays soccer once a week in a women's league. She's interested in writing a book about her father's career and enjoys genealogy. She hosted the Chicks of '86 in Seattle this past year. She can be reached at ktl1986@msn.com | 206-510-0504."},{"id":523,"n":"Mark Lee","u":"Mark","g":"H3","p":"C4","ph":"(757) 638-7269","em":"mark.m.lee@lmco.com","tw":"Orlando","st":"FL"},{"id":524,"n":"Michael Lee","u":"Mike","g":"C1","p":"B2","ph":"910-508-9993","em":"mjlee71647@gmail.com","tw":"Greenville","st":"SC","af":"Glee Club","ac":"I have enjoyed getting together with classmates for sporting events over the years and hope to do more of it in the coming years.","w":"Michael Lee Mike lives in Greenville, South Carolina. He met Andrea (Andy) during his first duty station assignment at Fort Hood. His oldest, Lauren, lives in Greenville, South Carolina - a Desert Storm baby who was a teacher but stays at home raising their three grandchildren (currently 5, 3, and 3 months) and helps her husband in home building. His second, Stephen, is married and is a civil engineer in Raleigh, North Carolina. His youngest, Andrew, also married, is in Charlotte and works for Ally Bank. Mike has many great memories of the Glee Club and the trips they took - including possibly renting a car in Hawaii, pulling into a beach parking lot, opening the back and having empty beer cans roll out clattering. He walked the area only once because he, Cabes, and Rooner returned from Spring Break minutes late for formation from skiing in Utah. Between Cow year and Firstie year, he and Hoke drove from New York to California, then picked up Cabes in Utah for the drive back to West Point and fried the CB radios in a lightning storm in South Dakota. He also remembers going home with Corsi to Dover, Ohio at Thanksgiving and playing the annual Turkey Bowl. On that trip he realized he did have a \"friend in Pennsylvania\" (highway patrol). He commissioned as a Signal officer and served in many types of units. As part of 2nd Armored Division, he deployed to Desert Storm with the Tiger Brigade attached to the 1st Marine Division. He was then stationed at Bragg where he did company command in the 82nd Airborne Division followed by a stint in a Special Mission Unit at Bragg - his most memorable times but he can't talk about them. He served in Germany with 1st Armored Division, then had an ROTC assignment in Boston as an APMS at MIT and as the PMS at Boston University. He retired after 22 years of service.  After retiring from the Army, he spent 17 years in banking as a consultant, retiring in December 2025. Mike has enjoyed getting together with classmates for sporting events over the years and hopes to do more of it in the coming years. He can be reached at mjlee71647@gmail.com | 910-508-9993."},{"id":525,"n":"James Leise","u":"Jim","g":"A1","p":"I3","em":"mjleise4@gmail.com","tw":"Tacoma","st":"WA"},{"id":526,"n":"Michael Lemanski","u":"Mike","g":"G1","p":"D2","ph":"443-370-8404","em":"lemampebk@yahoo.com","tw":"Davidsonville","st":"MD","ac":"skiing, skiing, skiing and travel, attending sports, hiking.","w":"Mike Lemanski resides in Davidsonville, Maryland, where he continues to work within the Department of Defense as he approaches retirement. Contact information includes 443-370-8404 and lemampebk@yahoo.com. He described his cadet experience with understatement, noting graduation itself as a highlight. He also spent considerable time skiing the West Point ski slope to get away and spent time with the G1 group. His most significant Army service included six years in Stuttgart, Germany serving first as a lieutenant and later returning as a major and lieutenant colonel. Mike taught in the EECS Department at West Point and commanded a company in the United Kingdom. After military service, he remained in Department of Defense–related work, continuing a long association with defense missions and institutions, and at time of writing is preparing for retirement. His current interests center heavily on skiing, travel, attending sporting events, and hiking. Mike and his wife Pam have two daughters living in Cleveland, a son in Colorado Springs, two grandchildren, and a son-in-law.zTBD"},{"id":527,"n":"Mark Levesque","u":"Mark","g":"I1","p":"H2","ph":"(207) 510-1877","em":"m.levesque7@yahoo.com","tw":"Scarborough","st":"ME"},{"id":528,"n":"David Ley","u":"David","g":"C3","p":"A1","ph":"817-881-2888","em":"dj_ley@hotmail.com","tw":"Trophy Club","st":"TX","ac":"Golf, Skeet Shooting, Travel, local sport events, Cruises (wife Julia is the cruise queen!)","w":"David Ley David lives in Trophy Club, Texas with his wife Julia, who hails from Nottingham, England—they married in November 2019. He has three daughters: two live locally (one married, one not), and one lives single in Orlando, Florida. His middle daughter in Orlando has a side gig as a professional wrestler. Julia is the \"cruise queen\" who loves cruising. His plebe company was A1, graduating from C3. He served from 1986-1991, completing Airborne School at Benning, Armor Officer Basic at Knox, then 5/77 Armor in Mannheim, Germany, Armor Officer Advanced at Knox, and Bradley NETT-T assignments at Knox, Benning, Polk, and Hood. His funniest cadet memory is probably his \"discovery of Ash Wednesday.\" After the Army, he worked primarily in commercial and government construction management and IT project management. He did a 6-month tour as logistics manager at McMurdo Station, Antarctica with Bill Woodring. His private sector construction work was primarily at Disney and Universal in Orlando. His public sector work included facility management and construction with the VA in Orlando and USACE at Bliss, Hood, San Antonio, and Kandahar (18-month tour), then IT project management at Treasury. He was a foster parent for 6 years in Florida. He's Christian and enjoys golf, skeet shooting, travel, local sport events, and cruises. He ballroom dances with Julia. He can be reached at dj_ley@hotmail.com | 817-881-2888."},{"id":529,"n":"Elizabeth Lind","u":"Liz","g":"F2","p":"F1","ph":"734-904-5123","em":"liz.lind@comcast.net","tw":"Ann Arbor","st":"MI","ac":"I have extreme fatigue with my long COVID. I likely will not attend the reunion.","w":"Elizabeth Lind Liz lives in Ann Arbor, Michigan. Her son Jonathan, 24, is a lovely person and an early childhood educator. He lives right around the corner from her and she sees him frequently. Liz remembers on R-day that she and her beast roommate, Caroline Keller, thought it was oddly thoughtful of the academy to provide them with shower caps, which were in fact their hat rain covers. A very relevant highlight was being assigned to West Point for 12 years as a Reservist to teach MA206, Probability and Statistics, in STAP. It was nice to come back with perspective and gratitude for her alma mater. After the Army, she has mostly worked in Information Technology in a variety of roles. She is currently at the University of Michigan getting set for one more big project before she retires. Liz has extreme fatigue with long COVID and likely will not attend the reunion. She can be reached at liz.lind@comcast.net | 734-904-5123."},{"id":530,"n":"Greg Lind","u":"Greg","g":"H3","p":"I4","ph":"757-535-0726","em":"galind@charter.net","tw":"Suffolk","st":"VA","ac":"Skiing, attending sporting events, shooting sports, fishing, the beach, boating and jet skiing","w":"Greg Lind Greg lives in Suffolk, Virginia. He has two daughters, two stepsons, and two granddaughters. His oldest daughter is an Army aviator flying the UH-60M and just took command of HHC, 1-229 Attack Battalion at JBLM. His youngest daughter is a senior at Auburn University majoring in Culinary Arts and Hospitality Management. His oldest stepson retired from the USAF as a C-5 pilot and is now flying for United Airlines. The younger stepson works in healthcare and lives nearby in Chesapeake, Virginia. His oldest granddaughter will graduate high school this year and is currently deciding where to go to college. The youngest will enter high school in the fall and is a talented softball player.Greg was a plebe in I4 living in the lost 50s and spent four years in H3. His best memory is finally making it to graduation. He has too many stories along that path to choose from—the car at P Lot, the motorcycle at P Lot, wrecking the motorcycle just north of the gate on Highway 218, getting turned back, broken ankle, torn ACL, and MAJ Tijerina as H3's TAC. His career path was unusual. He started as an infantryman destined for an assignment with TRADOC and a basic training company. In IOBC, he interviewed with The Old Guard, got selected, and served with several classmates including John Poncy, Joel Bagnal, and Bruce Gagne while stationed at Fort Myer, Virginia. During this tour in Washington, DC, he applied for, got selected, and completed flight school, transferring to Aviation Branch in 1989. Aviation assignments took him to Korea twice and Fort Bragg, North Carolina with the 82nd Aviation Brigade. His company command in 2-82 Assault Battalion was his favorite and most rewarding assignment. Other assignments as an analyst at the Defense Intelligence Agency, the Army Test and Evaluation Command, the Army Futures Center, and JFCOM rounded out his career. After retirement in 2008, he worked for Booz Allen Hamilton supporting Army capability development at Fort Monroe and Fort Eustis, Virginia, then transferred into government service in 2015 continuing capability development work until full retirement in 2025. In spite of being on the five-year plan, he never failed a class and ended up working for the government as an ORSA. Greg enjoys skiing, attending sporting events, shooting sports, fishing, the beach, boating, and jet skiing.He can be reached at galind@charter.net | 757-535-0726."},{"id":531,"n":"Duane Linenkugel","u":"Duane","g":"A1","p":"G2","ph":"(513) 530-0802","em":"dlinenkugel1@gmail.com","tw":"La Follette","st":"TN"},{"id":532,"n":"Racheau Lipscomb","u":"Ray","g":"B4","p":"B4","ph":"410-322-4881","em":"racheau.lipscomb@gmail.com","tw":"Longs","st":"SC","ac":"Worship, hunting, fishing, limited skiing, traveling, and hiking.","w":"Ray Lipscomb Ray lives in Longs near Myrtle Beach, South Carolina with his wife Sabrina, who retired from the Harford County (Maryland) Public School system in 2020. Ray retired from the USAR in 2014 and from civil service in 2022. They have two children: their son, 35, lives in San Antonio providing IT support to JSBA Lackland, is married, and has two sons and three daughters; their daughter, 45, is an HR manager with Infinite Legacy, which facilitates organ, eye, and tissue donation, and has four sons. Ray remembers hanging out with Bubs (Kevin Walker, '85), Los (Carlos Lopez, '85), and Berkliee (Berkley Cooke, '86), who kept him sane. Following CM OBC, he served as a chemical officer at battalion and DIVARTY levels as platoon leader, aide-de-camp, company commander, and deputy systems manager before going into the reserves. His most interesting assignment was as the first company commander for the Chemical Ammunition Company on Johnston Island, where he supervised the storage and transportation of the 155mm GB rocket stockpile for demilitarization at JACADS. He served in various IT positions before deploying to Afghanistan for a year, then served at the Pentagon for two years before retiring from the USAR. He worked as a defense contractor for 10 years before entering civil service as an IT professional, serving in positions from webmaster to helpdesk lead, systems analyst, site manager, and culminating as Information Systems Security Manager. During that time he also taught IT and certification preparation part time for community colleges and small business. He now teaches Networking Fundamentals part time at the University of Maryland Global Campus. Ray enjoys worship, hunting, fishing, limited skiing, traveling, and hiking. Anyone in the Myrtle Beach area has an open invitation to the Lipscomb household. He can be reached at racheau.lipscomb@gmail.com | 410-322-4881."},{"id":533,"n":"Donald Lobeda","u":"Don","g":"F2","p":"E4","ph":"931-237-3533","em":"dglobeda@cox.net","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA","ac":"Skiing, cycling, sitting and talking, attending sports events","w":"Don Lobeda Don lives in Fairfax, Virginia with his wife Sara, whom he married in 1992. They have two children and three grandchildren. Their son, Donald III, is currently a Navy lieutenant stationed in Norfolk, Virginia. He is married to Meghan and they have two children, Charlotte and James. Their daughter Katy is married to Simon, works part-time as a program manager for a food production company, and lives in Harrisonburg, Virginia. They have a one-year-old son, Abraham. Don says he was a mediocre cadet but loved being at West Point. He enjoyed leading the F2 triathlon (running, swimming, shooting) as a coach/participant to a brigade championship in 1985, along with many other good memories and some bad ones too. He really enjoyed his Army career both as an infantry officer and a JAG officer, making it difficult to say what was most interesting—his career took him from Bangkok to Baghdad, Las Vegas to Berlin. His family's favorite assignment was at West Point from 2007 to 2009 where he was Chief of Administrative Law in the OSJA. He enjoyed sharing his rockbound, highland home with his family and making it part of their life story. His kids skied a couple of times a week at the ski slope in winter, they went to Delafield or one of the lakes by Buckner in summer, and caught the train from Garrison several times for adventures to NYC.  He hung up the uniform twice, first in 1991 to attend law school, then reentered the Army as a JAG in 1995 and retired as a JAGC LTC in 2014. He then pursued a career as an ethics counselor/advisor at HHS, the USDA, and finally at the Department of the Army, retiring from civilian federal service in May 2025. He did the Hawaiian Ironman in 1990 and considered going pro as a triathlete but ultimately decided to get out of the Army to attend law school, get married, get born again as a Christian, and then pursue a career as a JAG, probably a wise decision. Don enjoys skiing, cycling, sitting and talking, and attending sports events. He can be reached at dglobeda@cox.net | 931-237-3533."},{"id":534,"n":"George Loche","u":"George","g":"A4","p":"E1","ph":"440-463-5146","em":"georgeloche@yahoo.com","tw":"Stow","st":"OH","ac":"Travel, attending sporting events, golf (I suck), a good meal (prepared by someone else)","w":"George Loche George lives in Stow, Ohio, with three children: Asher, 24, Eden, 23, and Jakob, 21. He served with 3rd Infantry Division (4/66 Armor - Iron Knights) from 1986 to 1989 and 1st Infantry Division (4/37 Armor) from 1990 to 1991. He went to Desert Storm with 4/37 but loved his time with 4/66 in Germany. After the Army, he worked in and around pharma. His most interesting role was leading an account team that sold data into pharma on the vendor side. He travels, attends sporting events, golfs, and enjoys a good meal prepared by someone else. He can be reached at georgeloche@yahoo.com | 440-463-5146."},{"id":535,"n":"Ralph Locke","u":"Ralph","g":"E4","p":"F2","tw":"Galloway","st":"OH"},{"id":536,"n":"Robert Lockett","u":"Bob","g":"I4","p":"C1","ph":"210-488-7464","em":"boblockett@icloud.com","tw":"Basking Ridge","st":"NJ","af":"Gospel Choir","ac":"He enjoys highly social, competitive, and physical activities. These include golf, basketball, boxing, fitness training, and informal sports competitions, as well as social gatherings built around travel, parties, and shared experiences. He values environments with energy, humor, and interaction rather than quiet or passive activities, and he emphasized enjoying reunions, sporting events, and unstructured social time.","w":"Bob Lockett Bob lives in Basking Ridge, New Jersey and splits time with St. Louis for work. He has four children. His three older children were born during his Army years at Fort Sill and Fort Polk, and his youngest, Aiden (17), has committed to play football for Franklin & Marshall College, in Lancaster, PA.. He grew up in East St. Louis and attended one year of Culver Military Academy in high school. His plebe company was C1. His strongest cadet memories center on Plebe year and company life, especially high-energy social episodes in C1 and later I4. He recalled Beast Barracks dining-hall mistakes, spirit missions, frequent minor disciplinary trouble, near-misses with inspections involving hidden alcohol, and a strong sense of camaraderie among roommates and classmates. He also remembered academic struggles early on, particularly being moved from a top thermofluid dynamics section to a lower one where a gifted instructor helped him succeed. And he will never forget the epic food fight our Firstie Year. At the Academy he was active in the Gospel Choir, boxing, and contemporary affairs, and was known for wide social connections across companies. A defining highlight was commanding an MLRS battery, which fulfilled his primary personal Army goal. He also cited his Desert Shield/Desert Storm service as formative, including firing missions in combat, liaison work with British artillery, and witnessing the real effects of large-scale firepower. After nine years of service, he transitioned into executive recruiting, then progressively senior HR leadership roles. His career included work at Lucas Group, Frito-Lay, Harrah's, Limited Brands, USAA, ADP, and other large organizations, culminating in multiple chief people officer and chief talent officer roles. He is currently Chief People Officer at Schnucks Markets. He is recognized for applying observation-driven problem solving to people systems, designing creative incentive structures, and framing diversity, talent, and culture through performance and economic outcomes rather than ideology. He enjoys highly social, competitive, and physical activities including golf, basketball, boxing, fitness training, and informal sports competitions, as well as social gatherings built around travel, parties, and shared experiences. He values environments with energy, humor, and interaction and enjoys reunions, sporting events, and unstructured social time. He can be reached at boblockett@icloud.com | 210-488-7464."},{"id":537,"n":"Wayne Locklin","u":"Wayno","g":"A4","p":"C3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":538,"n":"Laura (Carew) Loftus","u":"Laura","g":"B3","p":"D4","em":"lcloftus12@gmail.com","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":539,"n":"William Logan","u":"William","g":"I2","p":"E4","ph":"(215) 498-2511","em":"loganbill14@yahoo.com","tw":"Fort Myers","st":"FL"},{"id":540,"n":"Andrew Lombardo","u":"Andy","g":"B2","p":"E1","em":"aplombardo@att.com","tw":"Oceanport","st":"NJ","ac":"Outdoor activities, especially hiking, skiing and travel","w":"Andy Lombardo Andy lives in Oceanport, New Jersey, with three adult children—two sons and one daughter. He served two tours in Bavaria, Germany, including Desert Storm and the War on Terror. After the Army, he worked as a cybersecurity engineer and is now retired. He hikes, skis, and travels. He can be reached at aplombardo@att.com."},{"id":541,"n":"Lance Lombardo","u":"Lance","g":"C2","p":"G3","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"NC"},{"id":542,"n":"Darold Londo","u":"Darold","g":"C2","p":"I4","ph":"715-525-1224","em":"daroldlondo@gmail.com","tw":"Highland Falls","st":"NY","ac":"cruising","w":"Darold Londo Darold lives in Highland Falls, New York. All three of his kids are academy graduates: two graduated from USMA and one attended USCGA. He has two grandchildren. His plebe company was I4, graduating from C2. He served at Camp Casey, South Korea with a handful of classmates and follows Army football closely. After the Army, he worked as a lawyer, entertainment executive, and commercial real estate investor/developer. He tried retirement but it didn't work out—now he's full-time in real estate investing through strandsofvalue.com. He enjoys cruising. He can be reached at daroldlondo@gmail.com | 715-525-1224."},{"id":543,"n":"Michael Lonigro","u":"Michael","g":"H1","p":"B3","ph":"830-237-0279","em":"lonigrome@gmail.com","tw":"Canyon Lake","st":"TX"},{"id":544,"n":"Victor Losure","u":"Victor","g":"F4","p":"H3","em":"vic@elmpress.com","tw":"Bristol","st":"CT"},{"id":545,"n":"Robert Lott","u":"Rob","g":"G3","p":"H4","ph":"712-223-7053","em":"robbieandrita@outlook.com","tw":"Dakota Dunes","st":"SD"},{"id":546,"n":"David Lowe","u":"David","g":"C2","p":"C4","ph":"(610) 742-5802","em":"dslowe86@gmail.com","tw":"Kennett Square","st":"PA"},{"id":547,"n":"Douglas Luehe","u":"Douglas","g":"D4","p":"C1","em":"dluehe@gmail.com","tw":"La Plata","st":"MD"},{"id":548,"n":"Charles Luigs","u":"Chuck","g":"E4","p":"F3","em":"cvluigs@aol.com","tw":"Richmond Hill","st":"GA"},{"id":549,"n":"Mark Lukens","u":"Mark","g":"G2","p":"C3","ph":"703-498-0698","em":"Mark.w.lukens@gmail.com","tw":"Cape Coral","st":"FL","ac":"Skiing Sports and Travel","w":"Mark Lukens Mark lives in Cape Coral, Florida. All his children graduated from college. He served in Alaska and taught at West Point. After the Army, he worked as a Senior Civilian at the Pentagon. He skis and enjoys sports and travel. He can be reached at Mark.w.lukens@gmail.com | 703-498-0698."},{"id":550,"n":"Eric Lund","u":"Eric","g":"H3","p":"","tw":"Cary","st":"NC"},{"id":551,"n":"Rodney Lusher","u":"Rodney","g":"B2","p":"B1","ph":"(540) 421-4723","em":"rodney.l.lusher.civ@mail.mil","tw":"Lawton","st":"OK"},{"id":552,"n":"John Lynch","u":"John","g":"I2","p":"H4","ph":"704-231-9794","em":"jlynch@imprimis-financial.com","tw":"Mooresville","st":"NC","ac":"Everything and anything. Love spending time with classmates. Golf, Travel, sporting events","w":"John Lynch John lives in Mooresville, North Carolina. He has three great kids: Ryan (30), Nolan (28), and Alexis (26). His plebe company was H4, graduating from I2.His most memorable cadet experience was driving out of the gates on graduation day with the Thayer Hotel in the rearview mirror. He commanded a 270-soldier provisional company of non-deployables in HAA Savannah during the Gulf War. After the Army, he attended grad school for finance at NYU, then worked in currency trading. He loves investing in disruptive tech, noting that the world is changing fast and the change is accelerating. He enjoys everything and anything, loves spending time with classmates, golf, travel, and sporting events. He can be reached at jlynch@imprimis-financial.com | 704-231-9794."},{"id":553,"n":"Darryl MacDonald","u":"Daryl","g":"F2","p":"D4","ph":"978-808-7956","tw":"Wilmington","st":"MA"},{"id":554,"n":"Charles MacMaster","u":"Charlie","g":"F3","p":"I1","em":"macmaster@live.com","tw":"China Spring","st":"TX"},{"id":555,"n":"Joseph Macrina","u":"Joseph","g":"E1","p":"G2","em":"jrmacrina@hotmail.com","tw":"Orlando","st":"FL"},{"id":556,"n":"Kurt Maggio","u":"Kurt","g":"A4","p":"A3","ph":"(703) 848-2586","em":"dermatologyforlife@gmail.com","tw":"McLean","st":"VA"},{"id":557,"n":"John Magness","u":"John","g":"F4","p":"B2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":558,"n":"Raymond Maier","u":"Joe","g":"D1","p":"D3","em":"maier.1776@gmail.com","tw":"Eau Claire","st":"WI"},{"id":559,"n":"Clifford Mainor","u":"Cliff","g":"G2","p":"C3","ph":"469-818-1344","em":"cmainor11@gmail.com","tw":"Kemah","st":"TX","ac":"travel, sports events, boating","w":"Cliff Mainor Cliff lives in Kemah, TX. His son Jeremiah, 23, recently graduated from Dallas Baptist University and is now pursuing a law degree. His daughter, 20, attends college as a Junior majoring in Dance and performance arts. He enjoys travel, sports events, and boating. He can be reached at cmainor11@gmail.com | 469-818-1344."},{"id":560,"n":"Frederick Maiocco","u":"Fred","g":"E1","p":"H4","em":"fred.maiocco@gmail.com","tw":"Hermiston","st":"OR"},{"id":561,"n":"Thomas Malloy","u":"Thomas","g":"F4","p":"","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":562,"n":"John Maloney","u":"John","g":"C2","p":"G3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":563,"n":"Ranelle Manaois","u":"Ranelle","g":"C2","p":"G2","ph":"612-743-5692","em":"ranelle4july@aol.com","tw":"Aiea","st":"HI","af":"Volleyball","w":"Ranelle Manaois Ranelle lives in Aiea, Hawaii. Her strongest memories are of great people in C2, the Teens for Christ group being awesome, and her volleyball teammates being the best. After the Army, she worked in teaching. She can be reached at ranelle4july@aol.com | 612-743-5692."},{"id":564,"n":"Fred Manzo","u":"Fred","g":"A4","p":"","ph":"(703) 350-6979","em":"Fredmjr@earthlink.net","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":565,"n":"Raffi Maranian","u":"Raffi","g":"C3","p":"I4","ph":"858-204-2842","em":"Raffi.Maranian@outlook.com","tw":"Parker","st":"CO","ac":"He emphasized daily social connection and structured activities as essential to well-being in retirement. In Arizona he lives in a 55+ community he likened to a “stationary cruise ship,” with built-in programming and recurring social gatherings. His personal anchors are golf (he organizes a street-based group), fitness/social time at the gym, and a men’s Bible study he leads in a common area. He values casual, frequent contact over formal events, and he advocated for simple, repeatable mechanisms (coffee meetups, golf, small groups) that make connection automatic.","w":"Raffi Maranian Raffi lives between two residences with his wife Brandy, one near Denver and one in northeast Scottsdale near Rio Verde, spending most of the year in Arizona. He has three children: two sons live in Colorado (one in Fort Collins, one in the Denver suburbs) and his daughter lives in North Scottsdale about 30 minutes from his Arizona residence. They don't have grandchildren yet. His mother in Huntington Beach is in hospice following a femur fracture. His plebe company was I4, graduating from C3. In Arizona he lives in a 55+ community he likens to a \"stationary cruise ship\" with built-in programming and recurring social gatherings. He organizes a street-based golf group, spends time at the gym for fitness and socializing, and leads a men's Bible study in a common area. He emphasizes daily social connection and structured activities as essential to well-being in retirement, valuing casual, frequent contact over formal events. He advocates for simple, repeatable connection mechanisms like coffee meetups, golf, and small groups that make connection automatic. He strongly endorses lowering the \"resume-comparison\" barrier within the class by shifting away from accomplishment-centric formats toward informal catch-ups that share current location, routines, and interests. He shares a birthday with classmate Rob Hazen (C3). He golfs regularly, leads Bible study, and deliberately makes the first move with neighbors. He can be reached at Raffi.Maranian@outlook.com | 858-204-2842."},{"id":566,"n":"Ernest Marcone","u":"Rock","g":"C3","p":"I2","ph":"586-675-0640","em":"rock.marcone@gmail.com","tw":"Rochester","st":"MI"},{"id":567,"n":"John Markovich","u":"John","g":"G4","p":"H1","ph":"703-509-3854","em":"Goaliegolfer@gmail.com","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA","ac":"I'm still working so I'm not sure.","w":"John Markovich John lives in Fairfax, Virginia with his wife Kristen, whom he married in 1988. Their daughter Kathryn works as a flight attendant for United Airlines and lives nearby with her husband and their grandson Grant. Daughter Rachel works as a nurse practitioner in Palmer, Alaska with her husband and their granddaughter Hanna, and son David lives in Lynchburg.John retired after 22 years split between Armor and Acquisition Corps. He studied mechanical engineering at the Naval Postgraduate School in Monterey before working on the STRYKER vehicle, M1A2SEP upgrades, and intelligence systems during the global war on terrorism. His assignments took him through Korea, Fort Knox, Germany, Warren Michigan, and Fort Belvoir. His final two Army jobs were at the National Reconnaissance Office in Chantilly, where he says he worked with the smartest, most mission-focused people he's encountered in his career—even surpassing his time as a tank company commander. He continues working in Chantilly as an employee of MITRE Corporation, where after 16 years supporting the same government office he's become the greybeard. His daughter Kathryn has met several '86 classmates on flights, including Carolyn Elliott, David DesRoches, and Dan Hokanson, after spotting their West Point gear. John still teaches children's Sunday school and volunteers as an election officer in Fairfax County. He can be reached at Goaliegolfer@gmail.com | 703-509-3854."},{"id":568,"n":"Paul Marks","u":"Paul","g":"F3","p":"G4","ph":"(971) 201-9416","em":"paul.marks64@gmail.com","tw":"Brightwood","st":"OR"},{"id":569,"n":"Price Marr","u":"Price","g":"E3","p":"","ph":"219.241.3989","em":"pricemarr@gmail.com","tw":"Newbury","st":"NH","ac":"fishing, hunting, sporting events","w":"Price Marr Price lives in Newbury, New Hampshire. He has two adult daughters and one granddaughter. His most memorable cadet experiences were road trip weekends. He served in the Infantry with the 101st Airborne during the Gulf War. After the Army, he worked in electric and gas utilities during industry restructuring. He competed in and completed the 2022 World Ironman Championship (140.6 miles) in Hawaii. He enjoys fishing, hunting, and sporting events. He can be reached at pricemarr@gmail.com | 219-241-3989."},{"id":570,"n":"Ronald Marsh","u":"Ron","g":"I2","p":"I4","ph":"316-619-1682","em":"nocoastguy86@gmail.com","tw":"Salina","st":"KS","ac":"Golf, sporting events, tasting bourbon, visiting craft breweries, pretty open and up for most anything.","w":"Ron Marsh Ron lives in Salina, Kansas, with two children nearby in spirit. Son Chuck and his wife live outside Madison, Wisconsin, with two boys ages 4 and 1. Chuck recruits full time for the Wisconsin National Guard and works as a tattoo artist. Daughter Bonnie and her husband live in Wichita, where she works as an RN. His cadet highlights include adventures with the I2 Moose and Labor Day weekends at Matt Stanton's parents' house on Cape Cod. His most significant Army assignment was with the 1st Infantry Division at Fort Riley, deploying for Desert Storm. After leaving the Army, he worked several jobs before entering public service, where he spent 27 years, including 8 years in city management. He golfs, follows sporting events, tastes bourbon, and visits craft breweries and describes himself as pretty open and up for most anything. Ron can be reached at nocoastguy86@gmail.com | 316-619-1682."},{"id":571,"n":"Todd Marsh","u":"Todd","g":"A4","p":"I2","tw":"Rochester","st":"NH"},{"id":572,"n":"James Marshall","u":"Jim","g":"C1","p":"","ph":"910-263-1229","em":"jimz07@yahoo.com","tw":"Miramar","st":"FL","ac":"Traveling, fishing, sport shooting, hiking, researching and conducting battlefield terrain rides.","w":"Jim Marshall Jim lives in Miramar, Florida. He has three children: John, 25, who is autistic and lives with him; Lee, 22, who is graduating from the University of Central Florida with a degree in computer science and will be commissioned as a 2LT in Cyber branch, detailed to Armor; and Ashley, 19, who is also at UCF in Army ROTC, did a semester abroad in the UK, earned the Norwegian Foot March Badge, and is doing an internship with Lockheed Martin. As a cadet in C1, he roomed with Kevin Lauterjung, an unlikely pairing between a farm boy from Illinois and a guy from LA. That turned into a close friendship, including a cross-country road trip to California. Jim served as a Cavalry Officer in storied units including the 3rd Armored Division and the 3rd and 11th Armored Cavalry Regiments, deploying for Desert Shield and Desert Storm. He completed 33 rotations at the National Training Center, 3 as a unit, 20 with the Operations Group, and 10 with OPFOR. He later served as a Public Affairs Officer with a tour in Kosovo, travel throughout South America and Guantanamo, and earned a master's degree in Mass Communication from UNC Chapel Hill. He retired as a Colonel in 2010 after serving as Director of Public Affairs at U.S. Southern Command. After retirement, Jim worked as communications director for the FBI's Miami Field Office, enjoying the people and mission enough to stay longer than planned. Jim enjoys traveling, fishing, sport shooting, hiking, and researching and conducting battlefield terrain rides. He has taken his children on vacations to at least 41 states including Alaska twice. In summer 2027, he and Army buddies from his Germany LT days plan to follow the WWII battle route of the 3rd Armored Division across France, Belgium, and Germany while podcasting. He can be reached at jimz07@yahoo.com | 910-263-1229."},{"id":573,"n":"Joseph Martin","u":"Joe","g":"B4","p":"C2","ph":"254-285-7881","em":"Joetanker86@gmail.com","tw":"Keller","st":"TX","ac":"Golf, socializing and having fun.","w":"Joe Martin Joe lives in Keller which is in the Dallas-Fort Worth area. He and his wife moved to DFW to be near their daughter Kylie and her husband Ken, who are expecting Joe's first grandson in March. Their son Joey has been serving in the Army for nine years and lives in Savannah, Georgia with his wife Madison. Joe’s favorite cadet memory is Graduation Day. He long period of service included  assignments in Germany, Texas, Kentucky, Kansas, Pennsylvania, and the National Capital Region, with several trips to Iraq. His most interesting assignment was leading the CJFLCC during Operation Inherent Resolve. His most fun assignment was commanding the US Army National Training Center and Fort Irwin, California. Since retiring, he has worked in consulting, which he has found fulfilling in many ways. Joe enjoys golf, socializing, and having fun. He can be reached at Joetanker86@gmail.com | 254-285-7881."},{"id":574,"n":"Marielle (Smith) Martin","u":"Marielle","g":"E3","p":"G4","ph":"425-894-7010","em":"marielle.martin@comcast.net","tw":"Renton","st":"WA"},{"id":575,"n":"Steven Martin","u":"Steven","g":"F3","p":"F4","ph":"(703) 346-9392","em":"martinsj2@comcast.net","tw":"Reston","st":"VA"},{"id":576,"n":"Richard Martinez","u":"Rick","g":"D1","p":"I3","em":"rick.e.martinez@gmail.com","tw":"Belton","st":"TX","ac":"Sports events, hiking, cycling, eating, concerts","w":"Rick Martinez Rick lives in Belton, Texas. He has three children: Justis, married to Audra and living in Belton; Amanda, married to Jon Don and stationed at Fort Meade, Maryland with their daughter Izzy; and Micah, married to Abby and stationed at Offutt AFB, Nebraska with their daughter Sofia. As a cadet, Rick remembers being in his Tactical Officer's office with Dean Dorman and Ted Johnston, standing at attention while being disciplined for something he can't recall, and trying desperately to hold in the laughs, unsuccessfully. He served at Fort Sill, Fort Carson, and Fort Lee. After the Army, he spent many years in outside sales beginning with pharmaceuticals at Pfizer and culminating with MRO supplies and equipment at Grainger. He was offered a position as Assistant Director of Facilities Management for a school district while on a sales call and continued his career in facilities management, primarily in higher education. He retired from Southwestern University as Associate Vice President for Facilities Management in 2024. Rick quit drinking in 2019. Rick enjoys sports events, hiking, cycling, eating, and concerts. He can be reached at rick.e.martinez@gmail.com."},{"id":577,"n":"Victor Maslak","u":"Vic","g":"C3","p":"I1","ph":"330-699-1362","tw":"Hvre De Grace","st":"MD"},{"id":578,"n":"William Mason","u":"Bill","g":"B2","p":"A1","ph":"972-837-7813","em":"wrmas@aol.com","tw":"Allen","st":"TX","ac":"Golf, Travel, Sporting Events","w":"Bill Mason Bill lives in Allen, Texas, with eight grandkids. His favorite assignment was Alaska, standing up and activating the National Missile Defense System. After the Army, he served as a Program Manager and Product Portfolio Manager in the defense industry, providing products to all branches of the military. He golfs, travels, and attends sporting events.He can be reached at wrmas@aol.com | 972-837-7813."},{"id":579,"n":"Norman Massry","u":"Norm","g":"D4","p":"I1","ph":"518-257-0100","em":"norm.massry@gmail.com","tw":"Albany","st":"NY","ac":"I would enjoy golfing, scuba diving, and possible travel to far away places.","w":"Norm Massry Norm lives in Albany, New York and has two children, a daughter who works for TJX Corporation and a son who works as a software engineer for Klaviyo, both in Boston. After leaving active duty following service in Iraq during the Gulf War, he became a lawyer and eventually a Judge, serving in one of New York's busiest Justice Courts for 15 years. He is a Certified Information System Security Professional (CISSP) and founded West Point Security LLC, a Service-Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business that advises businesses, colleges, universities, and governmental entities on protecting their data and systems from cyberattacks. His favorite cadet memory is sneaking back on post after a night out, driving in the dark with no lights across the ski slope and down a walking trail near Michie Stadium in his Jeep, evading the MP Guard Shack. His favorite Army assignment was Korea, where he flew aeroscout reconnaissance missions along the DMZ as a young aviator, flying nearly every day. He enjoys golf, scuba diving, and travel to far-away places. He can be reached at norm.massry@gmail.com | 518-257-0100."},{"id":580,"n":"James Matheson","u":"Jim","g":"E3","p":"C4","em":"sabot_86@yahoo.com","tw":"Easthampton","st":"NJ","ac":"Current interests and activities for both Jim and Diane are tennis, fly fishing, and Army Football.  We are season ticket holders in Section U-13 Row G.  If any of you find yourselves at a Michie Stadium, please stop by U-13 which is known as the “fun section”.","w":"Jim Matheson Jim lives in Easthampton, New Jersey with his wife Diane. They have a son, two daughters, and four granddaughters. Their son Ryan is an Army Major and family practice physician currently stationed with his wife Maggie and granddaughter Nora at Fort Sam Houston. Daughter Rebecca is a mom of three granddaughters—Marcella, Cecily, and Cordelia—living with her husband in Tuscaloosa, Alabama. Daughter Abigail is not married and is a producer for a video and animation company in London. Jim doesn't have a specific memory or story from his time as a cadet but enjoyed being surrounded by really good people. He retired from the Army in 2008 following Garrison Command in Hohenfels, Germany and a final assignment as Deputy Commander of the Operations Group, Joint Multinational Readiness Center. He was a Math Professor from 1996-1999 and served as the Academy liaison for the Class of 1948 40th reunion, the class of Superintendent LTG Willard Scott. Since 2008, Jim has been employed as a Department of the Army Civilian. He and Diane were stationed in Germany and Italy continuously from 2000-2021 before being assigned by the Army to New Jersey in 2021. Since 2021, Jim has served as the Training Division Chief for Fort Dix. After returning to CONUS, Diane took a job as the 3rd grade teacher at Sacred Heart Catholic School in Mount Holly, New Jersey. Jim and Diane plan to retire in summer 2027. Jim and Diane's current interests are tennis, fly fishing, and Army football. They are season ticket holders in Section U-13 Row G, known as the \"fun section.\" If any classmates find themselves at Michie Stadium, please stop by U-13. He can be reached at sabot_86@yahoo.com."},{"id":581,"n":"Peter Mattes","u":"Peter","g":"C1","p":"C2","ph":"703-830-7434","em":"peter@mattesfamily.net","tw":"Centreville","st":"VA"},{"id":582,"n":"Albert Maxwell","u":"Albert","g":"I1","p":"A3","ph":"(732) 859-2854","em":"Atmax86@aol.com","tw":"Gaithersburg","st":"MD"},{"id":583,"n":"Willis McAdams","u":"Rich","g":"H2","p":"","ph":"256-658-5941","em":"r.mcadams@outlook.com","tw":"Hazel Green","st":"AL","ac":"Travel","w":"Willis Richard McAdams Rich lives in Hazel Green, Alabama. He has been married 39 years to his high school sweetheart, Annette. They have three children: Brittney (37), married to Ryan; Courtney (34), married to Chase; and Trey (32), married to Toby. Brittney and Ryan have three children—Reagan (11), Everett (9), and Riley (8). Trey and Toby have Marie, 14 months old. His plebe company was not specified, graduating from H2. His most memorable cadet experiences were the Happy Two Beach Parties they held in the barracks a week or two before spring break. He deployed to Desert Storm with the 24th Infantry Division. After Desert Storm, he got out and did 9 years in healthcare before spending the next 25 in the defense industry. His most interesting role is his current one where he works as a Deputy GM with classmate Jimmy Jenkins at AV, a defense technology company (AVAV). Their business group has some of the coolest capabilities in the entire company, including loitering munitions (Switchblade), Integrated Air & Missile Defense (Titan RF CUAS jammer), and Electronic Warfare. He genuinely loves supporting warfighters. He enjoys travel. He can be reached at r.mcadams@outlook.com | 256-658-5941."},{"id":584,"n":"James McAllister","u":"James","g":"I2","p":"I3","em":"mcallister.j@hotmail.com","tw":"Fairfax Station","st":"VA"},{"id":585,"n":"Todd McCaffrey","u":"Todd","g":"B3","p":"F1","ph":"703-244-3501","em":"todd.mccaffrey@gmail.com","tw":"Columbia","st":"SC","ac":"I play occasional bad golf; still ski when I can get to the mountains; and hike/backpack when I can find the time.  Living in a college town (University of South Carolina) I've become a big SEC football fan even though our local Gamecocks seem to be continuing under performers!","w":"Todd McCaffrey Todd lives in Columbia, South Carolina, with his wife Lisa and three adult children. Their oldest son Michael serves on active duty in the Army as an Armor officer now transferred to the Acquisition Corps, recently selected for Major; he and his wife Haley have one child, Margo Rose McCaffrey, nearly three. Their daughter Sara is an RN Nurse Manager in Roanoke, Virginia, and their youngest son Andrew will graduate medical school in May 2026 and begin his residency in orthopedic surgery. He retired from the Army in 2020 after more than 34 years in uniform, including three separate tours in Hawaii in both 25th ID and USARPAC. He led both a Stryker Battalion and Stryker brigade on combat deployments to Iraq. His final assignment was Chief of Staff, U.S. Africa Command in Stuttgart. After military retirement, he worked at the University of South Carolina for a bit more than a year, then did consulting work before taking his current role as South Carolina Secretary of Veterans Affairs. He plays occasional golf, skis when he can get to the mountains, and hikes and backpacks when he finds time. He's become a big SEC football fan living in a college town. He can be reached at todd.mccaffrey@gmail.com | 703-244-3501."},{"id":586,"n":"Thomas McCann","u":"Tom","g":"B4","p":"I2","ph":"901-490-9700","em":"tsmonthego@yahoo.com","tw":"Barrington","st":"RI"},{"id":587,"n":"William McCarley","u":"David","g":"A1","p":"","em":"Wdmccarley@gmail.com","tw":"Grapevine","st":"TX"},{"id":588,"n":"Stephen McCarty","u":"Stephen","g":"F2","p":"E3","ph":"(703) 978-0222","em":"stephen.mccarty@west-point.org","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA"},{"id":589,"n":"Timothy McConvery","u":"Tim","g":"G3","p":"C4","ph":"334-790-5172","em":"tim.mcconvery@outlook.com","tw":"The Villages","st":"FL","ac":"I enjoy golf, bike riding, and boating whenever I get the chance.","w":"Tim McConvery Tim and his wife Michele live in The Villages, Florida. Between them they have six children, four from his first marriage and two stepchildren, who are spread across Florida, Alabama, and Pennsylvania. His oldest son sells cars in Enterprise, Alabama, and has two boys. The second son works as an engineer in Florida. The third son is a firefighter in Dothan, Alabama, with two girls. His oldest daughter lives in Enterprise with her husband and three children. His next daughter has a master's in communication, works for Temple University in Philadelphia with her husband, and is applying to PhD programs. The youngest daughter owns and manages a barbecue restaurant in Enterprise with her husband and has three children. Ten grandchildren in all. Tim was attached to A Company 1-228th Aviation Regiment in Panama in 1989 with a section of his platoon, flying over the jungles and canal before Operation Just Cause. The next year he flew with 5-101st during Desert Storm, attached to the 101st Airborne Division. On the third flight into Iraq the day the ground campaign kicked off, he was forced to crash his Black Hawk—a total loss, but all 19 on board walked away unharmed. He left active duty in 1995 and stayed in the Army Reserve until 2016, instructing at CGSC, commanding a Drill Sergeant Battalion, then commanding an aviation mobilization brigade. Between 1995 and 2000 he worked as an engineer and supervisor in manufacturing, then returned to government service as a civilian for 25 years, ending up as a professor of requirements management at the Warfighting Acquisition University. He remembers going home early in the 1986 season with Joe DePinto and Bill Purcell for a three-day Mets series the year they won the World Seriesand crashing at his house in New Jersey between games. He plays golf, rides bikes, and gets out on the boat whenever he can. He takes his faith seriously as a born again Christian with clear priorities as a Christian first, husband second, father and grandfather third. He can be reached at tim.mcconvery@outlook.com | 334-790-5172."},{"id":590,"n":"Mark McCoy","u":"Marko","g":"I2","p":"D4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":591,"n":"Maria del Pilar McDermott","u":"Pilar","g":"B1","p":"D2","ph":"845-401-9122","em":"pilar.mcdermott@yahoo.com","tw":"Yorktown Heights","st":"NY","w":"Pilar McDermott Pilar lives in Yorktown Heights in the Hudson Valley of New York. She has lived in 26 houses over her lifetime, including multiple moves during her Army career. She is divorced with two adult children, including a daughter who rowed competitively. Pilar served 27 years in the Army, initially branching Chemical but transitioning to intelligence, artillery, and strategy positions. She was selected to return to West Point to teach history, earned her PhD in Renaissance Reformation history at the University of Pennsylvania, and spent her final decade as a history professor and division chief of the international division at the Academy. She worked closely with Kevin McKelvey and Karen Phelps during her cadet years. Since retiring, she has worked as a leadership consultant with the Thayer Leadership Group, delivers keynotes, and conducts staff rides with corporate leaders. She also teaches part-time at the Baseball Hall of Fame in Cooperstown, covering topics from civil rights and Jackie Robinson to labor history through baseball. Pilar is an accomplished competitive ballroom dancer, having started five months after beginning lessons and winning multiple competitions including the Empire Dance Sport Championship. She competes in international Latin styles—Cha Cha, Samba, Rumba, Paso Doble, and Jive—at high-level competitions in the New York area and nationally. She trains with European and Blackpool champions and competes regularly at events including the New York Dance Festival in February, Manhattan Dance Sport Championship over July 4th weekend, and the United States Dance Sport Championship in Orlando the week after Labor Day. She can be reached at pilar.mcdermott@yahoo.com | 845-401-9122."},{"id":592,"n":"Douglas McDowell","u":"Doug","g":"F3","p":"I2","em":"doug.mcdowell@mcdowasc.com","tw":"Novi","st":"MI","ac":"He values travel, shared experiences, and informal social connection with classmates more than specific recreational sports. He enjoys road trips, reunions, storytelling, and time spent reconnecting. He has a strong interest in mentoring, coaching, and service-oriented activities tied to West Point and youth development.","w":"Doug McDowell Doug  lives in Novi, Michigan. He has three daughters: Laura, born in 1987, manages a bar and restaurant; Ally works at Amazon; and Melanie works at McDow & Associates in an administrative role. All three live in Michigan. He is in a long-term relationship with Angela, a chemistry professor at Michigan State University, who has two children: Trevor, a sophomore at MSU, and Erica, a high school senior planning to attend MSU. His Army highlight was serving as an armor officer with 11th Armored Cavalry Regiment on the East-West German border during the Cold War. He served as a scout platoon leader in West Germany, lived with German families, and witnessed the fall of the Berlin Wall firsthand. He left the Army after completing Armor Officer Advanced Course at the four-year mark and joined Procter & Gamble for two years managing warehouse operations and maintenance teams. He then transitioned into the family firm, McDow & Associates, a geotechnical and environmental engineering company founded by his uncle. He earned a master's degree in civil/environmental engineering from Wayne State while working full-time and is now president of the firm, leading roughly 65 employees. He founded and coaches a youth track club, producing nationally ranked athletes and several future West Point cadets. He has spent over a decade working with the West Point Field Force to recruit candidates from Detroit and other underserved communities. He grew up in Fort Wayne and Bluffton, Indiana, raised by a single mother, and concentrated in international affairs and studied Russian at the Academy. He travels and values informal social connection with classmates. He can be reached at doug.mcdowell@mcdowasc.com."},{"id":593,"n":"Michael McDuffie","u":"Michael","g":"F3","p":"F2","ph":"(480) 981-3119","em":"michael.boyd4@gmail.com"},{"id":594,"n":"Brian McFadden","u":"Brian","g":"G3","p":"","ph":"(256) 852-0522","em":"mcfaddenbd@att.net","tw":"Harvest","st":"AL"},{"id":595,"n":"Michael McGinn","u":"Bucky","g":"H1","p":"C4","ph":"(410) 279-3488","em":"mlmbucky@aol.com","tw":"Annapolis","st":"MD"},{"id":596,"n":"Brian McGowan","u":"Brian","g":"I2","p":"H4","ph":"(407) 872-7042"},{"id":597,"n":"John McHugh","u":"Johnny","g":"D4","p":"G2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":598,"n":"John McIlhaney","u":"Randy","g":"I2","p":"H3","em":"jrandymc@gmail.com","tw":"Yorktown","st":"VA"},{"id":599,"n":"Kevin McKelvy","u":"Kevin","g":"B1","p":"C3","ph":"917-543-5445","em":"kevin.mckelvy@yahoo.com","tw":"Englewood","st":"NJ"},{"id":600,"n":"Michael McKinney","u":"Skinny","g":"E3","p":"F4"},{"id":601,"n":"Kaye McKinzie","u":"Kaye","g":"F4","p":"H1","ph":"501-813-5347","em":"kayemckinzie@gmail.com","tw":"Little Rock","st":"AR","w":"Kaye McKinzie Kaye lives in Little Rock, Arkansas.She pinned on colonel and left the Army as soon as her PhD commitment was up. She can be reached at kayemckinzie@gmail.com | 501-813-5347."},{"id":602,"n":"Alan McKirby","u":"Alan","g":"F2","p":"I4","em":"amckirby@gmail.com","tw":"West Caldwell","st":"NJ","ac":"Attending NASCAR events.  A gang of fellow 86ers have attended a race in each of the past 36 years","w":"Alan lives in West Caldwell, New Jersey. He has one son. No grandkids yet. He served with 25th Infantry Division and Ranger Training Brigade in Dahlonega. After the Army, he attended business school followed by a career in marketing. He retired last month. He attends NASCAR events. A group of fellow '86ers have attended a race each of the past 36 years. He can be reached at amckirby@gmail.com."},{"id":603,"n":"Balvin McKnight","u":"Balvin","g":"G1","p":"H2","ph":"610-220-2482","em":"bmcknight123@gmail.com","tw":"Norristown","st":"PA","ac":"Travel Anywhere Sport evemts","w":"Balvin McKnight resides in Norristown, Pennsylvania, where he is retired following a long career in systems integration. Contact information includes 610-220-2482 and bmcknight123@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience through everyday moments rather than formal milestones, recalling as a highlight playing tag while walking area tours, reflecting camaraderie and shared time with classmates. His Army service was spent entirely at Fort Bliss, Texas, where he worked on testing the FAADS family of systems, an assignment centered on technical evaluation and operational integration. After military service, he completed a 22-year civilian career as a systems integrator with GE Aerospace, which later became Martin Marietta and then Lockheed Martin. Balvin then progressed through successive corporate transitions while remaining in the same technical field. His current interests include travel and attending sports events. Balvin married his wife Crystal in 1987 and today have two daughters and two granddaughters. He remains closely connected to G1 classmates, noting that the group continues to gather whenever possible."},{"id":604,"n":"Charles McLaughlin","u":"Chuck","g":"B4","p":"F2","ph":"401-286-9462","em":"cjmcl4@gmail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA"},{"id":605,"n":"Craig McLeod","u":"Craig","g":"G4","p":"B1","ph":"(703) 266-3789","em":"craig.mike.mcleod@gmail.com","tw":"South Chesterfield","st":"VA"},{"id":606,"n":"Monica (Shepherd) McMillan","u":"Monica","g":"H2","p":"I3","em":"freefly4all@yahoo.com","tw":"Seattle","st":"WA"},{"id":607,"n":"Joseph Meadows","u":"Joe","g":"G1","p":"A4","em":"jmcmeadows@gmail.com","tw":"Easton","st":"PA","ac":"Hanging out, for any reason or no reason","w":"Joe Meadows resides in Easton, Pennsylvania, where he works as a lawyer. Contact information includes jmcmeadows@gmail.com, and (484) 379-7840. He states that his cadet experience is best captured through shared moments rather than a stated self-characterization, with his cadet highlight being the Army–Navy game in Pasadena, California, which stood out as a defining collective experience. His most significant Army assignment was with the 101st Airborne Division, 2nd Battalion, 327th Infantry Regiment (“No Slack”), an assignment notable for its operational identity and unit cohesion. After military service, he transitioned into the legal profession, building a civilian career as an attorney that continues to the present. His current interests center on spending time with others, whether for a specific purpose or simply to be together. He married his wife Tracy shortly after they both returned from Dessert Storm, and today have three children and two grandchildren."},{"id":608,"n":"William Meehan","u":"William","g":"H4","p":"H2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":609,"n":"Garry Melia","u":"Garry","g":"D2","p":"H1","ph":"(508) 865-6428","em":"grmelia@verizon.net","tw":"Sutton","st":"MA"},{"id":610,"n":"Derrick Mellberg","u":"Derrick","g":"I1","p":"I4","ph":"(254) 953-6129","em":"dmellberg@hotmail.com","tw":"Copperas Cove","st":"TX"},{"id":611,"n":"Michael Mennelle","u":"Mike","g":"E3","p":"C4","ph":"941-769-5398","em":"mikemennelle@gmail.com","tw":"Dover","st":"NH","ac":"Travel country in RV.","w":"Mike Mennelle Mike lives in Dover, New Hampshire. He has two married sons, a daughter, and one grandchild. His plebe company was C4. His most memorable cadet experiences were the friendships he made with Skinny, Mark, Paul, Rocky, Andy, Keith, Jay, Goody, and many others. Goody introduced him to his wife of 38 years. He served at Fort Riley, Kansas. After the Army, he worked in medical sales and service management and is now retired. He travels the country in his RV. He can be reached at mikemennelle@gmail.com | 941-769-5398."},{"id":612,"n":"Steven Merkel","u":"Steven","g":"C3","p":"G4","ph":"(317) 535-3350","tw":"Franklin","st":"IN"},{"id":613,"n":"Mark Merritt","u":"Mark","g":"C1","p":"C2","ph":"(404) 569-3773","em":"mmerritt3@me.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"GA"},{"id":614,"n":"David Mesick","u":"David","g":"A2","p":"B4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":615,"n":"Brian Metcalf","u":"Brian","g":"G4","p":"E1","em":"brian.f.metcalf@gmail.com","tw":"Collierville","st":"TN"},{"id":616,"n":"David Meyer","u":"David","g":"D1","p":"G4","ph":"(757) 576-4622","em":"dcrm1212@verizon.net","tw":"Yorktown","st":"VA"},{"id":617,"n":"Mark Michaelsen","u":"Mark","g":"I2","p":"H1","em":"MarkMichaelsen1@gmail.com","tw":"Keller","st":"TX"},{"id":618,"n":"Jonathan Millen","u":"Jay","g":"E2","p":"H3","ph":"786-740-9514","em":"jmillen@caldwellpartners.com","tw":"Charleston","st":"SC","ac":"Travel , fishing, just gathering and catching up","w":"Jay Millen Jay lives in Charleston, South Carolina. He and his wife Ginger have two children: daughter Zoe (21), a senior at Rose Hulman majoring in electrical engineering, and son Nate (19), a freshman at Ole Miss in their 5-year accounting master's program. His plebe company was H3, graduating from E2. His most memorable cadet experience was Company E-2's spectacular party on the Supe's boat firstie year. He was responsible for planning and made a slight math error on the alcohol requisition, resulting in even their OIC becoming more celebratory than appropriate. They had a rough landing at South Dock and a nighttime E&E back to the barracks. He served at the NTC, Fort Benning, France, and Latin America. His most fun assignment was as OPFOR at Fort Benning where he got to see and visit with classmates at each rotation. After the Army, he got into business with a Tenneco subsidiary and after helping with the divestiture effort went to International Paper, mainly abroad. He landed with Accenture leading the resources M&A group out of London. When he returned to the US in 2006, he got into executive recruiting and board services, initially with Korn Ferry. He will retire from the executive side in August with Caldwell and transition into board advisory only along with the diaconate in the Anglican Church. He's been truly blessed and giving back is his primary focus at this stage with local charities and initiatives started by the class. He enjoys travel, fishing, and just gathering and catching up. He can be reached at jmillen@caldwellpartners.com | 786-740-9514."},{"id":619,"n":"Dana Milner","u":"Dana","g":"C3","p":"B2","ph":"(978) 471-4090","em":"dana.milner@gmail.com","tw":"Ipswich","st":"MA"},{"id":620,"n":"Richard Minicozzi","u":"Rick","g":"A3","p":"G4","ph":"512-563-3617","em":"rickmm86@gmail.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":621,"n":"John Mitchell","u":"John","g":"D2","p":"G3","ph":"(304) 295-7597"},{"id":622,"n":"Laurence Mixon","u":"Laurence","g":"H3","p":"I4","ph":"(703) 270-8627","em":"laurence.mixon@yahoo.com","tw":"Elkton","st":"MD"},{"id":623,"n":"Thomas Monahan","u":"Tom","g":"I4","p":"I3","ph":"717-405-7355","em":"TKM_75218@yahoo.com","tw":"Lancaster","st":"PA","ac":"Charity fundraisers and sporting events.","w":"Thomas Monahan Tom lives in Lancaster, Pennsylvania. His daughter Maura was recently promoted at Oracle, and his son Thomas (USMA '20) is awaiting his first company command with the 82nd Airborne. His plebe company was I3, graduating from I4. His most memorable cadet experiences include beating the Navy Cycling Team at Annapolis in 1985 and beating Navy at the Vet in 1984. His first GWOT deployment in 2010-2011 allowed him to lead all Bradley and Abrams platform uparmoring activities in Iraq and Camp Arifjan. After the Army, he worked for Eaton as a senior project manager from 2007 to 2019. He still enjoys cycling frequently in bucolic Lancaster County and participates in charity fundraisers and sporting events. He can be reached at TKM_75218@yahoo.com | 717-405-7355."},{"id":624,"n":"Stephen Moniz","u":"Stephen","g":"A3","p":"G1","em":"monizduo@aol.com","tw":"Fairfax Station","st":"VA"},{"id":625,"n":"Dexter Monroe","u":"Dexter","g":"H1","p":"A2","ph":"803-360-9517","em":"monroe7740@gmail.com","tw":"Germantown","st":"TN"},{"id":626,"n":"Darren Moore","u":"Darren or \"D\"","g":"I3","p":"B4","ph":"405-778-0125","em":"darrenmmoore@sbcglobal.net","tw":"Jacksonville","st":"FL","ac":"Drinking beer and laughing about our cadet and life adventures!","w":"Darren Moore Darren lives in Jacksonville, Florida. He has been married to his wife Yong for 36 years. His oldest stepson is 49 and lives in Norman, Oklahoma with Darren's three granddaughters, ages 24, 22, and 19. His youngest stepson is 48, retired as a West Point DMI instructor, and lives in Fort Montgomery, New York with two granddaughters, ages 23 and 21. His daughter is 30 and lives in Houston, Texas, and his son is 28 and lives in Denver. Darren remembers hosting cadets at his house in Huntington Beach, California for the Army Navy game at the Rose Bowl during yearling year. He attended Fort Rucker for OBC and flight school in 86-87, then served 87-89 in the 55th Aviation Company at K-16 in Songnam, Korea as XO, Ops Officer, and Platoon Leader with eight classmates, flying VIPs into the JSA, DMZ, and supporting the 88 Summer Olympics. He returned to Fort Rucker for Advanced Course in 89-90, then served as Brigade Ops Officer with the 8th Infantry Division in Mainz, Germany in 90-91, deploying to Iraq for Operation Provide Comfort. From 91-92 he was a pharmaceutical rep for Allergan and a USAR Captain in the 168th Aviation Group in Los Alamitos, California. He served 92-00 as an active duty helicopter pilot for the US Coast Guard in Miami and Puerto Rico. From 00-22 he flew rotary wing, Predator B, and fixed wing aircraft for US Customs in Miami, Oklahoma City, Cocoa Beach, and Jacksonville, with drug interdiction missions in Miami being his most interesting role. He retired as a Coast Guard O6 in 2022 after assignments with Coast Guard Group Miami, USTRANSCOM, Coast Guard Institute, and USNORTHCOM. He and Yong moved to Melbourne, Florida after retirement and travel extensively. Darren enjoys drinking beer and laughing about cadet and life adventures with classmates. He can be reached at darrenmmoore@sbcglobal.net | 405-778-0125."},{"id":627,"n":"Kevin Moore","u":"Kevin","g":"H1","p":"A2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":628,"n":"Edward Moran","u":"Ted","g":"D1","p":"C4","tw":"Newfields","st":"NH"},{"id":629,"n":"Patrick Moran","u":"Pat","g":"C1","p":"A3","em":"moran_pjm@yahoo.com","tw":"Saint Paul","st":"MN","ac":"Golf","w":"Patrick Moran Pat lives in Saint Paul, Minnesota. He has three sons ages 23, 21, and 14. His plebe company was A3, graduating from C1. He served 2.5 years in Korea, which he describes as his favorite assignment. His most memorable cadet experience was Army-Navy in Pasadena. After the Army, he attended business school and worked in financial businesses. He golfs regularly. He can be reached at moran_pjm@yahoo.com."},{"id":630,"n":"James Morris","u":"Jim","g":"H2","p":"C1","em":"jim_morris@live.com","tw":"Dallas","st":"TX","af":"Basketball","ac":"Any venue to make fun of Dave Harmon and PJ Groce","w":"Jim Morris  Jim lives in Dallas with four kids spread across Dallas, New York City, and San Francisco—all four born within five calendar years. Two grandchildren are local. He met his wife Kai at classmate Dave Harmon's wedding. Morris served as intel officer with the 24th Infantry Division Assault Command Post during Desert Storm, stationed in Savannah with roommates Will Duke, Paul LaFontaine, Rich Pascoe, Andy Napoli, and others from '85 and '86. After the Army, he earned his MBA at Northwestern and worked at McKinsey in Chicago and South Africa, then held executive roles at Western Digital, Seagate, L3Harris, and Johnson Controls. He's currently Managing Director and Operating Partner at Nexus Capital, a private equity firm. At West Point, he created a basketball team sports information director job to stay off the radar and snuck off post Wednesdays as a junior to bring Mickey Haydak KFC before weigh-ins. He follows SEC football and enjoys venues where he can make fun of Dave Harmon and PJ Groce. He can be reached at jim_morris@live.com."},{"id":631,"n":"Joseph Morris","u":"Joseph","g":"E2","p":"D4","em":"josephtmorris@yahoo.com","tw":"Killingworth","st":"CT"},{"id":632,"n":"Charles Moses","u":"Charlie","g":"B4","p":"G1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":633,"n":"Edward Motley","u":"Ed","g":"G3","p":"C1","ph":"(419) 708-3121","em":"2edmotley@gmail.com","tw":"Pico Rivera","st":"CA"},{"id":634,"n":"Mark Moulton","u":"Mark","g":"H1","p":"A3","ph":"402-850-7839","em":"mytmou@cox.net","tw":"Omaha","st":"NE"},{"id":635,"n":"Edward Mount","u":"Edward","g":"H2","p":"D1","em":"emountie@aol.com","tw":"Hyattsville","st":"MD"},{"id":636,"n":"Marc Moyer","u":"Marc","g":"I4","p":"F3","ph":"717-580-2607","em":"sam1995@comcast.net","tw":"Pooler","st":"GA"},{"id":637,"n":"John Mulbury","u":"John","g":"D4","p":"C3","ph":"571-214-2241","em":"jmulbury@gmail.com","tw":"Wimauma","st":"FL","w":"John Mulbury John lives in Wimauma, Florida. He served in the Infantry and then Special Forces. He can be reached at jmulbury@gmail.com | 571-214-2241."},{"id":638,"n":"Michael Munoz","u":"Mike","g":"A1","p":"","ph":"406-544-3326","em":"mmunoz@ches.biz","tw":"San Juan","st":"Puerto Rico"},{"id":639,"n":"William Murphy","u":"Frank","g":"I4","p":"A1","ph":"(303) 403-4539","em":"billyfrank4@aol.com","tw":"Westminster","st":"CO"},{"id":640,"n":"Kimberly (Warren) Murray","u":"Kim","g":"G4","p":"C1","em":"murrayfamilys@comcast.net","tw":"Staunton","st":"VA"},{"id":641,"n":"Leslie Murray","u":"Les","g":"D3","p":"I2","ph":"818-669-6559","em":"lesmurray@gmail.com","tw":"Henderson","st":"NV"},{"id":642,"n":"Michael Murray","u":"Mick","g":"G1","p":"C4","ph":"714-454-5688","em":"mfmurray145@gmail.com","tw":"Tustin","st":"CA","ac":"Skiing, travel, sporting events or any gatherings where we can get together and have an opportunity to spend some quality time re-connecting.","w":"Mick Murray resides in Tustin, California, where he serves as a Superior Court Judge hearing criminal cases. Contact information includes (714) 454-5688 and mfmurray145@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience through shared stories, recalling as a highlight a Cow-year episode involving post-Easter treats that escalated into a memorable prank. His most significant Army assignment was serving as a scout platoon leader, which he cited as the most enjoyable period of his service due to the role’s pace and responsibility. He resigned his commission in 1991, attended law school in California, spent 25 years as a prosecuting attorney, including a decade focused on cold-case homicides, retired from prosecution in 2016, and became a Superior Court Judge in 2017, a role he continues today. His current interests include skiing, travel, attending sporting events, and gatherings that allow time to reconnect with others, and his family includes three adult children pursuing public service and science careers in Alaska and Hawaii."},{"id":643,"n":"Shawn Murray","u":"Shawn","g":"H1","p":"","ph":"917-319-7563","em":"shawn.murray@mcchrystalgroup.com","tw":"Alexandra","st":"VA"},{"id":644,"n":"Robert Nabb","u":"Bob","g":"G3","p":"","em":"bobnabb93@gmail.com","tw":"North Kingstown","st":"RI"},{"id":645,"n":"Dean Nakadate","u":"Dean","g":"E2","p":"","em":"take1of3@bendbroadband.com","tw":"Bend","st":"OR"},{"id":646,"n":"Andre Napoli","u":"Andy","g":"B2","p":"B3","ph":"312-965-2032","em":"Andy_Napoli@yahoo.com","tw":"Savannah","st":"GA","ac":"Andy enjoys travel, storytelling, and connecting over shared memories—especially those linked to his time in Savannah. Living downtown above the shop he runs with his wife, he welcomes classmates to visit and experience the charm of the Low Country. He would likely enjoy gatherings centered around good conversation, historic settings, and meaningful reconnection.","w":"Andy Napoli Andy lives in Savannah, Georgia, with his wife Robin. Their daughter Katie lives nearby with her husband Toby and two children. Their son Cooper lives in Colorado working in high-performance fitness training. As XO of Bravo Company, 3rd Engineer Battalion during Desert Storm, he oversaw deployment of heavy equipment through the Port of Savannah. When logistical delays prompted General Barry McCaffrey to fire the Navy and longshoremen, Andy and fellow exos loaded the ships themselves despite having no training. He later helped offload equipment in Saudi Arabia. He served as a company commander in Hawaii, attended grad school, taught at West Point, and transitioned to civilian life after 16 years. He joined Progressive Insurance with help from an '87 grad and moved several times for career opportunities before settling in Savannah. He and Robin now run a business downtown above their shop. He grew up in Cornwall, New York, 15 minutes from West Point, where his father worked in the admissions office. His best friend growing up was classmate Dean Dorman, and they joined West Point together. He travels and welcomes classmates to visit Savannah. He can be reached at Andy_Napoli@yahoo.com | 312-965-2032."},{"id":647,"n":"Bruce Nelson","u":"Bruce","g":"A4","p":"F1","ph":"(913) 682-3967"},{"id":648,"n":"David Nelson","u":"David","g":"F1","p":"A3","em":"david.nelson1370@gmail.com","tw":"Alpharetta","st":"GA"},{"id":649,"n":"Michael Nelson","u":"Mike (Nelly)","g":"F2","p":"G4","ph":"443-695-6646","em":"michael.r.nelson@hotmail.com","tw":"Rosedale","st":"MD","ac":"Sporting Events","w":"MIke lives in Rosedale, Maryland. He has two daughters, both living in North Carolina, who both graduated college (associate's degree) the same week they graduated high school. He oversaw the transition of the military intelligence school from Fort Devens to Fort Huachuca and served as the school's representative overseeing the $186M construction project at Fort Huachuca. After the Army, he became DEO of the largest privately held property management firm in Baltimore City. He made it to the rank of colonel and graduated from law school, passing the bar in the early 2000s. He attends sporting events. He can be reached at michael.r.nelson@hotmail.com | 443-695-6646."},{"id":650,"n":"Robert Ness","u":"Bob","g":"F4","p":"B1","ph":"(952) 474-0494","em":"bness4@yahoo.com","tw":"Excelsior","st":"MN"},{"id":651,"n":"Rodney Neudecker","u":"Rodney","g":"E2","p":"","tw":"Meridianville","st":"AL"},{"id":652,"n":"Eric Newman","u":"Spoon","g":"F1","p":"A2","em":"eric0newman@gmail.com","tw":"Charleston","st":"SC"},{"id":653,"n":"Walter Nichols","u":"Keith","g":"E3","p":"A4","ph":"(205) 586-1283","em":"walter.k.nichols.ctr@mail.mil","tw":"Arab","st":"AL"},{"id":654,"n":"James Nickolas","u":"Jim","g":"E2","p":"F4","em":"jamesdnickolas@icloud.com","tw":"Mansfield","st":"TX","ac":"He did not specify recreational interests. He signaled satisfaction with conversation, shared history, and professional transitions, suggesting that contact and fellowship themselves are the primary draw.","w":"Jim Nickolas Jim lives in Mansfield, Texas near family. His plebe company was F4.He recalls his father calling out to him during the Acceptance Day parade, a moment that mixed discipline with family pride. He also remembers a steady stream of bootleg boxes from home and the improbable streak of his parents winning the Thayer Hotel lottery for every major event. His identity as a cadet was shaped by soccer, a workmanlike approach to the regimen, and quiet determination to stay squared away. He served four years at the National Training Center. His career path included Korea, SAMS, battalion command in Baghdad during the surge (deployed understrength with inadequate facilities and broken equipment, leading a dispersed, high-tempo fight), War College, and DAIG investigations including Abu Ghraib. His battalion command in Baghdad stands out as his defining experience, citing the adaptability and resilience of soldiers under those conditions. His later work inspecting global detention operations under the DAIG also carried strategic weight. He earned multiple graduate degrees through Army schooling, then used the GI Bill to attend law school after retiring. He practiced estate planning briefly in Kansas before moving to Texas, taking the state bar, and running a small firm. His current vocation centers on church service and board work for a coffee company. He is active in his church and community. He can be reached at jamesdnickolas@icloud.com."},{"id":655,"n":"John Noble","u":"Nobes","g":"C2","p":"B3","ph":"954-531-4307","em":"nobes86@gmail.com","tw":"Lighthouse Point","st":"FL"},{"id":656,"n":"William Noble","u":"Bill","g":"D4","p":"D1","ph":"614-395-9775","em":"bnoblehbs@aol.com","tw":"Mason","st":"OH"},{"id":657,"n":"Frederick Nohmer","u":"Rick","g":"H3","p":"F4","ph":"850-368-2352","em":"rick.nohmer@gmail.com","tw":"Kittery Point","st":"ME"},{"id":658,"n":"Leonard Novak","u":"Leonard","g":"B4","p":"A1","ph":"630-441-0809","em":"leonard.j.novak@gmail.com","tw":"Vestavia","st":"AL","ac":"Travel, outdoor adventure, regional gatherings, hosting traveler in our home.","w":"Leonard Novak Leonard lives in Vestavia, Alabama, married to his high school sweetheart since 10 days after graduation. They have four children and two grandchildren. He served one tour in Germany with the First Armor Division as part of the divisional cavalry squadron. After working 23 years in the chemicals and construction aggregates industry, he was retired early by his employer. He then joined a small family-owned company after being with major corporations. He travels, enjoys outdoor adventure, regional gatherings, and hosts travelers in his home. He can be reached at leonard.j.novak@gmail.com | 630-441-0809."},{"id":659,"n":"Thomas O'Brien","u":"Tom","g":"E4","p":"D2","ph":"(781) 413-4175","em":"tobrienma@gmail.com","tw":"Needham","st":"MA"},{"id":660,"n":"Raymond Obst","u":"Ray","g":"D2","p":"I4","ph":"(609) 889-8048","em":"rayobst@me.com","tw":"Cape May","st":"NJ"},{"id":661,"n":"Gerald O'Connor","u":"Gerry","g":"C1","p":"D3","ph":"(832) 314-8622","em":"goconnor1963@gmail.com","tw":"Sugar Land","st":"TX","ac":"Skiing, travel, hiking, sporting events","w":"Gerald O'Connor Gerry and his wife Amy live between Houston, Texas in the winter and Cottage Grove, Minnesota in the summer, chasing the nice weather. Both of their children, Adam and Abby, are married and living in Austin, Texas.  His plebe company was D3, graduating with C1. His most rewarding assignment was commanding the 82nd Engineer Battalion (Blue Babe, Sir!) in Bamberg, Germany and deployed as a Task Force to Baqubah, Iraq during OIF in 2004-2005 as part of 3BCT, 1ID. His favorite cadet memories were getting away on weekends with C1 company mates. After the Army, he worked in project management for Fluor and Bechtel, including two assignments in Western Australia on LNG projects. He is now happily retired and endeavoring to visit every MLB ballpark with classmates. He enjoys golf, skiing, travel, hiking, and sporting events. He can be reached at goconnor1963@gmail.com | 832-314-8622."},{"id":662,"n":"Monica (Wyrwas) O'Connor","u":"Monica","g":"C3","p":"A2","em":"Oconnorml86@gmail.com","tw":"Arvada","st":"CO"},{"id":663,"n":"Patrick O'Connor","u":"Patrick","g":"C3","p":"D1","ph":"(303) 241-4889","tw":"Arvada","st":"CO"},{"id":664,"n":"Michael O'Dea","u":"Michael","g":"A3","p":"F2","ph":"(201) 251-2932","em":"hhkmikeodea@gmail.com","tw":"Ho Ho Kus","st":"NJ"},{"id":665,"n":"Von Odenwald","u":"Von","g":"E2","p":"C1","ph":"225-223-5916","em":"glosterarboretum@bellsouth.net","tw":"Gloster","st":"MS","ac":"Hunting","w":"Von Odenwald Von lives in Gloster, Mississippi. He is married with one child and three grandchildren. His plebe company was C1, graduating from E2. His most memorable cadet memory is the big red truck. He served in maintenance, then became an EOD officer. After the Army, he worked in law enforcement and is now Site Director for an arboretum. He enjoys hunting and describes himself as old, fat, and bald. He can be reached at glosterarboretum@bellsouth.net | 225-223-5916."},{"id":666,"n":"Thomas O'Driscoll","u":"Tom","g":"G4","p":"F3","ph":"(713) 898-6038","em":"tom_odriscoll@yahoo.com","tw":"Sugar Land","st":"TX"},{"id":667,"n":"Richard O'Hare","u":"Richard","g":"A2","p":"E4","ph":"(417) 525-4309","em":"Richardohare86@gmail.com","tw":"Oronogo","st":"MO"},{"id":668,"n":"Scott Okesson","u":"Okey","g":"I3","p":"A4","ph":"812-461-8256","em":"scott.okesson@gmail.com","tw":"Saint Charles","st":"IL"},{"id":669,"n":"Donald Okura","u":"Donald","g":"H4","p":"G1","ph":"(614) 733-0195","em":"okuradb@msn.com","tw":"Dublin","st":"OH"},{"id":670,"n":"Clay Olbon","u":"Clay","g":"E3","p":"F1","ph":"678-471-6010","em":"olbonc@yahoo.com","tw":"Lilburn","st":"GA","ac":"Cycling, Baseball games, Army Football","w":"Clay Olbon Clay lives in Lilburn, Georgia. He is married to Becky, whom he met at Fort Campbell some 35+ years ago. They have two kids - one in the workforce and one just finishing undergrad, with no grandchildren yet. His plebe company was F1. His most memorable cadet experiences were watching Father Matt break dance in the hallway as a firstie, trying to get a paper airplane from the 6th floor window of the barracks to diagonal walk (great being in E-3), and his 3-man firstie room all selecting infantry and Fort Campbell as their assignment. His only post was Fort Campbell, Kentucky, where he loved being a TOW company XO as his last job. After the Army, he worked for a small defense contractor in Huntsville, Alabama, moved to Detroit to work for a hospital as a systems administrator, worked for a dot-com startup and moved to Atlanta. He's spent the past 20+ years working for big consulting companies as an IT consultant, almost 19 years at Accenture where he's planning to retire. He currently leads their Accenture Song (their digital agency) portfolio for a large media and entertainment client. He spends most of his free time helping out at his church (leading adult Bible study among other things) and cycling with a local club. He enjoys cycling, baseball games, and Army football. He can be reached at olbonc@yahoo.com | 678-471-6010."},{"id":671,"n":"Michael O'Leary","u":"MIke","g":"B4","p":"H1","ph":"314-378-6180","em":"moleary648@gmail.com","tw":"Saint Louis","st":"MO"},{"id":672,"n":"Van Oler","u":"Van","g":"D1","p":"F3","em":"vancoler@cinci.rr.com","tw":"Milford","st":"OH"},{"id":673,"n":"Lawrence Oliver","u":"Larry","g":"B1","p":"G4","ph":"248-321-2562","em":"lawrenceoliver1932@gmail.com","tw":"Heath","st":"TX","w":"Lawrence Oliver Larrry lives in Heath, Texas, with seven children and expecting his first grandchild in April 2026. Five of his kids graduated from the Naval Academy, and one of his two Texas A&M graduates married a Navy pilot. He continues to work in manufacturing at a private HVAC company in Dallas after a career in the industry.He can be reached at lawrenceoliver1932@gmail.com | 248-321-2562."},{"id":674,"n":"Bruce Ollstein","u":"Bruce","g":"A4","p":"B2","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL"},{"id":675,"n":"Stanley Olson","u":"Stan","g":"D4","p":"E1","em":"wpmsm@hotmail.com","tw":"Elgin","st":"IL"},{"id":676,"n":"John Olvey","u":"JO","g":"I1","p":"H4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":677,"n":"Andrew Ornatowski","u":"Andrew","g":"A2","p":"C4","ph":"(256) 829-0202","tw":"Toney","st":"AL"},{"id":678,"n":"James Orner","u":"James","g":"D2","p":"F1","em":"jamesorner@gmail.com","tw":"Green Cove Springs","st":"FL"},{"id":679,"n":"Laurence Ortiz","u":"Laurence","g":"D3","p":"H4","ph":"915-731-5975","em":"lgortiz222@gmail.com","tw":"El Paso","st":"TX","ac":"No structured activities required for me. I just enjoy seeing classmates in a casual setting.","w":"Greg Ortiz Greg lives in El Paso, Texas. He has no grandchildren. His 27-year-old daughter lives in New York City working as a journalist, and his 25-year-old son lives in Los Angeles as an audio producer for Disney. His plebe company was H4, graduating from D3. He was a frustrated musician at West Point who tried to get a band going with classmates Bob Penna and Jim Seramba, though it never materialized. His most rewarding memory was working on the 100th-night show when he and classmate Mike Gwynn sat down at his electric keyboard - Gwynn gave him direction and lyrics, and he composed the music, calling it an amazing collaboration. He served 5 years as an MI officer with no command or combat tours. He attended Airborne school as an officer after OBC, completed OBC and OAC at Fort Huachuca, and served a 3-year tour in Stuttgart, Germany in various staff and support positions, the most interesting of which was Battalion Maintenance Officer. He served as Squadron S-2 for the 5th ID Cavalry but resigned his commission before their rotation to the NTC. After the Army, he was a public high school math and engineering teacher in El Paso ISD for 26 years, the only time he got close to using his Management Engineering degree. He is one of the \"Puerto Rico Four\" - all four attended the same high school in San Juan at the DoD school on Fort Buchanan. The three other graduates include Steve Sicinski (who was also in D-3 with him), John Badovinac, and non-graduate Kevin Burns. He enjoys seeing classmates in casual settings without structured activities required. He can be reached at lgortiz222@gmail.com | 915-731-5975."},{"id":680,"n":"Earl Oxendine","u":"Bucky","g":"F4","p":"C3","ph":"(703) 203-1563","em":"buckoxendine@aol.com","tw":"Aldie","st":"VA"},{"id":681,"n":"Gregory Palka","u":"Greg","g":"D2","p":"A4","ph":"719-231-9369","em":"palkag@aol.com","tw":"Colorado Spgs","st":"CO"},{"id":682,"n":"Kent Pankratz","u":"Kent","g":"E1","p":"A4","ph":"(703) 266-3622","em":"kgpankratz@gmail.com","tw":"Centreville","st":"VA"},{"id":683,"n":"Steven Parker","u":"Steve","g":"I2","p":"D1","ph":"540-660-2271","em":"steve@whitestonechurch.com","tw":"White Stone","st":"VA","ac":"Visiting","w":"Steven Parker Steve lives in White Stone, Virginia. He has five children and five grandsons. His plebe company was D1, graduating from I2. He met his wife in Seoul when they were both stationed there. After retiring as a school superintendent, he's now a Nazarene Pastor. He enjoys visiting. He can be reached at steve@whitestonechurch.com | 540-660-2271."},{"id":684,"n":"Bryan Parlier","u":"Bryan","g":"A2","p":"G1","em":"ourhalfdzn@jetbroadband.com","tw":"Forest","st":"VA"},{"id":685,"n":"Richard Pascoe","u":"Rich","g":"G2","p":"D1","ph":"858-342-4741","em":"rwpascoe86@gmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC","ac":"Travel, professional, sports, and mini reunions at Army football games","w":"Rich lives in Raleigh, NC with his wife Lou. They have two children and one grandchild. Their son lives in Oregon and their daughter in North Carolina. Rich and Lou have been married for 38 years after dating in high school and on and off through West Point. After graduation she dumped him, but a few years later he was able to woo her back. He served in field artillery, mostly at Fort Stewart, Georgia with the 24th ID. The highlight was being deployed to Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm. Following active duty, he joined the North Carolina National Guard in 1991 and stayed through 1999, achieving the rank of major. In 2016 he was selected as a Civilian Aide to the Secretary of the Army for the state of California. He started his career as a sales rep in the pharmaceutical business and has remained in that industry for 35 years, leading five companies as CEO and continuing to serve on various boards of directors. He recently joined a venture capital fund as a senior advisor. He's active as a board member on the Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund, which gives scholarships to children of the fallen in honor of classmate John McHugh. He enjoys travel, professional sports, mini reunions at Army football games, and boating. He can be reached at rwpascoe86@gmail.com | 858-342-4741."},{"id":686,"n":"Edward Pasquina","u":"Edward","g":"E4","p":"I3","ph":"(914) 777-1946","tw":"Mamaroneck","st":"NY"},{"id":687,"n":"Douglas Pavek","u":"Doug","g":"I4","p":"G2"},{"id":688,"n":"Matthew Pawlikowski","u":"Matt","g":"E3","p":"I2","em":"wpchap@yahoo.com","tw":"West Point","st":"NY"},{"id":689,"n":"Gary Pearcy","u":"Gary","g":"B3","p":"D4","ph":"612-599-4101","em":"pearcyge@yahoo.com","tw":"Rehoboth Beach","st":"DE","ac":"Love traveling, playing golf and enjoying a beautiful sunset","w":"Gary Pearcy Gary lives in Rehoboth Beach, Delaware with his wife Laurie. Both of their children, Emily and Kyle, live in New Orleans. They visit frequently as they are smitten with their two-year-old granddaughter, Poppy Mae. Gary has too many memories to enumerate but when you had roommates like Ken Carrick (RIP), Rob Healy, Tim Knight, John Lazar, and Paul Kapsner, one can only imagine. His B-3 Bandit company mates are an incredible group. He spent 12 years as an Army aviator, serving as UH-60 platoon leader, company commander (82nd Airborne), and in other roles. He served in Operation Desert Storm, deploying from Nurnberg, Germany with 4th Squadron, 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment, and spent a lot of time at Fort Rucker, Alabama. After leaving the military, he joined corporate America, first at GE, then honed his payments skills working at Wells Fargo and then in the fintech world. He celebrated his retirement in January 2025 and has not looked back. He and Laurie took a nice long trip to Italy in May and are planning their next vacation abroad, hopefully next spring. Gary loves traveling, playing golf, and enjoying a beautiful sunset. He can be reached at pearcyge@yahoo.com | 612-599-4101."},{"id":690,"n":"Gerald Pearman","u":"Gerald","g":"I4","p":"G2","em":"pearman1@netzero.net","tw":"Pacific Grove","st":"CA"},{"id":691,"n":"Pamela Pearson","u":"Pam","g":"I3","p":"B4","ph":"503-201-4463","em":"pearson_pam@ymail.com","tw":"Portland","st":"OR"},{"id":692,"n":"Mark Peasley","u":"Mark","g":"B4","p":"B2","ph":"281-686-9192","em":"mark.peasley@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX","ac":"Skiing and golf","w":"Mark Peasley Mark lives in Houston, Texas. His son Evan is class of 2016. His best assignment was 10th Special Forces. He retired after 20 years. After the Army, he worked in engineering across oil and gas, aerospace, and munitions testing and lethality. He skis and golfs. He can be reached at mark.peasley@gmail.com | 281-686-9192."},{"id":693,"n":"David Pekarek","u":"Dave","g":"E2","p":"I4","ph":"(214) 632-7248","em":"davidjpekarek@gmail.com","tw":"San Marcos","st":"TX"},{"id":694,"n":"Robert Peller","u":"Robert","g":"D4","p":"I3","ph":"(954) 385-3816","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":695,"n":"Valerie (Washington) Pendergrass","u":"Valerie","g":"A2","p":"A4","em":"val.pendergrass@gmail.com","tw":"Orlando","st":"FL"},{"id":696,"n":"Robert Penna","u":"Robert","g":"D3","p":"D2","em":"penna.robert@decforge.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":697,"n":"Frances (Strebeck) Pennington","u":"Frances","g":"E4","p":"C1","ph":"314-550-1451","em":"frances.s.pennington@gmail.com","tw":"Kirkwood","st":"MO"},{"id":698,"n":"Donald Peperak","u":"Donald","g":"H1","p":"C2","ph":"(412) 626-8199","tw":"Connellsville","st":"PA"},{"id":699,"n":"Scott Pepple","u":"Scott","g":"A1","p":"C4","ph":"303-489-6256","tw":"Denver","st":"CO"},{"id":700,"n":"Paul Pereira","u":"Paul","g":"B1","p":"E3","tw":"Carson","st":"CA"},{"id":701,"n":"Felix Perez","u":"Felix","g":"A2","p":"D1","em":"felix@pzweb.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":702,"n":"Broc Perkuchin","u":"Broc","g":"G2","p":"E1","ph":"202-510-4892","em":"perkuchins@mail.com","tw":"Arlington","st":"VA"},{"id":703,"n":"Gregory Perrotta","u":"Gregory","g":"D2","p":"G1","em":"gregory_perrotta@bah.com"},{"id":704,"n":"Danita (Pope) Perry","u":"Danita","g":"C3","p":"F4","em":"danitap06@gmail.com","tw":"Lawrenceville","st":"GA"},{"id":705,"n":"Barry Peterson","u":"Barry","g":"E3","p":"C4","ph":"775-636-4334","em":"barrynpeterson@gmail.com","tw":"Reno","st":"NV","af":"Sandhurst","ac":"He did not list specific recreational interests beyond earlier pursuits such as running, mountain biking, windsurfing, and yoga. His remarks suggest he values conversation, reconnection, and shared experiences. His willingness to engage in march-back preparations and future gatherings indicates openness to class activities that reinforce camaraderie.","w":"Barry Peterson Barry lives in Reno, Nevada. He is married with no children. His plebe company was C4. He remembers C-4's strong plebe cohort and later E-3's Sandhurst culture, where excellence, physicality, and unit pride aligned perfectly with his identity. His defining experience was serving as an infantry platoon leader after earning his Ranger tab and joining the 82nd Airborne. Just Cause influenced his decision to leave as he reevaluated priorities after the deployment. He transitioned first to Goodyear tire plant as a quality assurance engineer while earning an MBA. A knee injury and curiosity about human-machine performance led him into graduate work in virtual reality at the University of Washington and later to the Naval Postgraduate School, where he built simulation and training systems. After 9/11 he left DOD and spent over a decade as a full-time Bikram yoga teacher and trainer. He continues advocating for soldier resilience. He credits classmates for key course corrections. He can be reached at barrynpeterson@gmail.com | 775-636-4334."},{"id":706,"n":"Kristin (Powell) Peterson","u":"Kristin","g":"D4","p":"E1","em":"kristinmp@aol.com","tw":"Fort Myer","st":"VA"},{"id":707,"n":"Jody Petery","u":"Jody","g":"D3","p":"B4","ph":"(717) 502-6728","em":"peteryj03@yahoo.com","tw":"Avon","st":"IN"},{"id":708,"n":"Karen Phelps","u":"Karen","g":"B1","p":"E3","ph":"(706) 364-5074","em":"ksp@kestwick.com","tw":"Martinez","st":"GA"},{"id":709,"n":"Elliott Phillips","u":"Elliott","g":"I1","p":"G3","ph":"(910) 677-5375","em":"philleobills@yahoo.com","tw":"Hope Mills","st":"NC"},{"id":710,"n":"MaryEllen (Conway) Picciuto","u":"MaryEllen","g":"D3","p":"C2","ph":"845-926-7875","em":"me.picciuto@gmail.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA","ac":"I always enjoy catching up with classmates at reunions, on travel, Army sports events, or my fave, a good happy hour.","w":"MaryEllen (Conway) Picciuto ME lives in Ashburn, Virginia. She has been married nearly 40 years to her cadet sweetheart Jack Picciuto, USMA '84. Her daughter, 36, recently moved to Australia with her boyfriend after serving 11+ years as an Air Force intelligence officer. Her son, 33, lives in Huntington Beach, California where he works for an intelligence systems manufacturing and development company. He is married since 2018 and is a former Army intelligence officer who served 10 years. No grandchildren yet. ME's favorite cadet memories are Graduation, Ring Weekend, and when they were finally allowed in the Firstie Club. She served as a Quartermaster officer assigned to 13th COSCOM at Fort Hood, followed by 3rd Armored Division in Hanau, Germany. She deployed to Desert Shield and Storm and departed the Army in August 1991 to be a better (nondeployed) mother to her daughter, who was just eight months old when MaryEllen left for the desert. After hanging up her BDUs, she was a military spouse for another 20 years through lots of PCSs. She was a stay-at-home mom for 10 years, worked as a government civilian including 2.5 years as the \"Cadet Hostess\" at West Point, and held nonprofit manager and executive positions with lots of gratifying volunteer work. Her most interesting, challenging, and rewarding role was starting up (with Steve Cannon and Tony Guzzi) and leading the nonprofit Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund from inception to $50 million raised for scholarships for military children of the fallen or disabled. She retired in 2025 after 11 years in that career-culminating job and is finding she loves not working. She co-founded the Chicks of '86 with Julie DelGiorno and Carolyn Elliot-Lewis in 2010 to strengthen the bonds of women '86 classmates through annual gatherings and enhanced communications. She grew up just off Highway 9 in Freehold, New Jersey, home of \"The Boss,\" and is a Jersey girl through and through—she loves Springsteen, pizza, and not pumping her own gas.MaryEllen always enjoys catching up with classmates at reunions, on travel, Army sports events, or her favorite, a good happy hour. She can be reached at me.picciuto@gmail.com | 845-926-7875."},{"id":711,"n":"Dalton Pierce","u":"Dalton","g":"E2","p":"B3","em":"dalton.pierce73@gmail.com","tw":"Mound","st":"MN"},{"id":712,"n":"Scott Pierce","u":"Scott","g":"H4","p":"G1","ph":"203-979-7083","em":"spierce86@gmail.com","tw":"Cary","st":"NC","ac":"Pickleball","w":"Scott Pierce Scott lives in Cary, North Carolina. He has been married for 27 years and has three daughters: his oldest is an LTJG JAG in the US Navy after graduating from law school; his middle daughter is a UNC graduate and now a professional soccer player for Shelbourne in the Premier League of Ireland; and his youngest is striving to become an industrial engineer. His plebe company was G1 and he graduated from H4. His most memorable cadet experiences include the company boxing rivalries with G4 and I4, and seeing Bruce Springsteen in the Meadowlands in 1985 with classmates. He served in the 2nd ACR on the East-West German border when the walls came down, then left active duty to become a bond trader for JP Morgan and traded through the Asian debt crisis and fall of Long Term Capital Markets, then left the business to reenter the military in various special operations roles after the attacks of Sept 11th. He re-entered bond trading after the military break to help start a trading firm that eventually was sold to Banco Santander, so he continues to travel to NYC to complete the integration of the 2 firms. He enjoys working as a Field Force member in North Carolina interacting with West Point candidates, noting that these kids are a lot sharper than most of us were. He enjoys pickleball, canicross (running races with his dog) and leading the Second Dragoons Firepit Foundation (a 501c3). He can be reached at spierce86@gmail.com | 203-979-7083."},{"id":713,"n":"James Piggott","u":"Jim","g":"F4","p":"C1","ph":"904-669-0765","tw":"St Augustine","st":"FL","ac":"His current life centers on family, travel, and staying active. He and his wife have a cruise planned almost every month. He also plays golf and has spent years using golf as a primary outlet, especially during his Fort Polk era. He would likely enjoy travel, cruising, golfing, and relaxed social gatherings with classmates.","w":"Jim Piggott Jim lives in St. Augustine, Florida. He and his wife have two children, both living nearby in the St. Augustine area. They have two grandsons: Carson James and newborn Parker Gregory, both living within 20 minutes. Artillery defined his service, including fire direction work, chart-and-dart gunnery, and transition to battery computer systems. He served in Germany, Fort Lewis, and Korea; commanded a battery; and later served as the first Inspector General of the Maine National Guard. His years at West Point as assistant S-1, tactical officer, and Regimental XO were also major milestones. He retired from the Army in 2006 after 21 years and immediately transitioned to city government in St. Augustine, where he served as Director of General Services for 17 years, overseeing HR, purchasing, maintenance shops, the visitor center, and the marina. He and his wife fully retired in 2023. He grew up on a vegetable farm in Wappinger Falls, waking to his father playing reveille. He set the New York State discus record in high school, surpassing Al Oerter's mark, which led to West Point recruiting him. He later coached track throws at West Point and coached high school girls basketball for 12 years in Florida. He and his wife have a cruise planned almost every month. He plays golf and enjoys travel.He can be reached at piggottj@bellsouth.net | 904-669-0765."},{"id":714,"n":"Edgar Pigott","u":"Ed","g":"G4","p":"B2","ph":"719-553-7798","em":"edgarpigott@gmail.com","tw":"Medart","st":"FL","ac":"He enjoys informal social connection with classmates, particularly shared meals, travel, reunions, and sporting events. He has a strong interest in RV travel and visiting classmates across the country, often combining travel with reconnecting socially rather than structured activities. Basketball games and local sports also feature prominently. Travel, RV'ing, sports events","w":"Ed Pigott Ed Pigott lives in Medart, Florida, recently returned to his hometown after decades away. His older daughter, 31, lives in Brooklyn with her fiancé and works as a speech pathologist on travel assignments after studying in Colorado and Georgia. His younger daughter studied engineering and accounting at Colorado State University and now works in banking in Hampton, Virginia. Both daughters are independent and off the payroll. He served as an armor officer, drawn to the branch by lifelong familiarity with heavy equipment, and trained on older armored vehicles before the M1 at Fort Polk, where he valued the tight-knit group of classmates stationed there. He left the Army in 1990 during the post-Cold War drawdown and transitioned into manufacturing through a West Point connection. His civilian career spanned senior roles in heavy manufacturing, precision machining, energy, aerospace supply chains, and industrial operations across multiple states, frequently leading turnarounds and plant closures. He later became plant manager of solar PV module manufacturing after working for Exxon making gas pumps. He adopted RV living while continuing contract and leadership roles before entering semi-retirement. His cadet memories focus on B2 as a plebe and later G4, including being assigned to remedial marching due to lack of rhythm, then later becoming training sergeant and winning the guide-on for G4. He travels extensively by RV, visiting classmates across the country and combining travel with informal social connection through shared meals, reunions, and sporting events. He lives part-time in an RV on family land about 100 yards from the house he grew up in and is considering coaching youth sports. He can be reached at edgarpigott@gmail.com | 719-553-7798."},{"id":715,"n":"David Pinder","u":"David","g":"C3","p":"E2","ph":"952-240-4816","em":"dpinder@cardinalcorp.com","tw":"Eden Prairie","st":"MN","ac":"Golf, sporting events, and anything really.","w":"David Pinder Dave lives in Eden Prairie, Minnesota. He and his wife just had their first two grandchildren on September 1, 2025, twins, a boy and a girl. His plebe company was E2, graduating from C3. He served 10 years on active duty, including as a Desert Storm battery commander and later as a West Point TAC for Company G-4. His cadet memories are all positive—\"not one bad memory\" and he considers it an honor to be a member of the class. After the Army, he's been in the glass business for 28 years, serving the last 14 years as President of Cardinal Insulating Glass. Roughly 70% of all residential windows and doors contain Cardinal glass. He enjoys golf, sporting events, and \"anything really.\" He can be reached at dpinder@cardinalcorp.com | 952-240-4816."},{"id":716,"n":"Robert Pitulej","u":"Robert","g":"A3","p":"E1","ph":"(703) 4761528","em":"pitulej@aol.com","tw":"Reston","st":"VA"},{"id":717,"n":"Bret Platt","u":"Bret","g":"G2","p":"H4","ph":"540-841-4172","em":"bplatt62@gmail.com","tw":"Rome","st":"PA","w":"Bret Platt Bret and his wife Janet live in Rome, Pennsylvania, approaching their 40th anniversary in June 2026. They have four grown children, three sons and a daughter. They also have two grandchildren. Bret's first assignment took him to a Special Weapons unit in Longare, Italy, near Vicenza, where he worked multiple company grade positions before the site was decommissioned. After the advanced course he spent the bulk of his Army career at Fort Stewart and Hunter Army Airfield, moving through the Division Ammo Office, 724th Main Support Battalion, 24th Ordnance Company as commander, 260th Quartermaster Battalion, and the 24th Corps Support Group. His final military assignment was Maintenance Officer at Letterkenny Army Depot in Chambersburg, Pennsylvania. Leaving the Army in 1995, he worked program and project management consulting across Army depots, Air Force Air Logistics Centers, and after relocating to the DC area, multiple federal clients including TSA, DHS, EPA, Coast Guard, FEMA, DOL, DISA, and DLA. In 2016 he returned to federal service with the DLA Defense Agencies Initiative program office, retiring December 31, 2024 as DAI Portfolio Manager. He can be reached at bplatt62@gmail.com | 540-841-4172."},{"id":718,"n":"Richard Poirier","u":"Scott","g":"E1","p":"D4","ph":"617-694-3456","em":"scottpoirier@me.com","tw":"Wellesley","st":"MA","ac":"golf and pickleball","w":"Scott lives in Wellesley, Massachusetts. His son is a sophomore at the Naval Academy playing varsity squash, and his daughter is a senior in high school heading to Middlebury College next fall, also playing varsity squash. His plebe company was D4, graduating from E1. He served as a graduate assistant coach for tennis and squash at West Point, then as platoon leader, XO, and general staff in Germany. After earning his MBA, he built a finance career in New York City, London, and Boston before starting ProBuilder Financial LLC in 2016. He enjoys golf and pickleball. He can be reached at scottpoirier@me.com | 617-694-3456."},{"id":719,"n":"Clark Poland","u":"Clark","g":"H2","p":"C4","ph":"(314) 382-8991","em":"clarkpoland86@outlook.com"},{"id":720,"n":"Robert Pollard","u":"Lee","g":"A3","p":"H1","ph":"(919) 218-8115","em":"lee@computer-therapy.com","tw":"Jacksonville","st":"FL"},{"id":721,"n":"Michael Pompeo","u":"Mike","g":"C3","p":"A1","ph":"(316) 733-6896","em":"mikepompeo86@gmail.com"},{"id":722,"n":"John Poncy","u":"Ponce","g":"E1","p":"H3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":723,"n":"Joseph Posusney","u":"Joe","g":"F1","p":"H2","ph":"215-908-4885","em":"jopo29@gmail.com","tw":"Jacksonville","st":"FL","ac":"golf, fishing, boating, traveling, sporting events - soccer, football, etc.","w":"Joe Posusney Joe lives in Jacksonville, Florida. His daughter Meghan lives in Brooklyn with her husband Francesco. They both own an Italian restaurant called Sociale. He served with the 82nd Airborne MP Company at Fort Bragg, jumped into Panama, and deployed to Desert Storm/Shield. After the Army, he worked for Jon Guy as a Marketing Manager for a Swiss company and did a short tour at Waltron. He found his birth mother in 2018 and reunited to find he had a brother and sister with whom he now keeps contact. He golfs, fishes, boats, travels, and attends sporting events including soccer and football.He can be reached at jopo29@gmail.com | 215-908-4885."},{"id":724,"n":"Glenn Powers","u":"Glann","g":"E2","p":"G4","ph":"317-450-8183","em":"glennrobertpowers@gmail.com","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA","w":"Glenn Powers Glenn lives in Fairfax, Virginia with his wife, Robin. His oldest daughter Savannah also lives in Northern Virginia. His youngest daughter Libby lives in Dallas. Glenn can tell a good ghost story from his time in the 47th division with the G4 Guppies as a plebe, but his best memories are any with those loveable mutts the E-2 Dogs. He served a 20-year career as a light infantryman in the 7th Infantry Division, the 25th Infantry Division, and the 101st (Airborne) Division. Notable highlights include Operation Just Cause in Panama and Enduring Freedom in Afghanistan. In between those assignments he taught \"Dirt\" at West Point and served as a Professor of Military Science in Indianapolis. Upon Army retirement, Glenn became a regional director for the National Cemetery Administration (NCA) of the Department of Veterans Affairs. Fifteen years ago, NCA moved him to Washington to be the Deputy Under Secretary in charge of operations, something he has done ever since. At the last minute, Glenn's daughter Savannah changed a contract for the date of her wedding to deconflict it with the 40th reunion, freeing up her parents from the tough decision on which event to attend. He can be reached at glennrobertpowers@gmail.com | 317-450-8183."},{"id":725,"n":"David Pratt","u":"David","g":"G1","p":"B3","em":"dpratt245@comcast.net","tw":"Salinas","st":"CA","w":"David Pratt resides in Salinas, California, where he is fully retired and focused on family life and personal projects. He can be reached at dpratt245@comcast.net. As a cadet, he described his most meaningful experiences as occurring off campus rather than in formal settings of West Point. His cadet highlights consisted of traveling to away games, spending weekends with classmates’ families, visiting nearby relatives, and getting outside the wire during demanding academic terms, which he recalled as essential for recharging and maintaining balance. His most significant Army assignment followed graduation from OBC and flight school at Fort Rucker, when he served in the Aviation Brigade at Fort Ord in support of the 7th Infantry Division, including a deployment to Panama in 1989 as part of a joint task force immediately preceding Operation Just Cause; he resigned his commission in 1991 and ETS’d in the Monterey Bay area. After military service, he worked first in private manufacturing and later in the public sector in construction management and capital projects management for local government agencies, culminating in full retirement in 2024. Current interests include gardening, local hiking, RV travel, fly fishing in the Sierra Nevada, Army football travel, camping, home improvement projects, and spending time with his children and first grandchild."},{"id":726,"n":"Michael Preuss","u":"Mike","g":"A1","p":"B3","em":"preuss.mike@gmail.com","tw":"Jupiter","st":"FL"},{"id":727,"n":"Douglas Prevost","u":"Doug","g":"E4","p":"F1","em":"dougprevost@yahoo.com","tw":"Wasilla","st":"AK"},{"id":728,"n":"Jesus Prieto","u":"Jay","g":"B2","p":"E3","ph":"(610) 256-5674","em":"jprietousma@gmail.com","tw":"Malvern","st":"PA"},{"id":729,"n":"Scott Prihoda","u":"Scott","g":"E1","p":"A2","em":"Scottkprihoda@gmail.com","tw":"Downers Grove","st":"IL"},{"id":730,"n":"Matthew Pruden","u":"Matthew","g":"H4","p":"","ph":"(719) 406-2349","em":"mattjpruden@gmail.com","tw":"Pueblo","st":"CO"},{"id":731,"n":"Andrew Pullenza","u":"Andrew","g":"E4","p":"C2","ph":"(201) 978-0374","em":"apullenza@gmail.com","tw":"Fort Lee","st":"NJ"},{"id":732,"n":"LaVon Purnell-Wilson","u":"LaVon","g":"D2","p":"C3","ph":"703-434-9342","em":"lavon.purnell@gmail.com","tw":"Norfolk","st":"VA","af":"Gospel Choir","ac":"I would enjoy traveling with our classmates.","w":"LaVon Purnell-Wilson LaVon lives in Norfolk, Virginia. She has a 39-year-old stepson in Springfield, Ohio, a 37-year-old stepdaughter who is a police officer in Las Vegas, and a 34-year-old goddaughter near Atlanta. She has four grandchildren: granddaughters aged 16 and 6, and grandsons aged 8 and 5. LaVon served 28+ years in the Signal Corps. She commanded the 58th Signal Battalion in Okinawa, Japan and later served as commander of NATO Sector Norfolk under the NATO Communications and Information Systems Agency. As a cadet, she ran indoor and outdoor track and sang in the Cadet Gospel Choir. Since retiring, she served as Board Chair for the Crispus Attucks Cultural Center in Norfolk and founded Ocean Dreams Vacation Rentals, also in Norfolk. LaVon enjoys traveling and would welcome opportunities to travel with classmates. She can be reached at lavon.purnell@gmail.com | 703-434-9342."},{"id":733,"n":"William Pursel","u":"Bill","g":"G3","p":"H4","ph":"513-477-5708","em":"billpursel@aol.com","tw":"Watkins","st":"CO","ac":"Chess tournaments, attending sporting events. He enjoys travel, social connection, and veteran-service work. He is active in the VFW and American Legion, likes walking daily, and values time with friends. Colorado remains a major recreational base for him.","w":"Bill Pursel Weas lives in Watkins, Colorado. His daughter Kristin has a two-year-old son, CJ, living in Cincinnati. He served in short-range air defense and later as a Patriot officer. During Desert Storm he and a three-soldier crew shot down five Scuds, earning a Bronze Star. He valued his Germany tour, teaching the Patriot course at Fort Bliss, and the sustained camaraderie with soldiers he still hears from decades later. He entered sales with General Mills, then spent more than twenty years with Lawson Products in sales and sales leadership, including running military/government sales. After moving to Denver he worked for UPS, the Postal Service, United Airlines catering operations, and then 7-Eleven, where he has served in food safety, quality assurance, and financial planning and analysis for eight years. He survived brain cancer after surgery, chemo, and radiation, aided by classmate Jeff Thramann's guidance. He maintains a 10,000-steps-a-day streak approaching 3,300 consecutive days—almost nine years. He is deeply involved in veterans' organizations, served five years as VFW quartermaster, and continues hands-on support to veterans and surviving families. He and his wife Jenn completed visits to all 50 states and now live in Colorado with their two Shih Tzus, Fireball and Merlin. He attends chess tournaments and sporting events, and values time with friends. He can be reached at billpursel@aol.com | 513-477-5708."},{"id":734,"n":"James Quaider","u":"Jim","g":"G1","p":"F2","ph":"817-975-2752","em":"jq86@ymail.com","tw":"Mansfield","st":"TX","ac":"Enjoy hanging out catching up and sporting events","w":"James Quaider resides in Mansfield, Texas, where he works as a Senior Supervisory Principal at Citi Group. Contact information includes (817) 975-2752 and jq86@ymail.com. His command assignment in Germany was a defining Army highlight, serving in Leipheim in southern Germany. After military service, he began a career in financial services, starting as a Financial Advisor, advancing to District Manager, and ultimately moving into senior supervisory roles, including time with USAA until it sold its investment business, culminating in his current position at Citi Group. His current interests include spending time with friends and family, catching up with classmates, and attending sporting events. His family includes two children, a daughter and a son, and one granddaughter who recently turned four and, by her own account, is nearly five."},{"id":735,"n":"Leopoldo Quintas","u":"Lee","g":"A1","p":"H3","ph":"703-851-6031","em":"quintaslee@gmail.com","tw":"Lancaster","st":"SC","ac":"All those sound good!","w":"Lee Quintas Lee lives in Lancaster, South Carolina. His son Samuel is a firefighter with the Asheville Fire Department, married with a two-year-old son named Rowan. His daughter Emma is a stay-at-home mom in Columbia, South Carolina, married with a two-year-old son named Rhett. His best assignment was serving as Division Commander of the 3rd Infantry Division. After the Army, he became an Army Senior Mentor and serves on the WPAOG Board. He can be reached at quintaslee@gmail.com | 703-851-6031."},{"id":736,"n":"Keith Raines","u":"Keith","g":"C4","p":"I1"},{"id":737,"n":"Keith Ramsey","u":"Keith","g":"E1","p":"B4","ph":"571-217-6100","em":"keith@kramsey.net","tw":"Morrison","st":"TN"},{"id":738,"n":"Jaimy (Just) Rand","u":"Jaimy","g":"H3","p":"","ph":"254-220-3032","em":"jaimyrand@yahoo.com","tw":"Harborcreek","st":"PA","ac":"Frank and I are both retired and like to stay active.  We like taking advantage of the flexibility for travel and we like to play golf.","w":"Jaimy (Just) Rand Jaimy lives in Harborcreek, PA with her husband Frank. They've been married for 35 years and have one daughter in her final year of undergrad. She was a plebe in A-2 and an upperclassman in H-3, where the company became the H-3 Hamsters and acquired a mascot hamster named Sparky who lived in her room with roommate Leanne Garner. She commissioned into the MP Corps and after company command transitioned to Acquisition Corps. After grad school at University of Texas, she served in testing, contracting, and program management roles with her final assignment as Commander, Fort Hood Contracting Command. Stateside she was assigned to Fort McClellan, Fort Hood, and the Pentagon, and overseas to Pirmasens and Heidelberg, Germany. She deployed to the Balkans and to Iraq. One of her most memorable assignments was two years in DC, where the first year she led the ASAALT team in the Army ten miler and exactly one year later she and Frank had their daughter Reagan. After Army retirement she was employed at General Electric in Erie, PA establishing agreements for freight locomotive engineered systems, then went back to federal service at the VA in various contracting roles. She and Frank are both retired and like to stay active, take advantage of the flexibility for travel, and play golf. She can be reached at jaimyrand@yahoo.com | 254-220-3032."},{"id":739,"n":"Edwin Randolph","u":"Bruce","g":"G4","p":"C2","ph":"817-937-7134","em":"brandolph@earthlink.net","tw":"Plano","st":"TX","w":"Bruce Randolph Bruce Randolph lives in Plano, Texas. His most vivid West Point memory is playing Colonel \"Tex\" Turner in the 100th night show. He served as scout platoon leader for A Troop, 2/1 CAV with 2AD at Fort Hood—Patton's Division—before moving into manufacturing supervision for six years in steel stamping and semiconductors, then working as a software engineer for the last 26 years. He has lost 35 pounds in the last two years. He can be reached at brandolph@earthlink.net | 817-937-7134."},{"id":740,"n":"Patrick Reardon","u":"Patrick","g":"A1","p":"","ph":"714-697-0826","em":"reardonpd@gmail.com","tw":"Cypress","st":"CA"},{"id":741,"n":"John Recke","u":"John","g":"H2","p":"A3","ph":"(205) 647-3791","em":"jrecke2011@gmail.com","tw":"Gardendale","st":"AL"},{"id":742,"n":"Christopher Reed","u":"Christopher","g":"D1","p":"E3","ph":"+39 347 902-1954","em":"CDRINF@aol.com","tw":"APO","st":"AE","ac":"Travel/attending sports events.","w":"Christopher Reed Chris lives in Vicenza, Italy with his lovely wife and Desert Shield/Storm pen pal, Melissa. He has one son, Michael, who works as an audio engineer based in Nashville. His plebe company was E3, graduating from D1.His cadet memories include never ceasing to be amazed by the creativity of bored cadets—watching cadets roll a giant snowball and wedge it into a sally port, and the Sosh Show on WKDT cow year when after taps the DJ played Twisted Sister's \"We're Not Gonna Take It\" and the entire Corps blasted their stereo speakers out the barracks windows singing along. He did the Infantry thing for 30 years. His early claim to fame was going AWOL by not reporting to IOAC and going back to his old battalion, 1-327 Infantry in the 101st, so he could deploy with them to Desert Shield/Storm—he didn't get paid for six months for his efforts, but did meet and marry his pen pal, Melissa, so it all worked out. He became a training guy by mid-career, serving as a JRTC and BCTP O/C, commanding 1-19 Infantry at Fort Benning, and doing multiple tours as an advisor in Iraq and Afghanistan, culminating with command of NATO. Training Mission Afghanistan’s Regional Support Command South in Khandahar. The best assignment came at the end of his career when he got to be the senior US liaison officer at British Army HQ in the UK. After doing contract work for the Army, he became a DoD Civilian in 2017 and for the last six years has been in Vicenza, Italy as Deputy G7 for the Southern European Task Force, Africa (SETAF-AF) overseeing the development and management of training exercises in Europe and Africa. He has been skydiving as a hobby since lieutenant days at Fort Campbell and is still very active in the sport with 2,700+ jumps. His cadet car was a VW Beetle, the only one in the cadet parking lot. He parted with it in 1996 but after retiring acquired a 1971 VW Bus that became a second hobby—it's in the care of his cousin, a ‘94 Grad, in Kansas while he's in Italy. He enjoys travel and studying military history. He can be reached at CDRINF@aol.com or +39 347 902-1954"},{"id":743,"n":"Michael Reed","u":"Mike","g":"E3","p":"C4","ph":"(630) 232-7801","em":"reedmt5@msn.com","tw":"Geneva","st":"IL","ac":"His lifelong interests center on reading history, hiking, outdoor activity, and soccer, which he has played continuously since childhood. He still enjoys physical challenges and high-adventure outdoor settings. Nothing specific was stated about future classmate activities, but his interests suggest he would gravitate toward outdoor excursions, hikes, or informal gatherings.","w":"Mike Reed Mike lives in Geneva, Illinois. He and his wife Maureen have two adult children. Their son Travis is an electrical and computer engineer who also programs high-tolerance machining systems and once interned on analytics code still used today. Their daughter Olivia is married and lives across town in the Chicago area. His plebe company was C4. He remembers escaping to the library stacks during plebe stress, exploring old Howitzers, and listening to music where no one would haze him. His defining professional moment was receiving both a Bradley platoon and then an entire mortar platoon that he rehabilitated before Reforger 88, accumulating nearly three years of platoon-leader time. After the Army, he moved directly into engineering with Parsons, running and commissioning power plants at a prison, then UCLA, and later globally, leading to major field roles in Iraq and Nigeria. During the 2000s he shifted into industrial predictive analytics, joining SmartSignal, then GE, and later InStep and Schneider/AVEVA. He now works in an AI center of excellence integrating analytics across industrial software systems. He has lived and worked on four continents, survived malaria, dealt with corruption in Nigeria, and black-started UCLA's power plant after the Northridge earthquake. He met his wife while both were serving in West Germany. His lifelong interests center on reading history, hiking, outdoor activity, and soccer, which he has played continuously since childhood. He still enjoys physical challenges and high-adventure outdoor settings. He can be reached at reedmt5@msn.com | 630-232-7801."},{"id":744,"n":"David Regan","u":"David","g":"C3","p":"I1","ph":"703-772-2538","em":"reganjdp@verizon.net","tw":"Dumfries","st":"VA"},{"id":745,"n":"Daniel Regna","u":"Dan","g":"I2","p":"F3","em":"daniel.regna@outlook.com","tw":"Woodstock","st":"IL"},{"id":746,"n":"Samuel Reider","u":"Samuel","g":"G4","p":"E3","ph":"(410) 357-4653","em":"samuel.reider@libertymutual.com","tw":"Parkton","st":"MD"},{"id":747,"n":"Christopher Reilly","u":"Christopher","g":"B4","p":"G3","ph":"901-604-0348","em":"chrisdreilly1986@gmail.com","tw":"Middletown","st":"DE"},{"id":748,"n":"Jill (Spangler) Reilly","u":"Jill","g":"A4","p":"H2","ph":"901-240-6396","em":"cjreilly3849@yahoo.com","tw":"Middletown","st":"DE","ac":"I would enjoy travel, hiking, walking, attending sports, visiting museums/historical sites","w":"Jill Reilly Jill and Chris (B-4) live in Middletown, DE, have two children and two grandchildren. She was a stay-at-home mom for about 10 years, then began teaching math and coaching various sports in independent schools. She travels, hikes, walks, attends sports, and visits museums and historical sites. She can be reached at cjreilly3849@yahoo.com | 901-240-6396."},{"id":749,"n":"Jonathan Reinebold","u":"Jon","g":"F2","p":"B4","ph":"808-372-4854","em":"jreinebold@mac.com","tw":"Kekaha","st":"HI","ac":"Playing sports, or watching, hiking and traveling are my preferred activities.","w":"Jon lives in Kekaha, Hawaii. His daughter is a lieutenant in the USCG in Virginia Beach, and his son is a captain in the USMC in Kaneohe. He served chasing drug runners in the Bahamas, in special ops aviation, and on duty in Japan. After the Army, he was an EMS pilot for a few years, then retired. He participates in sports events and travels. He can be reached at jreinebold@mac.com | 808-372-4854."},{"id":750,"n":"Mary Bridget Reynolds","u":"Mary","g":"G1","p":"G3","ph":"248.343.3268","em":"Mbridr@gmail.com","tw":"Upatoi","st":"GA","ac":"I dont travel much anymore, so local sports to watch or play","w":"Mary Bridget Reynolds resides in Upatoi, Georgia, where she is retired. Contact information includes (248) 343-3268 and mbridr@gmail.com. Her Army career followed a split path, as she left active service in 1995, returned to service following September 11, and retired in 2016, continuing in the same functional line of work both in and out of uniform. After military service, she concluded her professional life in that same field before fully retiring. Her current interests focus on local sports, both watching and playing, and noted that she does not travel much anymore. Her family includes seven children, eleven grandchildren, and one great-grandchild."},{"id":751,"n":"Hugh Rhodes","u":"Hugh","g":"A4","p":"G3","ph":"937-626-0204","em":"dtaew@hotmail.com","tw":"Springboro","st":"OH"},{"id":752,"n":"Ronald Rice","u":"Ron","g":"B3","p":"","ph":"(850) 386-2001","em":"ron.rice@manausa.com","tw":"Tallahassee","st":"FL"},{"id":753,"n":"Clifford Richardson","u":"Clifford","g":"C4","p":"E3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":754,"n":"Kenneth Ring","u":"Ken","g":"D2","p":"F4","ph":"317-370-6459","em":"ken.ring1986@gmail.com","tw":"Cape Coral","st":"FL"},{"id":755,"n":"Ruben Rios","u":"Ruben","g":"G3","p":"E4","ph":"412-215-5214","em":"rubenarobles@outlook.com","tw":"Philadelphia","st":"PA","ac":"Attending and watching college & NFL games, traveling, skiing, scuba diving, and partying.","w":"Ruben Rios Ruben lives in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. He has three children: Alexa, 20; Michael, 22; and Ruben Jr., 35, who has an eight-month-old daughter, Lucia. Ruben's favorite memory is going out with friends to New York City. He did not serve in the Army due to his status as a foreign cadet at graduation. After West Point, he worked for various corporations for 36 years. Since 2023, he runs his own real estate investment firm. Ruben enjoys attending and watching college and NFL games, traveling, skiing, scuba diving, and partying. He can be reached at rubenarobles@outlook.com | 412-215-5214."},{"id":756,"n":"Daniel Rizzo","u":"Dan","g":"B4","p":"F3","ph":"847-721-9236","em":"dannyrizzo@hotmail.com","tw":"Nokesville","st":"VA","ac":"Dan would enjoy skiing, scuba diving, and cooking with classmates. As a cadet, he was deeply involved in both the Ski and Scuba Clubs—serving as president of the Ski Club and organizing Scuba Club spring break trips. He also enjoys good food, music, festivals, and New Orleans culture. He’s a passionate cook and baker and created a mobile pizza oven business after leaving the Army.","w":"Dan Rizzo Riz lives in Nokesville, Virginia. He has two sons: Michael, 28, who lives in the Chicago area and works in game design with a strong interest in Bitcoin and technology, and David, 25, who graduated from Purdue with a degree in mechanical engineering and works in a civil engineering lab focusing on concrete testing. Both sons live near their mother in the Chicago area. Dan is divorced. He served with 5th Infantry Division, stationed at Fort Polk as both platoon leader and XO, and later worked in public affairs. A standout moment was getting a tank airborne at NTC by driving full speed over a hill. He also trained at Jungle School with classmates like Chris \"Bumper\" Greer. After leaving the Army, he worked primarily in small manufacturing companies, especially fasteners. While living in the Chicago area, he designed and built a mobile wood-fired pizza oven and launched a business selling pizza at farmers markets and catering private events. He pursued an MBA at Northwestern in the late 1990s. He was one of the oldest cadets in the class, turning 22 at R-Day, and came to West Point after time in the Army and at the University of Minnesota. He's active in the Unity Call, a confidential peer-support group for classmates. He skis, scuba dives, and cooks. He can be reached at dannyrizzo@hotmail.com | 847-721-9236."},{"id":757,"n":"David Roberts","u":"David","g":"G2","p":"G1","ph":"850-892-2946","em":"davida.roberts@dot.state.fl.us","tw":"Ponce De Leon","st":"FL"},{"id":758,"n":"Ruben Robles","u":"Ruben","g":"C3","p":"G2","em":"rubenarobles@outlook.com","tw":"Lower Gwynedd","st":"PA"},{"id":759,"n":"Jonathan Rodden","u":"Jonathan","g":"D2","p":"H3","em":"jonathan.d.rodden.civ@mail.mil","tw":"FPO","st":"AE"},{"id":760,"n":"Daniel Rodstrom","u":"Dan","g":"F2","p":"I3","em":"djrodstrom@gmail.com","tw":"Estero","st":"FL","w":"Dan Rodstrom Dan lives in Estero, Florida. He is retired. He can be reached at djrodstrom@gmail.com"},{"id":761,"n":"James Rogers","u":"Jim","g":"A3","p":"G2","ph":"(350) 108-6710","em":"Jim@uschina.us","tw":"Wilmington","st":"DE"},{"id":762,"n":"Warren Rogers","u":"Dean","g":"G3","p":"F2","ph":"717-533-2358","em":"intel17@aol.com","tw":"Hershey","st":"PA"},{"id":763,"n":"Robert Roggeman","u":"Robert","g":"H2","p":"A4","ph":"(813) 446-5656","em":"robert.roggeman@sagusa.org","tw":"Valrico","st":"FL"},{"id":764,"n":"Craig Rollins","u":"Craig","g":"G3","p":"D2","ph":"(803) 984-5266","em":"craigr220@aol.com","tw":"Rock Hill","st":"SC","ac":"Golf, skiing and attending any college football games","w":"Craig Rollins Craig lives in Rock Hill, South Carolina. His son Chad is married in Denver and expecting a first child in March 2026, and his daughter Reagan is single in Charlotte. He served in aviation, stationed in Wiesbaden, Germany for over three years, Desert Shield/Storm for one year, Fort Huachuca for one year, and Orlando for two years with counter-drug, counter-insurgent missions. He recalls doing only two things wrong at West Point and getting caught on both—almost becoming a double-century man. He worked for the same industrial packaging company for 30 years, serving as VP/GM from 2016-2024. He delivered his first child unexpectedly at home, retired at 60, and is loving life. He golfs, skis, and attends college football games. He can be reached at craigr220@aol.com | 803-984-5266."},{"id":765,"n":"Michael Root","u":"Michael","g":"H3","p":"F4","ph":"(636) 458-7686","em":"rootboy6@gmail.com","tw":"Saint Clair","st":"MO"},{"id":766,"n":"Molly (Hagen) Root","u":"Molly","g":"H3","p":"","ph":"(636) 458-7686","em":"mmroot@hotmail.com","tw":"Saint Clair","st":"MO"},{"id":767,"n":"John Roper","u":"John","g":"B4","p":"H2","ph":"803-521-5493","em":"jwr0407@gmail.com","tw":"Irmo","st":"SC"},{"id":768,"n":"Troy Roper","u":"Troy","g":"B1","p":"I3","ph":"(425) 497-1555","em":"troy.w.roper@gmail.com","tw":"Woodinville","st":"WA"},{"id":769,"n":"Peter Rosen","u":"Peter","g":"H4","p":"C1","ph":"(612) 251-0910","em":"peter.rosen.64@gmail.com","tw":"Saint Paul","st":"MN"},{"id":770,"n":"Matthew Rotella","u":"Matt","g":"A2","p":"G1","ph":"201-638-2055","em":"financeguy63@gmail.com","tw":"Kinnelon","st":"NJ"},{"id":771,"n":"Bridget Rourke","u":"Bridget","g":"D1","p":"H2","ph":"(210) 854-8656","em":"bridgetrourke@hotmail.com","tw":"Chillicothe","st":"OH","ac":"Rich and I enjoy biking, hiking and sporting events.  We make time every year for trips to see the children, the great USA, and Europe.","w":"Bridget Rourke Bridget lives in Chillicothe, Ohio. She married Richard Arnold, a fellow Buckeye and USAF Officer. They have two children: Matthew and his wife Anchor are USMA Class of 2020 and stationed at Fort Bragg; Mary, USMA Class of 2022, is doing a year with a Recruiting Battalion in Minneapolis. Her plebe company was H2, graduating from D1. Her most memorable cadet experience was Graduation Day. She loved the Army and spent just over 29 years serving. Though Battalion and Brigade Command were awesome, her most satisfying assignment was as the CJ2 for CJTF-Horn of Africa. She returned home to small town Ohio as a home health aide to her aging parents and a volunteer for many social outreach service organizations in town. She runs her own calendar and couldn't imagine being anywhere else. She and Rich enjoy biking, hiking, and sporting events. They make time every year for trips to see the children, travel around the USA, and visit Europe. He can be reached at bridgetrourke@hotmail.com | 210-854-8656."},{"id":772,"n":"Bryan Rudacille","u":"Bryan","g":"C4","p":"","em":"Bryrud275@gmail.com","tw":"Virginia Beach","st":"VA"},{"id":773,"n":"Theresa Rudacille","u":"Theresa","g":"A4","p":"A3","ph":"(571) 465-6048","em":"trudacille@gmail.com","tw":"Virginia Beach","st":"VA"},{"id":774,"n":"Paul Rush","u":"Paul","g":"H2","p":"","ph":"(845) 985-7910","em":"prush@hvc.rr.com","tw":"Grahamsville","st":"NY"},{"id":775,"n":"Robert Rush","u":"Bobby","g":"F3","p":"H1","ph":"(360) 556-2838","em":"rmrj64@hotmail.com","tw":"Bellingham","st":"WA"},{"id":776,"n":"Matthew Russo","u":"Matt","g":"F1","p":"A4","ph":"(919) 418-9079","em":"mattrusso86@gmail.com","tw":"Pittsboro","st":"NC"},{"id":777,"n":"David Rutherford","u":"David","g":"I3","p":"G1","tw":"Louisville","st":"KY"},{"id":778,"n":"William Ryan","u":"Bill","g":"E3","p":"I4","em":"provenroi@gmail.com","tw":"De Pere","st":"WI"},{"id":779,"n":"Steven Sabia","u":"Steve","g":"H3","p":"","ph":"703-609-1098","em":"ssabia@hotmail.com","tw":"Woodbridge","st":"VA","w":"Steven Sabia Steve lives in Woodbridge, Virginia. He branched Infantry. He can be reached at ssabia@hotmail.com | 703-609-1098."},{"id":780,"n":"Robert Sadowski","u":"Bob","g":"I3","p":"E2","ph":"586-215-2990","em":"robert.w.sadowski2.civ@army.mil","tw":"Lake Orion","st":"MI"},{"id":781,"n":"James Saldivar","u":"James","g":"I2","p":"G1","ph":"(310) 377-0429","em":"saldivar_james@yahoo.com","tw":"San Jose","st":"CA"},{"id":782,"n":"Brian Samela","u":"Brian","g":"I4","p":"D3","ph":"518-369-9029","em":"briansamela1@gmail.com","tw":"Altamont","st":"NY"},{"id":783,"n":"Roger Sangvic","u":"Roger","g":"F1","p":"A2","ph":"717-422-4518","em":"roger.sangvic@gmail.com","tw":"Clarksville","st":"MD"},{"id":784,"n":"Mark Santarelli","u":"Mark","g":"A1","p":"E4","em":"balarranaga@aol.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":785,"n":"Gerald Sarnelli","u":"Jerry","g":"B2","p":"G4","ph":"(203) 938-9443","em":"gerald.sarnelli@gmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":786,"n":"James Saso","u":"Jim","g":"I1","p":"A3","em":"Jnlsaso@att.net","tw":"Wolfforth","st":"TX"},{"id":787,"n":"Cynthia (Isler) Sauer","u":"Cindy","g":"D3","p":"C4","em":"sauercyndi@gmail.com","tw":"Westlake Village","st":"CA"},{"id":788,"n":"Scott Sauer","u":"Scott","g":"F3","p":"C4","ph":"202-250-4901","em":"smsauer1986@gmail.com","tw":"Westlake Village","st":"CA","ac":"Running, golf, socializing with friends","w":"Scott Sauer Scott lives in Westlake Village, California. His son David, 23, works in Japan as an English teacher. His daughter Hannah, 20, works as a teacher's assistant in Newbury Park, California. He served with 2nd ACR in Amberg, Germany, and 1/4 CAV with 1st Infantry Division during the Gulf War. After the Army, he became an Audit Partner (CPA) with Deloitte & Touche LLP and retired in September 2025. He's transitioning to public and private company board roles and currently serves on the WPAOG Board of Directors. He's been married to Cyndi (Isler) for 32 years. He runs, golfs, and socializes with friends. He can be reached at smsauer1986@gmail.com | 202-250-4901."},{"id":789,"n":"Daniel Sauter","u":"Dan","g":"G3","p":"C4","ph":"760-267-7079","em":"dansauter3@gmail.com","tw":"Huntsville","st":"AL","ac":"Sports; Army events; Golf; Travel","w":"Dan Sauter Dan lives in Huntsville, Alabama. He has four children: Daniel and Leora (with Danny and Emma) in Philadelphia; Michael and Julia (with Leni and Roman) at Cannon AFB, New Mexico; Matthew and Olivia at Fort Leonard Wood heading to Fort Hood; and Jack at Cornell in New York City. Dan's best leadership experience was watching Coach Jim Young lead Army football back to a winning tradition. His favorite story or memory: pick any day in G-3, the company in the best class. He had the opportunity to serve with and help develop young American men and women over 27 years. After the Army, he worked for Lockheed Martin, where he has retired, and is currently with a startup. The Sauters were stationed with Rob (Rogge) Roggeman and family at six different duty locations. Mick Haydak and Rogge are godfathers to two of their boys. Dan enjoys sports, Army events, golf, and travel. He can be reached at dansauter3@gmail.com | 760-267-7079."},{"id":790,"n":"Thomas Sawyer","u":"Tom","g":"B1","p":"C3","em":"sharkbite83@yahoo.com","tw":"Schertz","st":"TX"},{"id":791,"n":"Michael Scanlin","u":"Scans","g":"C4","p":"G2","ph":"703-201-0842","em":"mscanlin86@gmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":792,"n":"Eric Schacht","u":"Eric","g":"D3","p":"G2","ph":"706-993-5431","em":"ericschacht@icloud.com","tw":"Kansas City","st":"MO","af":"150-Pound Football","ac":"Golf outings, Army games, Fishing outings - fresh water only, travel.","w":"Eric Schacht Eric lives in Kansas City, Missouri and remains single after divorcing in 2014 following 24 years of marriage. He has two children: Meg Ross is married to an Army Field Artillery Major stationed at Fort Stewart, Georgia. Meg and Geoff have two daughters, Emma (13) and Elli (9), and Geoff is currently deployed to Poland. Brian is an aviator married to Caisley Schacht (Ladd), daughter of Keith and Claudia Ladd (Class of '87). They have two daughters, Maeve (5) and Josie (2), and are currently stationed at Fort Huachuca, Arizona, where Brian works as a fixed wing aviator for T2COM. He lost his middle child Justin in 2007 when he was 15 and a half. His plebe company was G2, graduating from D3. His most memorable cadet experience was the 150-pound football game at Cornell as a freshman when he and Jim Howard got hauled out of a frat house after the game by their Senior OR, Colonel Jim Kays, well after midnight. He commanded 1-26 Infantry with a couple of trips to Iraq in 2004-2005 and 2006-2007, describing them as tough times in that theater. Since retiring from active duty in 2016, he has been a facilitator at the School of Command Preparation, preparing battalion commanders and command sergeants major for their roles. He enjoys golf outings, Army games, freshwater fishing outings, and travel. He can be reached at ericschacht@icloud.com | 706-993-5431."},{"id":793,"n":"Daniel Schafer","u":"Dan","g":"B4","p":"C2","ph":"405-245-8044","em":"rangerdan86@gmail.com","tw":"Naples","st":"FL","af":"Wrestling","ac":"Dan enjoys travel tied to work and makes a point of reconnecting with classmates wherever business takes him. He values informal social gatherings such as happy hours, meals, and reunions rather than structured events. He remains physically active with gym training, yoga, and resistance workouts and enjoys sports culture broadly, particularly wrestling and rugby, and appreciates opportunities to reconnect through shared experiences rather than formal programs.","w":"Dan Schafer Dan lives in Naples, Florida, with his wife Kimberly. He has four biological children and one stepdaughter. His oldest daughter lives in Chicago, is married, and works in theater and fitness management. His son is a former high-level collegiate wrestler who now coaches wrestling at the University of Arkansas at Little Rock. His second daughter lives in New York City and works professionally in musical theater. His youngest biological daughter lives in South Carolina and works as a chef. His stepdaughter is a college student in Alabama studying commercial interior design. No grandchildren yet, though several \"granddogs.\" He served as a field artillery officer in light units, including airborne-capable artillery, with assignments in California and Fort Sill. He attended Ranger School to build credibility supporting infantry units and later taught officer basic courses. He left active duty in the early 1990s after the birth of his first child and transitioned into civilian sales. He initially sold medical products, then moved into technology sales where he built a long career. His current role focuses on business development and new client acquisition, a position he has held for approximately 15 years. He grew up in Normal, Illinois, wrestled competitively, and was recruited to West Point primarily for wrestling. He travels for work and makes a point of reconnecting with classmates wherever business takes him. He can be reached at rangerdan86@gmail.com | 405-245-8044."},{"id":794,"n":"Joseph Schafer","u":"Joe","g":"A4","p":"C1","ph":"703-870-9787","em":"joseph.schafer@live.com","tw":"Arlington","st":"VA"},{"id":795,"n":"Mark Schake","u":"Mark","g":"H2","p":"I4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":796,"n":"Jeffrey Schamburg","u":"Jeff","g":"H3","p":"D4","ph":"(831) 241-4911","em":"schamburgj@yahoo.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL"},{"id":797,"n":"Miyako (Newell) Schanely","u":"Miyako","g":"F1","p":"H3","em":"mnschanely@twcny.rr.com","tw":"Eagle Bay","st":"NY"},{"id":798,"n":"Eric Scheidemantel","u":"Eric","g":"I4","p":"C1","ph":"(703) 753-1250","em":"scheids730@comcast.net","tw":"Bristow","st":"VA"},{"id":799,"n":"Robert Scheider","u":"Robert","g":"C3","p":"A1","em":"bob_scheider@yahoo.com"},{"id":800,"n":"Alfred Schellhorn","u":"Al","g":"H4","p":"A1","ph":"(205) 908-7565","em":"alschellhorn@yahoo.com","tw":"Acworth","st":"GA","ac":"Golf, fishing, attending Army football games (home or road)"},{"id":801,"n":"Richard Schemel","u":"Rick","g":"A1","p":"E2","ph":"573-513-2139","em":"rick@schemelcompanies.com","tw":"Perryville","st":"MO","ac":"Love to ski and deep sea fish.","w":"Rick Schemel Rick lives in Perryville, Missouri. His daughter Julia, 35, was at West Point (Class of 2012) until suffering a head injury. She is married and lives in Florida. His daughter Olivia, 34, is married with four boys and lives nearby in Perryville. Rick served with the 101st at Fort Campbell, Kentucky and loved his platoon leader time. He currently owns and operates two construction companies. In his off time he loves to ski and deep sea fish. He can be reached at rick@schemelcompanies.com | 573-513-2139."},{"id":802,"n":"Mark Schemine","u":"Mark","g":"D4","p":"A2","em":"mark.schemine@gmail.com","tw":"Fort Mill","st":"SC"},{"id":803,"n":"Chris Schiavo","u":"Chris","g":"E2","p":"A1","ph":"804-683-3344","em":"chrisschiavo4464@gmail.com","tw":"Glen Allen","st":"VA"},{"id":804,"n":"William Schiffer","u":"William","g":"A3","p":"F2","em":"schiffer.bill@gmail.com","tw":"Ridgefield","st":"CT"},{"id":805,"n":"Joel Schlachtenhaufen","u":"Joel","g":"G3","p":"I4","ph":"612-207-5149","em":"schlachty@gmail.com","tw":"Plymouth","st":"MN","af":"Rabble Rousers","ac":"He enjoys travel, especially trips connected to reunions and informal social gatherings with classmates. He values shared experiences such as sporting events, college trips, hiking, and time together away from structured activities. He remains closely connected to G3 classmates and enjoys company-based gatherings.","w":"Joel lives in Scottsdale, Arizona. He has four children: three sons close in age and a daughter a few years younger. His oldest son served four years in the Marine Corps and completed a computer science degree at the University of Iowa. His middle son works as an area manager for Speedway convenience stores and his third son excels in youth-focused roles with school-based after-school programs.  His daughter is pursuing an online marketing degree after transferring back closer to home. His children are all located in Twin Cities area. Joel served in aviation, initially flying fixed-wing aircraft (C-12) in Korea on VIP and military transport missions across the peninsula, to Japan, and occasionally elsewhere in the region. He then dual-branched Aviation and Military Intelligence, helped write doctrine for a new fixed-wing platform, and commanded one of the Army's earliest unmanned aerial vehicle units. He left active duty in 1995 to pursue an MBA at the University of Michigan. His civilian career included consulting at Deloitte, entrepreneurial startups during the dot-com era, a corporate role at Target, and over 18 years back at Deloitte as a partner leading complex M&A transactions including major divestitures during the AIG financial crisis. He is now approaching mandatory retirement while planning a transition period. He grew up in Iowa and entered West Point with little preparation, drawn largely by independence and opportunity rather than tradition. A defining cadet memory was running the sound system for the Rabble Rousers and cheerleaders, which allowed him to travel to all games while avoiding many routine obligations. He recalls Beast Barracks as culture shock and coping with pressure through humor rather than intimidation. He enjoys travel, especially trips connected to reunions and informal gatherings with classmates, and values shared experiences like concerts, sporting events, college trips, and hiking. He and his partner Leisa split time between Minnesota and Arizona. He can be reached at schlachty@gmail.com | 612-207-5149."},{"id":806,"n":"Vernon Schoonover","u":"Glenn","g":"G2","p":"D3","em":"glennsch@live.com","tw":"Winchester","st":"VA","w":"Glenn Schoonover Glennlives in Winchester, VA with three grandchildren: Alice (8), Matthew (3), and David (1). His first assignment after graduation was with 1st SOCOM, 96th CA Bn (A) at Ft. Bragg from '87-'91, where he deployed to Africa several times supporting Special Forces exercises and participated in Just Cause with several classmates, then Desert Storm. After his advanced course he was assigned to the 101st Airborne Division, where he commanded the Army's only Airborne, Air Assault Parachute Rigger company. The highlight of his command was participating in the 50th Anniversary of the D-Day jump into France in 1994, flying from England across the English channel in C-130s and parachuting into Northern France. He was then sent to school and ended up at the Pentagon as a 53 (System Automation Officer), becoming the first Director of Network Security at the Pentagon. In 2000 he left the Army and was hired by a startup called Inter.net, then landed at Microsoft in 2003 as a cyber security advisor to Federal clients. After 8 years he returned to the startup world before becoming CISO for the State of Vermont, where he ran into classmate and former prepster Larry Seaberg who was working for Keurig in Waterbury. He is currently an Executive Partner at Gartner. As a 2LT at Ft. Bragg he earned his private pilot's license and still flies whenever he can. He can be reached at glennsch@live.com."},{"id":807,"n":"Daniel Schultz","u":"Daniel","g":"C2","p":"G3","ph":"(516) 488-5556","em":"danztlu@gmail.com","tw":"Franklin Square","st":"NY"},{"id":808,"n":"Jill Schurtz","u":"Jill","g":"I3","p":"I2","ph":"(646) 773-6177","em":"jillschurtz@gmail.com","tw":"Wayzata","st":"MN"},{"id":809,"n":"Scott Schutzmeister","u":"Scott","g":"H3","p":"C1","ph":"(703) 579-7636","em":"scott.schutzmeister@gmail.com","tw":"Dayton","st":"OH","ac":"golf, travel and sports events","w":"Scott Schutzmeister Scott lives in Dayton, Ohio. He enjoys golf, travel, and sports events. He can be reached at scott.schutzmeister@gmail.com | 703-579-7636."},{"id":810,"n":"Brent Schvaneveldt","u":"Brent","g":"F2","p":"","ph":"(801) 796-8514","tw":"Cedar Hills","st":"UT"},{"id":811,"n":"Gerard Schwartz","u":"Gerry","g":"H2","p":"A3","ph":"402-216-1926","em":"goarmy1986@gmail.com","tw":"Papillion","st":"NE","ac":"All of those listed"},{"id":812,"n":"John Schwartz","u":"JR","g":"D3","p":"F2","ph":"703-203-7761","em":"jschwartz94@verizon.net","tw":"Haymarket","st":"VA"},{"id":813,"n":"Gordon Scott","u":"Gordon","g":"A4","p":"C2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":814,"n":"Richard Scott","u":"Richard","g":"B3","p":"G4","em":"dickscott7@gmail.com","tw":"Los Gatos","st":"CA"},{"id":815,"n":"Lawrence Seaberg","u":"Larry","g":"I2","p":"B4","ph":"(802) 595-9314","em":"lseaberg86@gmail.com","tw":"Williamsburg","st":"VA"},{"id":816,"n":"William Searcy","u":"Bill","g":"H4","p":"D3","ph":"(540) 548-1016","em":"wsearcy3@gmail.com","tw":"Fredericksburg","st":"VA"},{"id":817,"n":"Albert Sebright","u":"Nelson","g":"D4","p":"","ph":"385-228-3732","em":"nelson.sebright@gmail.com","tw":"Lewisville","st":"NC"},{"id":818,"n":"Daniel Selph","u":"Daniel","g":"H4","p":"I3","em":"urracaazul@protonmail.com","tw":"Rio Rancho","st":"NM"},{"id":819,"n":"Dennis Semmel","u":"Dennis","g":"A4","p":"A4","ph":"484-274-0882","em":"dsemmel@gmail.com","tw":"Schnecksville","st":"PA"},{"id":820,"n":"James Seramba","u":"Jim","g":"C3","p":"F1","ph":"336-549-7014","em":"jseramba64@gmail.com","tw":"Charlotte","st":"NC"},{"id":821,"n":"David Seymour","u":"David","g":"F2","p":"H3","em":"dgseymour9@gmail.com","tw":"Dallas","st":"TX"},{"id":822,"n":"David Shade","u":"David","g":"H2","p":"B4","em":"davidm@dmshade3.com","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA"},{"id":823,"n":"Terrence Shamblin","u":"Terry","g":"H4","p":"B2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":824,"n":"Thomas Sharp","u":"Thomas","g":"C2","p":"G3","ph":"760-249-6893","tw":"Wrightwood","st":"CA"},{"id":825,"n":"Marilyn (Gibbs) Shazor","u":"Marilyn","g":"G2","p":"E4","ph":"(513) 673-7541","em":"Mshazor@yahoo.com","tw":"Dumfries","st":"VA"},{"id":826,"n":"Richard Shelton","u":"Richard","g":"B2","p":"E1","em":"rshelton@roycecs.com","tw":"Reston","st":"VA"},{"id":827,"n":"George Shepard","u":"Thatch","g":"G1","p":"D3","ph":"601-278-2615","em":"thatchjennie@aol.com","tw":"Ridgeland","st":"MS","ac":"Ole Miss Football, Boating, Beaching it,","w":"Thatch Shepard resides in Ridgeland, Mississippi, where he is retired following a long career in engineering and public service. Contact information includes (601) 278-2615 and thatchjennie@aol.com. He did not offer a general self-characterization of his cadet experience, but his cadet highlight was participating in the March On at the 1985 Army–Navy game after dressing his younger brothers as cadets, an episode shared with a classmate. His Army career spanned 27 years of active duty, culminating in retirement from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers in Vicksburg, with assignments including Fort Belvoir, Fort Riley, Fort Benning, Schofield Barracks, New Orleans, the University of Florida, West Point as a professor of environmental engineering, Belgium with SHAPE/NATO, Savannah, and Vicksburg, and included managing levee demolition during the 2011 flood. After military service, he worked in private engineering before returning to the Corps of Engineers as a civilian, including a period serving while a classmate was Chief of Engineers. His current interests include Ole Miss football, boating, and spending time at the beach, and his family includes three children and five grandchildren. Two of his children are also West Point graduates."},{"id":828,"n":"Myra (Bridgeman) Shepherd","u":"Myra","g":"H1","p":"C4","em":"msusma86@gmail.com","tw":"Hot Springs Village","st":"AR"},{"id":829,"n":"Debra Shoemaker","u":"Debbie","g":"B3","p":"B2","tw":"Belton","st":"TX"},{"id":830,"n":"Brian Shoop","u":"Brian","g":"G1","p":"A3","ph":"703-221-9647","em":"brian.p.shoop86@gmail.com","tw":"Arlington","st":"VA","ac":"Drinking","w":"Brian Shoop Brian Shoop resides in Arlington, Virginia, where he works as a consultant supporting the U.S. Space Force. Contact information includes 703.609.0432 and brian.p.shoop86@gmail.com. His cadet highlight was graduation. After military service, he transitioned into consulting work, culminating in his current role advising the U.S. Space Force, and he is now approaching retirement."},{"id":831,"n":"Stephen Sicinski","u":"Stephen","g":"D3","p":"G4","ph":"(910) 261-3334","em":"stephen.sicinski@gmail.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":832,"n":"Alan Simmons","u":"Alan","g":"F1","p":"C4","ph":"(907) 488-6920","tw":"North Pole","st":"AK"},{"id":833,"n":"Robert Simmons","u":"Robert","g":"G3","p":"H2","ph":"(616) 460-8966","em":"simmons86@earthlink.net","tw":"Ada","st":"MI"},{"id":834,"n":"Emry Sisson","u":"Emry","g":"H1","p":"D4","ph":"901-484-5861","em":"emry.sisson@gmail.com","tw":"Germantown","st":"TN","ac":"Have enjoyed traveling with some H-1 classmates overseas and stateside.  Hiking and backpacking bringing back the old days","w":"Emry Sisson Emry lives in Germantown, Tennessee with his wife Amy, whom he married 34 years ago. They have two children, Emma, 31, and Graham, 27. Emry branched ADA though he attended the Infantry Officer Advance Course and Ranger School. His battery command at 3-4 ADAR with the 82nd Airborne was a highlight. After leaving the Army, he worked in healthcare on the payer side and is now retired. He hikes and backpacks, bringing back the old days, and has enjoyed traveling overseas and stateside with some H-1 classmates. He can be reached at emry.sisson@gmail.com | 901-484-5861."},{"id":835,"n":"Joseph Skarupinski","u":"Joseph","g":"B3","p":"B2","em":"joe-s@ti.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX"},{"id":836,"n":"Anthony Skubi","u":"Tony","g":"B2","p":"B4","ph":"512-705-5073","em":"ajskubi3@yahoo.com","tw":"Georgetown","st":"TX","ac":"Skiing, travel, sporting events, military wargaming","w":"Tony Skubi Tony Skubi lives in Georgetown, Texas. He has four children and two grandsons. Anthony remembers his time at the Jungle Warfare School in Panama as a defining experience. He went on to command a Reserve Military Police Institutional Training unit in Aurora, Colorado, a role he held twice, serving as both a Major and a Lieutenant Colonel. He retired from the Army in 2016. After retirement, Tony spent five years at Dell Technologies before joining the Texas Department of Transportation. His most unexpected post-military development? Deciding to settle permanently in Texas, something he always swore he'd never do, until he married a lifelong Texas girl. Tony enjoys skiing, travel, sporting events, and military wargaming. He can be reached at ajskubi3@yahoo.com | 512-705-5073."},{"id":837,"n":"Steven Sliwa","u":"Steven","g":"A1","p":"E3","em":"stevenasliwa210@gmail.com","tw":"Annandale","st":"VA"},{"id":838,"n":"Donald Smith","u":"Don","g":"A3","p":"D1","ph":"(573) 692-0355","em":"desmith1986@charter.net","tw":"Lake Ozark","st":"MO"},{"id":839,"n":"Eugene Smith","u":"Eugene","g":"I1","p":"","ph":"(419) 474-9646","em":"cbsouth221@outlook.com"},{"id":840,"n":"George Smith","u":"George","g":"I1","p":"E4","ph":"(859) 296-0375","em":"ga@woodsmithcreations.com","tw":"Nicholasville","st":"KY"},{"id":841,"n":"George Smith","u":"Sid","g":"H1","p":"G3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":842,"n":"James Smith","u":"James","g":"E1","p":"I3","ph":"(703) 581-4032","em":"jim.smith.nj@gmail.com","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL"},{"id":843,"n":"Joel Smith","u":"Joel","g":"D2","p":"B4","ph":"(623) 937-1366","tw":"Glendale","st":"AZ"},{"id":844,"n":"Lee C. Smith","u":"Lee","g":"C1","p":"F2","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":845,"n":"Lori (Stokan) Smith","u":"Lori","g":"E1","p":"C2","tw":"Tampa","st":"FL"},{"id":846,"n":"Michael Smith","u":"Mike","g":"G1","p":"H3","ph":"972-839-3656","em":"mdjs12@gmail.com","tw":"Frisco","st":"TX","ac":"Attending sporting events, pickleball and travel","w":"Michael Smith resides in Frisco, Texas, where he is retired and planning an internationally mobile lifestyle. Contact information includes 972-839-3656 and mdjs12@gmail.com. He did not offer a general self-characterization of his cadet experience, but his cadet highlight was weekend gatherings at a local Super 8 motel as a way to get away from post and spend time with classmates. His most significant Army assignment was service with the 4th Battalion, 31st Infantry, part of the 214th Field Artillery Brigade, the only infantry unit on the post, where the unit played a key role in training troops in preparation for Desert Storm. After military service, he transitioned into the information technology and consulting field, including work with his father’s IT firm supporting a Navy Reserve command in New Orleans and later contributing to the delivery of mobile technology initiatives for American Airlines, before retiring. His current interests include attending sporting events, playing pickleball, and travel. Mike has two children and three grandchildren."},{"id":847,"n":"Stephen Smith","u":"Stephen","g":"E4","p":"G3","em":"stephen.jos.smith@gmail.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":848,"n":"Thomas Smith","u":"Tom","g":"I4","p":"G3","ph":"(615) 386-9426","em":"tjs44@comcast.net"},{"id":849,"n":"Brian Snell","u":"Brian","g":"H4","p":"F1","ph":"(518) 802-0624","em":"briansnell64@gmail.com","tw":"Morrisonville","st":"NY"},{"id":850,"n":"Karl Snyder","u":"Karl","g":"C4","p":"G2","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":851,"n":"Kelly Snyder","u":"Kelly","g":"B2","p":"","ph":"254-291-3457","em":"kelynson@aol.com","tw":"Killeen","st":"TX","ac":"Travel, sports events","w":"Kelly Snyder Kelly lives in Killeen, Texas, with a 33-year-old son named Joshua. She served in Germany, Panama, Bosnia, and Kosovo. At Battle Command Battle Lab, she helped design the separate brigade concept. After the Army, she taught gifted students at the elementary level and earned a PhD in special education - gifted. She serves on Congressman Roger Williams' academy selection board, now in her 13th year. She travels and attends sports events. She can be reached at kelynson@aol.com | 254-291-3457."},{"id":852,"n":"James Solano","u":"James","g":"F1","p":"","ph":"(719) 282-8093","em":"james.j.solano.civ@mail.mil","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":853,"n":"Kurt Sonntag","u":"Kurt","g":"I1","p":"C4","em":"kurt.sonntag1986@gmail.com","tw":"Fayetteville","st":"NC"},{"id":854,"n":"Anthony Souza","u":"Tony","g":"A4","p":"I1","ph":"678-358-4563","em":"afsouza2664@gmail.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX"},{"id":855,"n":"Carolyn Spaulding-Wright","u":"Carolyn","g":"F4","p":"A1","ph":"410-692-0442","em":"cjwright@zoominternet.net","tw":"Havre De Grace","st":"MD"},{"id":856,"n":"Russell Spears","u":"Russ","g":"C1","p":"A4","ph":"(770) 693-9485","em":"jrspears4@att.net","tw":"Powder Springs","st":"GA"},{"id":857,"n":"Scott Spellmon","u":"Scott","g":"G1","p":"E4","ph":"586-713-5960","em":"scottandsharise@yahoo.com","tw":"Fort McNair","st":"DC","af":"Football","w":"Scott Spellmon resides in Haymarket, VA following his retirement from the US Army after a 38-year career culminating as the 55th Chief of Engineers and Commanding General of the US Army Corps of Engineers.  Today, Scott is a Senior Account Executive with SOS International LLC, a privately owned technology, intelligence and logistics services provider.  His contact information is (586) 713-5960 and scottspellmon4@gmail.com.Scott fondly recalls all his company-mates in G1 as well as his football teammates.  Scott thoroughly enjoyed playing for Army Head Football Coach Jim Young in the 1983-1985 seasons highlighted by victories over Michigan State in the inaugural Cherry Bowl in 1984 and over Illinois in the 1985 Peach Bowl.  Scott and Sharise are blessed with three children: Nicholas, Steven and Katherine.  They have one grandson, Shepard, who is 2 and a granddaughter “on the way” in February 2026."},{"id":858,"n":"Michael Spingler","u":"Mike","g":"E1","p":"B2","ph":"(404) 355-2163","em":"mspingler@comcast.net","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":859,"n":"Josef Spudich","u":"Josef","g":"A3","p":"F1","em":"jspudich@charter.net","tw":"Neosho","st":"WI"},{"id":860,"n":"Norman Spurlock","u":"Norman","g":"C4","p":"A2","ph":"(504) 982-6560","em":"spurlockn@earthlink.net","tw":"Kenner","st":"LA"},{"id":861,"n":"Newton Spurr","u":"Mike","g":"E2","p":"H4","ph":"978-276-1110","em":"thespurrfamily@yahoo.com","tw":"Raleigh","st":"NC"},{"id":862,"n":"Jeffrey Stanclift","u":"Jeff","g":"A3","p":"E1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":863,"n":"Joseph Stanjones","u":"Joseph","g":"H4","p":"","ph":"248-766-5620","em":"newfreedom13@yahoo.com","tw":"Cabin John","st":"MD"},{"id":864,"n":"Matthew Stanton","u":"Matthew","g":"I2","p":"D4","ph":"617-984-9075","em":"mdtstanton@gmail.com","tw":"Marshfield","st":"MA"},{"id":865,"n":"Dustin Starbuck","u":"Dusty","g":"D1","p":"H4","em":"dms110363@gmail.com","tw":"Bar Harbor","st":"ME"},{"id":866,"n":"Pernell Staudt","u":"Pernell","g":"G2","p":"F3","ph":"(410) 571-8697","em":"pernellstaudt@verizon.net","tw":"Annapolis","st":"MD"},{"id":867,"n":"Troy Stebbins","u":"Troy","g":"F2","p":"C1","em":"troy.stebbins@gmail.com","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":868,"n":"Kevin Steele","u":"Kevin","g":"G4","p":"E3","ph":"(412) 367-7703","em":"ksteele49@comcast.net","tw":"Pittsburgh","st":"PA"},{"id":869,"n":"Timothy Steele","u":"Tim","g":"D2","p":"B1","ph":"(801) 247-2189","em":"thsteele@weber.edu","tw":"Ogden","st":"UT","ac":"Climbing, backpacking, hiking","w":"Tim's plebe company was B1, and he graduated from D2. His most memorable cadet experience was graduating, and realizing that he would never have to go back to our Rockbound Highland Home, except of his own accord. He served with 3/325th Airborne Combat Team in Vicenza, Italy. After the Army, Tim earned a Ph. D. in mathematics from the University of California - Santa Barbara, and went on to become a Professor of Mathematics at Weber State University. Tim and his wife Emily now split their time between their house in Italy and Ogden, Utah. They spend most of every summer climbing, backpacking, and hiking in the Sierra of California. He can be reached at thsteele@weber.edu | 801-247-2189."},{"id":870,"n":"Stephen Steffes","u":"Stephen","g":"C1","p":"A2","ph":"(616) 450-1676","em":"sjsteffes86@gmail.com","tw":"Grand Rapids","st":"MI","ac":"Travel, service events and sports events","w":"Stephen Steffes Steve  lives in Grand Rapids, Michigan on the farm where he grew up, they literally \"bought the farm.\" He and his wife Theresa have four children (three boys and a girl) and five grandchildren.  He served at Fort Hood as well as at Aschaffenburg and Schweinfurt, Germany. He particularly appreciates those assignments where he got to meet and enjoy time with so many good people.  He really learned to appreciate the sacrifices of classmates and their families who served extended periods of time in Iraq and Afghanistan after his own short deployment under much better conditions during the First Gulf War. His favorite cadet memories are visits from Theresa and hanging out with classmates. After the Army, he pursued a career in operations management in the pharmaceutical industry. The events around COVID while he and Theresa were working out of Dublin were probably the most interesting, though not the most pleasant. He enjoys travel, service events, and sports events. He can be reached at sjsteffes86@gmail.com | 616-450-1676."},{"id":871,"n":"Stephanie Stephens","u":"Stephanie","g":"H4","p":"G2","em":"stephanie.stephens@hotmail.com","tw":"Jonesboro","st":"GA"},{"id":872,"n":"Katherine Stewart-Kelley","u":"Kathy","g":"B4","p":"F1","ph":"860-329-3445","em":"kask6993@gmail.com","tw":"Southern Pines","st":"NC","ac":"Hiking, but NOT land nav.😀 Historical tours. Wine and/or spirits tasting.","w":"Kathie Stewart-Kelley KASK lives in Southern Pines, North Carolina. Her roomies are her mum, Pat, and Tuppence, a crazy mutt. Her son is using his GI Bill toward a degree in biology and environmental science at UMass Boston. She deployed to Desert Storm with the 89th MPs out of Fort Hood. After the Army, she spent two years in retail management, six years as a Dallas Police officer, and 26 years and counting at Travelers Insurance Company. She hikes, knits, enjoys historical tours, and wine and spirits tasting. She is always reading at least four books at once and loves to discuss them with everyone and anyone. Apparently two book clubs are not enough. Her dream retirement job is already waiting for her at the local independent book shop. She can be reached at kask6993@gmail.com | 860-329-3445."},{"id":873,"n":"Steven Stone","u":"Steve","g":"E2","p":"H1","ph":"540-735-5238","em":"stonesw@cox.net","tw":"Moorefield","st":"WV","ac":"Hunting, fishing, long range shooting.","w":"Steve lives in Moorefield, WV.. He and his wife have five children—four daughters all married and one son—along with four grandchildren. Steve retired after serving 18 years at MITRE Corporation doing cyberspace operations work. He ran MITRE's support to US Army Cyber Command and served as the Cyber Advisor to the Missile Defense Agency. His last Army assignment was at Joint Task Force Global Network Operations. He retired to the West Virginia mountains in 2025. Steve hunts, fishes, and shoots long range. He was one of the E-2 Dogs in the Sports Illustrated photo of the 1984 Army-Navy game. He can be reached at stonesw@cox.net | 540-735-5238."},{"id":874,"n":"Craig Stopa","u":"Craig","g":"I4","p":"","ph":"(919) 448-4880","em":"cjstopa@gmail.com","tw":"Chapel Hill","st":"NC"},{"id":875,"n":"Russell Storms","u":"Russell","g":"F2","p":"","ph":"(202) 528-1628","em":"russell@stormsnet.com","tw":"Olney","st":"MD"},{"id":876,"n":"J Michael Stradinger","u":"Mike","g":"G1","p":"I2","ph":"816-304-4553","em":"mstradinger@holland1916.com","tw":"Mission Hills","st":"KS","ac":"Travel, reading, skiing, fishing, and golf","w":"Mike Stradinger resides in Mission Hills, Kansas, where he is active as a lawyer, manufacturer, company founder, and investor with a focus on manufacturing. Contact information includes (816) 304-4553 and mstradinger@holland1916.com. Graduation is his favorite cadet memory. His most significant Army service was as an engineer officer at Fort Belvoir and at U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Headquarters, where he worked in the Office of Strategic Planning for the Chief of Engineers, an assignment notable for its exposure to enterprise-level planning and institutional decision-making. After military service, he pursued a civilian career spanning law, manufacturing leadership, company formation, and investment, building a portfolio of roles centered on creating and scaling industrial enterprises. His current interests include travel, reading, skiing, fishing, and golf, and he is involved in the emerging field of cognitive warfare and narrative intelligence. His family includes three married children and three grandchildren, with a fourth grandchild expected."},{"id":877,"n":"Robert Straub","u":"Robert","g":"B4","p":"F1","ph":"612-760-1472","em":"rwstraub@comcast.net","tw":"Edina","st":"MN"},{"id":878,"n":"Daniel Stredler","u":"Danny","g":"E3","p":"F1","ph":"224-998-8606","em":"stredler@aol.com","tw":"Las Vegas","st":"NV","ac":"Golf, Sport Events, Fishing, Skiing, Travel football, hockey, and soon baseball, as well as hosting classmates in the Lake Las Vegas area. He also values skiing trips with classmates and fitness-oriented activities.","w":"Daniel Stredler Danny is divorced and lives in Lake Las Vegas, Nevada. He has two children has a home in Lake Las Vegas, Nevada. He has two children. His daughter Lauren works in data communications for a Washington, DC-based firm and is a Purdue graduate with a Northwestern certificate. Son Grant played four years of college hockey as a goalie at Augustana and now works in insurance in Chicago. A defining cadet memory was earning the Army football long snapper position. He also remembers the grind of balancing academics, football, and sleep deprivation during the program's turnaround years, including bowl seasons. He majored in applied science and engineering with a civil engineering concentration. Danny was married to Amy Dickinson, class of 1988. His Army highlight was serving as an artillery officer in Germany during the Cold War period, including being present when the Berlin Wall came down. He served in multiple roles, including platoon leader, battalion S1, and forward observer with an air cavalry unit, and was involved in significant logistical support during Desert Storm from Europe. After the Army he transitioned into the healthcare industry. He spent 28 years at Abbott Diagnostics, building a career in medical equipment sales, marketing, and product development, including work tied to blood safety and diagnostic testing. In retirement, he maintains a disciplined fitness routine, advocates strongly for health and longevity, and is considering a return to coaching football at the high school level. He recently took over a head freshman high school football coach position at New Port Harbor High School in Newport Beach, CA. He enjoys golf and sees Las Vegas as an ideal hub for class gatherings centered on golf, professional sports, dining, and entertainment. He is enthusiastic about attending major sporting events and hosting classmates in the Lake Las Vegas area. He also values skiing trips with classmates and fitness-oriented activities. He can be reached at stredler@aol.com | 224-998-8606."},{"id":879,"n":"Jon Strickler","u":"Jon","g":"G2","p":"D4","ph":"720-323-0793","em":"jon.strickler@gmail.com","tw":"Vail","st":"CO","ac":"He is deeply engaged in outdoor sports and would be interested in activities built around skiing, mountain biking, hiking, and travel. He competes in masters-level mountain biking, skis extensively, and enjoys trips with friends. He is committed to reconnecting with classmates and open to gatherings that emphasize shared experiences and the outdoors.","w":"Jon Strickler Jon lives in Vail, Colorado. He and his wife have two children. Their daughter is a junior at Butler University studying fine arts ballet at one of the top ballet programs in the country. Their son graduated from the Vail Ski & Snowboard Academy and is taking a gap year to pursue high-level ski racing, training with clubs in the U.S., Argentina, and Europe. His best Army experiences were as a combat engineer in Korea, where training was intense, demolition ranges were permissive, and junior officers had significant hands-on responsibility. His later tour at Fort Leonard Wood included basic-training leadership and an engineer battalion assignment. He left active duty early during the drawdown, earned an MBA at Missouri-Rolla, then joined Andersen Consulting as a programmer. He shifted to operational consulting and Lean Six Sigma work, moved into sales and value analysis roles, and eventually co-founded and helped build several startups. His most successful venture was a cannabis science company. He is a two-time masters national champion in mountain biking and has lived for years in the Colorado mountains, organizing his life around skiing, mountain biking, and adventure racing. He skis, mountain bikes, hikes, and travels. He can be reached at jon.strickler@gmail.com | 720-323-0793."},{"id":880,"n":"Steven Strifler","u":"Steven","g":"E4","p":"E3","ph":"(214) 697-9606","em":"Steve.strifler@gmail.com","tw":"Jacksboro","st":"TX"},{"id":881,"n":"Bryan Strong","u":"Bryan","g":"A3","p":"C1","ph":"989-595-6412","em":"bryan.strong@edwardjones.com","tw":"Alpena","st":"MI"},{"id":882,"n":"Carrie Stroup","u":"Carrie","g":"D4","p":"G1"},{"id":883,"n":"Kent Stueve","u":"Kent","g":"E4","p":"G2","ph":"(610) 458-8463","em":"kent.stueve@gmail.com","tw":"Chester Springs","st":"PA"},{"id":884,"n":"Rodney Sturdivant","u":"Rodney","g":"F3","p":"E2","em":"rodsturdivant@icloud.com"},{"id":885,"n":"Michael Sturgeon","u":"Michael","g":"F3","p":"I1","em":"sturgeonms@aol.com","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":886,"n":"Joseph Sullivan","u":"Sully","g":"E4","p":"G3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":887,"n":"John Sutton","u":"John","g":"D4","p":"B3","em":"johnhsutton615@gmail.com","tw":"Phoenix","st":"AZ"},{"id":888,"n":"Brian Sweeney","u":"Brian","g":"I1","p":"C2","tw":"South Boardman","st":"MI"},{"id":889,"n":"Michael Switzer","u":"Mike","g":"H3","p":"I2","ph":"772-214-9984","em":"switz86@aol.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL","ac":"Any and all, sports, travel, social","w":"Michael Switzer Mike lives in Madison, Alabama with a 26-year-old daughter. He stays connected with the H-3 hurricane community—about 18 classmates gather regularly in the Huntsville area. His military career centered on Army aviation, culminating as Program Manager at Redstone Arsenal where he oversaw five helicopter fleets including the OH-58D Kiowa Warrior. At one point 40% of the Kiowa fleet was deployed under his watch. A family highlight came during a military exchange assignment with the RAF in the UK, certifying British Apaches for combat deployment. Before that, memorable Academy experiences included scuba diving, a Panama Canal transit, summer flight training, and a project at Lawrence Livermore Labs. He also helped lead the H3 group—alongside Mike McMahon '85 and others—that ran onto the field in bathrobes during the ESPN Air Force game to spell out \"Beat AFA.\" After the Army he works as a civilian in acquisition programs supporting aviation, space, and missile systems. He manages Foreign Military Sales cases, particularly with British partners, finding that work rewarding. His family appeared in LIFE magazine in December 1999 with an update in 2000. He can be reached at switz86@aol.com | 772-214-9984."},{"id":890,"n":"Thomas Szoka","u":"Tom","g":"C4","p":"F1","ph":"256-603-0696","em":"tomszoka@gmail.com","tw":"Madison","st":"AL","ac":"I do the following with classmates now.  It’s enough (for now). Fishing, skiing, backbacking, rafting, travel, drinking beer, daily Wordle group.","w":"Tom lives in Madison, Alabama with his wife Shelley, his high school sweetheart. They have three children: Eric (36, married, one granddaughter age 1 in Augusta, Georgia), Adam (33, married, one granddaughter age 4 in Madison, Alabama), and Mary (30, married, living in Gainesville, Florida). He served with 16th Engineers, 1st Armored Division from 1987-1990 as S-4, where he planned and executed the operation to move all barrier material for the German Defense Plan (mines, concertina wire, etc.) using assets from division combat units, the division transport company, and locally procured equipment. After the Army, he worked in CAD software, eventually becoming Global Product Manager for $200M revenue 3D ship and process plant design software. His final role was running product management for a $600M division. His most memorable cadet experience was a trip to Rich Hatch's place in Newport, Rhode Island after spring term ended. He fishes, skis, backpacks, rafts, and travels with classmates, regularly drinking beer and participating in a daily Wordle group. He can be reached at tomszoka@gmail.com | 256-603-0696."},{"id":891,"n":"Curt Szuberla","u":"Curt","g":"I2","p":"C1","em":"caszuberla@alaska.edu","tw":"Dunnellon","st":"FL","ac":"In the bars, with the men who play guitarsSinging, drinking, and remembering the times...","w":"Curt Szuberla \"Zippy\" lives in Dunnellon, Florida, with his wife of 36+ years  whom he credits with having poor taste in men. They've had many dogs in lieu of children. His cadet highlight was wearing BG Boylan's uniform during the 100th Night Show. After graduation, he completed Ranger School on a non-refundable ticket which was motivation enough not to get recycled. After eight years teaching high school mathematics and physics in North Pole, Alaska, he joined the University of Alaska Fairbanks as Physics Department Chair, then stood up the nation's 14th University Affiliated Research Center, the Geophysical Detection of Nuclear Proliferation center, for the Assistant Secretary of Defense for Nuclear, Chemical and Biological Programs, serving as its Executive Director. That center is now the Arctic and Homeland Defense Center under NORAD-NORTHCOM. He also did a stint with DIA, applying digital statistical signal processing to the fight against IEDs. He enjoys singing and drinking in bars with the men who play guitars, chocolate ice cream, and has finally answered his wife's three-decade-old question: yes, West Point has foliage and football. He can be reached at caszuberla@alaska.edu."},{"id":892,"n":"David Tafares","u":"Dave","g":"B3","p":"H4","ph":"602-740-6980","em":"dave.tafares@gmail.com","tw":"Dripping Springs","st":"TX","ac":"Travel","w":"David Tafares Dave lives in Dripping Springs, Texas. He has two boys and one granddaughter. Dave’s favorite cadet memory was graduating. He served in Gelnhausen, Germany; Fort Benning, Georgia; and Fort Lewis, Washington—all of his assignments were great. After the Army, he spent 25 years with Frito-Lay, then four years as COO of Boozy Bites. He is working towards spending half of each year on the northwestern coast of Spain and half in the US. Dave enjoys travel. He can be reached at dave.tafares@gmail.com | 602-740-6980."},{"id":893,"n":"Karl Tappert","u":"Karl","g":"A4","p":"A1","ph":"908-910-8888","em":"ktappert7@comcast.net","tw":"Newark","st":"DE"},{"id":894,"n":"Marc Taylor","u":"Big 'Un","g":"G2","p":"I1","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":895,"n":"Thomas Telthorst","u":"Thomas","g":"F3","p":"G4","ph":"(913) 281-2080","em":"tom@524legal.com","tw":"Kansas City","st":"KS"},{"id":896,"n":"David Thelen","u":"David","g":"A3","p":"F1","ph":"636-284-4864","em":"davidathelen@yahoo.com","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":897,"n":"David Thomas","u":"David","g":"C4","p":"B2","tw":"Williamsburg","st":"MA"},{"id":898,"n":"Jeffrey Thompson","u":"Jeff","g":"F3","p":"E1","ph":"(336) 212-6238","em":"thompson.jet@gmail.com","tw":"Hillsborough","st":"NC"},{"id":899,"n":"Mark Thompson","u":"Mark","g":"A4","p":"E1","ph":"808-398-6447","em":"mark.w.thompson@army.mil","tw":"APO","st":"AE"},{"id":900,"n":"John Thomson","u":"John","g":"A1","p":"A2","ph":"(580) 284-8329","em":"john.c.thomson8@gmail.com","tw":"Killeen","st":"TX"},{"id":901,"n":"Harkley Thornton","u":"Harkley","g":"B1","p":"H2","em":"harkleythornton@me.com","tw":"Orlando","st":"FL"},{"id":902,"n":"Jeffrey Thramann","u":"Jeff","g":"A3","p":"I4","ph":"303-995-3036","em":"jeff@thramann.com","tw":"Niwot","st":"CO"},{"id":903,"n":"Christopher Tierney","u":"Chris","g":"E1","p":"A3","ph":"(505) 797-1706","em":"ctierney86@hotmail.com","tw":"Albuquerque","st":"NM"},{"id":904,"n":"Christopher Timmer","u":"Chris","g":"B1","p":"B3","em":"cb.timmer@gmail.com","tw":"Oceanside","st":"CA"},{"id":905,"n":"Jeanne Tofferi","u":"Jeanne","g":"E3","p":"I4","ph":"(210) 231-0012","em":"jtofferi@aol.com","tw":"San Antonio","st":"TX"},{"id":906,"n":"Mark Tolmachoff","u":"Mark","g":"B1","p":"E2","em":"mbtolmachoff@att.net","tw":"Atchison","st":"KS"},{"id":907,"n":"Todd Tolson","u":"Todd","g":"C3","p":"I1","ph":"703-863-6585","em":"toddtolson@aol.com","st":"FL","ac":"Fishing","w":"Todd Tolson Todd is in Florida. In the Army he commanded an armor company in Germany. After the Army, he worked as a defense contractor. He enjoys fishing. He can be reached at toddtolson@aol.com | 703-863-6585."},{"id":908,"n":"Roy Tomlinson","u":"Roy","g":"E2","p":"D1","ph":"+81 70 9077 2910","em":"roytomlinson86@gmail.com","tw":"Tokyo","st":"Japan","ac":"I would enjoy hosting mini-reunions in Japan.","w":"Roy Tomlinson Roy lives in Tokyo, Japan and has no children. His plebe company was D1, graduating from E2. He has many memorable cadet stories, including having tea with Dusty Scott in the Supe's residence yearling year. He had led a spirit mission to steal the sign off the Supe's lawn, and after fingers pointed at him, he was given an order to return the sign and apologize. Mrs. Scott, always a kind person, invited him in for tea and they had a delightful 30 minutes getting to know each other over tea and cookies. He reported to his TAC that he had indeed apologized and Mrs. Scott had accepted the apology. His most memorable assignment was being in Germany when the wall went down, which he describes as surreal. After the Army, he's been an international school teacher for over 25 years in Singapore, Manila, Tokyo, and Kathmandu. He served as President of the West Point Society of Singapore for 6 years, got the Singaporean grads involved, and they now run the society. He would enjoy hosting mini-reunions in Japan. He can be reached at roytomlinson86@gmail.com | +81 70 9077 2910."},{"id":909,"n":"Brien Tonkinson","u":"Brien","g":"D4","p":"F2","ph":"(254) 231-5817","em":"jenn_brien@yahoo.com","tw":"Clovis","st":"CA"},{"id":910,"n":"Robert Townley","u":"Robert","g":"G4","p":"I2","em":"86rct50@gmail.com","tw":"Ashburn","st":"VA"},{"id":911,"n":"Richard Travaglini","u":"Richard","g":"E1","p":"E3","ph":"(609) 581-1511","tw":"Hamilton","st":"NJ"},{"id":912,"n":"Vincent Trollan","u":"Vince","g":"E4","p":"I1","ph":"828-446-7490","em":"vtrollan@charter.net","tw":"Hickory","st":"NC","ac":"Chess, golf, travel, sporting events","w":"Vincent Trollan Vince lives in Hickory, North Carolina. He has a daughter Meg and a son Jim, plus a granddaughter Maya. His son Jim is a 2016 graduate of West Point. His plebe company was I1, graduating from E4. His most memorable cadet experience was graduation. He served in Fulda, Germany, which he describes as so much fun. After the Army, he worked in pharmaceuticals with Novartis Oncology. He enjoys chess, golf, travel, and sporting events. He can be reached at vtrollan@charter.net | 828-446-7490."},{"id":913,"n":"Lawrence Tubbs","u":"Lawrence","g":"I3","p":"F2","em":"lawrence.tubbs@hotmail.com","tw":"Naples","st":"IT","af":"Baseball","ac":"Golf, travel, sporting events, cycling, trong interest in travel-based reunions and shared experiences, drawing on memories of team trips to Florida, California, and games against high-profile opponents. His current overseas assignment in Italy suggests comfort with international travel, and his enthusiasm for baseball gatherings indicates he would enjoy sports-related events, reunions, and shared trips centered on common experiences rather than individual leisure activities.","w":"Lawrence Tubbs Lawrence lives in Naples, Italy, where he is currently stationed working for the Navy alongside his wife, who is also employed there. They expect to return from overseas in 2027 to Bucks County, Pennsylvania. They plan to split time between Pennsylvania and Costa del Sol, Spain in retirement. He has four children and two granddaughters. His plebe company was F2, graduating from I3. A standout cadet memory was walking on to the Army baseball team after hearing an announcement during Beast and asking his parents to mail his cleats and glove. He recalled surviving the whittling-down tryout process, gaining a starting position as a Plebe during the team’s Florida spring break trip, annual 45 game schedules between fall and spring seasons, the camaraderie of winter practices in the Fieldhouse and many team road trip away from West Point, and countless memories with teammates on and off the field including annual spring trips to the NY Yankees’ spring training complex in Florida and playing against three professional teams (Mets, Tigers, and Astros) on Doubleday Field. He spent the last 15 years of his military career in the Civil Affairs branch with many unique assignments, with battalion command in Europe as the highlight. He retired as a Colonel. As a career civil servant, he balanced Army Reserve life with jobs in the Federal Bureau of Prisons, VA, Army, Census Bureau, DLA, and Navy. Having lived in Europe twice (Germany for 10 years and Italy for 5 years), he enjoys travelling through Europe which contributed to his plan to live there part-time in retirement. He remains as active as ever and enjoys the daily grind of keeping in shape as an age-group triathlete. He swims, cycles, and/or runs most days. He looks forward to retirement and the freedom to pursue other interests including golf, travel, sporting events, cycling and more time spent with family. He looks forward to the opportunity to reconnect with friends at reunions and shared trips centered on common experiences. He can be reached at lawrence.tubbs@hotmail.com."},{"id":914,"n":"Albert Tumminello","u":"Trey","g":"C2","p":"D3","ph":"757-254-7099","em":"treytumminello86@gmail.com","tw":"Raphine","st":"VA","w":"Trey Tumminello Trey lives in Raphine, Virginia with his wife Dana, whom he married shortly after graduation. They have two children and five grandchildren. AJ (USMA 2013) is an intelligence officer stationed at the US Embassy in New Delhi, India. Grace, a former UH60 pilot, is married to a USAFA grad, and they are stationed in Aviano, Italy. Trey fondly remembers the \"Grey Berets\" missions into the steam tunnels and late night poker games in the basement trunk room that didn't end well. He served in the infantry in various assignments with the 1st Cavalry Division including Desert Storm, 7th Infantry Division, and 3rd Ranger Battalion. His time with the Ranger Regiment was his favorite, where the quality and dedication of the men, NCOs, and officers was exemplary.  After the Army, Trey and Dana returned to Yorktown, Virginia where he sold medical devices and they raised their two kids. When AJ and Grace left for college and the Army, Trey left his sales job, and he and Dana bought a bed and breakfast in the Shenandoah Valley that they successfully ran for six years. They fell in love with the beauty and slow pace of life in the Valley, and with their kids living overseas, they sold the business in 2025 and remained in the area. They found a \"fixer upper\" with beautiful views of the valley and mountains that Trey is remodeling. Trey enjoys outdoor activities, especially hunting. He and Dana love traveling overseas and are always ready to visit a new exotic country. He can be reached at treytumminello86@gmail.com | 757-254-7099."},{"id":915,"n":"William Turner","u":"Bill","g":"I2","p":"F1","ph":"571-721-8352","em":"wat19868762@gmail.com","tw":"Manhattan","st":"KS"},{"id":916,"n":"Steven Turpening","u":"Steven","g":"B4","p":"F2","ph":"610-704-0281","em":"sturpening@aol.com","tw":"Kissimee","st":"FL"},{"id":917,"n":"Eve (Hemmans) Tuset","u":"Eve","g":"H1","p":"D3","ph":"(919) 436-6232","em":"evexcel365@gmail.com","tw":"Wendell","st":"NC"},{"id":918,"n":"Thomas Upp","u":"Tom","g":"E1","p":"C2","ph":"281-686-5505","em":"tomupp@comcast.net","tw":"The Woodlands","st":"TX"},{"id":919,"n":"Bradley Upton","u":"Bradley","g":"H1","p":"I3","ph":"(707) 334-2846","em":"rufflehead@gmail.com","tw":"Benicia","st":"CA"},{"id":920,"n":"David Urban","u":"Dave","g":"B3","p":"B4","em":"urbandavidjohn@gmail.com","tw":"Fort Myers","st":"FL"},{"id":921,"n":"Kristine Urbauer","u":"Kris","g":"A4","p":"","ph":"708-704-2391","em":"urbs86@comcast.net","tw":"Oak Lawn","st":"IL","ac":"She does not specify recreational interests. Her comments suggest she enjoys connection, conversation, and shared experiences more than specific activities. Teaching, community engagement, and time with classmates appear to fit her current rhythm.","w":"Kris Urbauer Kris lives in Oak Lawn, Illinois. Her most meaningful service includes company command at Fort Bragg in an airborne topographic engineer unit, earning Jumpmaster wings on the first attempt, and deploying to Bosnia in 1994 as the lone U.S. topographic engineer with a British team managing safe-route mapping during active shelling. Earlier roles included platoon leadership at Fort Riley, NTC rotations, humanitarian missions in Honduras, and facilities engineering across Korea. She earned a master's degree in geotechnical engineering, became a licensed PE, and joined GE as a Six Sigma Black Belt, later becoming a Master Black Belt and instructor. She moved into regional service leadership, then corporate personnel relations conducting global positive-employee-relations work. Her final and favorite role was running GE's veteran programs and leading the company's veteran network after more than a decade in that senior role. She volunteered for post-9/11 service, was recalled to active duty, and spent a year with the New York District of the Army Corps of Engineers supporting Ground Zero cleanup while living in Manhattan. She now substitute-teaches, including at the grade school she attended. She can be reached at urbs86@comcast.net | 708-704-2391."},{"id":922,"n":"Mark Vakkur","u":"Mark","g":"A2","p":"A4","ph":"404-964-9883","em":"mvakkur@gmail.com","tw":"Decatur","st":"GA","ac":"Traveling to a historical battlefield with a historian would be cool, but the prices of West Point sponsored trips seem excessive, so I generally didn't commit (although I was tempted by the Normandy one around D-Day '24).","w":"Mark Vakkur Mark lives in Decatur, Georgia. His son is in medical school in Augusta, his oldest daughter is pursuing a PsyD in Indianapolis, and his youngest daughter is a junior at Georgia Tech studying chemical engineering. No grandchildren yet. He found Fort Huachuca interesting and was in the 1989 San Francisco earthquake at the Presidio. He trained as a flight surgeon and flew nap-of-the-earth medevac missions over the Potomac to Walter Reed during rush hour. He served four years as a psychiatrist at the Atlanta VAMC, then spent the rest of his career in private practice. He took a brief detour into financial market research, wrote novels and co-authored a book on cultural psychiatry, and published articles on investing and trading. He spent 30 years as a husband and father to three children, including five years in Switzerland where he worked briefly for the World Health Organization while primarily managing family logistics. He skied extensively in the Alps, met four stars of Stranger Things on Atlanta streets, attended church with Jimmy and Rosalynn Carter in Plains, Georgia, and had dinner with President Ford. He would be interested in traveling to historical battlefields with a historian. He can be reached at mvakkur@gmail.com | 404-964-9883."},{"id":923,"n":"Matthew Van Kirk","u":"Matthew","g":"E1","p":"I2","ph":"(410) 437-6394","em":"mfvankirk1@verizon.net","tw":"Pasadena","st":"MD"},{"id":924,"n":"Steven Van Straten","u":"Steven","g":"D3","p":"E2","em":"sjvs64@hotmail.com","tw":"Garden Ridge","st":"TX"},{"id":925,"n":"Steven Vass","u":"Steve","g":"B2","p":"E4","ph":"913-300-1834","em":"genealogysv4@hotmail.com","tw":"Platte City","st":"MO","ac":"I would be interested in enjoying travel and attending sports events with classmates.","w":"Steve Vass Steve lives in APO AE with his wife Sonja and three adult children—two boys and one girl. Their oldest son is in the Army. His most enjoyable assignment was as a rifle platoon leader in the 7ID(L) at Fort Ord, California. His best assignment location was Hohenfels, Germany, where he met his wife; Hawaii was a close second. He became an Army Civilian Professional after retiring and currently serves as co-chair for the HQDA Ukraine Lessons Learned Integration Task Force. Over two military tours and an extended stay as an ACP, he was assigned to Hohenfels for 25 years and six months. For one of those years, he was on a trip section to Baghdad as chief of an Iraqi national police brigade transition team. He travels and attends sports events. He can be reached at genealogysv4@hotmail.com | 913-300-1834."},{"id":926,"n":"John Velliquette","u":"John","g":"G2","p":"E1","em":"johnsandyvel@comcast.net","tw":"Sumner","st":"WA"},{"id":927,"n":"Patrick Venezia","u":"Patrick","g":"H4","p":"I2","tw":"Nashville","st":"TN"},{"id":928,"n":"John Vickers","u":"John","g":"D2","p":"D4","ph":"607-437-9117","em":"johnbethvickers@gmail.com","tw":"Delhi","st":"NY","ac":"Travel, golf, fishing and hunting would all be fun with classmates.","w":"John Vickers John lives in Delhi, New York with his wife Beth. They have two sons: Teddy is a chemical engineer in Houston who recently became engaged to his sweetheart Daniella, and Paul is an IT engineer for a hedge fund company in Manhattan. John remembers the D2 tactical officer, CPT Gary Andersen, who had some funny mannerisms, and one of their ex-classmates, Michael Bowers, did a great imitation. Also one time as a practical joke, one of them slathered sticky orange juice on the door handle to one of the rooms and CPT Andersen came by for SAMI and grabbed the handle. John enjoyed aspects of every assignment: Fort Ord as a lieutenant with multiple NTC rotations and lots of golf; Germany as a captain with construction projects all around Germany and travel all over Europe with Beth; ACS at University of Colorado where he learned about water resources and did lots of fishing; US Army Corps of Engineers assignments in Buffalo and Philadelphia where he served as the USACE forward operations officer and then commander for USACE response to 9/11 at the WTC site; ACRC at Fort Drum where he started hunting; and finally running an ROTC Battalion at Northern Michigan University where he commissioned numerous quality officers and did lots of hunting and fishing. Following retirement in 2006, they moved to upstate New York and John started a second career as an engineer in the NYC Water Supply. He ended up as Director of Source Water Operations responsible for leading several hundred people in the delivery of 1.1 billion gallons of high quality drinking water a day to almost half the population of New York State. They retired in 2024 and now are traveling more and enjoying their time together. They hope to start getting around more in the US and seeing classmates. Upstate New York is wonderful in the summer and they have plenty of room, a heated pool, and welcome visitors. John would enjoy travel, golf, fishing, and hunting with classmates. He can be reached at johnbethvickers@gmail.com | 607-437-9117."},{"id":929,"n":"Mark Visosky","u":"Mark","g":"E4","p":"I3","em":"mvisosky@yahoo.com","tw":"Fairfax","st":"VA"},{"id":930,"n":"Marian Vlasak","u":"Marian","g":"I4","p":"","em":"mevpaz@msn.com","tw":"Leavenworth","st":"KS"},{"id":931,"n":"David Volkman","u":"David","g":"B2","p":"G4","ph":"(513) 505-7248","em":"d.n.volkman@gmail.com","tw":"Maineville","st":"OH"},{"id":932,"n":"Mark Von Heeringen","u":"Mark","g":"G4","p":"G3","tw":"Germantown","st":"MD"},{"id":933,"n":"Thomas Voris","u":"Tom","g":"F1","p":"H2","ph":"760-784-0628","em":"tom.voris@gmail.com","tw":"Oceanside","st":"CA"},{"id":934,"n":"Thomas Voytek","u":"Tom","g":"D1","p":"F3","ph":"347-899-6354","em":"tom.voytek@gmail.com","tw":"Mount Vernon","st":"NY"},{"id":935,"n":"William Vredenburgh","u":"Bill","g":"C4","p":"B1","ph":"(475) 393-8856","em":"wev2102@mac.com","tw":"Darien","st":"CT"},{"id":936,"n":"Robert Vrindten","u":"Bob","g":"B1","p":"E4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":937,"n":"John Wagner","u":"John","g":"E3","p":"A4","ph":"(318) 210-1422","em":"bwagner1986@gmail.com","tw":"Shreveport","st":"LA"},{"id":938,"n":"Mark Waite","u":"Mark","g":"B2","p":"I1","ph":"(949) 231-9417","em":"waite1024@yahoo.com","tw":"Kihei","st":"HI"},{"id":939,"n":"Michael Wallace","u":"Michael","g":"C3","p":"H2","ph":"(864) 286-9406","tw":"Greenville","st":"SC"},{"id":940,"n":"Nathan Wallace","u":"Nate","g":"I1","p":"C4","ph":"907-232-4380","em":"nwallace6@yahoo.com","tw":"Pilot Valley","st":"NV","ac":"All the stuff Lissa listed is great (especially the beer parts) except hiking-my knees and ankles can’t handle much after 10 years of jump status late in my Army life.","w":"Nate Wallace Nate lives in Pilot Valley, Nevada with his wife Anathea Beecher - they've been married 39 years. They are retired on 80 acres of sage brush in the middle of nowhere. He has two kids: a daughter in Alaska and a son at Hill AFB, Utah working as an Air Force civilian. Nate remembers that Army-Navy games were always great times, even the time they had to pay for a shattered toilet before they would let them check out of the hotel from the weekend (Weilep/Saso/Stanko?) during cow year. His highlight was going back to Ranger School as a battalion XO/S3 and watching the students suffer and excel as much as they did in the late 80s - except on staff it was like being in Groundhog Day for 23 iterations of Benning phase but with food and sleep. His most interesting assignment was as a senior advisor to an Iraqi National Police Battalion in east Baghdad for a year. After the Army, he worked as an Army civilian in Alaska, facility manager at a Pringles plant, city manager in Alaska, then retired as a Deputy State Director in Wyoming for BLM. City manager in Palmer, Alaska was the most fun by far. Nate started making beer after his first tour in Germany and has since expanded into wine and spirits. He is trying to start a tiny vineyard in the sage brush desert of northeast Nevada now. He enjoys all the activities listed by Lissa (especially the beer parts) except hiking - his knees and ankles can't handle much after 10 years of jump status late in his Army life. He can be reached at nwallace6@yahoo.com | 907-232-4380."},{"id":941,"n":"Kevin Walrath","u":"Kevin","g":"G4","p":"C3","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":942,"n":"William Walter","u":"Will","g":"G2","p":"D4","ph":"601-310-4024","em":"williamcwaltercnq@gmail.com","tw":"Corinth","st":"MS","ac":"Any and all","w":"Will Walter Billy lives in Corinth, Mississippi. His highlight was leaving Fort Polk and the Army. After the Army, he went to law school, then practiced law for 30 years. He's now retired. He can be reached at williamcwaltercnq@gmail.com | 601-310-4024."},{"id":943,"n":"George Ward","u":"George","g":"G2","p":"","em":"gw_ward@hotmail.com","tw":"Springfield","st":"VA"},{"id":944,"n":"William Ward","u":"Bill","g":"C3","p":"G4","ph":"NA","em":".No Email - Deceased","tw":"NA","st":"NA"},{"id":945,"n":"Stephen Warnock","u":"Steve","g":"A4","p":"H3","ph":"(813) 418-1499","em":"swarnock88@gmail.com","tw":"Apollo Beach","st":"FL"},{"id":946,"n":"Vance Warren","u":"Van","g":"C4","p":"F3","em":"vwarren6@att.net","tw":"Columbus","st":"GA"},{"id":947,"n":"Dennis Watson","u":"Dennis","g":"G1","p":"D3","ph":"864-979-4151","em":"dennis1047@att.net","tw":"Greer","st":"SC","ac":"Fly fishing, travel","w":"Dennis Watson resides in Greer, South Carolina, where he works in engineering with a career that progressed into process engineering and project management. Contact information includes (864) 979-4151 and dennis1047@att.net. He recalls the Memphis football game played in heavy snow, remembered vividly for the conditions and shared atmosphere among the Corps. His most significant Army assignment was with 4th Battalion, 64th Armor Regiment (“Tuskers”) in the 24th Infantry Division at Fort Stewart. After military service, he transitioned into civilian engineering, building a career focused on technical problem solving, process improvement, and project leadership. His current interests include fly fishing and travel. Dennis has been married to his high school sweetheart, Karen, since 1987. They have two sons Ryan and Matthew."},{"id":948,"n":"Kendal Weidinger","u":"Kendal","g":"D2","p":"C4","ph":"971-563-2456","em":"kwingdinger@hotmail.com","tw":"Whitehall","st":"MT"},{"id":949,"n":"Roger Weilep","u":"Roger","g":"I1","p":"D3","ph":"516-476-9958","em":"rjmak1@mac.com","tw":"Manhasset","st":"NY"},{"id":950,"n":"Kevin Weiler","u":"Kevin","g":"I2","p":"C3","ph":"(949) 459-5894","em":"weilerak1964@gmail.com","tw":"Trabuco Canyon","st":"CA"},{"id":951,"n":"Thomas Weiss","u":"Tom","g":"G1","p":"A2","ph":"847-894-8009","em":"tom.weiss86@gmail.com","tw":"Cape Canaveral","st":"FL","ac":"Scuba diving, in Carribean area for starters. Cruises! Ideally out of Port Canaveral but also European rivers, Mediterranean. Non-Caribbean cruises pending wife's retirement in ~3 years.","w":"Tom Weiss resides in Cape Canaveral, Florida, where he recently finished a career in telecommunications focused on cellular infrastructure. Contact information includes (847) 894-8009 and tom.weiss86@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience candidly, crediting George Bond and other G1 classmates with supporting him through difficult periods. His cadet memories center less on specific events than on those peer relationships. His most significant Army assignment was with the 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment at El Paso, where he participated in the last full maneuver REFORGER exercise in 1988 and later deployed for six months to Saudi Arabia and Iraq during Desert Shield and Desert Storm. After military service, he built a career in telecommunications, working on cellular infrastructure with companies including Motorola, Nokia, and Gogo, traveling extensively to Japan in the 1990s and contributing to industry standards development. His current interests include scuba diving, cruising in the Caribbean and Europe, and future travel plans tied to his wife’s anticipated retirement and his family includes a son and step-grandchildren."},{"id":952,"n":"John Wendel","u":"John","g":"F4","p":"D2","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":953,"n":"Thomas Wenneson","u":"Tom","g":"D4","p":"F2","ph":"408-598-5634","em":"tom@wenneson.com","tw":"Buda","st":"TX","af":"Parachute Team","ac":"Any and all that is convenient and cost effective. Unlike many, I had only moderate ambition and have a modest financial life. So while hanging with classmates is awesome, staying financially balanced is even more so.","w":"Tom Wenneson Tom lives in Buda, Texas. He just married Holly in November 2025. He has an adopted son, Marco, who graduated from West Point in 2005 and served tours in Iraq and Afghanistan, first as Infantry then as Civil Affairs. Marco is married to Jennifer Kim, and they have two daughters and currently live in Salt Lake City where he works with Goldman Sachs. Tom was on the Sport Parachute team was everything he could hope for in terms of memories, a lifelong dream fulfilled that created great connections with teammates from all classes. One of his more vivid memories was carrying the Virginia state flag at the Army Navy game in the Rose Bowl during plebe year. He attended Fort Rucker for flight school and Apache qualification, then Fort Hood for unit formation of 5/6 Cavalry and training. He served in Germany at Wiesbaden until Desert Storm, then deployed to Saudi Arabia. Post Desert Storm, he returned to Fort Rucker and trained as an Apache instructor pilot, training pilots for two years. He completed advanced course then returned to Fort Hood (1/6 Cavalry) as Assistant S3, where he left the Army in 1995. His best assignment was Apache IP at Rucker, another dream fulfilled. In 1995, he hired into Applied Materials as a Technical Trainer teaching semiconductor manufacturing equipment operations, maintenance, and repair to major industry players, traveling much of the world in technical and supervisory roles. His most interesting role was learning to teach installation, maintenance, and operation of SEM (Scanning Electron Microscopes) which involved multiple trips to Israel. In 2009, he moved to the VOIP telecommunication industry with ShoreTel and then Mitel after acquisition, continuing in technical training and management roles. In 2019, he moved into Sales Enablement and now manages a program team building sales training and sales skills development. Tom has come to love Jesus, cooking, gardening, travel, and beer. He makes very edible BBQ smoked brisket and crazy tasty and crazy hot sauces from peppers he has grown. If you swing down south of Austin, look him up. He can be reached at tom@wenneson.com | 408-598-5634."},{"id":954,"n":"David Werntz","u":"David","g":"B3","p":"F1","ph":"214-505-5035","em":"dave@sabresurgical.com","tw":"Bartonville","st":"TX"},{"id":955,"n":"Eric Wesley","u":"Eric","g":"E3","p":"H4","em":"eric.wesley2@gmail.com","tw":"Monument","st":"CO"},{"id":956,"n":"Jeffrey Weston","u":"Jeff","g":"A1","p":"G3","ph":"602-819-3011","em":"jeffweston2010@gmail.com","tw":"Scottsdale","st":"AZ"},{"id":957,"n":"George Whale","u":"George","g":"H2","p":"B4","ph":"(501) 265-9118","em":"georgelwhale@gmail.com","tw":"Little Rock","st":"AR"},{"id":958,"n":"Eric Whipple","u":"Eric","g":"C4","p":"B1","ph":"402-525-0464","em":"enwhipple@gmail.com","tw":"Lincoln","st":"NE","af":"Ski Patrol","ac":"Eric is an enthusiastic participant in skiing and shared memorable stories of ski patrol duty at West Point. He enjoys reconnecting with classmates through activities like reunions and travel. He has maintained strong ties with company mates and expresses interest in staying connected through shared events—he even jokes about skiing while his buddy recovered in a hospital visible from the slope. He’s also fond of golf and has a deep appreciation for Army football and classmate camaraderie.","w":"Eric Whipple Whips lives in Lincoln, Nebraska, about a mile from his daughter Emily, a dedicated high school math teacher who switched from elementary education to middle and high school instruction. Eric lost his wife Lori in 2022 after 29 years of marriage. His plebe company was B1. Eric's standout Army story involves executing a bold flanking maneuver during a training exercise in Germany—diverting from the expected plan and leading his platoon over a ridgeline for a surprise attack that earned praise from a visiting general. He also crawled the entire Darby Queen obstacle course at Ranger School under intense instructor pressure, which became legendary. He served as rifle platoon leader, XO, and scout platoon leader before leaving just before Desert Shield. His wildest cadet memory was being the \"victim\" on a runaway toboggan during ski patrol training that wasn't properly secured, leading to a chaotic descent down the ski slope. After the Army, he built a 35+ year pharmaceutical sales career with Sandoz (Novartis) and GlaxoSmithKline, thriving in Nebraska and underserved regions. He skis, golfs, and follows Army football closely, maintaining strong ties with company mates through reunions and shared events. Following Lori's passing, he became involved in facilitating grief share programs. He can be reached at enwhipple@gmail.com | 402-525-0464."},{"id":959,"n":"Kevin Whitaker","u":"Kevin","g":"C3","p":"C2","ph":"(724) 695-1446","tw":"Imperial","st":"PA"},{"id":960,"n":"James White","u":"James","g":"F3","p":"E2","em":"polbndr@gmail.com","tw":"Atlanta","st":"GA"},{"id":961,"n":"Robert White","u":"Bob","g":"G3","p":"D1","ph":"(775) 883-3457","em":"bobusma86@hotmail.com","tw":"Carson City","st":"NV","w":"Bob White Bob lives in Carson City, Nevada. He has four children—one natural, two adopted, and one stepchild—and one grandchild. He served with 6th Infantry Division (Light) at Fort Wainwright, Alaska, including field exercises at 80 degrees below zero. He can be reached at bobusma86@hotmail.com | 775-883-3457."},{"id":962,"n":"Joseph Whitlock","u":"Joe","g":"G4","p":"H2","ph":"571-263-5874","em":"JoeWhitlock1986@gmail.com","tw":"Alexandria","st":"VA","w":"Joe Whitlock Joe lives in Alexandria, Virginia. He remembers life in G-4 was as fun as they were able to make it. One of the most interesting things he did was serve as a lead planner in Third Army/ARCENT/Coalition Forces Land Component Command for the ground campaign for Operation Iraqi Freedom during 2002-2003. He ended up staying for an entire career in the Army, which he never thought he would do when he graduated in 1986. After retiring, he is serving as a Program Manager for a defense contractor supporting the Space Force Headquarters, the newest service in the Department of Defense that was established in 2019. He can be reached at JoeWhitlock1986@gmail.com | 571-263-5874."},{"id":963,"n":"Steven Whitmarsh","u":"Steve","g":"H2","p":"B1","ph":"(703) 250-4401","em":"steve.whitmarsh@gmail.com","tw":"Burke","st":"VA"},{"id":964,"n":"Justin Whitney","u":"Justin","g":"B2","p":"D4","ph":"207-274-8182","em":"justin@aswpl.com","tw":"Yarmouth","st":"ME"},{"id":965,"n":"Robert Wiggins","u":"Rob","g":"D1","p":"F4","em":"rwiggins86@gmail.com","tw":"Dallas","st":"TX"},{"id":966,"n":"Thomas Wilk","u":"Thomas","g":"A1","p":"A3","ph":"(540) 660-5810","em":"lncr06@gmail.com","tw":"Purcellville","st":"VA"},{"id":967,"n":"Antonio Williams","u":"Antonio","g":"E4","p":"I1","ph":"281-435-5447","em":"arlenegwilliams@aol.com","tw":"Houston","st":"TX","af":"Glee Club","ac":"Attending games, golf, travel.","w":"Antonio Williams Antonio lives in Houston, Texas. He has been married to Arlene for over 37 years. They have two daughters: Katherine lives in Las Vegas and Elizabeth lives in Louisville, Kentucky. His plebe company was I1, graduating from E4. His most memorable cadet experiences were Glee Club participation, including performing at an NBA All Star game, and playing on the Handball Team at the Pentagon against Army officers stationed there. He served at Fort Knox for OBC, then Fort Polk for his first assignment as platoon leader, XO, battalion staff, and brigade staff. He returned to Knox, then did one year in Korea on brigade staff in 2nd Infantry Division, then back to Polk where he left the Army in 1992. After leaving the Army in 1992, he went into the chemicals business, ran a sales team for Honeywell, ran a plant for Amcor Flexibles, and currently runs a business that produces polymeric resin binder in rocket propellant for solid rocket motors used in aerospace and defense systems. He plays racquetball a few times a week when not traveling for business. He and Arlene frequently cruise out of Galveston, Texas whenever they can. He enjoys attending games, golf, and travel. He can be reached at arlenegwilliams@aol.com | 281-435-5447."},{"id":968,"n":"Bryan Williams","u":"Bryan","g":"B1","p":"I3","tw":"Cypress","st":"TX"},{"id":969,"n":"Charles Williams","u":"Chuck","g":"G4","p":"I2","em":"cewjr0228@gmail.com","tw":"Louisville","st":"KY","w":"After graduation, COLONEL (Ret) Charles 'Chuck' Williams enjoyed an exciting, highly decorated and rewarding military career of 23.5 years. There he served two Presidents in the White House as well as  in and out of combat, in the command positions of Troop Commander, Squadron Commander and Brigade Commander before retiring early to pursue a career in Corporate America. Following his love for business (an Economics major) he held positions: DO, SVP, COO, PRES and CEO in various corporate organizations. This was all done while simultaneously owning several restaurants in multiple states completing a childhood dream of his. Chuck is currently \"fully retired\" just sitting on a few boards and residing in the lovely coastal waterfront city of New Bern NC. He is married and has 3 adult children and 3 grandkids."},{"id":970,"n":"George Williams","u":"George","g":"H3","p":"H2","ph":"(909) 307-1594","em":"geoswill2007@yahoo.com"},{"id":971,"n":"Jeffrey Williams","u":"Jeff","g":"I3","p":"B1","ph":"(813) 657-1345","em":"jwwillie@aol.com","tw":"Lithia","st":"FL"},{"id":972,"n":"Thearon Williams","u":"Thearon","g":"D1","p":"F3","ph":"580-583-4313","em":"twilliams1906@hotmail.com","tw":"Manassas","st":"VA"},{"id":973,"n":"Eric Wilson","u":"Bruce","g":"C2","p":"I4","ph":"952-472-7352","em":"kebwilson@gmail.com","tw":"Minnetrista","st":"MN"},{"id":974,"n":"Jonathan (Wilson) Wildman","u":"Jon","g":"H1","p":"C2","ph":"510-710-7177","em":"jonathan.wildman@gmail.com"},{"id":975,"n":"Troy Wilson","u":"Troy","g":"B3","p":"A2","em":"troyswilson@aol.com","tw":"Saint Petersburg","st":"FL"},{"id":976,"n":"Robert Wineinger","u":"Kent","g":"G2","p":"D1","ph":"540-903-0488","em":"kent.wineinger@gmail.com","tw":"Fredericksburg","st":"VA","ac":"Golfing, Fishing, Skiing, Travel, Sporting Events, come to Virginia and visit me at my lake house and we can fish and golf there or just drink and tell stories.","w":"Kent Wineinger Kent lives in Fredericksburg, Virginia. He has three children, all out of the house. No grandchildren yet. He served in Germany in the 82nd Engineer Battalion, where he met his wife. After the Army, he worked as a defense contractor as an ORSA and a Marine Corps Civilian ORSA. His most interesting roles were a seven-month stint at Amazon and a year working in the Defense Suicide Prevention Office. He golfs, fishes, skis, travels, attends sporting events, and welcomes visitors to his lake house in Virginia. He can be reached at kent.wineinger@gmail.com | 540-903-0488."},{"id":977,"n":"David Wisnosky","u":"David","g":"B3","p":"I2","ph":"904-521-2450","em":"dwisnosky@bellsouth.net","tw":"Saint Augustine","st":"FL"},{"id":978,"n":"Michael Witherspoon","u":"Michael","g":"F2","p":"A3","em":"spoonware@gmail.com","tw":"Portsmouth","st":"NH"},{"id":979,"n":"Robert Witzmann","u":"Robert","g":"G2","p":"D1","ph":"(702) 701-6675","em":"Bob.witzmann@gmail.com","tw":"Winnemucca","st":"NV"},{"id":980,"n":"Caroline (Keller) Wolf","u":"Caroline","g":"H2","p":"B1","em":"caroline_8608@yahoo.com","tw":"Ottawa","st":"IL"},{"id":981,"n":"Mark Wolf","u":"Mark","g":"I2","p":"B4","ph":"503-330-8476","em":"mdavidw86@gmail.com","tw":"Woodbridge","st":"VA","af":"Fencing, Lacrosse","ac":"Wolf enjoys staying connected with classmates and has taken an active role in organizing monthly West Point ’86 gatherings in the National Capital Region, including lunches in the Pentagon and local happy hours. He has also played in West Point Society golf tournaments and clearly values face-to-face time, conversation, and informal social events as his preferred ways to spend time with classmates.","w":"Mark Wolf Mark lives in Woodbridge, Virginia in the same house since 2008. He has an older son who completed college in Oregon, worked in Dallas, and sadly died of cancer about six to seven months before his interview; a middle son who attended Radford University in Virginia; and a daughter who was in middle school when the family moved to Virginia. He grew up as a military child, moving frequently, and developed an early interest in military history from visits to Civil War and World War II sites with his father. His plebe company was B4, graduating from I2. A vivid plebe-year memory is being in B-4 under a very intense squad leader, Josh Cronin. During minutes, he choked on a response about the lunch menu, muttered an unwise comment under his breath, and was immediately called out for it. The combination of a hard-charging squad leader, a famously unconventional classmate like Doug Bies in the same squad, and the constant pressure of that first year left a strong impression. Later, moving to I-2, he remembers it as a good company with many enduring friendships. In high school he played lacrosse and soccer and even fenced, helped initially as a team manager before being pulled onto the team because of his height and aptitude. At West Point he describes himself as a \"middle of the class\" student who did what was needed to pass rather than chase stars. He identifies his first assignment at Fort Irwin and work with the Opposing Force as a major highlight of his Army career. As an armor platoon leader and later XO in the OPFOR, he participated in 37 NTC rotations. He recalls in detail units that excelled and those that failed, including a movement-to-contact where a battalion stretched 24 kilometers front-to-back and was systematically rolled up. He also deployed to Iraq as a major, serving in Baghdad as a force manager coordinating Army, Navy, Air Force, and Marine contributions. He left active duty in 1995, transitioned to the National Guard and then the Army Reserve, and in civilian life worked in the semiconductor industry in California. After 9/11 he moved into full-time Active Guard/Reserve roles, focusing on current operations and training support. He deployed to Iraq and later moved to the Washington, DC area, serving at the Office of the Chief of Army Reserve overseeing current operations, including responses like Hurricane Sandy. He retired from the Army in 2015 and now works in Virginia for the Association of the United States Army (AUSA), applying data analytics and continuing to work closely with the Army community. He is pursuing a master's degree in data analytics. He enjoys staying connected with classmates and has taken an active role in organizing monthly West Point '86 gatherings in the National Capital Region, including lunches in the Pentagon and local happy hours. He has also played in West Point Society golf tournaments and clearly values face-to-face time, conversation, and informal social events. He emphasizes the importance of staying in touch with family and classmates, shaped in part by the loss of both parents and his eldest son. He can be reached at mdavidw86@gmail.com | 503-330-8476."},{"id":982,"n":"Randall Wolken","u":"Randy","g":"H1","p":"C3","ph":"315-391-6674","em":"rwolken@macny.org","tw":"Syracuse","st":"NY","ac":"Attending sports events, traveling"},{"id":983,"n":"Andreas Wolter","u":"Andy","g":"A3","p":"H1","ph":"(914) 232-3368","em":"awolter@seetaeye.com","tw":"Katonah","st":"NY","ac":"Golf and movies","w":"Andreas Wolter Andy lives in Katonah, New York, with two boys and two girls. He served on staff at West Point. After the Army, he became a private practice ophthalmologist. He golfs and watches movies. He can be reached at awolter@seetaeye.com | 914-232-3368."},{"id":984,"n":"Scott Womack","u":"Scott","g":"A4","p":"G1","ph":"304-992-4405‬","em":"scott_womack@hotmail.com","tw":"Union","st":"WV","ac":"Living history, equestrian activities, homestead life, hunting/fishing/foraging","w":"Scott Womack Scott lives in Union, West Virginia. His elder son Josiah graduated from VMI in 2019 and is a U.S. Army ADA Captain, married to Rachel with a daughter named Angeleena. His younger son Samuel graduated from Washington and Lee in 2021 and works as a geologist at a gold mine in Elko, Nevada. His most memorable assignment was serving as U.S. Defense Attaché to eight countries in Sub-Saharan Africa during GWOT, enjoying freedom of action with counterparts while the region remained an economy-of-force mission. During CTLT with the 2nd ACR on the Czech border, he spoke German and conducted joint patrols with the Bundesgrenzschutz and Zoll. After the Army, he bought a homestead farm in West Virginia and taught and coached at the local high school for 14 years. He recently retired from teaching and was elected to the local school board, now serving as Board President. He's also state President of the West Virginia Professional Educators, a non-union association of teachers and administrators. He serves as one of the class Volunteer Veteran Services Liaisons with WPAOG. He's interested in living history, equestrian activities, homestead life, and hunting, fishing, and foraging. He can be reached at scott_womack@hotmail.com | 304-992-4405."},{"id":985,"n":"Elizabeth (Studebaker) Wood","u":"Liese","g":"A1","p":"B3","ph":"207-947-1472","em":"booter86@aol.com","tw":"Veazie","st":"ME","ac":"I want to go back to Germany for Oktoberfest in the next year or two. Red Sox and Patriots  fans but Boston is 5 hrs away so we mostly go to AA Portland Sea Dogs games. U Maine Orono is 10 min away so we also like to go to their hockey and football games. I geocache, hike, bird watch and kayak.","w":"Liese (Studebaker) Wood Liese lives in Veazie, Maine with her husband Dan, a retired lawyer. Their daughter Amanda is an RN married to Rob, and they have a 10-year-old granddaughter Leah who lives 20 minutes away. She served two tours in Germany, then assignments in Boston and DC before leaving the Army when she fell for a Maine boy with a young child who needed family stability after losing her mother. She became a high school mathematics teacher and Dean of Students at a private school in Bangor. She wants to get back to Germany for Oktoberfest in the next year or two. Liese and Dan are huge Red Sox and Patriots fans but Boston is five hours away, so they mostly catch AA Portland Sea Dogs games. University of Maine Orono is 10 minutes away and they go to hockey and football games there. She geocaches, hikes, bird watches, and kayaks. Living 12 minutes from Bangor airport, she's offered to put up any classmate who gets stranded there. She can be reached at booter86@aol.com | 207-947-1472."},{"id":986,"n":"Sandra (Benavides) Woodfint","u":"Sandra","g":"A1","p":"F2","ph":"330-360-8884","em":"ssrdw6@gmail.com","tw":"Loudon","st":"TN","w":"Sandra (Benavides) Woodfint Sandra lives in Loudon, Tennessee. She can be reached at ssrdw6@gmail.com | 330-360-8884."},{"id":987,"n":"Walter Woodring","u":"Woody","g":"G2","p":"A3","em":"walter.woodring@gmail.com","tw":"Lanham","st":"MD","ac":"i like to travel","w":"Woody Woodring Woody lives in Lanham, Maryland. Woody was a plebe in A3 and graduated from G2. His favorite cadet memory was graduating. His highlight assignment was Germany in the 80s. His most interesting assignment was Afghanistan in 2006, his most taxing was the Pentagon, his assignment with the most work was Fort Bragg, and his best location was Hawaii. His career path was not a straight line to retirement—he was RIFed in the 90s, then came back in after 9-11, followed by Afghanistan and the DC area where he had the interesting fortune to work for the executive branch, the legislative branch, and the Pentagon.  He had a heart attack in 2014 and open heart surgery at age 50 and is still recovering. He retired after 30 years and went into commercial real estate, working on low income housing for seven years. He sold everything and now focuses on his health and traveling. He has been to 50 countries and would like to see a few more. Woody likes to travel. He can be reached at walter.woodring@gmail.com."},{"id":988,"n":"William Woodring","u":"Bill","g":"C3","p":"A1","em":"wowoodring@gmail.com","tw":"Spotsylvania","st":"VA"},{"id":989,"n":"Paul Worsfold","u":"Paul","g":"D1","p":"D4","ph":"813-352-0482","em":"pworsfold@tampabay.rr.com","tw":"Valrico","st":"FL","ac":"He emphasized strong ongoing contact with D1 through a standing text thread and mentioned a Scotland trip involving several D1 classmates. He also positioned his new “Hidden Creek” property as a potential mini-reunion destination for D1, designed to host around 40 people, oriented around shared time together rather than business. He described outdoors and family activities on the property such as walking trails, river time, and “sharks teeth” hunting, suggesting he values informal, shared experiences over structured events.","w":"Paul Worsfold Paul lives in Valrico, Florida. He has three children, two married, and five granddaughters. He is married to Christina, whom he met at a Mount St. Mary's party during firstie year where he volunteered as the keg attendant. He described the advantage of living in D1 along Cullum Road, allowing them to see and talk from the window. His plebe company was D4, graduating from D1. He served armor and stayed at Fort Knox for five years, with frequent travel to training events such as NTC, Fort Bliss, and REFORGER. His major highlight was being assigned to a DARPA effort involving SIMNET and large-scale combat simulation used to run repeated scenarios based on Middle East terrain and logistics assumptions—he asserted the work informed senior decision-making during Desert Storm planning. He left active duty as Desert Storm unfolded and transitioned via Cameron-Brooks-era recruiting into pharmaceutical sales at Pfizer, initially working the Duke area. He stayed about 19 years at Pfizer, moving through sales and management, then moved across several firms (including BMS, UCB, Diplomat/Optum, and Heritage) in progressively more specialized federal and VA-facing roles, building a niche as a national account leader for federal accounts, VA systems, and military bases. His current company provides emergency medicines to the VA. He emphasizes strong ongoing contact with D1 through a standing text thread and mentioned a Scotland trip involving several D1 classmates. He is building a family retreat on property called \"Hidden Creek\" that is themed like an old west town, designed to host around 40 people as a potential mini-reunion destination for D1. The property features walking trails, river time, and \"sharks teeth\" hunting. He can be reached at pworsfold@tampabay.rr.com | 813-352-0482."},{"id":990,"n":"Gregory Wright","u":"Gregory","g":"A2","p":"E3","ph":"(540) 720-9286","em":"colgwright@gmail.com","tw":"Stafford","st":"VA"},{"id":991,"n":"Joseph Wucik","u":"Joe","g":"F4","p":"G1","ph":"(915) 275-9119","em":"joe.wucik@sbcglobal.net","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":992,"n":"James Yentz","u":"Jim","g":"H4","p":"B2","em":"yentzdj@hotmail.com","tw":"Germany","st":"APO AE","ac":"Hiking/jogging/travel","w":"Jim is based in northwestern Germany.  He and his wife have no children. His plebe company was B2, graduating from H4. His most memorable cadet experiences were H4 spirit missions and CTLT -- with 1st Battalion, 9th Infantry (later redesignated 1st Battalion, 506th Infantry), which turned out the be the same unit where he started his career in the \"real Army.\" He served in Infantry on the DMZ in Korea, Special Forces in Europe, one CONUS-based assignment as analyst with the Defense Intelligence Agency, and Foreign Area Officer assignments in Europe, Russia, and Kazakhstan. After his service in uniform, he worked in civil service at U.S. European Command and U.S. Army Europe and Africa (USAREUR-AF) on strategic communications, security cooperation and arms control. After retiring from civil service in 2021, he has participated in the USAREUR-AF Retired Soldier Council led by Dave Fulton, and assists active and retired Soldiers on overseas military transition issues. He enjoys hiking, jogging, and travel -- and still runs orienteering when and where possible. He can be reached at yentzdj@hotmail.com."},{"id":993,"n":"Kenston Yi","u":"Ken","g":"I3","p":"E2","em":"NA","tw":"UNK","st":"UNK"},{"id":994,"n":"Philip Yost","u":"Philo","g":"I3","p":"H2","em":"philipdyost@comcast.net","tw":"Austin","st":"TX"},{"id":995,"n":"Lissa Young","u":"Lissa","g":"I1","p":"A2","ph":"617.947.5021","em":"lissa.young@westpoint.edu","tw":"Highland Falls","st":"NY","ac":"1) Supe's Boat tour on the Hudson with BEER!  2) An afternoon at the Tin Barn Brewing Company in Chester! 3) A hike in the Black Rock Forest and 4) An afternoon at Westy's in Highland Falls, drinking beer together!","w":"Lissa lives in Highland Falls, New York. She jokes \"I am not a breeder!\" when it comes to children. Her plebe company was A2, graduating from I1. Her most memorable cadet experience was flying the entire Corps of Cadets to California and marching in the Rose Bowl parade—or if not the Rose Bowl parade, some kind of parade. That joy stopped after the first 38 seconds when Navy began stomping the hell out of them. She was an aviator and did not love being on Jump Status at Bragg, but did enjoy her command there. She also loved commanding the Army's High Altitude Rescue Team (HART) in Fairbanks, Alaska. After the Army, she devoted herself to becoming a scholar, went to graduate school, earned her PhD, and then returned to West Point to teach. She's been there ever since and it has been a joy. She has dreams of being a motorcycle mechanic and riding across the world on a motorcycle. Her ideal classmate activities include: 1) Supe's Boat tour on the Hudson with beer, 2) An afternoon at the Tin Barn Brewing Company in Chester, 3) A hike in the Black Rock Forest, and 4) An afternoon at Westy's in Highland Falls drinking beer together. She can be reached at lissa.young@westpoint.edu | 617-947-5021."},{"id":996,"n":"Michael Young","u":"Michael","g":"D2","p":"H3","ph":"(719) 391-8821","em":"young_mike@msn.com","tw":"Colorado Springs","st":"CO"},{"id":997,"n":"Fouad Zeidan","u":"Fouad","g":"D4","p":"E2","ph":"(703) 759-7743","tw":"Great Falls","st":"VA"},{"id":998,"n":"Alfonso Zelaya","u":"Alfonso","g":"I2","p":"D1","ph":"714-454-5955","em":"Apzelaya79@gmail.com","tw":"San Diego","st":"CA"},{"id":999,"n":"Allen Zick","u":"Allen","g":"H1","p":"H4","ph":"845-294-0955","em":"allen_zick@yahoo.com","tw":"Circleville","st":"NY","ac":"Traveling and attending sports events."},{"id":1000,"n":"Robert Zinnen","u":"Bob","g":"G1","p":"D2","ph":"215-920-9210","em":"rzinnen@finchmt.com","tw":"Norfolk","st":"VA","ac":"Travel, History, Fishing, Getting together for a drink!","w":"Bob Zinnen resides in Norfolk, Virginia, and runs a manufacturing business. Contact information includes (215) 920-9210 and rzinnen@finchmt.com. He described his cadet experience through close-knit relationships, recalling as a highlight time spent with the G-1 family in the day room watching television, talking, and laughing together. His most significant Army assignments included service at Aberdeen Proving Ground and Fort Campbell, roles notable for their operational environments and responsibilities. After military service, he transitioned into hospital administration and later expanded into manufacturing leadership, combining healthcare operations with private enterprise. His current interests include travel, history, fishing, and getting together socially with friends, family and G1 classmates. His family includes three children pursuing advanced education and early careers, with one attending law school at the University of Wisconsin, one in medical school at Ohio State, and one a recent Ohio State graduate entering the workforce. He stated that he is very proud to be part of the G-1 Class of 1986 family and expressed strong pride in his Greek brothers and sisters."},{"id":1001,"n":"William Ziomek","u":"Bill","g":"F2","p":"A3","em":"billz2012@hotmail.com","tw":"Vero Beach","st":"FL"},{"id":1002,"n":"Bernard Zoppa","u":"Bernie","g":"D3","p":"C4","em":"bjzoppa@live.com","tw":"Hartley","st":"DE"}];